series of notes listed in the table below (the \"Notes\").","month":"12","year":"2013","publishDate":"December 11, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citigroup Announces Expiration and Final Tender Results of Offers to Purchase Three Series of Outstanding Notes","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/citigroup-announces-expiration-and-final-tender-results-of-offers-to-purchase-three-series-of-outstanding-notes-1","tags":["Press Release Migration","Citi-Wide"]},{"summary":"New York - The <i>Financial Times</i> and Citi are pleased to announce that Sanergy has been named the global winner of the 2013 FT/Citi Ingenuity Awards: Urban Ideas in Action program. The Nairobi-based non-profit organization was selected by a distinguished panel of judges, including last year's winner, for developing a sustainable and hygienic sanitation system that recycles human waste to generate electricity and fertilizer for local farmers.","month":"12","year":"2013","publishDate":"December 10, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Sanergy is Named Global Winner at 2013 FT/Citi Ingenuity Awards","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/sanergy-is-named-global-winner-at-2013-ftciti-ingenuity-awards","tags":["Press Release Migration","Citi-Wide","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"Guangzhou /Shanghai - The 2013 \"Citi Cup\" Financial Innovation Application Competition today announced the awards at Sun Yat-Sen University in Guangzhou. \"31337\" team from Shanghai University of Finance and Economics snagged the highly coveted award, outdoing 58 other groups with their \"Luamatic Securities Auto Trade Platform\" project. The team received US$10,000 for the first prize as well as the Best Technology Realization Award at the ninth annual Citi Cup.","month":"12","year":"2013","publishDate":"December 09, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":