, the Citi Foundation is contributing $200,000 to the Nelson Mandela Children's Hospital in Johannesburg, which honors Mr. Mandela's life-long commitment to children. The ambitious project, initiated by the Nelson Mandela Children's Fund, aims to build a 200-bed academic and pediatric referral facility that will serve children across Southern Africa.","month":"12","year":"2013","publishDate":"December 05, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Honors Nelson Mandela with a $200,000 Citi Foundation Contribution to the Nelson Mandela Children's Hospital","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/citi-honors-nelson-mandela-with-a-200000-citi-foundation-contribution-to-the-nelson-mandela-children-s-hospital","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"Prague - In cooperation with MasterCard, Citibank Europe plc is offering another benefit for its premium clients who use the Citigold program. MasterCard® premium card holders now have free access to the SKY Lounge and JET Lounge at the Vienna International Airport from November 2013. As a special promotion, up to 4 persons accompanying a client can enjoy free access to the lounges until the end of 2013.","month":"12","year":"2013","publishDate":"December 04, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citigold Clients Now Have Free Access to Airport Lounges at the Vienna International Airport","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/citigold-clients-now-have-free-access-to-airport-lounges-at-the-vienna-international-airport","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"Moscow - Citi announces the introduction of a new standard for its Cash Back offer. Now clients who hold Cash Back cards can receive up to 5 percent of the value of each purchase in certain categories of retail outlets, the list of which will be updated every 3 months. At the end of every year, clients will receive an additional reward - a 10 percent annual bonus on top of the total sum of cash-back rewards received during the course of the year.","month":"12","year":"2013","publishDate":"December 03, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Russia: Citi Sets New Standard for Cash Back","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/russia-citi-sets-new-standard-for-cash-back","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"New York - John Gerspach, Chief Financial Officer of Citigroup, will present at the Goldman Sachs 2013 Financial Services Conference on Tuesday, December 10, 2013. The presentation is expected to begin at approximately 12:30 p.m. (Eastern). A live webcast will be available at <a href=\"https://www.citigroup.com/global/investors\">www.citigroup.com/global/investors</a>. A replay and transcript of the webcast will be available shortly after the event.","month":"12","year":"2013","publishDate":"December 03, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citigroup CFO John Gerspach to Present at the Goldman Sachs 2013 Financial Services Conference","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/citigroup-cfo-john-gerspach-to-present-at-the-goldman-sachs-2013-financial-services-conference","tags":["Press Release Migration","Citi-Wide"]},{"summary":"New York - The Citi Foundation and the Low Income Investment Fund (LIIF) today announced the launch of the Partners in Progress (PIP) initiative to bolster the ability of 13 organizations around the country to increase economic progress in low-income communities. With $3.25 million in funding from the Citi Foundation, administered by LIIF, the support is part of an effort to transform the field of community development by advancing the community \"quarterback\" model. The model leverages the capacity of high-performing local organizations to lead and coordinate across sectors and stakeholders to achieve shared goals.","month":"12","year":"2013","publishDate":"December 03, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"U.S.: Citi Foundation and Low Income Investment Fund Launch Nationwide \"Partners in Progress\" Initiative","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/us-citi-foundation-and-low-income-investment-fund-launch-nationwide-partners-in-progress-initiative","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"month":"12","destinationLink":"http://www.partnersinprogressproject.org/announcing-partners-in-progress/","year":"2013","publishDate":"December 03, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"The Citi Foundation and the Low Income Investment Fund launch Partners in Progress, an initiative to help transform the field of community development by advancing the community \"quarterback\" model and increase economic progress in low-income communities.","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/foundation/news/press-release/2013/the-citi-foundation-and-the-low-income-investment","tags":["Destination Link"]},{"summary":"Miami, Florida - Citi has been named by <i>Global Finance</i> magazine as the \"Best Foreign Exchange Bank and Provider\" in Latin America for the ninth consecutive year, in the magazine's World's Best Foreign Exchange and Provider 2014 Awards. Citi was also recognized as \"Best Foreign Exchange Bank and Provider\" in Argentina, Costa Rica, Ecuador, El Salvador, Guatemala, Honduras, Peru, Uruguay and Mexico (Banamex).","month":"12","year":"2013","publishDate":"December 02, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Named \"Best Foreign Exchange Bank and Provider\" in Latin America for Ninth Consecutive Year by Global Finance Magazine","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/citi-named-best-foreign-exchange-bank-and-provider-in-latin-america-for-ninth-consecutive-year-by-global-finance-magaine","tags":["Press Release Migration","Institutional Clients Group"]},{"summary":"Prague - Citibank Europe plc. provides the Citi Loan, a general-purpose credit product, entirely free of charge. Charges for premature repayment were abolished in October 2013, and beginning November 20, 2013, Citi charges no fees for the processing of credit documents. The same terms apply for the Consolidation with Citi Loan product, which has been offered without any charges to consumers since its launch in the market in 2012.","month":"12","year":"2013","publishDate":"December 02, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Czech Republic: Citi Loan Now Entirely Free of Charge, Interest Rates Are Simpler","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/cech-republic-citi-loan-now-entirely-free-of-charge-interest-rates-are-simpler","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"Based on the overwhelming support of her peers and coaches, Kate was recently voted as the","image":"638e3262a3c47c530c0a660e","year":"2013","publishDate":"December 02, 2013","type":"insights","title":"4 Questions for US Rowing's Female Athlete of the Year on what it takes to succeed","author.jobTitle":["Global Head of Enterprise Payments at Citi"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2013/4-questions-for-us-rowings-female-athlete-of-the-year-on-what-it-takes-to-succeed","tags":["Perspective Migration"],"month":"12","author.displayName":["Deborah McWhinney"],"siteId":"citigpa","category":"PERSPECTIVES"},{"summary":"In 2011, when Sirisha was in third grade, <a href=\"https://www.roomtoread.org/\">Room to Read</a> established a library at her school in Andhra Pradesh, India. She had been struggling with her reading skills, barely able to read a few words, but when the library's doors opened, Sirisha was captivated by the visual appeal of the environment and her love of books was instantly born. <br><br>Two years later, Sirisha makes sure she leaves home early each morning so that she has extra time to read a few stories in the library before class begins. With support from the school's head teacher, Sirisha is now an avid and skilled reader. Sirisha's parents, who are illiterate, are proud of their daughter's academic progress and enjoy listening to her read the stories she's borrowed from the library. \"The library is my best friend--I love spending time with all those books,\" Sirisha says. One of Room to Read's published children's titles, A Day in the Market, has special significance for Sirisha as it reminds her of the shopping trips she takes with her mother to buy vegetables. \"The day I could read it without faltering, I took the book home and read it aloud to her,\" she says proudly. <br><br>At Room to Read, we believe that World Change Starts with Educated Children and we have committed to focusing on two key areas where we can have the greatest impact: Literacy and Girls' Education. Since our founding in 2000, with the support of inspired investors, we have impacted nearly eight million children across Asia and Africa through our network of libraries and schools, local language children's books, teacher training and reading and writing instruction curriculums. To ensure our programs are successful and sustainable, we partner with communities and governments in our ten countries of operation. <br><br>Of the 774 million illiterate people in the world today, a staggering two-thirds are female. We continuously work to encourage awareness and action to turn the tide on illiteracy. Educating women and girls is widely acknowledged as a powerful and effective way to address global poverty--one extra year of education for a girl can earn her 20 percent more as an adult. In fact, the World Bank has stated that educating girls yields the highest rate of return than any other investment in the developing world. We agree. Our Girls' Education program supports girls to not only graduate secondary school, but develop the necessary skills--such as critical thinking, self-confidence and financial planning-- to make key life decisions. <br><br>We have all seen how the power of one voice calling for change, when multiplied across communities and geographies can swell into an indelible force that demands the world's attention. Room to Read is committed to amplifying the call for global literacy and gender equality and we are proud to be one of the beneficiaries in Citi Velocity's e for Education campaign. With the support of Citi Velocity traders, Room to Read can reach 10 million children by 2015, making their futures better and brighter and equipping the world with the next generation of leaders.","image":"638e3264a3c47c530c0a661a","year":"2013","publishDate":"December 01, 2013","type":"insights","title":"A Portfolio for Global Literacy","author.jobTitle":["Room to Read"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2013/-in-2011-when-sirisha","tags":["Perspective Migration"],"month":"12","author.displayName":["Room to Read"],"siteId":"citigpa","category":"PERSPECTIVES"},{"summary":"In Latin America, Citi also received a total of seven regional sub-category awards and seventeen country awards in the Best Corporate/Institutional Internet Banks category and two country awards in the Best Consumer Internet Banks category","month":"11","year":"2013","publishDate":"November 27, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi is Recognized by Global Finance Magazine as \"Best Corporate/Institutional Internet Bank\" in Latin America for the Seventh Consecutive Year","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/citi-is-recognied-by-global-finance-magaine-as-best-corporateinstitutional-internet-bank-in-latin-america-for-the-seventh-consecutive-year","tags":["Press Release Migration"]},{"summary":"Tel Aviv - Citi announced today it will continue to support the Milken Institute to improve and expand financial inclusion for underserved and unbanked populations in Israel. Recent publications indicate that significant segments of Israel's population are not served by formal financial institutions. Over the last seven years, more than 22 percent of Israeli households are living in poverty, making it the most impoverished country among the world's thirty-four economically developed countries. Small and micro business represents 96 percent of all business in Israel, employ 60 percent of the workforce but receive only 20 percent of bank financing. According to the World Bank, over 12 percent of the population in the bottom 40 percent of the income distribution are unbanked and only 25 percent of that population has savings accounts. Only 17 percent of that population has access to consumer credit. ","month":"11","year":"2013","publishDate":"November 26, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi and the Milken Institute Develop Innovation Lab to Promote Financial Inclusion in Israel","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/citi-and-the-milken-institute-develop-innovation-lab-to-promote-financial-inclusion-in-israel","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"New York - Citigroup Inc. (\"<b>Citigroup</b>\") announced today, that it has increased the maximum aggregate principal amount of specified series of notes (the \"<b>Notes</b>\") that it will accept (each, a \"<b>Maximum Series Tender Cap</b>\") in its previously announced cash tender offers (each, an \"<b>Offer</b>\" and, collectively, the \"<b>Offers</b>\"), as set forth in the table below.","month":"11","year":"2013","publishDate":"November 26, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citigroup Announces Upsizing of Offers to Purchase Specified Series of Outstanding Notes","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/citigroup-announces-upsiing-of-offers-to-purchase-specified-series-of-outstanding-notes-1","tags":["Press Release Migration","Citi-Wide"]},{"summary":"New York - Citigroup Inc. (\"<b>Citigroup</b>\") announced today the applicable Reference Yield and Total Consideration for the previously announced cash tender offers (each, an \"<b>Offer</b>\" and, collectively, the \"<b>Offers</b>\") with respect to each series of Notes listed in the table below (the \"<b>Notes</b>\").","month":"11","year":"2013","publishDate":"November 26, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citigroup Announces Reference Yields and Total Consideration for Note Tender Offers","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/citigroup-announces-reference-yields-and-total-consideration-for-note-tender-offers-1","tags":["Press Release Migration","Citi-Wide"]},{"summary":"Shanghai - Citi China is proud to have retained the coveted \"Best Bank in China\" award at <i>The Asset</i> Triple A Country Awards 2013 for seventh year in row.","month":"11","year":"2013","publishDate":"November 25, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Awarded \"Best Bank in China\" by The Asset for Seventh Year in Row","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/citi-awarded-best-bank-in-china-by-the-asset-for-seventh-year-in-row","tags":["Press Release Migration","Institutional Clients Group"]},{"summary":"Dubai - Citi International Personal Bank (IPB) EMEA today announced the launch of its Switzerland Booking Centre in Geneva, giving Citigold Private Clients based in the UAE access to the world's biggest and most exclusive investment center.","month":"11","year":"2013","publishDate":"November 24, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi International Personal Bank EMEA Launches Swiss Booking Centre In Geneva","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/citi-international-personal-bank-emea-launches-swiss-booking-centre-in-geneva","tags":["Press Release Migration","Institutional Clients Group"]},{"summary":"New York - The U.S. Chamber of Commerce Foundation's Business Civic Leadership Center (BCLC) has named Citi as the winner in two categories in the 2013 Corporate Citizenship Awards competition. Citi received the Best Partnership award, together with the National Community Tax Coalition (NCTC), for its work promoting college success in the United States. Citi also received the Best Economic Empowerment Program award for its efforts to invest in and advance entrepreneurship around the world. The winners of the 2013 Citizens Awards were announced on November 21 during a ceremony at the U.S. Chamber of Commerce in Washington, D.C.","month":"11","year":"2013","publishDate":"November 22, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Earns Double Honors at U.S. Chamber Foundation's 2013 Corporate Citizenship Awards","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/foundation/news/press-release/2013/citi-earns-double-honors-at-us-chamber-foundation-s-2013-corporate-citienship-awards","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"<br>Kirsten Saenz Tobey and Kristin Groos Richmond are Citi clients of mine and the co-founders of Revolution Foods, a company that is tackling the challenge of the more than 20 million Americans who lack access to healthy food. I sat down with them recently to talk about the growth of their business and the importance of building a team from within the cities they serve. In these select excerpts from the interview, Kristen and Kristin share Revolution Foods' origins, their passion for food and the impact their company has had beyond the school lunchroom. Catch the Q&amp;A in its entirety on Monday, December 2nd, on Huffington Posts's <a href=\"https://www.huffingtonpost.com/news/urban_progress/\">Urban Progress blog</a>, presented by Citi. <br><br><strong>Q: So tell us, how did you two meet? What's the story behind Revolution Foods? </strong> <br><br><em>Kristin Groos Richmond</em>: We met on the first day of business school and within our first year we started crafting the business plan for Revolution Foods. Both of us had a passion for food and nutrition, so we saw what an opportunity there was, both from an impact standpoint and from a business-building standpoint. <br><em><br>Kirsten Saenz Tobey</em>: We started seven-and-a-half years ago with very humble roots as most entrepreneurs do. Revolution Foods began with three schools, serving about 500 meals a day out of a 500-square-foot kitchen in Oakland, California. We hand-produced every meal -- we made our homemade turkey sandwiches, rolled our quesadillas, packed our fruit -- and delivered each one to schools every day in one truck that we leased. <br><br><strong>Q: I met you both as your business really began to expand, first to more schools and then to new product lines. What has that been like? </strong> <br><em><br>Kirsten Saenz Tobey</em>: From that original kitchen, we have now expanded to seven culinary centers around the country, and we are now serving over one million meals a week. It's a tremendous undertaking and a very complex operational business. It's also one that has allowed us to create more than 1,000 jobs in urban communities, which is one of the things that we treasure most about Revolution Foods. <br><br><em>Kristin Groos Richmond</em>: We knew early on that we wanted to have a large-scale impact and to provide as many families in America as possible access to high-quality food. That came first in the form of expanding to new geographic areas: serving more schools and more families through our school meals program. But very quickly we also realized that teachers and parents wanted to see our food on store shelves, so we recently launched our meal kits, which are now available nationwide. <br><strong><br>Q: Kirsten, you mentioned the pride you feel in creating jobs for your teammates. Tell us more about that. </strong> <br><br><em>Kirsten Saenz Tobey</em>: When we do town halls with our team, we always say we've done almost every job in the company and really respect the folks who are working at Revolution Foods in cities across the country. It feels good to have grown up with the idea, to have created it step-by-step, and most importantly to have built an incredible team to help us scale. One of the things we're most proud of is watching our teammates grow and turn jobs into careers. <br><br><em>Kristin Groos Richmond</em>: People come in for an interview because they're looking for a job, but then they join the company because they believe in what we're doing. They stay because they have opportunities to grow and to contribute. It's really the ability for someone to come in at an entry level and earn a sustainable income while gaining an ownership stake in the company, and then be managing a team of 20 people within four to five years with hard work, solid coaching, and great performance.","image":"638e3266a3c47c530c0a6623","year":"2013","publishDate":"November 22, 2013","type":"insights","title":"How Can Good Business Make America's Cities Healthier?","author.jobTitle":["Managing Director, Citi"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2013/how-can-good-business-make-americas-cities-healthier","tags":["Perspective Migration"],"month":"11","author.displayName":["Mark Paris"],"siteId":"citigpa","category":"PERSPECTIVES"},{"summary":"Lima - The Citi Microentrepreneurship Awards are the flagship initiative of the Citi Foundation, emphasizing the importance of micro-entrepreneurship and microfinance in financial inclusion processes and the socio-economic empowerment of low-income individuals. The program was launched in 2005 and is now offered in 36 countries, which use the awards to recognize the contributions of microentrepreneurs and microfinance institutions to the local economy. This year, the Citi Microentrepreneurship Awards, organized by Citibank Peru in partnership with the IPAE business school, honored 10 microentrepreneurs from around the country.","month":"11","year":"2013","publishDate":"November 21, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Peru: Citi Announces 10 Winners of Eighth Annual Microentrepreneurship Awards","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/foundation/news/press-release/2013/peru-citi-announces-10-winners-of-eighth-annual-microentrepreneurship-awards","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"Santo Domingo - In the Dominican Republic, Citi invited its Citigold clients, who receive the most exclusive personal and wealth management services, to a special presentation offering a global vision of the economy and investment prospects. The talk was held as part of a conference on \"Investment Prospects and Global Economic Outlook,\" a cycle of talks the bank is presenting in a number of countries to provide its clients with current information about global economic trends and investment prospects.","month":"11","year":"2013","publishDate":"November 21, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Dominican Republic: Citi Presents Exclusive Forum for Citigold Clients","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/dominican-republic-citi-presents-exclusive-forum-for-citigold-clients","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"New York - In an effort to provide aid to children with disabilities, cancer, and autism in the United States, Citibank today announced that it will support Teletón USA's second annual fundraiser by accepting donations in its branches across the country and providing the organization with a $300,000 donation during its telethon event. Citibank's support of Teleton USA builds off of Banamex' 17-year history serving as the Bank of Teleton in Mexico. ","month":"11","year":"2013","publishDate":"November 21, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citibank to Support Teletón USA Campaign to Aid Children with Disabilities, Cancer and Autism in the U.S.","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/citibank-to-support-teletón-usa-campaign-to-aid-children-with-disabilities-cancer-and-autism-in-the-us","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"San Juan, Puerto Rico - Citi announced the finalists in the Citi Microentrepreneurship Awards, offered for the first time in Puerto Rico this year. The awards, administered by Fundación Comunitaria de Puerto Rico, are a Citi global initiative that recognizes microfinance institutions, microenterprises and microentrepreneurs that promote economic development in the country holding the award competition. ","month":"11","year":"2013","publishDate":"November 20, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Puerto Rico: Citi Microentrepreneurship Award Finalists","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/foundation/news/press-release/2013/puerto-rico-citi-microentrepreneurship-award-finalists","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"Prague - Reaffirming its leadership in the field of innovation, Citi began to issue Visa Micro Tag contactless payment stickers with Citi O2 credit cards from November 19, 2013. This is first partnership of its kind between Visa Europe and a bank in the Czech Republic, making Citi the first bank in the Czech market to offer this new type of contactless device. ","month":"11","year":"2013","publishDate":"November 19, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Clients First To Use Visa Contactless Payment Stickers in Czech Republic","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/citi-clients-first-to-use-visa-contactless-payment-stickers-in-cech-republic","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"<br>For sixteen years, <a href=\"https://uncommonschools.org/\">Uncommon Schools</a> has been redefining what is possible in urban public education - starting and running outstanding public charter schools that close the achievement gap and prepare low-income students to enter, succeed in, and graduate from college. We started small, opening North Star Academy Charter School with 72 fifth-grade students in Newark in 1997. Two years later, Roxbury Preparatory Charter School in Boston welcomed its first class of sixth-graders. This fall, nearly 10,000 students entered our classrooms in our 38 schools across five cities: Boston, Newark, New York City, Rochester, and Troy. We have grown dramatically since those first years - Uncommon is now larger than 94% of public school districts nationwide and is one of the largest charter management organizations in the country. <br><br>But growth is only positive if it means more kids are getting access to an outstanding education - which is why I am so proud to say that Uncommon is proving it IS possible to run great schools at scale. This fall, CREDO - an independent research organization at Stanford - released a study highlighting Uncommon as proof that the achievement gap can be closed, finding specifically that: <br><br>• Uncommon low-income students performed so well in math and reading that the effects of being at an Uncommon school \"completely cancel out the negative effect associated with being a student in poverty.\" <br>• Low-income students who attend an Uncommon school on average grow as much or more than their non-low-income peers attending traditional public schools. <br>• In math, students of color who attend an Uncommon school had on average more significant academic growth than white students at traditional public schools. <br>• Our special education students experienced academic growth almost as strong as general education students in traditional public schools. <br><br>These results are a reflection of the incredibly hard work our scholars and their teachers do every day in every Uncommon school. We felt grateful to be honored for this hard work this summer when we received the 2013 Broad Prize for Public Charter Schools, which recognizes \"the public charter management organization that has demonstrated the most outstanding overall student performance and improvement in the nation in recent years while reducing achievement gaps for low-income students and students of color.\" <br><br>Just as importantly, Uncommon is demonstrating the financial viability of our efforts. Every one of our schools is designed to operate on public per-pupil funding once it reaches full enrollment. Today, 24 of our 38 schools are operating on public funding alone, with another seven slated to achieve financial sustainability next year. As a result of this disciplined financial management, we are able to leverage and target our philanthropic dollars strategically. Citi's support and other private donations help fund each school's start-up years, the purchase of new buildings as we expand, and allow us to pursue special initiatives as we tackle our biggest challenges, such as supporting, developing, and retaining our exceptional teachers. <br><br>I'm extraordinarily proud to be a part of this movement, and I'm grateful every day for the intelligence, creativity, and commitment of my colleagues. We look forward to growing our impact over the coming years, eventually serving over 16,000 students as our current schools grow to full enrollment and we open additional new schools, We'll continue to think about how to share what we've learned with others but also continue to ask ourselves how we can get better at our work, because we know that the work of serving students and families is as difficult as it is important, and there is always room for growth. That's why I'm so grateful for the generosity of partners like Citi. Support from 'e for education' will help us continue to provide life-changing educational opportunities to children across the Northeast.","image":"638e3267a3c47c530c0a662c","year":"2013","publishDate":"November 19, 2013","type":"insights","title":"Uncommon Schools: Redefining Urban Public Education","author.jobTitle":["CEO, Uncommon Schools"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2013/uncommon-schools-redefining-urban-public-education","tags":["Perspective Migration"],"month":"11","author.displayName":["Brett Peiser"],"siteId":"citigpa","category":"PERSPECTIVES"},{"summary":"Prague - The Citi Foundation and Tereza Maxová Foundation launched a pilot project aimed at improving financial literacy among mothers and women living in shelters in the Czech Republic this summer. The primary purpose of the project is to prevent children being taken away from women who face difficult situations in life for financial reasons. Named \"Financial Literacy for Mothers and Women in Shelters,\" the project aims to help these women address their existing difficult situation and regain control of their lives, in effect becoming able to raise their children so they can grow up in their biological families.","month":"11","year":"2013","publishDate":"November 18, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Czech Republic: Citi Foundation and Tereza Maxová Foundation Pilot Project Aims To Provide Financial Education to Mothers in Shelters","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/cech-republic-citi-foundation-and-terea-maxová-foundation-pilot-project-aims-to-provide-financial-education-to-mothers-in-shelters","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"Miami, Florida - Citi ® Mobile Collect was named Best Mobile Money Deployment in the Americas in the <a href=\"http://www.mobile-money-gateway.com/event/mobile-money-global-2013/page/mobile-money-global-awards\" target=\"blank\">2013 Mobile Money Global Awards</a> at the Dubai World Trade Centre during the annual Global & Digital Payments Summit on November 6.","month":"11","year":"2013","publishDate":"November 18, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"\"Citi ® Mobile Collect\" Recognized as Best Mobile Money Deployment in the Americas in The Mobile Money Global & Digital Payments Summit 2013","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/citi-reg-mobile-collect-recognied-as-best-mobile-money-deployment-in-the-americas-in-the-mobile-money-global-digital-payments-summit-2013","tags":["Press Release Migration","Institutional Clients Group"]},{"month":"11","author.displayName":["Jud Linville"],"year":"2013","publishDate":"November 18, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"You Spoke, We Listened","category":"PERSPECTIVES","author.jobTitle":["Citi Cards CEO"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2013/you-spoke-we-listened-7","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"Manila - In response to the overwhelming devastation wrought by Typhoon Yolanda (international name Haiyan), Citi launched a series of initiatives around the world to support the ongoing around-the-clock relief efforts.","month":"11","year":"2013","publishDate":"November 17, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Responds to Appeal for Communities Devastated by Typhoon Yolanda","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/citi-responds-to-appeal-for-communities-devastated-by-typhoon-yolanda","tags":["Press Release Migration","Citi-Wide","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"New York - Stephen Bird, Chief Executive Officer of Asia Pacific, will present at the Citi 2013 Global Financial Conference in Hong Kong on Tuesday, November 19, 2013. The presentation is expected to begin at approximately 1 p.m. HKT (12 midnight EST), and will not be webcast or teleconferenced. Presentation materials will be available at <a href=\"https://www.citigroup.com/global/investors\">www.citigroup.com/global/investors</a>.","month":"11","year":"2013","publishDate":"November 15, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citigroup Asia Pacific CEO Stephen Bird to Present at the Citi 2013 Global Financial Conference in Hong Kong","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/citigroup-asia-pacific-ceo-stephen-bird-to-present-at-the-citi-2013-global-financial-conference-in-hong-kong","tags":["Press Release Migration","Citi-Wide"]},{"summary":"Buenos Aires, Argentina - The Citi Microentrepreneurship Award, the flagship initiative of the Citi Foundation, showcases the importance of micro-entrepreneurship and microfinance in financial inclusion processes and the socioeconomic empowerment of low-income individuals. Since its launch in 2005, 36 countries have joined the program and use the contest to recognize the contributions of microentrepreneurs and microfinance institutions to their local economies.","month":"11","year":"2013","publishDate":"November 14, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Latin America: Citi Stands Alongside Microentrepreneurs at Regional Event Promoting Business Development","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/latin-america-citi-stands-alongside-microentrepreneurs-at-regional-event-promoting-business-development","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"New York - Citi, the Overseas Private Investment Corporation (OPIC) and the Bank of Georgia announced the closing of a US$10 million term loan to fund the growth of Bank of Georgia's Microfinance portfolio to promote the financial inclusion of micro-entrepreneurs and small businesses in the Republic of Georgia. This loan will be the first from Citi and OPIC for the microfinance sector in Georgia and is a part of Citi and OPIC's joint global initiative to support microfinance lending in emerging markets. ","month":"11","year":"2013","publishDate":"November 14, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi, OPIC and Bank of Georgia Support the Growth of the Microfinance Sector in Georgia with US $10 Million Term Funding","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/citi-opic-and-bank-of-georgia-support-the-growth-of-the-microfinance-sector-in-georgia-with-us-10-million-term-funding","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"Hong Kong - Reaffirming Citi's position as the leading digital bank in the region, <i>Global Finance</i> magazine has named Citi Best Consumer Internet Bank and Best Corporate/ Institutional Internet Bank in Asia Pacific in its annual World's Best Internet Bank Awards.","month":"11","year":"2013","publishDate":"November 14, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Global Finance Names Citi Best Internet Bank in Asia Pacific","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/global-finance-names-citi-best-internet-bank-in-asia-pacific","tags":["Press Release Migration","Institutional Clients Group","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"Guiyang, China - At Guiyang Art Museum, Citibank (China) Co. Ltd. (\"Citi China\") and Community-Based Conservation and Development Research Center of Guizhou (\"CCDRC\") today announced the achievements of a three-year household enterprise support program known as \"Guizhou Indigenous Craftwork Development Program.\" The announcement was made together with the launch of an exhibition themed \"2013 Absolute Guizhou Cultural Week\" and a charity bazaar, both of which are part of results from the program. Andrew Au, Chairman and CEO of Citi China, and Professor Ren Xiaodong, Executive Director of CCDRC, joined local government officials, indigenous artisans, program key stakeholders and villagers at the event.","month":"11","year":"2013","publishDate":"November 13, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"China: Citi Supports the Indigenous Craftwork Development Program in Guizhou Province","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/china-citi-supports-the-indigenous-craftwork-development-program-in-guihou-province","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"New York - Citigroup Inc. (\"<b>Citigroup</b>\") today announced the commencement of offers to purchase for cash certain of its notes of the series set forth in the table below (each offer with respect to any series set forth in the table below, an \"<b>Offer</b>\" and, collectively, the \"<b>Offers</b>\"). We refer to our offer to purchase each series of Notes as an \"Offer\" and collectively as the \"Offers.\" The Notes have an aggregate principal amount outstanding of approximately $2 billion as of November 11, 2013.","month":"11","year":"2013","publishDate":"November 12, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citigroup Inc. Announces Offers to Purchase Three Series of Outstanding Notes","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/citigroup-inc-announces-offers-to-purchase-three-series-of-outstanding-notes-1","tags":["Press Release Migration","Citi-Wide"]},{"summary":"At <a href=\"https://www.teachfirst.org.uk/\">Teach First</a> we are working toward a future when every child can succeed, regardless of background. We believe that inspirational teaching and leadership can transform a child's life opportunities. <br><br>When people in the developed world think about people living in poverty, the images that come to mind aren't often of the communities that surround us. Yet in Britain today, 3.5 million children are growing up in households so poor that providing basics such as heating and food is a daily struggle. Children growing up in poverty can all too often become trapped in a downward spiral of low educational achievement, inferior job opportunities and greatly increased chances of drug use, poor health and involvement with crime. In some areas they will even die sooner than their wealthier neighbour. <br><br>The gap in educational achievement is wider in the UK that in almost any other developed country, and the cost to the country is grave. <br><br>• The reading skills of children from disadvantaged families are, on average, more than two years behind those of pupils from wealthier backgrounds, a gap twice as wide as most other developed countries. <br><br>• 1 in 6 young people leave school unable to read, write and add up properly. <br><br>• Just 16% of youngsters eligible for free schools meals progress to university, compared in 96% of young people educated in independent schools. <br><br>• The UK's economy will see cumulative losses of up to £1.3 trillion over the next 40 years if we fail to bring the educational outcomes of children from poorer homes up to the UK average. <br><br>At Teach First, we recruit dynamic, passionate graduates and career-changers to teach in schools in low-income communities. We select only those who demonstrate leadership potential, a passion to change children's lives and the other skills and attributes needed to become an excellent teacher and leader. <br><br>These participants teach and lead in our partner primary and secondary schools in low-income communities across England and Wales. We only work with schools where more than half the pupils come from the poorest homes. Only 4% of newly qualified teachers would consider working in these schools, but all of our teachers commit to working there for a minimum of two years, ensuring that every child has access to an excellent education. <br><br>Since 2002, we have trained more than 4,500 teachers to work at more than 500 schools in low-income communities. We are building a movement of leaders who will change the education system, eradicating educational disadvantage and making a meaningful impact on children, their families and communities. <br><br>But there is still so much to be done. There are still more than 4,000 schools in the UK that are eligible to work with Teach First that we are not yet partnered with. By 2015, we want to recruit, train and place 2,000 new teachers every year to work in the schools that need them the most. <a href=\"https://www.citivelocity.com/equity/public/charity/index.jsp\">Citi Velocity</a> can help us to reach this ambitious target, reaching out to more passionate and determined individuals who can make life-changing impact in classrooms across the country. <br><br>Our mission to end educational inequality drives everything we do - it's an ambitious goal and we know we cannot achieve it alone. So we work in partnership with schools, charities, businesses and individuals who want to ensure that every young person can succeed in life. We nurture and champion innovative approaches to education, initiate conversations and influence decision makers to bring about change. We run projects to increase young people's confidence and participation in important decisions about their future, including access to higher education. Citi Velocity and E for Education will help us to expand and accelerate our impact and change more children's lives.","image":"638e326aa3c47c530c0a6639","year":"2013","publishDate":"November 12, 2013","type":"insights","title":"Teach First: Inspirational Leaders Transforming Children's Lives","author.jobTitle":["CEO/Founder, Teach First"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2013/teach-first-inspirational-leaders-transforming-childrens-lives","tags":["Perspective Migration"],"month":"11","author.displayName":["Brett Wigdortz"],"siteId":"citigpa","category":"PERSPECTIVES"},{"summary":"On November 6, <a href=\"https://veteransonwallstreet.com/\">Veterans on Wall Street</a>, a consortium of large financial institutions including Citi, Deutsche Bank and Goldman Sachs, was the presenting sponsor of the <a href=\"https://bobwoodrufffoundation.org/sufh/\">Stand up for Heroes</a> concert in New York City to benefit the <a href=\"https://bobwoodrufffoundation.org/\">Bob Woodruff Foundation</a>. It was an extraordinary evening of music and laughter, that was made even more meaningful thanks to the generosity of our clients, vendors and colleagues who helped us raise critical funds to support our injured men and women in uniform as they return home.","image":"638e326ba3c47c530c0a6642","year":"2013","publishDate":"November 11, 2013","type":"insights","title":"Saluting Those Who Serve","author.jobTitle":["Regional Head of Markets, North America, Citi"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2013/saluting-those-who-serve","tags":["Perspective Migration"],"month":"11","author.displayName":["Suni Harford"],"siteId":"citigpa","category":"PERSPECTIVES"},{"summary":"Bogota - Citi announced the launch of Prestige, the first global credit card especially designed to offer benefits to affluent clients. Colombia is the sixth country where clients of Citi's worldwide network can obtain the card. The others are Hong Kong, Malaysia, Singapore, the United States and Mexico. ","month":"11","year":"2013","publishDate":"November 07, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Presents Its New \"Prestige\" Credit Card in Colombia","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/citi-presents-its-new-prestige-credit-card-in-colombia","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"São Paulo - Starting November 21, one of São Paulo's landmark entertainment venues, currently known as Credicard Hall, will have a new name. The country's leading and most versatile show arena will now be called Citibank Hall. The name change underscores Citi's commitment to offering its clients exclusive benefits.","month":"11","year":"2013","publishDate":"November 06, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Brazil: Citibank Hall Will Be the New Name of Credicard Hall, Brazil's Premier Performance Venue","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/brail-citibank-hall-will-be-the-new-name-of-credicard-hall-brail-s-premier-performance-venue","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"Caracas - For the ninth year in a row, The Citi Microentrepreneurship Awards - promoted and organized by Citibank Venezuela and the Citi Foundation, with the support of Asociación Civil Centro Lyra - has raised awareness of the importance of microcredit as a way to reduce poverty and the contributions microentrepreneurs make to their local economies with their efforts and talent.","month":"11","year":"2013","publishDate":"November 06, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Recognizes the Efforts of Venezuelan Microentrepreneurs","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/citi-recognies-the-efforts-of-veneuelan-microentrepreneurs","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"Asunción, Paraguay - Citibank, via the Citi Foundation and in partnership with Avina, honored the winners of the 2013 Citi Microentrepreneurship Awards on Wednesday, November 6, 2013, in a ceremony at the Citicenter building (Mcal.Lopez 3794/Cruz del Chaco, Salón Auditorio, 12th Floor). The awards were co-sponsored by Red de Microfinanzas del Paraguay and La Nación newspaper. ","month":"11","year":"2013","publishDate":"November 06, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Paraguay: Citi Rewards the Year's Top Microentrepreneurs","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/paraguay-citi-rewards-the-year-s-top-microentrepreneurs","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"Miami, Fla. - IDG Latin America and PC World en español recognized the <i>Beneficios de Citi mobile</i> application as the <i>Best Consumer Mobile App in Latin America</i> during the 2013 Latin American Digital Awards.","month":"11","year":"2013","publishDate":"November 06, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"\"Beneficios De Citi\" Is Recognized as Best Consumer Mobile App in the 2013 Latin American Digital Awards","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/beneficios-de-citi-is-recognied-as-best-consumer-mobile-app-in-the-2013-latin-american-digital-awards","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"Selangor - Citi and UPM are launching the training initiative for 800 mature women from the low income group, as part of the Citi-UPM Financial Empowerment for Mature Women Programme. The program will be carried out among members of UPM Woman's Association (PERMATA) and National Council of Women Organisation (NCWO). ","month":"11","year":"2013","publishDate":"November 06, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Malaysia: Citi Launches Pilot Training Initiative as Part of CITI-UPM Financial Empowerment for Mature Women Program","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/foundation/news/press-release/2013/malaysia-citi-launches-pilot-training-initiative-as-part-of-citi-upm-financial-empowerment-for-mature-women-program","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"New York - Manuel Medina-Mora, Co-President of Citigroup and Chief Executive Officer of Global Consumer Banking, will present at the Bank of America Merrill Lynch 2013 Banking & Financial Services Conference on Tuesday, November 12, 2013. The presentation is expected to begin at approximately 10:30 a.m. (Eastern). A live webcast will be available at <a href=\"https://www.citigroup.com/global/investors\">www.citigroup.com/global/investors</a>. A replay and transcript of the webcast will be available shortly after the event.","month":"11","year":"2013","publishDate":"November 05, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citigroup Co-President and CEO of Global Consumer Banking Manuel Medina-Mora to Present at the Bank of America Merrill Lynch 2013 Banking & Financial Services Conference","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/citigroup-co-president-and-ceo-of-global-consumer-banking-manuel-medina-mora-to-present-at-the-bank-of-america-merrill-lynch-2013-banking-financial-services-conference","tags":["Press Release Migration","Citi-Wide"]},{"summary":"<br>Education is critical for young people to be able to transition to adulthood and capitalize on their potential. It helps to ensure young people can find jobs, be engaged in their communities, and become productive members of society. Sixty-five low and middle income countries lose approximately $92 billion annually by failing to educate girls to the same standard as boys. <a href=\"https://www.empowerweb.org/\"> EMpower</a>-The Emerging Markets Foundation- was founded with the mission to help such youth achieve their educational potential. We work exclusively in Emerging Market (EM) countries, partnering with locally-led organizations that share our mission of empowering at-risk young people between the ages of 10-24. Rather than a one-size-fits-all approach, we support relevant education strategies that address specific needs in different countries and communities, and are based on best practices in youth development. <br><br>Education is the largest of EMpower's four investment portfolios. We make strategic contributions in EM countries experiencing a huge bulge in the population of young people (nearly 1 billion youth in the 14 countries where we work), and widening inequalities in education, health, income and opportunity. Through these investments, we work with local grantee partners to grow, develop and, most importantly, transform, the lives of youth in their communities. And we have staying power: we are willing to fund organizations that demonstrate results for up to 10 years, an industry best practice. <br><br>Two nations where we've seen our commitments have measureable impact are South Africa and India. In South Africa, where the apartheid legacy has not erased yawning gaps and the quality of math and science education is substandard (South Africa ranked 137 out of 139 countries), EMpower is investing in 'second chance' programs that level the playing field. After-school and Saturday tutoring programs and math and science intensives for girls are just a few of the initiatives we've help put in place. Education-focused grantees include Ikamva Youth, Future of the African Daughter, Equal Education, Wilderness Foundation, Etafeni Trust. <br><br>In India, education is compulsory and free through grade 8. However, schools then experience high drop-out rates, especially among girls. We are investing in programs to keep girls in school through covering fees and uniforms, conducting outreach to mitigate parents' concerns about their daughters' safety and marriageability, and ensuring a high quality of education so it is seen as value-add not an opportunity cost. Education-focused grantees include Vidhayak Sansad, Lend a Hand India, Ibtada, Parivaar Education Society, Nishtha. See more <a href=\"https://www.empowerweb.org/global-reach/global-grantee-projects/\">examples</a> of our work across the world. <br><br>We believe young people are a critical, untapped resource in every country. To ensure they have bright futures, EMpower remains committed to finding and funding the most promising, innovative and scalable models to help educate them and impart 21st century skills (computer literacy, English, etc.). <br><br>","image":"638e326da3c47c530c0a664b","year":"2013","publishDate":"November 05, 2013","type":"insights","title":"EMpower: Ensuring At-Risk Youth Have a Better Tomorrow","author.jobTitle":["President, EMpower"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2013/empower-ensuring-at-risk-youth-have-a-better-tomorrow","tags":["Perspective Migration"],"month":"11","author.displayName":["Marta Cabrera"],"siteId":"citigpa","category":"PERSPECTIVES"},{"summary":"New York - The Asset Building Policy Network (ABPN), a coalition of the nation's leading advocacy, policy and civil rights organizations and Citi, has launched five new groundbreaking asset-building programs funded by the Citi Foundation and designed to build pathways to long-term economic security and expand equal opportunity for low- and moderate-income (LMI) communities of color.","month":"11","year":"2013","publishDate":"November 04, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Asset Building Policy Network Launches New Programs to Reduce Wealth Gap in U.S.","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/foundation/news/press-release/2013/asset-building-policy-network-launches-new-programs-to-reduce-wealth-gap-in-us","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"Miami, Florida - Citi has been named \"Best Regional Derivatives Provider in Latin America\" by <i>Global Finance</i> magazine, for the third consecutive year, as part of the ninth annual \"World's Best Derivatives Providers\" awards for 2013. A full report on the awards will be published in the December issue of the prestigious publication.","month":"11","year":"2013","publishDate":"November 04, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Global Finance Magazine Names Citi \"Best Regional Derivatives Provider\" in Latin America for the Third Consecutive Year","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/global-finance-magaine-names-citi-best-regional-derivatives-provider-in-latin-america-for-the-third-consecutive-year","tags":["Press Release Migration","Institutional Clients Group"]},{"summary":"Kingston - Jamaica, Belize and Suriname were in winners' row at the second annual Citi Microentrepreneurship Awards ceremony, held Thursday, October 31, 2013, at the Courtleigh Hotel & Suites, Kingston.","month":"11","year":"2013","publishDate":"November 01, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Jamaica, Belize, Suriname, Earn 2013 Citi Microentrepreneurship Awards","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/foundation/news/press-release/2013/jamaica-belie-suriname-earn-2013-citi-microentrepreneurship-awards","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"Johannesburg - Citi South Africa has announced the winners of the 2013 Citi Micro-Entrepreneurship Awards Program. Five local entrepreneurs were awarded and will share the prize money of R110,000. ","month":"10","year":"2013","publishDate":"October 31, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Announces Winners of the 2013 Citi Micro-Entrepreneurship Awards in South Africa","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/citi-announces-winners-of-the-2013-citi-micro-entrepreneurship-awards-in-south-africa","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"Caracas, Venezuela - One hundred and twenty people, most of them heads of household, attended <i>My Sustainable Recycling Business</i>, a forum held in Caracas on October 31. The program offers environmental and financial education with the goal of helping participants start their own businesses, exposing them to cases of Venezuelan entrepreneurs who have succeeded through projects based on recycling.","month":"10","year":"2013","publishDate":"October 31, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Venezuela: Citi Launches Fourth Annual \"My Sustainable Business\" Program","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/foundation/news/press-release/2013/veneuela-citi-launches-fourth-annual-my-sustainable-business-program","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"Hong Kong - 3 Hong Kong, the mobile operation of Hutchison Telecommunications Hong Kong Holdings Limited (SEHK: 215), and Citibank Hong Kong jointly announce the launch of '3 Citi Wallet' - the mobile wallet service exclusively tailored for people who are both 3 Hong Kong mobile subscribers and designated Citibank Visa credit card1 users. Using Near Field Communication (NFC) technology, the '3 Citi Wallet' is a multi-purpose mobile wallet service that includes mobile payment, transaction history, a location-based special offer service and a search function that directs customers to the best deals within their vicinity. Marking a new chapter in the history of mobile payment, the '3 Citi Wallet' turns mobile phones into digital wallets that offer consumers speed, convenience and benefits when they spend. ","month":"10","year":"2013","publishDate":"October 31, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"3 Hong Kong and Citibank Jointly Launch '3 Citi Wallet'","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/3-hong-kong-and-citibank-jointly-launch-3-citi-wallet-","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"London - Citi today announced the appointment of Anil Wadhwani as Head of Consumer Banking in Europe, the Middle East and Africa (EMEA). Citi has a Consumer and Commercial Banking presence in 10 markets in EMEA, serving 2.5 million unique customers and 17,000 commercial clients with a network of 202 branches and a credit card market share exceeding 5 percent.","month":"10","year":"2013","publishDate":"October 31, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Appoints Anil Wadhwani Head of Consumer Banking in Europe, Middle East & Africa","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/citi-appoints-anil-wadhwani-head-of-consumer-banking-in-europe-middle-east-africa","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"Quito, Ecuador - The second conference on \"Empowering Women in Latin America,\" organized by the Citi Foundation and Junior Achievement, brought more than 20 representatives from 12 Latin American and Caribbean countries - Argentina, El Salvador, Guatemala, Paraguay, Dominican Republic, Colombia, Honduras, Costa Rica, Trinidad & Tobago, Paraguay, Panama and the United States - to Quito in mid-October.","month":"10","year":"2013","publishDate":"October 30, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Supports Empowering Women in Latin America","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/citi-supports-empowering-women-in-latin-america","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"New York, and Mountain View, Calif. - <a href=\"http://www.citi.com/\">Citi</a> and <a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/\" target=\"blank\">LinkedIn</a> today released results from their third <i>Today's Professional Woman Report</i>, a national survey exploring women's career and financial concerns inspired by the conversations on <a href=\"http://linkd.in/professionalwomen\" target=\"blank\"><i>Connect: Professional Women's Network</i></a> - the fast-growing LinkedIn group of more than 190,000 professional women powered by Citi. For the first time, the survey, which looked at a representative sample of 1,023 professionals, also explored men's perspectives on success and the factors that shape the career paths men pursue.","month":"10","year":"2013","publishDate":"October 30, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"New Survey from Citi and LinkedIn Explores the Factors that Shape Men's and Women's Professional Paths - and Their Varied Definitions of Success","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/new-survey-from-citi-and-linkedin-explores-the-factors-that-shape-men-s-and-women-s-professional-paths-and-their-varied-definitions-of-success","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"Education is closely tied to future economic prosperity, health and wellness. Yet millions of students, particularly those in underserved neighborhoods, aren't getting the education they deserve. <br><br>Public charter schools have great potential to create hope in these communities by fostering opportunity, but demand outpaces availability. One of the greatest hurdles to charter school expansion is real estate. Nationally, an estimated 920,000 students are on waiting lists for a public charter school and the average charter school waiting list has over 150 students. <br><br>To create greater opportunity for children, <a href=\"https://www.civicbuilders.org/\">Civic Builders</a> partners with the nation's best educators to build inspirational school buildings in previously neglected neighborhoods, transforming students' lives and revitalizing communities. <br><br><strong>Who We Are </strong> <br><br>Launched in 2002, Civic Builders is a nonprofit school facilities developer working in underserved communities to ensure that real estate will never be a barrier to an excellent education. <br><br>To date, we have created 18 schools for 9,000 students who have been affected by limited and unsuitable facilities. However, nearly 60 percent of public charter schools say they will run out of space for their students within the next five years. <br><br><strong>How Can You Help Meet This Need? </strong> <br><br>For the next three months, Citigroup Inc. will donate $1 for every $1 million it executes for clients on its Citi Velocity trading platform. We ask that you join us in our fight by supporting Citi Velocity's e for Education program. <br><br>Your support will help Civic Builders create two schools for more than 700 children in the South Bronx and Providence County, Rhode Island - giving students stuck in poorly performing schools a far better chance to reach their potential, and creating great new school space for generations to come. <br><br>Additionally, e for Education proceeds will help us access a $10 million capital investment from the Bill &amp; Melinda Gates Foundation, which requires that funds be matched. <br><br>In the years to come, our efforts will help the public charter school movement grow to meet demand, creating opportunities for students who will be the future of tomorrow. <br><br>Learn more about <a href=\"https://www.civicbuilders.org/\">Civic Builders</a> and <a href=\"https://www.citivelocity.com/equity/public/charity/index.jsp\">Citi Velocity's e for Education program</a>.","image":"638e326ea3c47c530c0a6654","year":"2013","publishDate":"October 30, 2013","type":"insights","title":"Civic Builders - Shaping the Future of Tomorrow","author.jobTitle":["CEO and Co-Founder of Civic Builders"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2013/education-is-closely-tied-to","tags":["Perspective Migration"],"month":"10","author.displayName":["David Umansky"],"siteId":"citigpa","category":"PERSPECTIVES"},{"summary":"New York - On the one-year anniversary of Hurricane Sandy, Citi and the Mayor's Fund to Advance New York City announced that they are committing a combined $250,000 in additional support to complete the restoration of businesses that were devastated by the storm along Beach 116th Street in the Rockaways, and citywide, as part of the Storefront Improvement Programs managed by the NYC Department of Small Business Services. Since launching in May, the Beach 116th Street pilot program has awarded more than $400,000 to 26 businesses to assist with storefront repairs and create a fresh, cohesive image for the Beach 116th Street commercial corridor. There are 40 businesses in the planning and approval phase through the citywide program, which launched in August, with distribution of grants beginning this week. ","month":"10","year":"2013","publishDate":"October 29, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi & the Mayor's Fund to Advance New York City Commit Additional Support to City's Storefront Improvement Programs","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/citi-the-mayor-s-fund-to-advance-new-york-city-commit-additional-support-to-city-s-storefront-improvement-programs","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"Hong Kong - Citi was named the \"Clearing Bank of the Year\" by <i>Asia Risk</i> magazine, a trade publication covering the risk management and structured products industry in the Asia-Pacific region. This is the second year in a row that Citi has received this award.","month":"10","year":"2013","publishDate":"October 28, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Named \"Clearing Bank of the Year\" by Asia Risk","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/citi-named-clearing-bank-of-the-year-by-asia-risk-1","tags":["Press Release Migration","Institutional Clients Group"]},{"summary":"On October 1, 2013 CitiFX launched <i><a href=\"https://www.citivelocity.com/equity/public/charity/index.jsp\">e for Education</a>, </i>an<i> </i>initiative in which we donate $1 for every $1 Million traded on our platform.","image":"638e3270a3c47c530c0a665d","year":"2013","publishDate":"October 28, 2013","type":"insights","title":"Global Education Opportunities are an FX Trade Away","author.jobTitle":["Global Head of G-10 Foreign Exchange, Citi"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2013/global-education-opportunities-are-an-fx-trade-away","tags":["Perspective Migration"],"month":"10","author.displayName":["Jeff Feig"],"siteId":"citigpa","category":"PERSPECTIVES"},{"summary":"New York - Citi® Commercial Bank today announced the expansion of its asset-based lending (ABL) unit to enhance and expand lending to middle market and mid-corporate U.S. businesses seeking revolving lines and term loans based on underlying assets. The strategic growth compliments Citi's Institutional Clients Group ABL franchise, which has been meeting the needs of Citi's corporate clients for more than 25 years.","month":"10","year":"2013","publishDate":"October 24, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Commercial Bank Expands Asset-Based Lending Practice in the U.S. with New Hires for Specialty Segment","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/citi-commercial-bank-expands-asset-based-lending-practice-in-the-us-with-new-hires-for-specialty-segment","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"New York - Continuing its support of the next generation of Team USA, Citi today announced a $500,000 donation to the United States Olympic Committee to launch the Every Step of the Way® program for the Sochi 2014 Olympic and Paralympic Winter Games. Launched in 2012, Every Step of the Way benefits U.S. Olympic and Paralympic hopefuls and athletes of all ages in communities across America. Following the program's success in 2012, Citi is passing the torch to a new team of Citi athletes and extending the program through 2014, donating a total of $1 million to the U.S. Olympic Committee since 2012.","month":"10","year":"2013","publishDate":"October 24, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Announces $500,000 Donation to U.S. Olympic Committee to Benefit the Next Generation of Team USA","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/citi-announces-500000-donation-to-us-olympic-committee-to-benefit-the-next-generation-of-team-usa","tags":["Press Release Migration","Citi-Wide"]},{"summary":"Singapore - Citi today announced the launch of CitiDirect Banking Evolution (BE<sup>SM</sup>), its next-generation electronic banking platform for institutional clients, in Singapore. The platform addresses the key challenges institutions face around accessing timely, accurate, relevant and easy to understand information so that new opportunities can be identified and prompt decisions can be made to improve business outcomes.","month":"10","year":"2013","publishDate":"October 24, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Launches Award-Winning Electronic Banking Platform for Institutional Clients in Singapore","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/citi-launches-award-winning-electronic-banking-platform-for-institutional-clients-in-singapore","tags":["Press Release Migration","Institutional Clients Group"]},{"summary":"Hong Kong - Citi Treasury and Trade Solutions (TTS), a division of the Institutional Clients Group, announced the launch of Citi® Payments Risk Manager earlier today. This new functionality gives clients enhanced visibility and control over their payment flows by providing aggregated payments data, reporting and trend detection capabilities to facilitate the clients' investigation of potential outlier transactions. With the release of this latest analytical tool, Citi further distinguishes itself from its competitors by providing an innovative account payables risk management solution available through the award-winning CitiDirect BE<sup>SM</sup> platform.","month":"10","year":"2013","publishDate":"October 24, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Hong Kong: Citi Launches Innovative Payments Risk Management Tool for Corporate Clients","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/hong-kong-citi-launches-innovative-payments-risk-management-tool-for-corporate-clients","tags":["Press Release Migration","Institutional Clients Group"]},{"summary":"Sydney - Citibank Australia has been announced as the Gold award winner for its 'Best Jobs in the World' campaign at <i>Marketing Events Magazine's</i> 2013 Awards.","month":"10","year":"2013","publishDate":"October 24, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citibank Strikes Gold for 'Best Jobs' Campaign to Boost Tourism in Australia","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/citibank-strikes-gold-for-best-jobs-campaign-to-boost-tourism-in-australia","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"Lima - Citibank Peru has inaugurated a new smart branch in Jockey Plaza and renovated its branches in Chocavento and Benavides to make them \"smart\" as well. The new branch model offers clients a unique experience, thanks to innovations in atmosphere and design, technological solutions, customer service and, above all, digital communications. ","month":"10","year":"2013","publishDate":"October 23, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citibank Peru Inaugurates Jockey Plaza Smart Branch","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/citibank-peru-inaugurates-jockey-plaa-smart-branch","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"New York – Citi and the <a href=\"http://vets.syr.edu/\" target=\"blank\">Institute for Veterans and Military Families</a> (IVMF) at Syracuse University today announced that the <a href=\"http://us.accion.org/\" target=\"blank\">Accion U.S. Network</a> will provide first-stop financing for aspiring small-business owners participating in the <a href=\"https://www.citigroup.com/citi/citizen/community/citisalutes/realizing_your_dream.html\">Citi Salutes<sup>SM</sup>: Realizing Your Dream</a> program for veteran entrepreneurs, which is funded by the Citi Foundation. The country's largest nationwide micro- and small-business lending network will provide crucial access to microloan capital and technical assistance for graduates of the IVMF's entrepreneurship training programs including: <a href=\"http://whitman.syr.edu/vwise\" target=\"blank\">Veteran Women Igniting the Spirit of Entrepreneurship</a> (V-WISE) and <a href=\"http://boots2business.org/\" target=\"blank\">Boots to Business</a>, both joint initiatives of the U.S. Small Business Administration (SBA).","month":"10","year":"2013","publishDate":"October 23, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Accion U.S. Network Joins Citi & Institute for Veterans and Military Families to Offer Strategic Financing Support for Veteran Entrepreneurs","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/accion-us-network-joins-citi-institute-for-veterans-and-military-families-to-offer-strategic-financing-support-for-veteran-entrepreneurs","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"Hong Kong - Citibank Korea Inc. today announced the launch of cross-border automated cash concentration services to facilitate foreign currency cross-border trade flows into Korea, making it the first bank to offer such liquidity management solutions in the market.","month":"10","year":"2013","publishDate":"October 23, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi First to Launch Automated Cross-Border Sweeping in Korea","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/citi-first-to-launch-automated-cross-border-sweeping-in-korea","tags":["Press Release Migration","Institutional Clients Group"]},{"summary":"Manila - Citi Philippines announced it will offer payment relief to its credit cardholders and personal loan customers that were displaced by the recent earthquake that hit Central Visayas. The 7.2-magnitude earthquake that shook Bohol was also felt in nearby areas with various earthquake intensities recorded in Cebu City, Negros Occidental, Guimaras Island, Bacolod City, and Leyte, stretching to Davao City, Zamboanga Peninsula, Antique and Surigao del Sur. The National Disaster Risk Reduction and Management Council reported an estimated 3.2 million people were affected by the earthquake.","month":"10","year":"2013","publishDate":"October 21, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Philippines: Citi Offers Payment Relief for Bohol Earthquake Victims","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/philippines-citi-offers-payment-relief-for-bohol-earthquake-victims","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"<br>","month":"10","year":"2013","publishDate":"October 21, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Streetline - Reimagining Parking","category":"PERSPECTIVES","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2013/streetline---reimagining-parking","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"By 2050, the population of the United States is projected to grow from 314 million to approximately 400 million people -- and most of this growth is projected to be in our cities. Put another way, less than 40 years from today, 89 percent of our population will claim a city as home. In the middle of the last century that number was 67 percent. Within the span of 100 years, the U.S. will essentially have become a country of cities.","month":"10","author.displayName":["Jonathan F.P. Rose","Andrew Ditton"],"year":"2013","publishDate":"October 21, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Creating Communities of Opportunity","category":"PERSPECTIVES","author.jobTitle":["President, Jonathan Rose Companies","Co-Head of Citi Community Capital"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2013/creating-communities-of-opportunity","tags":["Perspective Migration","Public Affairs","Global Functions","Branding"]},{"summary":"Atlanta, Ga., and Fort Worth, Texas - RadioShack and Citi Retail Services today announced a long-term agreement to extend their 28-year consumer credit relationship. Under the agreement, Citi will continue to provide service-enhancing solutions and analytics in support of RadioShack's targets for growth. RadioShack customers will continue to enjoy comprehensive financing programs and top-tier customer service. ","month":"10","year":"2013","publishDate":"October 17, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"RadioShack and Citi Retail Services Extend Consumer Credit Agreement","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/radioshack-and-citi-retail-services-extend-consumer-credit-agreement","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"Hong Kong - In a recent industry poll by <i>Asiamoney</i> magazine, Citi retained its top spot from last year by being voted the best foreign exchange (FX) service provider by corporations in Asia. The poll surveyed 3,504 senior treasury, financial and management officials based in Asia, representing 3,044 different institutions.","month":"10","year":"2013","publishDate":"October 17, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Tops Asia Foreign Exchange Poll","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/citi-tops-asia-foreign-exchange-poll","tags":["Press Release Migration","Institutional Clients Group"]},{"summary":"New York - The Board of Directors of Citigroup Inc. today declared a quarterly dividend on Citigroup's common stock of $0.01 per share, payable on November 22, 2013 to stockholders of record on November 4, 2013.","month":"10","year":"2013","publishDate":"October 17, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citigroup Declares Common Stock Dividend","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/citigroup-declares-common-stock-dividend-1","tags":["Press Release Migration","Citi-Wide"]},{"summary":"Kuala Lumpur - Citibank won five top awards at the 14th Annual Customer Relationship Management and Contact Center Association of Malaysia's (CCAM) annual awards ceremony.","month":"10","year":"2013","publishDate":"October 17, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Malaysia: Citibank Bags Five Customer Service Awards","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/malaysia-citibank-bags-five-customer-service-awards","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"Getting back to nature and helping sea turtles has been a Banamex tradition for eight years and such a popular one that 1,000 employees applied to volunteer at this summer's Sea Turtle Conservation & Community Development program. Over the years, the program has been developed in partnership with the Mexican government and local communities where the sea turtles come ashore to lay their eggs.","image":"638e3274a3c47c530c0a6678","year":"2013","publishDate":"October 17, 2013","type":"insights","title":"A Banamex Tradition: Sea Turtle Conservation in Mexico","author.jobTitle":["Community Relations, Banamex"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2013/a-banamex-tradition-sea-turtle-conservation-in-mexico","tags":["Perspective Migration"],"month":"10","author.displayName":["Luis Alonso Martinez"],"siteId":"citigpa","category":"PERSPECTIVES"},{"summary":"Port-Au-Prince, Haiti - Citi Haiti recently obtained LEED (Leadership in Energy and Environmental Design) certification for its new offices in Port-au-Prince. The building is the first on the island to be designed and built according to the highest environmental standards in an effort to earn the LEED certification.","month":"10","year":"2013","publishDate":"October 16, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi is the First Company in Haiti to Obtain LEED Certification","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/citi-is-the-first-company-in-haiti-to-obtain-leed-certification","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"Three Caribbean microfinance institutions and three microentrepreneurs are the finalists for the 2013 Citi Microentrepreneurship Awards for the Caribbean. The winners will be announced during a ceremony at the Courtleigh Hotel & Suites, Kingston, Jamaica, on October 31, 2013. Peter Moses, Managing Director & Citi Country Officer at Citi Jamaica, will present.","month":"10","year":"2013","publishDate":"October 16, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Carribean: Six Vie for Citi Microentrepreneurship Awards","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/foundation/news/press-release/2013/carribean-six-vie-for-citi-microentrepreneurship-awards","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"Miami, Florida - Non-financial institutions chose Citi as the no. 1 Regional Cash Management Bank in Latin America for the seventh consecutive year in <i>Euromoney's</i> prestigious annual Cash Management Survey 2013. Furthermore, the bank has been ranked by non-financial institutions as the Best Domestic Cash Management Bank in Argentina, Peru, and Uruguay, second best in Venezuela and Mexico (Banamex), and third best in Colombia. Additionally, financial institutions ranked Citi among the top 5 in dollar, euro, sterling, and yen transactions in Latin America.","month":"10","year":"2013","publishDate":"October 16, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Ranks as #1 Cash Management Provider in Latin America in the Euromoney Cash Management Poll 2013","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/citi-ranks-as-1-cash-management-provider-in-latin-america-in-the-euromoney-cash-management-poll-2013","tags":["Press Release Migration","Institutional Clients Group"]},{"summary":"Santo Domingo - Citi, a global expert in agency and trust services, will play a key role at the 22nd Latin American Trust Conference (COLAFI 2013). Two high-ranking Citi executives, Michael C. Morcom and Omar P. Rashid, will serve as featured speakers and will share their experiences in various markets where the bank operates. ","month":"10","year":"2013","publishDate":"October 15, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Participates in Dominican Republic Conference on Trusts","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/citi-participates-in-dominican-republic-conference-on-trusts","tags":["Press Release Migration","Institutional Clients Group"]},{"summary":"New York - Citigroup Inc. today reported net income for the third quarter 2013 of $3.2 billion, or $1.00 per diluted share, on revenues of $17.9 billion. This compared to net income of $468 million, or $0.15 per diluted share, on revenues of $13.7 billion for the third quarter 2012.","month":"10","year":"2013","publishDate":"October 15, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citigroup Reports Third Quarter 2013 Earnings per Share of $1.00; $1.02 Excluding CVA/DVA","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/citigroup-reports-third-quarter-2013-earnings-per-share-of-100-102-excluding-cvadva","tags":["Press Release Migration","Citi-Wide"]},{"summary":"<p class=\"blog-listing-body\"> Earlier this morning, Citi released its earnings report for the third quarter of 2013. Chief Financial Officer John Gerspach discusses the report in this video. For more information and the full earnings report, visit the <a href=\"https://www.citigroup.com/global/investors\">Investor Relations section of Citigroup's website</a>. </p>","month":"10","year":"2013","publishDate":"October 15, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Releases Third Quarter 2013 Earnings","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/citi-releases-third-quarter-2013-earnings"},{"summary":"CitiMortgage and VeteransPlus, a national veteran service organization, are coming to the Washington, D.C. area on Thursday, October 17, 2013, with Citi's proprietary 2013 Road to Recovery for the Military, featuring a homeowner support event for current and former members of the Armed Forces. At this event, Citi's Homeowner Support Travel Team of mortgage professionals and VeteransPlus financial counselors will have one-on-one discussions with current and former service members in need of assistance with their mortgages, offering clear answers to their mortgage questions in a private setting. All military service members and veterans, including those who have missed payments or have payment concerns, are invited and do not have to be CitiMortgage customers to attend. Find event details <a href=\"https://community.homeownersupport.com/thread/1762?tstart=0\">here</a>.","image":"638e3277a3c47c530c0a668b","month":"10","year":"2013","publishDate":"October 14, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Hosts Foreclosure Prevention/Homeowner Assistance Event for Service Members and Veterans on Oct. 17 in the D.C. Area.","category":"PERSPECTIVES","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2013/citi-hosts-foreclosure-preventionhomeowner-assistance-event-for-service-members-and-veterans-on-oct","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"In 2009, my decision to return to the financial services industry in the thick of the economic crisis may have surprised some. However, once the crisis hit, I knew almost immediately that I needed to be part of fixing the industry to which I had dedicated more than three decades of my life. While I knew I was embarking on unprecedented financial times, I was excited by the challenges of this opportunity.","image":"638e3278a3c47c530c0a6692","year":"2013","publishDate":"October 10, 2013","type":"insights","title":"Deborah McWhinney: Paving the Path to Success-Define Your Passion","author.jobTitle":["COO Global Enterprise Payments, Citi"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2013/deborah-mcwhinney-paving-the-path-to-success-define-your-passion","tags":["Perspective Migration"],"month":"10","author.displayName":["Deborah McWinney"],"siteId":"citigpa","category":"PERSPECTIVES"},{"summary":"New York - Citi today announced an initiative to expand the Corporation for Enterprise Development's (CFED) state-level Assets & Opportunity Scorecard to cities nationwide. With the support of a $1 million Citi commitment, CFED will launch the Household Economic Security Project to equip municipal policy makers, civic leaders and private sector stakeholders with the city-level data and tools they need to assess and build the financial security of local households. To demonstrate how household financial security metrics should inform smart economic policymaking and programs, Citi and CFED proposes to work with partners in 10 U.S. cities to receive in-depth research, analysis and guidance on transforming data into action.","month":"10","year":"2013","publishDate":"October 08, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi & Corporation for Enterprise Development Announce Initiative to Bolster Household Economic Security in U.S. Cities","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/citi-corporation-for-enterprise-development-announce-initiative-to-bolster-household-economic-security-in-us-cities","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"Lima, Peru - Citi Peru announced the issue of the first letter of credit denominated in Renminbi (RMB), the currency used in the Chinese market, more commonly known as the Yuan. Thanks to the letter of credit, an important bank client in the retail sector was able to significantly improve conditions for its imports.","month":"10","year":"2013","publishDate":"October 07, 2013","siteId":"citigpa",