":"insights","title":"Citigroup Announces Expiration and Final Tender Results of Offers to Purchase Seven Series of Outstanding Notes","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/citigroup-announces-expiration-and-final-tender-results-of-offers-to-purchase-seven-series-of-outstanding-notes-2","tags":["Press Release Migration","Citi-Wide"]},{"summary":"Physical inactivity is a reality that busy working professionals face every day. Since many of Citi's employees are desk-based, we supply a variety of fitness and health education programs to encourage them to pursue heart-healthy activities. In fact, Citi was <a href=\"https://www.heart.org/HEARTORG/\">nationally recognized</a> with a Platinum Level Fit-Friendly Company Award in 2011 and 2012. The award is given to \"extraordinary\" employers who go above and beyond in promoting workplace health and represented an improvement over our Gold Level award in 2010.","image":"638e3280a3c47c530c0a66be","year":"2013","publishDate":"September 12, 2013","type":"insights","title":"Citi Fitness: Promoting a Culture of Health","author.jobTitle":["Corporate Medical Director, Citi","Health Promotion Manager, Citi"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2013/citi-fitness-promoting-a-culture-of-health","tags":["Perspective Migration"],"month":"09","author.displayName":["Lori Zimmerman","Megan Grabel"],"siteId":"citigpa","category":"PERSPECTIVES"},{"summary":"Penang - Citi is teaming up with InvestPenang to further promote Penang and Malaysia as a strategic center for treasury management activities.","month":"09","year":"2013","publishDate":"September 11, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Partners with InvestPenang to Promote Penang and Malaysia as Center for Treasury Management Operations","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/citi-partners-with-investpenang-to-promote-penang-and-malaysia-as-center-for-treasury-management-operations","tags":["Press Release Migration","Institutional Clients Group"]},{"summary":"Manila - Citi Philippines recently gathered the treasury and finance officials of corporate clients in an economic briefing entitled \"Citi Perspectives.\" This event is one of several economic briefings held throughout the year for clients, offering relevant up-to-date information to help corporate clients map their financial future.","month":"09","year":"2013","publishDate":"September 11, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"'Citi Perspectives' Hosted for Corporate Clients","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/-citi-perspectives-hosted-for-corporate-clients","tags":["Press Release Migration","Institutional Clients Group"]},{"summary":"Hong Kong - Citi and Po Leung Kuk today held the kick-off ceremony of the fifth \"Agent Penny and Will Power\" series. Funded by the Citi Foundation and supported by the Education Bureau of the Hong Kong Government, the \"Agent Penny and Will Power\" series aims to promote financial literacy in the form of a comic book and drama designed for upper-primary school students aged 10-12 in Hong Kong. ","month":"09","year":"2013","publishDate":"September 10, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi and Po Leung Kuk Kick Off Fifth \"Agent Penny and Will Power\" Series","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/citi-and-po-leung-kuk-kick-off-fifth-agent-penny-and-will-power-series","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"São Paulo - Citibank and Visa, the world's largest payments technology company, announced today the launch of a prepaid card for corporate and public sector clients in Brazil. The product represents a new payment alternative that allows issuers to replace old methods of payment, such as cash, checks or vouchers, with a more secure and efficient electronic payment option. ","month":"09","year":"2013","publishDate":"September 10, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Launches Prepaid Corporate Card in Brazil","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/citi-launches-prepaid-corporate-card-in-brail","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"Atlanta, Ga., & New York, N.Y. - Citi announced that it successfully completed on September 6 the acquisition from Capital One Financial Corp. of Best Buy's U.S. credit card portfolio and the conversion today of the portfolio to Citi's systems. Citi Retail Services, the premier provider of credit card products, services and solutions for North America retailers, will manage the portfolio going forward. The portfolio currently totals more than $6 billion in receivables.","month":"09","year":"2013","publishDate":"September 09, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Successfully Completes the Acquisition and Conversion of Best Buy's U.S. Credit Program","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/citi-successfully-completes-the-acquisition-and-conversion-of-best-buy-s-us-credit-program","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"Tegucigalpa - Citi Honduras recently obtained gold-level LEED (Leadership in Energy and Environmental Design) certification for its new offices in Altia Business Park in San Pedro Sula. The building is the first in Honduras to be designed and built according to the highest environmental standards in an effort to earn LEED certification.","month":"09","year":"2013","publishDate":"September 06, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi is the First Bank in Honduras with LEED Certification","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/citi-is-the-first-bank-in-honduras-with-leed-certification","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"Puerto Rico - With a cocktail reception at the Ritz-Carlton Hotel & Casino in Isla Verde on August 28, Citi marked 95 years at the forefront of excellence in financial services in Puerto Rico. More than 200 clients attended, along with special guests and public sector officials, with Citi Puerto Rico Country Officer Guillermo Gómez presiding. ","month":"09","year":"2013","publishDate":"September 05, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi: 95 Years of Excellence in Puerto Rico","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/citi-95-years-of-excellence-in-puerto-rico","tags":["Press Release Migration"]},{"summary":"Prague - Czechs frequently use credit cards for making payments at retailers and for cash withdrawals from ATMs when traveling abroad, and this significantly increases during the summer holiday period. This is also confirmed by the latest data from Citibank Europe plc, which suggests that the number of foreign transactions through Citi credit cards almost doubled (up by 90 percent) in July 2013 compared to the average number of transactions executed through credit cards per month in the first half of this year. The overall volume of these transactions increased by more than one half (up by 55 percent). A similar trend was also visible in August this year. Citibank's share of Czech clients' foreign transactions executed through credit cards is about one fifth of the Czech market. ","month":"09","year":"2013","publishDate":"September 05, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Czech Republic: Czechs Increasingly Use Credit Cards During Holidays Abroad","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/citi-cech-republic-cechs-increasingly-use-credit-cards-during-holidays-abroad","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"Budapest, Hungary - Réthy Fashion, Family-Friendly City Social Cooperative, Li-Ko 97' and BEN-Team were the four best performing social enterprises who received awards from Aftab Ahmed, Citi Country Officer for Hungary, and Anna Horvath, Country Director of NESsT Hungary, on September 4 for their outstanding performance in the 2012/2013 NESsT-Citi Social Enterprise Development Program.","month":"09","year":"2013","publishDate":"September 05, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"NESsT and Citi Hungary Announce Four Winners of the 2012/2013 Social Enterprise Development Competition","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/nesst-and-citi-hungary-announce-four-winners-of-the-20122013-social-enterprise-development-competition","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"We noticed that many new college graduates who came in to interview with Citi Singapore could not distinguish between the various businesses and functions in banking. That got us thinking....how can we help them progress their interest in making banking their career? Since Citi is the largest banking employer and 2nd largest private sector employer in Singapore, we felt we could and should contribute to ensuring a pipeline of young talent for our company and the industry.","image":"638e3284a3c47c530c0a66e2","year":"2013","publishDate":"September 05, 2013","type":"insights","title":"A Student's Story: Improving Undergraduate Knowledge of and Interest in Banking","author.jobTitle":["Student, Citi Banking 101 Foundational Program"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2013/citis-banking-101-program---a-students-perspective-on-career-prep-for-the-financial-world","tags":["Perspective Migration"],"month":"09","author.displayName":["Cheong Por Yee"],"siteId":"citigpa","category":"PERSPECTIVES"},{"summary":"Guatemala City, Guatemala - Citi Guatemala announced today the launch of its new Citi Súper MultiPremios credit card as part of its commitment to innovation and offering new financial products and solutions to its clients in Guatemala. ","month":"09","year":"2013","publishDate":"September 04, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Guatemala Presents Its New Citi Super MultiPremios Credit Card, Which Allows Users to Earn Miles at All of the Country's Supermarkets","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/citi-guatemala-presents-its-new-citi-super-multipremios-credit-card-which-allows-users-to-earn-miles-at-all-of-the-country-s-supermarkets","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"Manila - Three community leaders came together to reach out to more than 250 children and help them and their families better respond in times of typhoons and other natural disasters.","month":"09","year":"2013","publishDate":"September 04, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Philippines: Teaching Kids to Be Disaster-Ready","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/philippines-teaching-kids-to-be-disaster-ready","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"Hagatna, Guam - Six Citi Guam employees were among 1,190 Citi U.S. employees qualified for the President's Volunteer Service Award. In total, these 1,190 employees gave nearly 332,000 volunteer hours in 2012.","month":"09","year":"2013","publishDate":"September 03, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Guam Employees Among 2012 U.S. President's Volunteer Service Awardees","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/citi-guam-employees-among-2012-us-president-s-volunteer-service-awardees","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"Budapest, Hungary - Citi's Commercial Banking clients in Hungary can now quickly and easily monitor financial and liquidity related information on up to 300 of their partner companies on the free online Citi-Opten PartnerWatch Service. ","month":"09","year":"2013","publishDate":"September 03, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Hungary's Commercial Banking Clients Can Now Monitor Information on Their Partners Through the Free Citi-Opten PartnerWatch Service","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/citi-hungary-s-commercial-banking-clients-can-now-monitor-information-on-their-partners-through-the-free-citi-opten-partnerwatch-service","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"To further meet client demand for increased efficiency and convenience, Citibank Taiwan has extended its partnership with Vieshow Cinemas to offer a new paperless or QR code ticketing service. With the new service, clients who book tickets using Citi credit cards on their smartphones will be able to enter cinema halls directly, without having to queue up to collect their movie tickets. ","month":"09","year":"2013","publishDate":"September 01, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Taiwan Extends Partnership with Vieshow Cinemas to Launch Electronic Ticketing Service","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/citi-taiwan-extends-partnership-with-vieshow-cinemas-to-launch-electronic-ticketing-service","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"Singapore - On Citi Singapore's Family Day on August 31, more than 1,600 Citi employees and their families built more than 750 sandcastles to donate 52,500 bowls of rice to needy families in the South East district of Singapore. Citi Singapore pledged 70 bowls of rice for each sandcastle. The feat also created a record in the Singapore Book of Records for the \"Most Number of Sandcastles Built at One Location.\" The sandcastles were built on Tanjong Beach at Sentosa. ","month":"08","year":"2013","publishDate":"August 31, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citibankers and Their Families Donate 77,500 Bowls of Rice to Less Privileged Families in the South East District of Singapore","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/citibankers-and-their-families-donate-77500-bowls-of-rice-to-less-privileged-families-in-the-south-east-district-of-singapore","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"New York - Citigroup Inc. is announcing the redemption, in whole, of its 6.100% Enhanced TRUPS® issued by Citigroup Capital X (CUSIP: 173064205) (the \"Redeemed TRUPS®\").","month":"08","year":"2013","publishDate":"August 29, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citigroup Announces $369 Million Redemption of Citigroup Capital X Trust Preferred Securities","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/citigroup-announces-369-million-redemption-of-citigroup-capital-x-trust-preferred-securities","tags":["Press Release Migration","Citi-Wide"]},{"summary":"Elephants have played a central and important part in Thai culture for centuries and have been embraced by kings and the rural poor alike. Unfortunately, economic development and modernization have led to the marginalization of elephants, destruction of their habitats, and serious issues affecting their wellbeing. In an effort to raise awareness about the importance of elephant conservation in Thailand, Citi worked with community partner and Corporate Banking client the Minor Group's - <a href=\"https://goldentriangle.anantara.com/elephantcamp.aspx\">Anantara Golden Triangle Elephant Camp &amp; Resort in Chiang Rai</a> to launch the Citi Elephant Nursery. Anantara's charitable arm, the <a href=\"https://www.anantara.com/golden-triangle-asian-elephant-foundation/\">Golden Triangle Asian Elephant Foundation</a>, was set up in 2006 to improve the plight of Thailand's elephants. <br><br>By working with Anantara, Citi hopes to promote innovative new techniques in furthering the welfare of baby elephants, and to help raise awareness of the issues they face in a modern Thailand. As part of the initiative, Citi is funding the construction of a new permanent shelter and a baby elephant nursery facility on Anantara grounds in Chiang Rai. <br><br>","image":"638e3285a3c47c530c0a66eb","year":"2013","publishDate":"August 29, 2013","type":"insights","title":"Citi's Elephant Nursery - Helping Elephant Conservation in Thailand","author.jobTitle":["Citi Country Officer of Thailand"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2013/-citis-elephant-nursery---helping-elephant-conservation-in-thailand","tags":["Perspective Migration"],"month":"08","author.displayName":["Darren Buckley"],"siteId":"citigpa","category":"PERSPECTIVES"},{"summary":"Nadeem Lodhi, Citi Country Officer for Pakistan, and a member of The British Asian Trust Pakistan Advisory Council, joined other members of the council at a special meeting hosted by HRH the Prince of Wales, the President of the Trust. ","month":"08","year":"2013","publishDate":"August 28, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Country Officer for Pakistan Meets HRH the Prince of Wales","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/citi-country-officer-for-pakistan-meets-hrh-the-prince-of-wales","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"Boise, ID - The Citi Foundation has awarded the Women's and Children's Alliance (WCA) a grant for $30,000 to support the Treasure Valley Economic Action Program (TVEAP) that provides financial literacy training.","month":"08","year":"2013","publishDate":"August 28, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Grant Supports Financial Literacy for Domestic & Sexual Abuse Survivors","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/grant-supports-financial-literacy-for-domestic-sexual-abuse-survivors","tags":["Press Release Migration"]},{"summary":"New York - Citigroup Inc. (\"<b>Citigroup</b>\") announced today the applicable Reference Yield and Total Consideration for the previously announced cash tender offers (each, an \"<b>Offer</b>\" and, collectively, the \"<b>Offers</b>\") with respect to each series of Notes listed in the table below (the \"<b>Notes</b>\").","month":"08","year":"2013","publishDate":"August 28, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citigroup Announces Reference Yields and Total Consideration for Note Tender Offers","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/citigroup-announces-reference-yields-and-total-consideration-for-note-tender-offers-2","tags":["Press Release Migration","Citi-Wide"]},{"summary":"New York - Citigroup Inc. (\"<b>Citigroup</b>\") announced today that it has increased the maximum aggregate principal amount of specified series of notes (the \"<b>Notes</b>\") that it will accept (each, a \"<b>Maximum Series Tender Cap</b>\") in its previously announced cash tender offers (each, an \"<b>Offer</b>\" and, collectively, the \"<b>Offers</b>\"), as set forth in the table below.","month":"08","year":"2013","publishDate":"August 28, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citigroup Announces Upsizing of Offers to Purchase Specified Series of Outstanding Notes","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/citigroup-announces-upsiing-of-offers-to-purchase-specified-series-of-outstanding-notes-2","tags":["Press Release Migration","Citi-Wide"]},{"summary":"New York - Citi Microfinance and Kiva are launching Kiva U, a new program to engage students and educators in a global effort to expand financial inclusion and foster community among the next generation of change makers. Kiva U is an ambitious initiative to build, strengthen and connect school-based microfinance clubs across the nation, develop teaching tools for experiential learning across education levels and foster leadership among students active in social enterprise, international development and financial inclusion. College students, high school students and educators are encouraged to connect with peers from across the nation by joining Kiva U at <a href=\"http://www.kiva.org/kivau\" target=\"blank\">www.kivau.org</a> and by following Kiva U on social media.","month":"08","year":"2013","publishDate":"August 27, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi and Kiva Launch Kiva U to Engage Students and Educators in Global Effort to Expand Financial Inclusion","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/citi-and-kiva-launch-kiva-u-to-engage-students-and-educators-in-global-effort-to-expand-financial-inclusion","tags":["Press Release Migration"]},{"summary":"We are listening to you every day - about what is not working and just as important, what we have changed that is working for you. Your suggestions and experiences continue to help us understand where we can improve. Here are some recent changes we made based on what you have told us. <br><br><strong>We know you expect fast, simple service without having to pay extra for it.</strong> We are happy to let you know that you will no longer be charged an expedited payment fee when you need to make your payment quickly over the phone. You can also now request copies of your past billing statements at no additional cost. <br><br>Similarly, for those of you making purchases internationally, we have four cards that do not charge foreign transaction fees on purchases and each includes chip technology that provides global acceptance and added security when making purchases at merchants that use chip terminals: <a href=\"https://www.citi.com/credit-cards/credit-card-details/detail.do?ID=citi-thankyou-premier-credit-card&amp;category=reward-credit-cards\">Citi ThankYou® Premier Card</a>, the <a href=\"https://www.citi.com/credit-cards/credit-card-details/detail.do?ID=citi-prestige-card&amp;category=reward-credit-cards\">Citi Prestige® Card</a>, the <a href=\"https://www.citi.com/credit-cards/credit-card-details/detail.do?ID=hilton-hhonors-reserve-card&amp;category=reward-credit-cards\">Citi® Hilton HHonors™ Reserve Card</a>, and the <a href=\"https://www.citi.com/credit-cards/credit-card-details/detail.do?ID=citi-executive-aadvantage-world-elite-mastercard&amp;category=reward-credit-cards\">Citi Executive SM / AAdvantage® World Elite™ MasterCard®</a>. <br><br><strong>Many of you have asked how automatic payments work - and how they help you manage your account.</strong> We have three different options available for automatic online bill payments to your Citi Card. You can set up the payment for your minimum amount due, for your full monthly balance, or a specific amount set by you. Learn more about AutoPay and set your account in the Payments section on Account Online. Sign on to your account at <a href=\"https://www.citi.com/credit-cards/creditcards/CitiHome.do\">Citi.com</a> to get started. <br><br><strong>You told us you want to earn points faster. Now you can with two cards that provide some of the best benefits out there.</strong> The Citi ThankYou and Citi ThankYou Preferred Cards are the <u>only</u> cards that let you earn double ThankYou Points on purchases for both dining and entertainment at no annual fee. This means you earn 2 ThankYou Points for every dollar spent on dining and entertainment purchases, from your morning coffee to dinner out, to an afternoon at the ballpark, a night at the movies, or digital music downloads. Other purchases will earn 1 ThankYouPoint for every dollar spent. Learn more about the ThankYou Preferred Card or apply <a href=\"https://www.citi.com/credit-cards/credit-card-details/detail.do?ID=citi-thankyou-credit-card-preferred-card&amp;category=view-all-credit-cards\">here</a>. <br><br>We know you have many credit card choices - we are working hard to ensure Citi is the card you reach for every time you make a purchase. You can look forward to more updates in the coming months. We ask that you continue sharing your feedback so we can keep making changes to serve you better.","image":"638e3287a3c47c530c0a66f4","year":"2013","publishDate":"August 27, 2013","type":"insights","title":"You Spoke, We Listened","author.jobTitle":["Citi Cards CEO"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2013/you-spoke-we-listened-6","tags":["Perspective Migration"],"month":"08","author.displayName":["Jud Linville"],"siteId":"citigpa","category":"PERSPECTIVES"},{"summary":"New York - For the fourth consecutive year, Citi has been ranked as the number one Corporate Card issuer in the U.S. by <i>The Nilson Report</i>. The ranking is based on 2012 transaction volume and places Citi well ahead of its nearest competitors.","month":"08","year":"2013","publishDate":"August 26, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"The Nilson Report Ranks Citi® as Number One U.S. Corporate Card Issuer for Fourth Consecutive Year","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/the-nilson-report-ranks-citi-as-number-one-us-corporate-card-issuer-for-fourth-consecutive-year","tags":["Press Release Migration"]},{"summary":"Tegucigalpa, Honduras - Citi recently offered more than 1.2 million lempiras in grants to United Way, FUNADEH and Junior Achievement in support of community educational and entrepreneurship programs. Each of these non-profit organizations operates a range of projects that benefit Honduran communities.","month":"08","year":"2013","publishDate":"August 23, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Awards Grants to Honduran Non-Profits","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/citi-awards-grants-to-honduran-non-profits","tags":["Press Release Migration"]},{"summary":"Guatemala City - More than 500 high school students participated today in the young entrepreneur training program \"<i>Socios por un Día</i>\" (Partners for a Day), organized by Empresarios Juveniles with support from Citi.","month":"08","year":"2013","publishDate":"August 22, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Companies Invite Young People to be \"Partners for a Day\"","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/companies-invite-young-people-to-be-partners-for-a-day","tags":["Press Release Migration"]},{"summary":"By Irene Blake, Coordinator of Citi's Wireless Drop-off Campaign","image":"638e3288a3c47c530c0a66fb","year":"2013","publishDate":"August 22, 2013","type":"insights","title":"Citi Employee's 2013 Wireless Drop-off Campaign/Partnered with e-Cycle Donates to Three Charities","author.jobTitle":["Coordinator of Citi's Wireless Drop-off Campaign"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2013/citi-employees-2013-wireless-drop-off-campaignpartnered-with-e-cycle-donates-to-three-charities","tags":["Perspective Migration"],"month":"08","author.displayName":["Irene Blake"],"siteId":"citigpa","category":"PERSPECTIVES"},{"summary":"Chongqing - Citibank (China) Co. Ltd. (\"Citi China\") and Humana People to People (\"HPP\") today unveiled an achievement exhibition of Citi Wanzhou Rural Micro Enterprise Development Program (\"Wanzhou Program\") in Chongqing to celebrate the success of the three-year program. Meanwhile, Citi announced its continuous support to HPP to conduct a similar program in Chongqing's Haokou township of Wulong county starting in January 2014, helping 1,500 local households (about 6,000 individuals) to increase their income level. ","month":"08","year":"2013","publishDate":"August 21, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Deepens Support of Rural Small Enterprises Development in Chongqing","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/citi-deepens-support-of-rural-small-enterprises-development-in-chongqing","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"San José, Costa Rica - Citi, the Citi Foundation, the ADRI Association and MEIC announced the opening of nominations for the seventh annual Citi Microentrepreneurship Awards in Costa Rica.","month":"08","year":"2013","publishDate":"August 21, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi, ADRI and MEIC Launch Seventh Annual Microentrepreneurship Awards in Costa Rica","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/foundation/news/press-release/2013/citi-adri-and-meic-launch-seventh-annual-microentrepreneurship-awards-in-costa-rica","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"Citibank Singapore Limited today launched a new risk advisory tool offering Citigold clients a holistic overview of their investment portfolios. The portfolio risk evaluator tool is the first of its kind to provide clients with an analysis of the performance and resilience of their existing investment portfolios through simulating historical stress events. With this, clients are able to get a more in-depth and detailed understanding of their risk exposure and make more informed financial decisions. This tool is also the latest enhancement to Citibank's Citigold proposition catering to affluent clients with liquid assets of between S$200,000 and S$1 million. ","month":"08","year":"2013","publishDate":"August 21, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citibank Launches Singapore's First Portfolio Risk Evaluator Tool for Affluent Segment","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/citibank-launches-singapore-s-first-portfolio-risk-evaluator-tool-for-affluent-segment","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"Panhandle, Texas - Tapping into a premier wind resource, Pattern Energy Group LP is starting construction of the 218-megawatt Panhandle Wind Project using Texas' new Competitive Renewable Energy Zone transmission infrastructure and connecting to the state's main power grid operator, the Electric Reliability Council of Texas. GE (NYSE: GE) unit GE Energy Financial Services and Citigroup, Inc. (NYSE: C) unit Citigroup Global Markets, Inc. will invest structured equity in the project. ","month":"08","year":"2013","publishDate":"August 20, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Pattern, GE, Citi Enter Texas Panhandle Wind Market","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/pattern-ge-citi-enter-texas-panhandle-wind-market","tags":["Press Release Migration","Institutional Clients Group"]},{"summary":"Before my internship with Citi, if someone told me that working at a bank would be interesting, I would have disagreed. Growing up, I've been very aware of the positive impact doctors make on people's lives and decided that's the kind of profound impact I want to have on others. As I changed over the years and learned more about the profession, this goal became more appealing. However, I never really took the time to learn about other professions. My experience with the digital communications and social media team at Citi was the first time I stepped out of my comfort zone and it ended up making me rethink my career path. I was a little skeptical going in, but once I started, I was more than surprised. There's more to the banking world than I realized. I absolutely loved everything about interning at Citi; the tasks I had at hand and the people I worked with were all so kind and supportive. I now realize that there are other things that I would enjoy doing for the rest of my life, that do not necessarily relate to medicine.","month":"08","author.displayName":["Ashley Budhai"],"year":"2013","publishDate":"August 20, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Interning at Citi: A Pencil Fellows' Story","category":"PERSPECTIVES","author.jobTitle":["Pencil Fellow and Citi Digital Communications Intern"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2013/interning-at-citi-a-pencil-fellows-story","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"Panama City - After marking its 200th anniversary at the global level, Citi is now celebrating 109 years in Panama. Present in the country since 1904, Citi opened its first affiliate outside of the United States there as the International Banking Corporation. Today, Citi leads the cash management, FX, derivatives, electronic banking and public sector solutions markets.","month":"08","year":"2013","publishDate":"August 17, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Celebrates 109 Years in Panama","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/citi-celebrates-109-years-in-panama","tags":["Press Release Migration"]},{"summary":"Miami, Florida - As part of its innovative digital strategy, Citi Latin America recently launched <i>Beneficios de Citi</i>, a digital tool that gives Citi clients fast and easy access to information about discounts, promotions and branch and ATM locations via clients' mobile devices. The app is available in Argentina, Peru, Panama, El Salvador, Guatemala, Costa Rica and Venezuela, and is coming soon to Brazil, Colombia, Nicaragua and Honduras.","month":"08","year":"2013","publishDate":"August 15, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Expands Connectivity and Digital Innovation with Its \"Beneficios de Citi\" Mobile Application in Latin America","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/citi-expands-connectivity-and-digital-innovation-with-its-beneficios-de-citi-mobile-application-in-latin-america","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"New York - Citigroup Inc. (\"<b>Citigroup</b>\") today announced the commencement of offers to purchase for cash certain of its notes of the series set forth in the table below (each offer with respect to any series set forth in the table below, an \"Offer\" and, collectively, the \"<b>Offers</b>\"). We refer to our offer to purchase each series of Notes as an \"Offer\" and collectively as the \"<b>Offers</b>.\" The Notes have an aggregate principal amount outstanding of approximately $11.5 billion as of August 13, 2013.","month":"08","year":"2013","publishDate":"August 14, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citigroup Inc. Announces Offers to Purchase Seven Series of Outstanding Notes","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/citigroup-inc-announces-offers-to-purchase-seven-series-of-outstanding-notes-2","tags":["Press Release Migration","Citi-Wide"]},{"summary":"Kuala Lumpur - Citibank Berhad plans to strengthen its position in the business-to-business (B2B) card payments market by capturing 20 percent of the market with the launch of its two new commercial cards - the Citibank Business Signature Card and Citibank Travel Account.","month":"08","year":"2013","publishDate":"August 13, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Malaysia: Citibank to Capture 20 Percent of Market Share in B2B Spending","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/malaysia-citibank-to-capture-20-percent-of-market-share-in-b2b-spending","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"Cities across the world are rapidly shifting their development strategies to adapt to the new global and local economic and demographic realities. As the Founder and Editor in Chief of <a href=\"https://thisbigcity.net/\">This Big City</a>--an online publication sharing ideas and encouraging discussion about sustainable cities--I've seen, through research and interviews, that in addition to the economic and population challenges, inequality, system management and migration are three challenges cities across the world increasingly face.","image":"638e328da3c47c530c0a6714","year":"2013","publishDate":"August 13, 2013","type":"insights","title":"Urban Ingenuity Series: This Big City","author.jobTitle":["Founder and Editor in Chief of This Big City"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2013/urban-ingenuity-series-this-big-city","tags":["Perspective Migration"],"month":"08","author.displayName":["Joe Peach"],"siteId":"citigpa","category":"PERSPECTIVES"},{"summary":"Irrigation has tremendous potential to increase productivity, raise income levels for smallholder farmers in Africa, and provide a sustainable solution to the rural poor's most important need - a way to consistently earn money. Reliable crop watering methods and innovative tools can mean the difference between break-even sustenance farming and an income-producing livelihood.","image":"638e328ea3c47c530c0a671d","year":"2013","publishDate":"August 09, 2013","type":"insights","title":"Increasing Crop Yields and Incomes for Smallholder Farmers in Africa","author.jobTitle":["Co-Founder and CEO, KickStart International"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2013/increasing-crop-yields-and-incomes-for-smallholder-farmers-in-africa","tags":["Perspective Migration"],"month":"08","author.displayName":["Martin Fisher"],"siteId":"citigpa","category":"PERSPECTIVES"},{"summary":"Shanghai - Citibank (China) Co., Ltd. (\"Citi China\") announced today that it will be the first international bank to launch a paperless processing solution for renminbi (RMB) cross-border settlement. ","month":"08","year":"2013","publishDate":"August 08, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi China Launches New Automated Solution for RMB Cross-Border Settlement","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/citi-china-launches-new-automated-solution-for-rmb-cross-border-settlement","tags":["Press Release Migration","Institutional Clients Group"]},{"summary":"Port-Au-Prince, Haiti - Citi Haiti announces the grand opening of their new offices in Port-Au-Prince. Nearly 40 employees displaced from their workspace in 2010 after the devastating earthquake will now service clients from the new offices located at the Corner of Boulevard Toussaint Louverture and Rue Frères Simmonds.","month":"08","year":"2013","publishDate":"August 08, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Opens New Building in Haiti Three Years After Earthquake","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/citi-opens-new-building-in-haiti-three-years-after-earthquake","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"New York - <a href=\"http://www.citi.com/\" target=\"_top\">Citi</a> and <a href=\"http://www.seventeen.com/\" target=\"_new\">Seventeen Magazine</a> today released findings from the <i style=\"font-style: italic;\">2013 College Student Pulse</i>, a national survey of over 1,000 high school seniors and college students exploring the way students save, spend, and manage the finances of college life. The survey found that students are taking an active role in funding and managing the costs of college, with nearly four in five students working their way through school, and the majority using their own money for a number of college expenses.","month":"08","year":"2013","publishDate":"August 07, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"U.S.: New Citi/Seventeen Survey - College Students Take Control of Their Financial Futures","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/us-new-citiseventeen-survey-college-students-take-control-of-their-financial-futures","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"Many know that Citi has an extraordinary 200-year history that helped chart the course of modern financial services - but equally impactful is the nearly half-century commitment that Citi has demonstrated to expanding financial inclusion for some of the most vulnerable in our society - those living in poverty. <br><br>Today, the Citi Foundation is the lead partner and founding sponsor of the <a href=\"https://www.centerforfinancialinclusion.org/fi2020\">Financial Inclusion 2020 initiative</a>, an effort spearheaded by the <a href=\"https://www.centerforfinancialinclusion.org/\">Center for Financial Inclusion</a> (CFI) at <a href=\"https://www.accion.org/\">Accion</a>. Using the year 2020 as a focal point for action, FI2020 aims to mobilize stakeholders around the world to work collaboratively towards full financial inclusion, which CFI defines as \"a state in which everyone who can use them has access to a full suite of quality financial services, provided at affordable prices, in a convenient manner, with respect and dignity.\" <br><br>Since January, working groups have been mapping the so-called \"<a href=\"https://www.centerforfinancialinclusion.org/fi2020/mapping-the-invisible-market\">invisible market</a>\" to better understand the broad demographic changes occurring at the base of the global economic pyramid. Others are developing the \"<a href=\"https://www.centerforfinancialinclusion.org/fi2020/roadmap-to-inclusion\">Roadmap to Inclusion</a>,\" an action-oriented blueprint for reaching new and underserved markets and for achieving a financially inclusive world. Together, we'll address issues of financial literacy, data analytics, technology-enabled business models, and more. <br><br>Citi's commitment to the years-long push behind this ambitious goal is the latest example of its work with key partners, including Accion, to expand financial inclusion. We have been working with Citi for nearly 50 years, starting in 1965 when Accion was a small non-profit focused on community development in Latin America. Together, over several decades, we've helped build microfinance institutions around the world, created financial education programs, and fueled research and thought-leadership activities. Over time, our ambition and scale have grown, but our partnership endures. <br><br>Whether in the developed world or in the developing world, Citi and Accion share the view that access to basic financial services can unlock enormous opportunity. We all need a safe place to save, access to credit to manage large purchases, go to school or build a business, insurance and efficient payment mechanisms. <br><br>Accion has worked with Citi Microfinance in a number of countries supporting Accion member institutions to reduce foreign exchange risk, to access local currency funding, in investing jointly in the Microfinance Growth Fund and in establishing Accion Microfinance Bank, the leading microfinance institution in Nigeria. In very challenging environments from Latin America to Africa and elsewhere, Accion and Citi have helped advance a global microfinance industry that is making progress in meeting enormous needs. <br><br>Citi continues to support research, innovations, institutions, intermediaries and networks that expand financial inclusion by combining access with education, while achieving scale and sustainability. As a result of a strategic, high-impact engagement over decades, Citi helps drive a global conversation on financial inclusion from every angle. <br><br>Over the last few decades, microfinance has grown to reach more than 200 million people around the world. This is very impressive - yet there is much more to do. Today, 2.5 billion people live in poverty and lack access to financial services. We can change that. We can build a financial system that includes those who are left out. We are very proud to be a very long-term partner with Citi. Together, we will help build a truly financially inclusive world","image":"638e3290a3c47c530c0a6726","year":"2013","publishDate":"August 06, 2013","type":"insights","title":"Accion and Citi: Partnership in Building a Financially Inclusive World","author.jobTitle":["President & CEO, Accion"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2013/accion-and-citi-partnership-in-building-a-financially-inclusive-world","tags":["Perspective Migration"],"month":"08","author.displayName":["Michael Schlein"],"siteId":"citigpa","category":"PERSPECTIVES"},{"summary":"New York - Americans' views of current and future economic conditions rose to their highest levels in five years, according to the latest Citi Economic Pulse, which reached positive territory for the first time since its inception in 2009. Citi today issued the results of the nationwide survey, which was conducted by Hart Research Associates. The +1 score marks a five-point gain from August 2012 and an 18-point gain from its lowest point in August 2011. Among the key shifts that have pushed the Pulse to positive territory are:","month":"08","year":"2013","publishDate":"August 05, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"U.S.: Consumer Sentiment Reaches Highest Point in Five Years as Citi Economic Pulse Enters Positive Territory for First Time","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/us-consumer-sentiment-reaches-highest-point-in-five-years-as-citi-economic-pulse-enters-positive-territory-for-first-time","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"Over a year ago, I began my quest to find answers to my two most pressing entrepreneurial questions: What does it really take for an entrepreneur to be successful? And what does it take for a business owner to be the best of the best?","image":"638e3291a3c47c530c0a672f","year":"2013","publishDate":"August 05, 2013","type":"insights","title":"3 Cardinal Rules for Entrepreneurs","author.jobTitle":["Managing Director and Head, Content & Social, Global Consumer Bank"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2013/3-cardinal-rules-for-entrepreneurs","tags":["Perspective Migration"],"month":"08","author.displayName":["Linda Descano"],"siteId":"citigpa","category":"PERSPECTIVES"},{"summary":"Access to safe, stable and affordable housing is a key component of livable communities. And while that work is ongoing, yesterday in Sioux Falls, South Dakota, Citi CEO Mike Corbat joined local employees and partners to celebrate CitiHousing's 20-year record of innovative community problem-solving for low- and moderate-income families, our seniors, the homeless and people with disabilities.","image":"638e3293a3c47c530c0a6738","year":"2013","publishDate":"August 02, 2013","type":"insights","title":"In Sioux Falls, Citi Marks 20 Years as a Leader in Affordable Housing","author.jobTitle":["Executive Director, CitiHousing, Inc."],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2013/in-sioux-falls-citi-marks-20-years-as-a-leader-in-affordable-housing","tags":["Perspective Migration"],"month":"08","author.displayName":["Mary Entinger"],"siteId":"citigpa","category":"PERSPECTIVES"},{"summary":"New York - Citi's ThankYou Preferred card now rewards cardmembers for doing what they love by offering two points per dollar spent on dining out and entertainment at no annual fee. New and existing ThankYou Preferred cardmembers earn two ThankYou® Points per dollar on dining at restaurants and entertainment purchases from takeout to fine dining, music downloads to movie rentals, as well as tickets to sports and entertainment events. ThankYou Preferred cardmembers will continue to earn one point per dollar on other purchases. ","month":"08","year":"2013","publishDate":"August 01, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"U.S.: Citi ThankYou® Preferred Card Now Offers Double Points on Dining Out and Entertainment at No Annual Fee","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/us-citi-thankyou-preferred-card-now-offers-double-points-on-dining-out-and-entertainment-at-no-annual-fee","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"Citi Maghreb announced today that the U.S. Overseas Private Investment Corporation (OPIC) has provided its consent for a new $40 million, eight-year term loan facility with Attijariwafa Bank to support loans to small and medium-sized enterprises (SMEs) in Morocco under a risk sharing agreement between OPIC and Citi.","month":"08","year":"2013","publishDate":"August 01, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"U.S. Government Partners with Citi to Commit $40M to Morocco's Attijariwafa Bank","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/us-government-partners-with-citi-to-commit-40m-to-morocco-s-attijariwafa-bank","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"Tel Aviv - Citi announced today the establishment of the first Accelerator program in the Financial Technology industry in Israel. The Citi Accelerator program is designed to help young startups grow and achieve key milestones. The program will operate as part of the Citi Innovation Lab TLV, within Citi's global network of innovation centres and will be located in their new premises in Atidim.","month":"07","year":"2013","publishDate":"July 31, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Launches the First Financial Technology Accelerator Program in Israel","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/citi-launches-the-first-financial-technology-accelerator-program-in-israel","tags":["Press Release Migration"]},{"summary":"Miami, Florida - The Citi Foundation in partnership with the Caribbean Microfinance Alliance (CMFA) is now accepting submissions from outstanding micro-entrepreneurs and institutions for the 2013 Citi Microentrepreneurship Awards for the Caribbean, the objective of which is to raise awareness about microfinance in the Caribbean, build consciousness on the role micro-entrepreneurs play in their local economies and develop the next generation of microfinance institutions. Candidates have until Wednesday, August 7, 2013 to submit their nominations.","month":"07","year":"2013","publishDate":"July 31, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Announces the Opening of the Second Annual Citi Microentrepreneurship Awards for the Caribbean","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/citi-announces-the-opening-of-the-second-annual-citi-microentrepreneurship-awards-for-the-caribbean","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"With growing urban centers globally comes a considerable amount of data related to citizen's behaviors, municipalities' operations or environmental evolutions. Through advanced technologies, ingenuity and increasing analytical capabilities, what is now commonly called Big Data is about to revolutionize cities' development and citizen's interactions with public services and authorities.","image":"638e3295a3c47c530c0a6741","year":"2013","publishDate":"July 31, 2013","type":"insights","title":"Urban Ingenuity Series: Big Data","author.jobTitle":["Founder and Chairman of the New Cities Foundation"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2013/urban-ingenuity-series-big-data","tags":["Perspective Migration"],"month":"07","author.displayName":["John Rossant"],"siteId":"citigpa","category":"PERSPECTIVES"},{"summary":"Prague - Citibank Czech Republic has joined its affiliates in more than 100 countries around the world to launch a Citi Alumni online network for former employees in the Czech Republic. The purpose of the Citi Alumni network is to give Citibank's former employees an opportunity to keep in touch with the bank and also their former colleagues. The <a href=\"http://www.citialumninetwork.com/\" target=\"blank\">www.citialumninetwork.com</a> global website has a common global basis but each country has its own section that has been localized in their respective languages. Former employees ('alumni') can register and follow developments at the bank as they happen, and also enjoy some of the benefits to which Citibank's current employees have access.","month":"07","year":"2013","publishDate":"July 30, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Czech Republic Launches Alumni Network","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/citi-cech-republic-launches-alumni-network","tags":["Press Release Migration"]},{"summary":"<a href=\"https://www.citigroup.com/rcs/citigpa/storage/public/CitiOpen_ThinkStock.jpg\"></a>The Citi Open tennis tournament kicked off this past weekend, and Washington is enjoying some exciting tennis action! Citi is proud to once again sponsor this renowned tournament, which has become a summer sports staple in the DC-area for the past 45 years. And the 2013 Citi Open tournament promises to be the best yet.","image":"638e3296a3c47c530c0a674a","year":"2013","publishDate":"July 30, 2013","type":"insights","title":"Washington Abuzz with Citi Open Tennis Tournament","author.jobTitle":["Executive Vice President, Global Government Affairs, Citi"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2013/washington-abuzz-with-citi-open-tennis-tournament","tags":["Perspective Migration"],"month":"07","author.displayName":["Candi Wolff"],"siteId":"citigpa","category":"PERSPECTIVES"},{"summary":"New York - Citi Microfinance and Citi Commercial Bank today announced US$2,000,000 in financing to support KickStart International, a non-profit social enterprise that designs, manufactures and sells high-quality, low-cost irrigation pumps for use by smallholder farmers across Sub-Saharan Africa. With support from the Skoll Foundation, the loan will be the first from Citi directed to the social enterprise sector and will specifically support smallholder farmers in Sub-Saharan Africa, where farm yields are among the lowest in the world.","month":"07","year":"2013","publishDate":"July 29, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"With Skoll Foundation Support, Citi Provides Financing for Innovative Social Enterprise KickStart International","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/with-skoll-foundation-support-citi-provides-financing-for-innovative-social-enterprise-kickstart-international","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"Manama, Bahrain - Citibank Bahrain has won the \"Best Consumer Internet Bank\" and the \"Best Corporate/Institutional Internet Bank\" awards in the first round of <i>Global Finance</i> magazine's awards for the 2013 Best Internet Banks in the Middle East and Africa.","month":"07","year":"2013","publishDate":"July 28, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citibank Bahrain Named Winner in Global Finance Magazine's Awards for \"Best Internet Bank\" and \"Best Corporate/Institutional Internet Bank\"","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/citibank-bahrain-named-winner-in-global-finance-magaine-s-awards-for-best-internet-bank-and-best-corporateinstitutional-internet-bank","tags":["Press Release Migration","Institutional Clients Group","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"Manila - Citi Philippines recently launched the Citi Debit Card, designed to provide its banking clients enhanced security features and convenience of shopping at millions of merchants worldwide.","month":"07","year":"2013","publishDate":"July 26, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Philippines Launches Debit Card for Banking Clients","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/citi-philippines-launches-debit-card-for-banking-clients","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"Not many people are aware that nearly three billion people lack access to clean cooking facilities, with 95% of those residing in Sub-Saharan Africa or Asia. In fact, approximately four million people die each year from smoke exposure caused by cooking with dirty fuels.* The good news is that distribution of cleaner and more energy efficient products to low-income communities in emerging markets is already benefitting underserved families and reducing pressure on the environment. While new technologies continue to be developed, innovation in expanding awareness, distribution and financing of such products is also playing a critical role.","image":"638e3299a3c47c530c0a6756","year":"2013","publishDate":"July 26, 2013","type":"insights","title":"With Citi Support, Impact Carbon Connects Clean Cooking to Improved Health & Livelihoods","author.jobTitle":["Executive Director, Impact Carbon"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2013/with-citi-support-impact-carbon-connects-clean-cooking-to-improved-health-livelihoods","tags":["Perspective Migration"],"month":"07","author.displayName":["Evan Haigler"],"siteId":"citigpa","category":"PERSPECTIVES"},{"summary":"Prague - Citibank Europe plc in the Czech Republic was named the \"Best Consumer Internet Bank\" and the \"Best Corporate/Institutional Internet Bank in <i>Global Finance</i> magazine's \"2013 World's Best Internet Banks\" awards. Citi also won several prestigious awards in different categories in countries all over the world, including the Central and Eastern Europe region (CEE).","month":"07","year":"2013","publishDate":"July 25, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citibank Named Best Consumer Internet Bank and Best Corporate/Institutional Internet Bank in the Czech Republic","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/citibank-named-best-consumer-internet-bank-and-best-corpo