ishDate":"July 23, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Financial Times and Citi Announce Judging Panel for the 2013 FT/Citi Ingenuity Awards","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/financial-times-and-citi-announce-judging-panel-for-the-2013-ftciti-ingenuity-awards","tags":["Press Release Migration","Citi-Wide"]},{"summary":"Port of Spain, Trinidad - Citi Trinidad & Tobago hosted a Citi Alumni event at which the bank recognized alumnus Joy Caesar for her commitment and contributions to the community. The Citi Alumni Awards distinguish the accomplishments of the organization's former employees who still make Citi very proud, in the areas of Leadership & Ingenuity, Network Development and Community Involvement. Joy Caesar was awarded the 2013 Citi Distinguished Alumni Award for Community Involvement.","month":"07","year":"2013","publishDate":"July 22, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Trinidad & Tobago Honors Bank Alumni","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/citi-trinidad-tobago-honors-bank-alumni","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"<em></em>","image":"638e329aa3c47c530c0a675f","year":"2013","publishDate":"July 22, 2013","type":"insights","title":"Vélib' - A Success Story on Bike-Sharing in Paris","author.jobTitle":["Vice President of Strategy, Research and Marketing at JCDecaux"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2013/velib---a-success-story-on-bike-sharing-in-paris","tags":["Perspective Migration"],"month":"07","author.displayName":["Albert Asseraf"],"siteId":"citigpa","category":"PERSPECTIVES"},{"summary":"The Citi-PPAF Microentrepreneurship Awards (CMA) were held at Serena Hotel in Islamabad. Ahsan Iqbal, Federal Minister for Planning & Development, and Citi Country Officer Nadeem Lodhi led the ceremony at which 20 microentrepreneurs were awarded.","