se Migration","Institutional Clients Group"]},{"summary":"Moscow - The awards ceremony for winners of the 2012 Brand of the Year / EFFIE awards was held on May 24, 2013, at the Central Exhibition Hall Moscow Manege. Citi was awarded the bronze prize for its international 200 Years Citi campaign, which was implemented as part of Citi's 200th anniversary celebrations. ","month":"05","year":"2013","publishDate":"May 28, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Named Financial Brand of the Year in Russia","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/citi-named-financial-brand-of-the-year-in-russia","tags":["Press Release Migration"]},{"summary":"Abu Dhabi - Citibank today inaugurated its main Abu Dhabi branch, located at Al-Falah Street. The inauguration ceremony was hosted by Mr. James Cowles, Citi's Chief Executive Officer for Europe, Middle East & Africa (EMEA), who is currently visiting the region, as well as Mr. Atiq Ur-Rehman, CEO for the Middle East.","month":"05","year":"2013","publishDate":"May 28, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"U.A.E: Citi Opens its Main Abu Dhabi Branch at Al-Falah Street","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/uae-citi-opens-its-main-abu-dhabi-branch-at-al-falah-street","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"Am I taking too much risk? To answer this question, we'll often look at our portfolio, focusing on the mix of stocks and conservative investments.","image":"638e32c0a3c47c530c0a6834","year":"2013","publishDate":"May 28, 2013","type":"insights","title":"How to Put Your Portfolio's Risk Level in Perspective","author.jobTitle":["Director of Financial Education, Citi Personal Wealth Management"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2013/how-to-put-your-portfolios-risk-level-in-perspective","tags":["Perspective Migration"],"month":"05","author.displayName":["Jonathan Clements"],"siteId":"citigpa","category":"PERSPECTIVES"},{"summary":"Lanzhou, China - Citibank (China) Co. Ltd. (\"Citi China\") today announced its support for the Gansu Living & Learning Microfinance Program (\"The Program\").","month":"05","year":"2013","publishDate":"May 27, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"China: Citi Supports Microfinance Program in Gansu","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/china-citi-supports-microfinance-program-in-gansu","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"Shanghai - Citibank (China) Co., Ltd. (\"Citi China\") today announces the launch of Citi® Mobile Collect, an advanced and innovative solution under its receivables solution suite. Together with <i>E-Custom</i> and <i>E-Tax</i> launched recently, Citi China is sparing no efforts to develop its digitalized solutions.","month":"05","year":"2013","publishDate":"May 27, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi China Launches Citi Mobile Collect Offering","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/citi-china-launches-citi-mobile-collect-offering","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"By Charles Blauner","image":"638e32c4a3c47c530c0a6844","month":"05","year":"2013","publishDate":"May 24, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Cyber Threats and Security Solutions","category":"PERSPECTIVES","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2013/cyber-threats-and-security-solutions","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"Today the <i>New York Times</i> <a href=\"https://dealbook.nytimes.com/2013/05/23/banks-lobbyists-help-in-drafting-financial-bills/\">reported</a> on Citi's effort to fix a misguided provision of the Dodd-Frank financial reform law. Here's some additional context to the story. <br><br>Citi has been a strong supporter of financial reform--not just Dodd-Frank Act but also Basel III's higher capital requirements and a range of other issues. Yet, as with any effort to address complex issues, some ideas clearly miss the mark. <br><br>Case in point: Section 716 of Dodd-Frank, or the \"swaps push-out\" provision, requires financial institutions to push most derivatives transactions out of the bank into a separate entity. This provision does absolutely nothing to create a safer financial system. In fact, Section 716 would negatively impact U.S. companies, financial firms, and their counterparties, while actually increasing systemic risk. This provision would create undue costs and burdens on U.S. financial firms. Swaps and other instruments covered by this rule are legitimate financial tools that are useful to a variety of companies in a range of circumstances. 716 won't make them go away. Rather, those companies that need to use these services will simply do business elsewhere, hurting U.S. competitiveness, and often pushing that business into less regulated corners of the financial system. <br><br>Everyone from Federal Reserve Chairman Ben Bernanke to former House Financial Services Chairman Barney Frank, the bill's namesake, has expressed concerns over the potential consequences of Section 716. Rarely do we see such bipartisan consensus across Congress, financial regulators, and the financial industry--and not just here in the U.S., but also amongst foreign banks that have significant U.S. operations. <br><br>Citi has taken on a lead role in working with our peers and Members of Congress to find a common sense solution. The result of this collaboration is legislation outlining a more straightforward and simplified approach to derivatives transactions--one that would not force swaps into lesser regulated entities. <br><br>Moreover, this new bill has received widespread bipartisan backing. Earlier this month in the House Financial Services Committee, the legislation garnered an overwhelming, bipartisan vote of support, 53 to 6. Efforts to modify Section 716 are a great example of how the industry and Congress can work together to find common ground toward our shared goal of strengthening the financial system.","image":"638e32c2a3c47c530c0a683b","year":"2013","publishDate":"May 24, 2013","type":"insights","title":"Strengthening Financial Reform","author.jobTitle":["Executive Vice President | Enterprise Services and Public Affairs"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2013/strengthening-financial-reform","tags":["Perspective Migration"],"month":"05","author.displayName":["Ed Skyler"],"siteId":"citigpa","category":"PERSPECTIVES"},{"summary":"New York - Michael Corbat, Chief Executive Officer of Citigroup, will present at the Sanford C. Bernstein 29th Annual Strategic Decisions Conference on Wednesday, May 29, 2013. The presentation is expected to begin at approximately 2 p.m. (Eastern). A live webcast will be available at <a href=\"https://www.citigroup.com/global/investors\">www.citigroup.com/global/investors</a>. A replay and transcript of the webcast will be available shortly after the event.","month":"05","year":"2013","publishDate":"May 22, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citigroup CEO Michael Corbat to Present at the Sanford C. Bernstein 29th Annual Strategic Decisions Conference","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/citigroup-ceo-michael-corbat-to-present-at-the-sanford-c-bernstein-29th-annual-strategic-decisions-conference","tags":["Press Release Migration","Citi-Wide"]},{"summary":"Approximately 3.5 billion people today live in cities. Road traffic has become a must-consider factor for many of us on a daily basis. According to the <a href=\"https://mobility.tamu.edu/ums/\">2012 Urban Mobility Report</a>, American commuters spend almost the equivalent of a work week behind the wheel in one year. The world's population is growing and more and more people are seeking opportunities in urban areas. Citi is committed to helping transform and modernize infrastructure and enhance the cities' livability. One example is the assistance to the Republic of Panama in facilitating funds for the first metro line in Panama City, where there have been long-standing issues of congestion, road insecurity and inadequate infrastructure. <br><br>Set to open in March 2014, below are three ways the Panama Metro system will improve the lives of Panama City residents: <br><br>","image":"638e32c5a3c47c530c0a684d","year":"2013","publishDate":"May 22, 2013","type":"insights","title":"Living in a Better World: 3 Ways Mass-Transit Systems Make Cities More Sustainable","author.jobTitle":["Secretary of the Panama Metro Secretariat"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2013/living-in-a-better-world-3-ways-mass-transit-systems-make-cities-more-sustainable","tags":["Perspective Migration"],"month":"05","author.displayName":["Roberto Roy"],"siteId":"citigpa","category":"PERSPECTIVES"},{"summary":"Miami, Florida - Citi, through its Treasury and Trade Solutions division, announces a significant investment in its Commercial Card-issuing business through the launch of its Global Issuing platform in the Latin America region. Puerto Rico will be the first to adopt this new technology, positioning Citi as the first local Commercial Card Issuer to deliver a chip-card solution into that market.","month":"05","year":"2013","publishDate":"May 21, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi to Enhance Its Investment in Its Commercial Cards Offering in Latin America","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/citi-to-enhance-its-investment-in-its-commercial-cards-offering-in-latin-america","tags":["Press Release Migration","Institutional Clients Group"]},{"summary":"Manama, Bahrain - <i>EMEA Finance Magazine</i> has named Citi \"Best Foreign Investment Bank in Bahrain\" jointly with JP Morgan and Standard Chartered Bank as part of the magazine's Middle East Banking Awards 2012. The awards were recently announced at a charity awards dinner held at Jumeirah Emirates Towers in Dubai.","month":"05","year":"2013","publishDate":"May 21, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"EMEA Finance Names Citi \"Best Foreign Investment Bank\" In Bahrain for the Second Year in a Row","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/emea-finance-names-citi-best-foreign-investment-bank-in-bahrain-for-the-second-year-in-a-row","tags":["Press Release Migration","Institutional Clients Group"]},{"summary":"Rates on 30-year fixed-rate mortgages are at historic lows--but your initial interest rate would likely be even lower if you opted for some sort of adjustable-rate loan. Does that mean you should go for an ARM, as adjustable-rate mortgages are often called? <br><br>Like many things in life, it depends. <br><br>","image":"638e32c7a3c47c530c0a6856","year":"2013","publishDate":"May 21, 2013","type":"insights","title":"Homebuyer's Choice: Fixed Rate or Adjustable Mortgage?","author.jobTitle":["Director of Financial Education, Citi Personal Wealth Management"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2013/homebuyers-choice-fixed-rate-or-adjustable-mortgage","tags":["Perspective Migration"],"month":"05","author.displayName":["Jonathan Clements"],"siteId":"citigpa","category":"PERSPECTIVES"},{"summary":"Prague - Citibank is the first bank in the Czech market to offer its clients trading via an on-line platform. When clients invest in premium forex products, the on-line platform displays the current yields for different currency pairs and the relevant rates at any given moment. Clients can therefore very easily select the optimum investment strategy. ","month":"05","year":"2013","publishDate":"May 20, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Czech Republic: First Online Platform for Investment in Forex Products","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/citi-cech-republic-first-online-platform-for-investment-in-forex-products","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"London - Citi announces Hotel Privileges, a program designed to give Citi card members access to tangible benefits at top hotels including best available rates and services such as complimentary breakfast for two, free internet and late check-out - simply for being a Citi customer.","month":"05","year":"2013","publishDate":"May 20, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Europe, Middle East & Africa: Citi Invites Its Cardholders to Upgrade with Hotel Privileges","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/europe-middle-east-africa-citi-invites-its-cardholders-to-upgrade-with-hotel-privileges","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"Miami - Citi has been recognized as the number one FX bank in 11 countries across Latin America in the prestigious <i>Euromoney</i> FX Survey 2013. The firm has the largest FX market share in Argentina, Colombia, Costa Rica, Ecuador, Guatemala, Haiti, Honduras, Mexico, Trinidad & Tobago, Uruguay and Venezuela . In addition, Citi ranked second in Latin America overall, with a 20.7 percent market share, and was named the number one Bank for Corporates (non-financial organizations) in Latin America, the Caribbean and in Central America. Citi was also recognized as the top firm for trading Latin American currencies, with a 5.59 score in the Qualitative Ranking for Currencies in the","month":"05","year":"2013","publishDate":"May 20, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Named Best FX Bank in 11 Countries in Latin America in Euromoney's FX Survey 2013","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/citi-named-best-fx-bank-in-11-countries-in-latin-america-in-euromoney-s-fx-survey-2013","tags":["Press Release Migration","Institutional Clients Group"]},{"summary":"Some people are reluctant to fund Individual Retirement Accounts and 401(k) plans, fearing they are setting themselves up for big tax bills in retirement. After all, retirement-account withdrawals are typically taxed as ordinary income, which can mean paying a federal rate as high as 39.6% in 2013. By contrast, in a taxable account, any qualifying dividends and long-term capital gains are taxed at a maximum federal rate of 20%. <br><br>What to do? If you're eligible, you can always fund a Roth IRA or Roth 401(k) instead. Roth accounts don't offer an initial tax deduction, but withdrawals can be federal and state tax-free if you follow the rules. <br><br>But even if the Roth isn't an option, a tax-deductible IRA or 401(k) remains a fine choice. That's because the initial tax deduction often pays for the eventual tax bill. <br><br>To understand why, consider a simple example. Suppose you are in the 25% federal income-tax bracket today--and you're still in the 25% bracket once you retire. If you put $1,000 in a tax-deductible IRA, your out-of-pocket cost would be $750, thanks to the $250 tax savings. <br><br>By the time you retire, let's assume your IRA has grown a hypothetical 100% to $2,000 (though there are, of course, no guarantees). At that juncture, you cash out the account, paying 25% to the government. That leaves you with $1,500, or 100% more than your $750 investment. In effect, the IRA gave you tax-free growth on your initial $750 out-of-pocket cost. <br><br>To be sure, if you are in a higher tax bracket in retirement, you won't enjoy totally tax-free growth. On the other hand, if your tax bracket falls in retirement--which often happens--you will benefit at Uncle Sam's expense.","image":"638e32c8a3c47c530c0a685d","year":"2013","publishDate":"May 17, 2013","type":"insights","title":"Retirement Accounts: Should You Fear the Eventual Tax Bill?","author.jobTitle":["Director of Financial Education, Citi Personal Wealth Management"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2013/retirement-accounts-should-you-fear-the-eventual-tax-bill","tags":["Perspective Migration"],"month":"05","author.displayName":["Jonathan Clements"],"siteId":"citigpa","category":"PERSPECTIVES"},{"summary":"New York - Citigroup Inc. (\"<b>Citigroup</b>\") today announced the commencement of offers to purchase for cash up to US$400,000,000 aggregate principal amount (the \"<b>Overall Tender Cap</b>\") of its notes of the series set forth in the table below (the \"<b>Notes</b>\"). The offer to purchase each series of Notes is referred to as an \"<b>Offer</b>\" and all four such offers are referred to collectively as the \"<b>Offers</b>.\" The \"<b>Any and All Offers</b>\" as set forth in the table below are being made on a fixed price basis in connection with the Offer for Notes denominated in Euros and on a fixed spread basis in connection with the Offer for Notes denominated in Canadian dollars. The \"<b>Waterfall Tender Offers</b>\" as set forth in the table below are being made on a fixed spread basis. The Notes had an aggregate principal amount outstanding of approximately US$2.04 billion as of May 15, 2013 (based on U.S. dollar exchange rates as of that date).","month":"05","year":"2013","publishDate":"May 16, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citigroup Inc. Announces Offers to Purchase Four Series of Outstanding Notes","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/citigroup-inc-announces-offers-to-purchase-four-series-of-outstanding-notes-1","tags":["Press Release Migration","Citi-Wide"]},{"summary":"PRAGUE - According to Citibank's latest survey conducted in cooperation with IPSOS, only every 14th Czech (7.4 percent) is willing to invest more than CZK 50,000 per year in financial products. The single largest part of the adult population (37.3 percent) invests up to CZK 10,000. Approximately one-fourth (25.5 percent) invest CZK 10,000 to 50,000 per year. Almost 30 percent do not invest at all. The survey has also shown that when it comes to growing their money through investment in financial products, Czechs still remain very conservative: more than 56 percent prefer savings products such as savings accounts or schemes of savings and loan associations. Traditional investment products for appreciation of financial assets over the long term, such as stocks, mutual funds, or bonds, are used by 40 percent of investors (13.5 percent stocks, 18.6 percent mutual funds, and 8.3 percent bonds). Short-term investments in forex products remain an underestimated opportunity and are currently used by only 3.2 percent of Czech investors.","month":"05","year":"2013","publishDate":"May 15, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Czechs Overly Cautious with Investing, Missing Out on Attractive Opportunities","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/cechs-overly-cautious-with-investing-missing-out-on-attractive-opportunities","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"Caracas, Venezuela - On Wednesday, May 15, as part of the \"Tu Hogar con Citi\" (Your Home with Citi) program, the President of Citibank N.A. Venezuela, Nelson Acosta, and Mary Gloria Olivo, General Director of FUDEP (Popular Development Promotion Association), granted microloans to women and men seeking to remodel, expand or build their own homes. ","month":"05","year":"2013","publishDate":"May 15, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Venezuela: Citibank and FUDEP Launch \"Tu Hogar Con Citi\"","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/veneuela-citibank-and-fudep-launch-tu-hogar-con-citi","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"London - Citi has won Energy Risk Manager of the Year Award from <i>Energy Risk</i> magazine.","month":"05","year":"2013","publishDate":"May 15, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Wins Energy Risk Manager of the Year Award","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/citi-wins-energy-risk-manager-of-the-year-award","tags":["Press Release Migration","Institutional Clients Group"]},{"image":"638e32c9a3c47c530c0a6864","month":"05","author.displayName":["Jud Linville"],"year":"2013","publishDate":"May 15, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Cards Answers Your Questions","category":"PERSPECTIVES","author.jobTitle":["Citi Cards CEO"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2013/thank-you-for-sharing-your","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"New York - Citi Brazil announced today that it has reached a definitive agreement with Banco Itaú Unibanco to sell Credicard, its non-banking credit card and consumer finance business, subject to approval by Brazilian regulatory authorities.","month":"05","year":"2013","publishDate":"May 14, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Announces Sale of Credicard to Banco Itaú Unibanco","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/citi-announces-sale-of-credicard-to-banco-itauacute-unibanco","tags":["Press Release Migration","Citi-Wide","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"New York - Citigroup Inc. is redeeming, in whole, all $94.3 million aggregate liquidation preference of Depositary Shares representing interests in its 8.5% Series F Noncumulative Preferred Stock (ticker \"C Pr M\") (the \"Series F Preferred Stock\") and its 6.5% Series T Convertible Noncumulative Preferred Stock (ticker \"C Pr I\") (the \"Series T Preferred Stock\" and, together with the Series F Preferred Stock, the \"Redeemed Preferred Stock\").","month":"05","year":"2013","publishDate":"May 14, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citigroup Announces Redemption of Series F Preferred Stock and Series T Convertible Preferred Stock","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/citigroup-announces-redemption-of-series-f-preferred-stock-and-series-t-convertible-preferred-stock","tags":["Press Release Migration","Citi-Wide","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"New York - Ever paid a bill late? You're not alone. More than half of Americans have paid a bill late, and, in a recent survey sponsored by Citi, forgetfulness was the top reason they cited. Designed to provide a simplified credit experience and alleviate the frustration of late fees, Citi Simplicity is the only card to never charge late fees, a penalty rate and an annual fee (<a href=\"http://www.citi.com/simplicity\" target=\"blank\">www.citi.com/simplicity</a>). You can say goodbye to these fees forever as a Citi Simplicity cardmember, as illustrated in the new television commercial, \"Kickboxer\" which debuts this week.","month":"05","year":"2013","publishDate":"May 14, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Simplicity® Says Goodbye to Frustration of Late Fees in New Advertising Campaign","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/citi-simplicity-says-goodbye-to-frustration-of-late-fees-in-new-advertising-campaign","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"Wind, as a source of energy, has numerous advantages and is a responsible way of addressing our current and future energy needs. <br><br><strong>1) Wind energy is renewable and clean.</strong> Wind is generated from a pollution-free and inexhaustible natural resource that protects both air and water quality. Citi recently helped finance EDF Renewable Energy's Pacific Wind project located in Kern County, California, which achieved commercial operation in 2012 and can supply the electricity needs of 54,000 households. In addition, the Pacific Wind Project encompasses approximately 8,500 acres of leased land, but less than 2 percent of the land area will be occupied by wind turbines, allowing the balance to remain largely undisturbed. <br><br><strong>2) Wind energy helps offset other, more polluting sources of energy.</strong> When we use our wind farms to generate electricity, we provide long-term fixed pricing in an environment where pricing is constantly increasing, while also reducing CO2 emissions, the leading greenhouse gas. In fact, the Pacific Wind project helps avoid emissions of 165,866 Metric Tons of CO2 annually. <br><strong><br>3) Wind energy provides economic benefits to local communities.</strong> Jobs in manufacturing, construction, and wind farm operations are created as a result of wind energy project developments Landowners enjoy an additional income stream and local communities reap benefits from resulting tax revenues. As an example, the Pacific Wind project created approximately 250 jobs while under construction. <br><br>Environmental sustainability is a key issue for businesses, their clients, and the communities they operate in. Wind energy projects such as Pacific Wind is one way to help contribute to this effort.","image":"638e32caa3c47c530c0a686b","year":"2013","publishDate":"May 14, 2013","type":"insights","title":"Living in a Better World: 3 Ways Wind Power Makes Our World Better","author.jobTitle":["EDF Renewable Energy"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2013/living-in-a-better-world-3-ways-wind-power-makes-our-world-better","tags":["Perspective Migration"],"month":"05","author.displayName":["EDF Renewable Energy"],"siteId":"citigpa","category":"PERSPECTIVES"},{"summary":"Lusaka - Citibank Zambia Limited today hosted a conference to discuss the newly introduced Statutory Instrument No. 32 of 2013 (SI 32), which was announced on April 29, 2013 and issued on May 2, 2013. The new SI32 comes into effect on May 16, 2013.","month":"05","year":"2013","publishDate":