type":"insights","title":"Citi Supports Growth of Jordan's Microfinance Sector with US$2 Million (JOD Equivalent) Local Currency Term Funding","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/citi-supports-growth-of-jordan-s-microfinance-sector-with-us2-million-jod-equivalent-local-currency-term-funding","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"New York - John Gerspach, Chief Financial Officer of Citigroup, will present at the 2013 Credit Suisse Financial Services Forum on Tuesday, February 12, 2013. The presentation is expected to begin at approximately 3:15 p.m. (Eastern). A live webcast and presentation materials will be available at <a href=\"https://www.citigroup.com/global/investors\">www.citigroup.com/global/investors</a>. A replay and transcript of the webcast will be available shortly after the event.","month":"02","year":"2013","publishDate":"February 05, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citigroup CFO John Gerspach to Present at the 2013 Credit Suisse Financial Services Forum","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/citigroup-cfo-john-gerspach-to-present-at-the-2013-credit-suisse-financial-services-forum","tags":["Press Release Migration","Citi-Wide"]},{"summary":"My earliest good fortune was to have been raised by parents who instilled in me the importance of family, community and the simple pleasure of having \"sand in my shoes\" - a sentiment treasured by all those who live in the Rockaway communities. Every year my parents, my brother and I spent our summers on the white sandy beaches of the Rockaways, a narrow sand bar of an island between the bay and the ocean within eyesight of Manhattan. For generations we had joined its residents to enjoy all the peninsula had to offer and my husband and I continued to pass these traditions and love for the Rockaways on to our children. From the Parks Department concessions on the board walk to the Public Libraries in Far Rockaway and Rockaway Park, shopping in Bell Harbor to dining at the restaurants in Breezy Point; the Rockaways were not just a summer oasis but a significant member of our family.","image":"638e3313a3c47c530c0a6a01","year":"2013","publishDate":"February 05, 2013","type":"insights","title":"Reflections on Hurricane Sandy from one of the Rockaways' Own","author.jobTitle":["New York Tri-State Director, Citi Community Development"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2013/reflections-on-hurricane-sandy-from-one-of-the-rockaways-own","tags":["Perspective Migration"],"month":"02","author.displayName":["Eileen Auld"],"siteId":"citigpa","category":"PERSPECTIVES"},{"summary":"Prague - Citipůjcčka took third place in the 'Loans' category at the 2012 Financial Product competition, organized by analytical company Scott & Rose. ","month":"02","year":"2013","publishDate":"February 04, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Czech Republic: Citipujccka Voted Third-Best Loan Product on the Czech Market","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/cech-republic-citipujccka-voted-third-best-loan-product-on-the-cech-market","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"Dallas, Texas - The WorkPlace and Workforce Solutions Greater Dallas, with the support of AARP Foundation, Citi Community Development and the Walmart Foundation, announce the national expansion of the highly successful Platform to Employment (P2E) program beginning in Dallas, Texas. This is the first of 10 sites across the country that will replicate P2E in 2013. The program creates a pathway to employment for the long-term unemployed. With 4.8 million Americans unemployed for 27 weeks or longer in December, long-term unemployment remains a significant concern to reviving the American economy and strengthening our communities.","month":"02","year":"2013","publishDate":"February 04, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Dallas Launches Successful Program Putting the Long-Term Unemployed Back to Work","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/dallas-launches-successful-program-putting-the-long-term-unemployed-back-to-work","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"São Paulo - Citi is launching a new product to help Brazilians plan for their financial future while addressing the country's social issues, especially the large numbers of children and young people who lack access to a quality public education. The CDB Instituto Ayrton Senna is a certificate of deposit that offers excellent yields (99 percent of the interbank rate) and a differential interest rate. Citi will dedicate a portion of the earnings to the Ayrton Senna Institute, which benefits 2 million public school students around the country each year. ","month":"02","year":"2013","publishDate":"February 04, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Launches New Product for Investors Planning for the Future and Concerned About Improving Access to Education in Brazil","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/citi-launches-new-product-for-investors-planning-for-the-future-and-concerned-about-improving-access-to-education-in-brail","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"Manila - More and more Filipinos now understand the value of budgeting and planning for their retirement and claim building their savings has become a personal priority, says Citi Philippines as it announced the latest results of its annual Citi Fin-Q survey. ","month":"02","year":"2013","publishDate":"February 04, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Fin-Q Survey Reports Filipinos More Money-Wise","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/citi-fin-q-survey-reports-filipinos-more-money-wise","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"You might have a bank account, brokerage account, a few Individual Retirement Accounts and maybe money in both your current employer's 401(k) plan and also an old employer's plan. But do all of these accounts, taken together, give you a sensible investment mix?","image":"638e3315a3c47c530c0a6a0a","year":"2013","publishDate":"February 04, 2013","type":"insights","title":"Why You Should Keep an Eye on the Big Picture","author.jobTitle":["Director of Financial Education, Citi Personal Wealth Management"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2013/why-you-should-keep-an-eye-on-the-big-picture","tags":["Perspective Migration"],"month":"02","author.displayName":["Jonathan Clements"],"siteId":"citigpa","category":"PERSPECTIVES"},{"summary":"Bangkok - Citi was honored with special recognition from the World Customs Organization (WCO) on Friday, January 25. Presented by Mrs. Benja Louichareon, Commissioner of the Royal Thai Customs Department, the award recognized Citi as a leading organization in innovation, progress and development in the field of customs management. ","month":"02","year":"2013","publishDate":"February 01, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Thailand: Citi's Innovative Approach Recognized by the World Customs Organization","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/thailand-citi-s-innovative-approach-recognied-by-the-world-customs-organiation","tags":["Press Release Migration","Institutional Clients Group"]},{"summary":"<a href=\"https://www.citigroup.com/rcs/citigpa/storage/public/heathceramics.jpg\"></a>This past week, I took a short walk with my two young daughters from our house to a 100-year-old industrial building in the heart of our Mission District neighborhood in San Francisco. We went to see the massive kilns being prepared to fire the first San Francisco-made tile in more than 50 years at <a href=\"https://www.heathceramics.com/san-francisco\">Heath Ceramics</a>.","image":"638e3316a3c47c530c0a6a11","year":"2013","publishDate":"January 31, 2013","type":"insights","title":"The Possibility of Urban Manufacturing","author.jobTitle":["Founding Executive Director, SFMade"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2013/the-possibility-of-urban-manufacturing","tags":["Perspective Migration"],"month":"01","author.displayName":["Kate Sofis"],"siteId":"citigpa","category":"PERSPECTIVES"},{"summary":"Tegucigalpa, Honduras - Citi announced today the launch of its new and exclusive Citi LifeMiles Infinite credit card, which offers Citi clients more privileges and improved benefits, inviting them to pursue continued growth in a world of prestige and distinction. ","month":"01","year":"2013","publishDate":"January 30, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Honduras: Citi Presents a New Exclusive Card for Its Clients","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/honduras-citi-presents-a-new-exclusive-card-for-its-clients","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"Citi is the best bank in Asia for 2012 according to leading industry publication <i>FinanceAsia</i>. The decision was made by the editorial team at <i>FinanceAsia</i> magazine and was based on the performance of banks across institutional and retail banking for the last 12 months.","month":"01","year":"2013","publishDate":"January 30, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Awarded Best Bank in Asia by FinanceAsia Magazine","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/citi-awarded-best-bank-in-asia-by-financeasia-magaine-1","tags":["Press Release Migration","Institutional Clients Group","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"Manila - More than 12 million Filipinos may now enjoy the convenience of Citi's electronic payments platform with the introduction of the Pag-Ibig Citi Prepaid Card. The launch followed the signing late last year of an agreement between Citi and its first public sector client for Prepaid Cards, the Home Development Mutual Fund (HDMF), also known as the Pag-Ibig Fund.","month":"01","year":"2013","publishDate":"January 30, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Philippines: Citi Launches First Public Sector Prepaid Card with Home Development Mutual Fund","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/philippines-citi-launches-first-public-sector-prepaid-card-with-home-development-mutual-fund","tags":["Press Release Migration","Institutional Clients Group"]},{"summary":"Who said doing good and doing well are mutually exclusive? <a href=\"https://twitter.com/ggauthereau\">Guillaume Gauthereau</a> (this week's live chat host -- <a href=\"https://facebok.com/events/109909259158773/\">RSVP here</a>) is living proof that they're not.","image":"638e30fda3c47c530c0a5f13","year":"2013","publishDate":"January 30, 2013","type":"insights","title":"Meet Guillaume Gauthereau of Totsy on #StartupLab","author.jobTitle":["The Young Entrepreneur Council"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2013/meet-guillaume-gauthereau-of-totsy-on-startuplab","tags":["Perspective Migration"],"month":"01","author.displayName":["The Young Entrepreneurship Council"],"siteId":"citigpa","category":"PERSPECTIVES"},{"summary":"Citi Private Bank is proud to sponsor Art13 London, the first truly global art fair. With offices around the world, Citi Private Bank shares Art13 London's international perspective.","image":"638e3319a3c47c530c0a6a27","year":"2013","publishDate":"January 30, 2013","type":"insights","title":"Citi Private Bank Sponsors Global Art Fair \"Art13 London\"","author.jobTitle":["Chief Executive Officer, Citi"],"url":"/global/news/perspective/2013/citi-private-bank-sponsors-global-art-fair-art13-london","tags":["Perspective Migration"],"month":"01","author.displayName":["Jane Fraser"],"siteId":"citigpa","category":"PERSPECTIVES"},{"summary":"Santo Domingo, Dominican Republic - This month, the Ministry of Finance's General Office of Public Credit presented the 2012 rankings for its Market Creator Program. Citi Dominican Republic and Citinversiones ranked #1 and #4, respectively. ","month":"01","year":"2013","publishDate":"January 29, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Dominican Republic Ranks #1 Among Finance Ministry's Market Creators","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/citi-dominican-republic-ranks-1-among-finance-ministry-s-market-creators","tags":["Press Release Migration","Institutional Clients Group"]},{"summary":"More than 2 billion people around the world lack access to basic financial services such as savings accounts, credit cards, insurance, and a way to make or receive payments. Citi and the Citi Foundation have worked for decades to broaden financial inclusion among underserved individuals and markets, and this week those efforts took a massive step forward with the launch of Financial Inclusion 2020 (FI2020).","image":"638e331ba3c47c530c0a6a37","year":"2013","publishDate":"January 29, 2013","type":"insights","title":"Citi joins with CFI and Visa to launch Financial Inclusion 2020","author.jobTitle":["Director of Corporate Citizenship, Citi and President & CEO of the Citi Foundation"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2013/citi-joins-with-cfi-and-visa-to-launch-financial-inclusion-2020","tags":["Perspective Migration"],"month":"01","author.displayName":["Pamela Flaherty"],"siteId":"citigpa","category":"PERSPECTIVES"},{"summary":"Since Citi's founding in 1812, we have applied our passion for innovation to connect clients to the world. Our most recent example of this innovative spirit is Citibank Express - a \"Smart Banking\" machine that allows customers to do almost all of their banking without visiting a branch, including opening accounts and applying for loans, cards and cashier's checks. The first Citibank Express machines were unveiled last week at Citibank branches in Singapore, Malaysia and the Philippines.","image":"638e331ea3c47c530c0a6a40","year":"2013","publishDate":"January 29, 2013","type":"insights","title":"New Smart Banking ATM Citibank Express Creates Next-Gen Customer Experience","author.jobTitle":["Global Head of Retail Banking and Head of Consumer Banking, Citi Asia Pacific"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2013/citibank-express-creates-next-gen-customer-experience","tags":["Perspective Migration"],"month":"01","author.displayName":["Jonathan Larsen"],"siteId":"citigpa","category":"PERSPECTIVES"},{"summary":"New York - Today, the Financial Times and Citi announce a global call for submissions for the 2013 FT/Citi Ingenuity Awards: Urban Ideas in Action, a global program that will recognize individuals, teams, organizations and community groups that have developed groundbreaking solutions to urban challenges that benefit cities, citizens and urban communities. ","month":"01","year":"2013","publishDate":"January 28, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Financial Times and Citi Announce Global Call for Submissions for 2013 FT/Citi Ingenuity Awards","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/financial-times-and-citi-announce-global-call-for-submissions-for-2013-ftciti-ingenuity-awards","tags":["Press Release Migration","Citi-Wide","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"Washington, D.C. - The Center for Financial Inclusion at Accion, together with Citi and Visa Inc., today announced the launch of the Financial Inclusion 2020 campaign (FI2020). FI2020 is focused on the acceleration of financial inclusion by uniting the private sector, governments, nongovernmental organizations (NGOs) and other relevant parties to develop and advance a comprehensive strategy to achieve this aim.","month":"01","year":"2013","publishDate":"January 28, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"The Center for Financial Inclusion at Accion, Citi and Visa Inc. Launch Financial Inclusion 2020 to Accelerate Universal Financial Access","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/the-center-for-financial-inclusion-at-accion-citi-and-visa-inc-launch-financial-inclusion-2020-to-accelerate-universal-financial-access","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"Prague - Citibank Europe plc has received the MasterCard® Multifunctional Card Award for 2012. The award recognizes Citi Opuscard, which was launched in cooperation with the Liberec Region last autumn. The Citi Opuscard is the first multifunctional credit card of its kind in the Czech Republic and combines the advantages of the Citi Life credit card with the regional multifunctional Opuscard, which has mainly been used in public transport to date. With a single card, customers can use public transport in the Liberec Region and make everyday payments in shops in the Czech Republic and all over the world, as well as over the internet, and make cash withdrawals from ATMs.","month":"01","year":"2013","publishDate":"January 28, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Czech Republic: Citibank Receives MasterCard Award for Citi Opuscard, the First Multifunctional Credit Card","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/cech-republic-citibank-receives-mastercard-award-for-citi-opuscard-the-first-multifunctional-credit-card","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"Federal taxes are climbing for many folks in 2013. But thanks to inflation adjustments, so too are some key tax thresholds. You can now save more for retirement, make larger gifts without worrying about the gift tax and even pay a little less tax on your children's investment gains. Here are some key changes:","image":"638e331fa3c47c530c0a6a49","year":"2013","publishDate":"January 28, 2013","type":"insights","title":"Know Your Limits: 2013's Tax Thresholds Rise With Inflation","author.jobTitle":["Director of Financial Education, Citi Personal Wealth Management"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2013/tax-thresholds-rise-with-inflation","tags":["Perspective Migration"],"month":"01","author.displayName":["Jonathan Clements"],"siteId":"citigpa","category":"PERSPECTIVES"},{"summary":"Today, Citi is pleased to announce that submissions for the 2013 FT/Citi Ingenuity Awards: Urban Ideas in Action program are now being accepted! In 2012, Citi partnered with the Financial Times to sponsor the FT/Citi Ingenuity Awards: Urban Ideas in Action program to recognize those fueling progress in cities around the world.","month":"01","year":"2013","publishDate":"January 28, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Enabling Urban Progress -- FT/Citi Ingenuity Awards: Urban Ideas in Action","category":"PERSPECTIVES","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2013/enabling-urban-progress-ftciti-ingenuity-awards","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"New York - Citi Community Development today released <i>Money Matters</i>, a market-specific publication appearing in 16 states across the United States that encourages working taxpayers to take advantage of refunds available through the federal Earned Income Tax Credit (EITC). The publication, the centerpiece of Citi's second annual national EITC awareness campaign, also highlights the availability of free tax preparation services through the Volunteer Income Tax Assistance (VITA) program of the Internal Revenue Service (IRS). The publications are available in English and Spanish at <a href=\"http://www.citicommunitydevelopment.com\">www.citicommunitydevelopment.com</a>.","month":"01","year":"2013","publishDate":"January 25, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Community Development Marks National EITC Awareness Day with Release of Money Matters Publication","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/citi-community-development-marks-national-eitc-awareness-day-with-release-of-money-matters-publication","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"Today is National EITC Awareness Day in the U.S., and in a guest post on the New America Foundation's blog The Ladder, Bob Annibale, Citi's Global Director of Community Development, focuses on ways to provide the tools and knowledge necessary for working families to achieve economic stability. <a href=\"https://bit.ly/10SiMvF\">From Access to Assets: The Vital Role of EITC VITA</a> sites details on how Citi is working with nonprofit organizations across the country to increase awareness of tax credits like the Earned Income Tax Credit (EITC) through Volunteer Income Tax Assistance (VITA) sites, and connecting people with comprehensive support to build financial assets.","image":"638e3321a3c47c530c0a6a54","month":"01","year":"2013","publishDate":"January 25, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Marks National EITC Awareness Day","category":"PERSPECTIVES","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2013/citi-marks-national-eitc-awareness-day","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"<em>Left to right: Tom Cochran, CEO and Executive Director, US Conference of Mayors, Edwin M. Lee, Mayor of San Francisco, Bob Annibale, Global Director, Citi Microfinance and Community Development, Hon. Jose Cisneros, Treasurer of the City and County of San Francisco, Scott Smith, Mayor of Mesa, AZ and Vice President of the US Conference of Mayors</em>","image":"638e3322a3c47c530c0a6a5b","year":"2013","publishDate":"January 25, 2013","type":"insights","title":"San Francisco and Citi Honored with the Excellence in Public-Private Partnerships Award","author.jobTitle":["San Francisco Treasurer"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2013/san-francisco-and-citi-honored-with-the-excellence-in-public-private-partnerships-award","tags":["Perspective Migration"],"month":"01","author.displayName":["the Hon. José Cisneros"],"siteId":"citigpa","category":"PERSPECTIVES"},{"summary":"Hong Kong - Citibank and The University of Hong Kong (HKU) today held the inauguration ceremony for The University of Hong Kong - Citibank University Banking Course 2012-2013.","month":"01","year":"2013","publishDate":"January 24, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citibank Launches Citibank University Banking Course with the University of Hong Kong","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/citibank-launches-citibank-university-banking-course-with-the-university-of-hong-kong-2","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"Shanghai - Citibank (China) Co., Ltd. (\"Citi China\") today announced the completion of its first cross-border lending transaction in Renminbi (RMB). ","month":"01","year":"2013","publishDate":"January 24, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Completes the First Cross-Border RMB Lending Transaction","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/citi-completes-the-first-cross-border-rmb-lending-transaction","tags":["Press Release Migration","Institutional Clients Group"]},{"summary":"Shanghai - Citibank (China) Co., Ltd. (\"Citi China\") today announced the completion of its first cross-border lending transaction in Renminbi (RMB).","month":"01","year":"2013","publishDate":"January 24, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi and Meta Trader 5 Gain Traction Amongst Brokers with the Integration of CitiFX TradeStream","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/citi-and-meta-trader-5-gain-traction-amongst-brokers-with-the-integration-of-citifx-tradestream","tags":["Press Release Migration","Institutional Clients Group"]},{"summary":"<a href=\"https://blog.citigroup.com/2012/05/citis-thought-leadership-product-suite-citi-gps-global-perspectives-solutions-now-online.shtml\">Citi Global Perspectives & Solutions (Citi GPS) is Citi's latest thought leadership initiative</a> through which we are delivering insights and viewpoints on compelling issues and structural thematic trends in the global economy. In the most recent opinion article: <strong>\"Is There a US Manufacturing Renaissance?\",</strong> I discuss how there has been a notable influx of high-profile capital goods companies investing in US manufacturing facilities in the past several years. While the media has trumpeted this trend as a resurgence of US manufacturing, our analysis indicates that the motivations behind these investment decisions are broad-ranging and more often company-specific. Check out an excerpt from the full report below:","image":"638e3159a3c47c530c0a60b6","year":"2013","publishDate":"January 24, 2013","type":"insights","title":"Is There a US Manufacturing Renaissance?","author.jobTitle":["CFA – Global Industrials Sector Leader, Citi"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2013/is-there-a-us-manufacturing-renaissance","tags":["Perspective Migration"],"month":"01","author.displayName":["Deane M. Dray"],"siteId":"citigpa","category":"PERSPECTIVES"},{"summary":"Singapore, Manila, Kuala Lumpur - Citi introduced a next-generation banking channel today in Asia - Citibank Express. Citibank Express, a \"Smart Banking\" machine, allows customers to do almost all of their banking without visiting a branch, including opening accounts and applying for loans, cards and cashier's checks. ","month":"01","year":"2013","publishDate":"January 23, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Asia: Citi Unveils Next-Generation Banking Experience, \"Citibank Express\"","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/asia-citi-unveils-next-generation-banking-experience-citibank-express","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"New York - <a href=\"http://www.citibank.com/\" target=\"http://www.citibank.com/\">Citibank® Online</a> and Citi's digital banking services were recognized today as the top among major U.S. banks in a Forrester Research, Inc. January 2013 report\"2012 <em>U.S. Bank Secure Website Rankings: Citi Moves to the Top with Added Functionality and a New Look.</em>\" In the report, Forrester attributes Citi's top ranking to the launch of the newly redesigned Citibank Online in 2011 and the launch of its acclaimed tablet banking apps, <em>Citibank for iPad®</em> and <em>Citibank® (Kindle Fire Edition)</em>.","month":"01","year":"2013","publishDate":"January 22, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"U.S.: Citi Tops Secure Website Rankings","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/us-citi-tops-secure-website-rankings","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"Prague - Starting in February 2013, Citibank Europe plc will issue - automatically and free of charge - a contactless payment sticker with each new Citi Life, Citi Life Metropole, Citi Broker Consulting, Citi BILLA and Citi CSA credit card. Payments using contactless payment stickers work in the same way as contactless credit cards: simply hold the sticker in front of the reader at the payment terminal, and the transaction is completed. The contactless stickers will make shopping even quicker and more convenient for Citibank clients.","month":"01","year":"2013","publishDate":"January 22, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Czech Republic: Citi to Start Issuing Contactless Payment Stickers for New Credit Cards","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/cech-republic-citi-to-start-issuing-contactless-payment-stickers-for-new-credit-cards","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"<a href=\"https://www.citigroup.com/rcs/citigpa/storage/public/taxlaw.jpg\"></a>As folks come to grips with the new federal tax law, much of the focus has been on the higher tax rates and new limits on exemptions and deductions that affect upper-income Americans. But the law also includes some less-publicized provisions:","image":"638e3325a3c47c530c0a6a6d","year":"2013","publishDate":"January 22, 2013","type":"insights","title":"New Tax Law: Check Out These Less-Publicized Provisions","author.jobTitle":["Director of Financial Education, Citi Personal Wealth Management"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2013/new-tax-law","tags":["Perspective Migration"],"month":"01","author.displayName":["Jonathan Clements"],"siteId":"citigpa","category":"PERSPECTIVES"},{"summary":"Mumbai - Citibank India today announced the launch of a fully integrated and certified mobile payment solution in India and across the Citigroup network, globally. The mobile payment solution, developed by Citi's partner Ezetap Mobile Solutions, allows for more than 320 million card customers in India to make payments through their debit and credit cards at the point of payment. The secured paperless transaction not only does away with managing charge slips but also combines the many benefits enjoyed by Citibank card customers, including instant redemption of reward points, accelerated rewards as well as the ability to opt for the popular EMI payment option while using this new payment alternative. Merchant partners using this device for customer payments and collections will be given real time information during the payment and collection process, providing an integrated, secured and efficient receivables payment solution.","month":"01","year":"2013","publishDate":"January 21, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"India: Citibank Launches the First Fully Integrated and Certified Mobile Payment Solution","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/india-citibank-launches-the-first-fully-integrated-and-certified-mobile-payment-solution","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"New York - The City and County of San Francisco and Citi Community Development today received the 2013 Excellence Award for Public-Private Partnerships at the U.S. Conference of Mayors 81st Winter Meeting in Washington, D.C. The award, which honors the outstanding achievements made possible through the combined effort of cities and members of the Mayors Business Council, recognizes the cross-sector collaboration on Kindergarten to College, the nation's first universal college savings program for children.","month":"01","year":"2013","publishDate":"January 19, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"The City & County of San Francisco and Citi Community Development Receive 2013 Excellence Award in Public-Private Partnerships from U.S. Conference of Mayors","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/the-city-county-of-san-francisco-and-citi-community-development-receive-2013-excellence-award-in-public-private-partnerships-from-us-conference-of-mayors","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"Last week, Citi hosted a Twitter roundtable focused on innovation with 18 influencers from the three <a href=\"https://on.citi.us/COTY\">City of the Year</a> finalists: Medellín, New York and Tel Aviv. The conversation generated more than 800 tweets from 380 contributors who discussed innovation using the hashtag <a href=\"https://rebelmouse.com/citiinnovation\">#CitiInnovation</a>. The roundtable provides a snapshot of the appetite for dialogue around this topic in each of the three cities. Here is a sample of some of the most insightful and interesting tweets shared by online influencers:","image":"638e3327a3c47c530c0a6a77","month":"01","year":"2013","publishDate":"January 18, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Hosts #CitiInnovation Twitter Chat Highlighting City of the Year Finalists","category":"PERSPECTIVES","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2013/citi-hosts-citiinnovation-twitter-chat-highlighting-city-of-the-year-finalists","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"<p><strong>The unemployment rate is likely to fall further in 2013 barring exogenous shocks.</strong> Given survey work from both Manpower and the National Federation of Independent Business, modest job growth should continue to drive down unemployment over the next six-to-nine months. While the job numbers may not be overly powerful, steady progress, albeit slow, should be maintained.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","image":"638e3328a3c47c530c0a6a7e","year":"2013","publishDate":"January 18, 2013","type":"insights","title":"Equity Strategy: January 2013 Chart of the Month","author.jobTitle":["Chief US Equity Strategist, Citi"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2013/equity-strategy-january-2013-chart-of-the-month","tags":["Perspective Migration"],"month":"01","author.displayName":["Tobias Levkovich"],"siteId":"citigpa","category":"PERSPECTIVES"},{"summary":"In celebration of Citigroup's 200th Anniversary, we have been sharing stories from our rich history here on this blog. The final installment below covers how the bank began to take a leadership role in promoting sustainability and environmental awareness. <a href=\"https://blog.citigroup.com/2013/01/citi-turns-200-citi-supports-american-communities.shtml\">Read the 37th installment, which explains how the bank supported American communities through job creation, small-business finance, and affordable housing initiatives, here</a>.","image":"638e30faa3c47c530c0a5f05","month":"01","year":"2013","publishDate":"January 18, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Turns 200: Banking fosters sustainability","category":"PERSPECTIVES","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2013/citi-turns-200-banking-fosters-sustainability","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"New York - Citigroup Inc. today reported net income for the fourth quarter 2012 of $1.2 billion, or $0.38 per diluted share, on revenues of $18.2 billion. This compared to net income of $956 million, or $0.31 per diluted share, on revenues of $17.2 billion for the fourth quarter 2011. ","month":"01","year":"2013","publishDate":"January 17, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citigroup Reports Fourth Quarter 2012 Earnings per Share of $0.38; $0.69 Excluding CVA/DVA and Repositioning Charges","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/citigroup-reports-fourth-quarter-2012-earnings-per-share-of-038-069-excluding-cvadva-and-repositioning-charges","tags":["Press Release Migration","Citi-Wide"]},{"summary":"Just ask <a href=\"https://twitter.com/lewishowes\">Lewis Howes</a>, this week's live chat host (<a href=\"https://facebook.com/events/485420968137422/\">RSVP here</a>).","image":"638e30fda3c47c530c0a5f13","year":"2013","publishDate":"January 17, 2013","type":"insights","title":"Meet Lewis Howes of SportsNetworker.com on #StartupLab.","author.jobTitle":["The Young Entrepreneur Council"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2013/meet-lewis-howes-of-sportsnetworkercom-on-startuplab","tags":["Perspective Migration"],"month":"01","author.displayName":["The Young Entrepreneurship Council"],"siteId":"citigpa","category":"PERSPECTIVES"},{"month":"01","year":"2013","publishDate":"January 17, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Releases Fourth Quarter 2012 Earnings","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/citi-releases-fourth-quarter-2012-earnings"},{"summary":"Citi was named best Southeast Asia financial advisor for 2012 in the annual awards from the FT's Mergermarket Group. The award is for advisory services to institutional clients covering mergers and acquisitions (M&A).","month":"01","year":"2013","publishDate":"January 16, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Named Southeast Asia Financial Adviser of the Year by FT's Mergermarket","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/citi-named-southeast-asia-financial-adviser-of-the-year-by-ft-s-mergermarket","tags":["Press Release Migration","Institutional Clients Group"]},{"summary":"New York - Rising Tide Capital, a leading New Jersey entrepreneurship incubator, will create a new online system called Rising Tide 2.0 to streamline the connection between New Jersey entrepreneurs and appropriate micro-lenders. The effort will be funded by a $150,000 grant from Citi Community Development. ","month":"01","year":"2013","publishDate":"January 16, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"U.S.: Rising Tide Capital and Citi Community Development to Launch New Website for N.J. Entrepreneurs","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/us-rising-tide-capital-and-citi-community-development-to-launch-new-website-for-nj-entrepreneurs","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"New York - The Board of Directors of Citigroup Inc. today declared a quarterly dividend on Citigroup's common stock of $0.01 per share, payable on February 22, 2013 to stockholders of record on February 4, 2013.","month":"01","year":"2013","publishDate":"January 16, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citigroup Declares Dividends","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/citigroup-declares-dividends-15","tags":["Press Release Migration","Citi-Wide"]},{"summary":"New York - In an effort to provide aid to children with disabilities and cancer in the United States, Citibank today announced that its support of Teletón USA during the holiday season generated $1.4 million in donations. ","month":"01","year":"2013","publishDate":"January 16, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citibank Support of Teletón USA Generates $1.4 Million","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/citibank-support-of-teletoacuten-usa-generates-14-million","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"Reflecting on 2012 and the past few years, many of us feel that the world is vastly changed. Suddenly, it seems, we live in a world where debate on our national budget can put us on a fiscal cliff, hurricanes can cripple mighty New York City, and employed Americans are homeless. Most of us may be unaware of this last change: that poverty afflicts even those who work hard. It contradicts a dearly held belief about what it means to be American.","image":"638e332ba3c47c530c0a6a91","year":"2013","publishDate":"January 16, 2013","type":"insights","title":"Community Development and the New Normal","author.jobTitle":["Regional Director, Citi Community Development"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2013/community-development-and-the-new-normal","tags":["Perspective Migration"],"month":"01","author.displayName":["Debbie Taylor"],"siteId":"citigpa","category":"PERSPECTIVES"},{"summary":"Kuala Lumpur - The launch of the new Citibank Rewards Platinum Card today made Citibank Berhad the first international bank in Malaysia to pioneer a suite of customizable card services incorporating internet and smartphone technology. ","month":"01","year":"2013","publishDate":"January 15, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Malaysia: Citibank Pioneers Innovative Approach to Credit Cards","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/malaysia-citibank-pioneers-innovative-approach-to-credit-cards","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"Citi and the Wall Street Journal have teamed up to name the \"<a href=\"https://on.citi.us/COTY\">City of the Year</a>,\" an award given to the most innovative city. Based on a combination of judging from the <a href=\"https://www.uli.org/\">Urban Land Institute</a> and popular vote, New York City is one of the three finalists for the title of \"City of the Year.\"","image":"638e332da3c47c530c0a6a9d","month":"01","year":"2013","publishDate":"January 15, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"City of the Year Finalist Entrepreneur Spotlight: Yaron Galai of Tel Aviv","category":"PERSPECTIVES","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2013/city-of-the-year-finalist-entrepreneur-spotlight-yaron-galai-of-tel-aviv","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"Manila - Citi Philippines and the FINEX Research and Development Foundation, Inc. (FINEX Foundation) recently celebrated the completion of the Ninth Citi Junior Bankers Congress with a fellowship dinner in honor of its student graduates. Funded by the Citi Foundation, the CJBC is a signature citizenship program of Citi that aims to train and provide job opportunities to the top students of state universities and colleges in the country.","month":"01","year":"2013","publishDate":"January 14, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Philippines: Ninth Citi Junior Bankers Congress Graduates Feted","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/philippines-ninth-citi-junior-bankers-congress-graduates-feted","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"<a href=\"https://www.citigroup.com/rcs/citigpa/storage/public/college_money_bluewave.jpg\"></a>A college degree may be a fine investment. But increasingly, it also comes with hefty debt. According to the Federal Reserve Bank of New York, student loans totaled $956 billion as of 2012's third quarter, up from $529 billion five years earlier.","image":"638e332ea3c47c530c0a6aa4","year":"2013","publishDate":"January 14, 2013","type":"insights","title":"A Good Education Isn't Priceless, Alas","author.jobTitle":["Director of Financial Education, Citi Personal Wealth Management"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2013/a-good-education-isnt-priceless-alas","tags":["Perspective Migration"],"month":"01","author.displayName":["Jonathan Clements"],"siteId":"citigpa","category":"PERSPECTIVES"},{"summary":"New Delhi - At the Citi Micro Enterprise Awards (CMEA) ceremony today, four Community Micro Enterprises and one Innovative Livelihoods Enterprise Promoter were felicitated for successfully building self-sustaining businesses and creating employment, and for their meaningful contribution to their communities. The Honorable United States Ambassador to India, Nancy J. Powell, together with CEO of Citi India Pramit Jhaveri and the Governing Council Members of the Awards program, presented the awards to the winners at the Sirifort Auditorium in New Delhi.","month":"01","year":"2013","publishDate":"January 12, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi India Honors Exemplary Community Micro Enterprises","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/citi-india-honors-exemplary-community-micro-enterprises","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance","Institutional Clients Group"]},{"summary":"This Sunday, South West Community Development Council (CDC) and Citi Singapore will launch the Citi-South West Family Save-and-Grow program. The new customized financial literacy program is part of the CDC's upstream intervention efforts to equip participating families, including their children, with financial management skills towards long-term financial independence. The program will reach out to a total of 50 needy families in 2013 and comprise three pilot features: matched savings for dual accounts of the families, a mentoring pairing with staff from Citi Singapore and a progressive financial literacy course. ","month":"01","year":"2013","publishDate":"January 11, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"First Customized Financial Literacy Program to Help Inculcate Saving Habits in Lower-Income Families","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/first-customied-financial-literacy-program-to-help-inculcate-saving-habits-in-lower-income-families","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance","Institutional Clients Group","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"The fifth installment of a special financial inclusion series underwritten by the Citi Foundation will debut this evening on the PBS weekly public affairs news program \"Need to Know\". The five-part series, \"Your Money and Your Life,\" illustrates the Citi Foundation's commitment to educate, empower and transform low-income communities by supporting efforts to build financial capability among consumers.","image":"638e3100a3c47c530c0a5f23","year":"2013","publishDate":"January 11, 2013","type":"insights","title":"Citi Foundation-supported PBS series continues, focusing on federal tax benefits","author.jobTitle":["Citi Foundation Program Officer"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2013/citi-foundation-supported-pbs-series-continues-focusing-on-federal-tax-benefits","tags":["Perspective Migration"],"month":"01","author.displayName":["Daria Sheehan"],"siteId":"citigpa","category":"PERSPECTIVES"},{"summary":"London - Citi has won the \"OTC Client Clearing Service of the Year\" award in <i>Risk</i> magazine's annual rankings. <i>Risk</i> is a financial risk management publication focused on economic and regulatory risk capital. Citi was chosen by a survey of industry participants along with an editorial panel from <i>Risk</i>.","month":"01","year":"2013","publishDate":"January 10, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Named OTC Client Clearing Service of the Year by Risk Magazine","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/citi-named-otc-client-clearing-service-of-the-year-by-risk-magaine","tags":["Press Release Migration","Institutional Clients Group"]},{"summary":"New York, London, Hong Kong - Citi is launching a tri-party collateral management solution in conjunction with tri-party agents that allows clients to consolidate their equity and fixed income holdings into a single collateral pool by combining assets held at Citi as Custodian with those held at tri-party agents.","month":"01","year":"2013","publishDate":"January 10, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Launches Expanded Tri-Party Collateral Management Solution","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/citi-launches-expanded-tri-party-collateral-management-solution","tags":["Press Release Migration","Institutional Clients Group"]},{"summary":"<a href=\"https://twitter.com/rahimthedream\">Rahim Fazal</a>, this week's live chat host (<a href=\"https://facebook.com/events/374806409256456\">click here to RSVP</a>), still remembers the exact moment he knew he would be a lifelong entrepreneur. It was June 14th, 2000. Rahim was in his senior year at high school, and he'd just sold his first venture, a Web hosting company, for a sweet $1.5 million.","image":"638e30fda3c47c530c0a5f13","year":"2013","publishDate":"January 09, 2013","type":"insights","title":"Meet YEC's Rahim Fazal of Involver on #StartupLab","author.jobTitle":["The Young Entrepreneur Council"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2013/meet-yecs-rahim-fazal-of-involver-on-startuplab","tags":["Perspective Migration"],"month":"01","author.displayName":["The Young Entrepreneurship Council"],"siteId":"citigpa","category":"PERSPECTIVES"},{"summary":"Recently, the global environmental community lost one of its strongest advocates, Rebecca (Becky) Tarbotton, the Executive Director of the Rainforest Action Network (RAN), in a tragic accident. We want to offer our sincere condolences to Becky's family and to the RAN staff and board. We know that her loss will be deeply felt not just by her loved ones, but also by the entire environmental movement, especially those of us who worked with her. Becky was a great leader who had already made a huge impact on the issues she cared deeply about.","image":"638e3332a3c47c530c0a6ab8","year":"2013","publishDate":"January 09, 2013","type":"insights","title":"Remembering Rebecca Tarbotton","author.jobTitle":["Chief Sustainability Officer, Citi","CEO and President, the Citi Foundation and Director, Corporate Citizenship","Director Corporate Sustainability, Citi","MD, Environmental and Social Risk Mgmt"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2013/remembering-rebecca-tarbotton","tags":["Perspective Migration"],"month":"01","author.displayName":["Val Smith","Pam Flaherty","Bruce Schlein","Shawn Miller"],"siteId":"citigpa","category":"PERSPECTIVES"},{"summary":"Manila - For the ninth consecutive year, Citi Philippines bagged the Best Bank award at The Asset Triple A Country Awards 2012. The country's leading foreign bank also picked up its third consecutive win as Best Foreign Investment Bank in the Philippines.","month":"01","year":"2013","publishDate":"January 08, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Philippines Wins The Asset's Nod for Best Bank, Best Investment Bank","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/citi-philippines-wins-the-asset-s-nod-for-best-bank-best-investment-bank","tags":["Press Release Migration","Institutional Clients Group","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"Citi Global Perspectives & Solutions (Citi GPS) is Citi's latest thought leadership initiative through which we are delivering insights and viewpoints on compelling issues and structural thematic trends in the global economy. In the most recent opinion article: \"<strong>Emerging Markets: The Earnings Challenge in 2013</strong>\", I discuss how EM economies saw much weaker growth than originally forecast for 2012, which contributed to virtually no corporate earnings growth last year. With EM equities rising by 15% in 2012, valuations increased. Looking ahead to 2013, I argue that, with equity markets not likely to re-rate again, the key to further market gains will be a solid rebound in GDP and earnings growth, which we expect. Our call is for EM equities to rise by close to 10% in 2013.","image":"638e3159a3c47c530c0a60b6","year":"2013","publishDate":"January 08, 2013","type":"insights","title":"Emerging Markets: The Earnings Challenge in 2013","author.jobTitle":["Global Emerging Markets Strategist"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2013/emerging-markets-the-earnings-challenge-in-2013","tags":["Perspective Migration"],"month":"01","author.displayName":["Geoffrey Dennis"],"siteId":"citigpa","category":"PERSPECTIVES"},{"summary":"New York - Citi today released the following statement on the agreement in principle reached with the Office of the Comptroller of the Currency (OCC) and the Federal Reserve Board regarding the Independent Foreclosure Review process. ","month":"01","year":"2013","publishDate":"January 07, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Statement on Independent Foreclosure Review Agreement in Principle","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/citi-statement-on-independent-foreclosure-review-agreement-in-principle","tags":["Press Release Migration","Citi-Wide"]},{"summary":"New York - Citi Chief Executive Officer Michael Corbat today announced the roles and responsibilities of the members of his management team and appointed Jamie Forese and Manuel Medina-Mora as Co-Presidents of Citi. Mr. Forese will be responsible for all of Citi's Institutional businesses, and Mr. Medina-Mora will continue to oversee Global Consumer Banking and Citi's franchise in Mexico. The Operations & Technology functions supporting the Institutional and Consumer businesses will now directly report to Mr. Forese and Mr. Medina-Mora, respectively, to better align the functions with the priorities of each business and improve efficiency.","month":"01","year":"2013","publishDate":"January 07, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi CEO Michael Corbat Announces Management Team","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2013/citi-ceo-michael-corbat-announces-management-team-2","tags":["Press Release Migration","Citi-Wide"]},{"summary":"If you want to get the New Year off to a good financial start, consider funding your Individual Retirement Account for the 2012 tax year--and also socking away money for 2013. While the maximum IRA contribution for 2012 is $5,000, it rises to $5,500 in 2013. For both years, you can contribute an additional $1,000 if you're age 50 or older. You have until the April 15 tax-filing deadline to make your 2012 contribution.","image":"638e3337a3c47c530c0a6acd","year":"2013","publishDate":"January 07, 2013","type":"insights","title":"IRA Contributions: It's a Matter of Income","author.jobTitle":["Director of Financial Education, Citi Personal Wealth Management"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2013/ira-contributions-its-a-matter-of-income","tags":["Perspective Migration"],"month":"01","author.displayName":["Jonathan Clements"],"siteId":"citigpa","category":"PERSPECTIVES"},{"summary":"In celebration of Citigroup's 200th Anniversary, we are sharing stories from our rich history here on this blog. The 37th installment below covers how the bank supported American communities through job creation, small-business finance, and affordable housing initiatives. <a href=\"https://blog.citigroup.com/2012/12/citi-turns-200-ensuring-access-for-all.shtml\">Read the 36th installment which explains how Citi and the Citi Foundation promoted financial inclusion worldwide, here</a>.","month":"01","year":"2013","publishDate":"January 04, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Turns 200: Citi supports American communities","category":"PERSPECTIVES","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2013/citi-turns-200-citi-supports-american-communities","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"Women &amp; Co. President and CEO, Linda Descano CFA®, recently shared 5 easy-to-keep money resolutions (that you can make in 10 minutes or less). She advises that before you start tackling long-term planning, think about day-to-day financial tasks that you wish you could simplify. <a href=\"https://blog.womenandco.com/2012/12/five-easy-to-keep-money-resolutions---that-you-can-make-in-10-minutes-or-less.html\">Read her tips on the Women &amp; Co. blog</a>.","image":"638e3117a3c47c530c0a5f95","month":"01","year":"2013","publishDate":"January 03, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"On the Women & Co. Blog: Five Easy-to-Keep Money Resolutions","category":"PERSPECTIVES","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2013/on-the-women-co-blog-five-easy-to-keep-money-resolutions","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"When <a href=\"https://nickfriedman.com/\">Nick Friedman</a> (this week's live chat host -- <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/events/449261605119543/\">RSVP here</a>) and his best friend <a href=\"https://twitter.com/OmarJunkMan\">Omar Soliman</a> co-founded <a href=\"https://collegehunkshaulingjunk.com/\">College Hunks Hauling Junk</a>, all they had was a beat-up van and a local service.","image":"638e30fda3c47c530c0a5f13","year":"2013","publishDate":"January 02, 2013","type":"insights","title":"Meet Nick Friedman of College Hunks Hauling Junk on #StartupLab","author.jobTitle":["The Young Entrepreneur Council"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2013/meet-nick-friedman-of-college-hunks-hauling-junk-on-startuplab","tags":["Perspective Migration"],"month":"01","author.displayName":["The Young Entrepreneurship Council"],"siteId":"citigpa","category":"PERSPECTIVES"},{"summary":"This bi-annual report by the Assets and Education Initiative discusses how an asset approach to college financial aid may deliver superior educational outcomes.","image":"637217960de6635088314f60","month":"01","destinationLink":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/foundation/pdf/news130716.pdf","year":"2013","publishDate":"January 01, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Building Expectations, Delivering Results: Asset-Based Financial Aid and the Future of Higher Education","category":"REPORT","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/foundation/news/article/2013/building-expectations-delivering-results-asset-based-financial-aid-and-the-future-of-higher-education","tags":["Report Migration"]},{"summary":"This briefing, the first in a series, presents an overview of the market size and scope of local bank lending to smallholder farmers. Access to finance for smallholder farmers can serve as a critical catalyst for economic growth and poverty alleviation. Yet local bank lending - which should be a main avenue for smallholder financial access - meets only 3% of overall demand. Currently, global development donors have tried to incentivize bank lending to smallholders by focusing on guarantees, but those have not been sufficient to stimulate lending.","image":"637217960de6635088314f63","month":"01","destinationLink":"https://www.citigroup.com/rcs/citigpa/akpublic/storage/public/first_series.pdf","year":"2013","publishDate":"January 01, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Local Bank Financing for Smallholder Farmers: A $9 Billion Drop in the Ocean","category":"REPORT","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/foundation/news/article/2013/local-bank-financing-for-smallholder-farmers-a-$9-billion-drop-in-the-ocean","tags":["Report Migration"]},{"summary":"NeighborWorks America and the Citi Foundation released a new report and video that highlight how financial coaching can level the economic playing field by offering the information and support needed to help consumers reduce debt, increase savings, and reach their financial goals.","image":"6372179a0de6635088314f73","month":"01","destinationLink":"https://www.citigroup.com/rcs/citigpa/akpublic/storage/public/news100713.pdf","year":"2013","publishDate":"January 01, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Scaling Financial Coaching: Critical Lessons and Effective Practices","category":"REPORT","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/foundation/news/article/2013/scaling-financial-coaching-critical-lessons-and-effective-practices","tags":["Report Migration"]},{"summary":"The Low Income Investment Fund, with funding from the Citi Foundation, partnered with the Federal Reserve Bank of San Francisco to publish \"\", a collection of essays from key leaders in the U.S. community and economic development field that provides dozens of innovative ideas that can bring new opportunities to America's struggling communities. Visit the link to download a free digital copy of the book and learn more about this initiative.","image":"6372179c0de6635088314f7b","month":"01","destinationLink":"https://www.whatworksforamerica.org/","year":"2013","publishDate":"January 01, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Investing in What Works for America's Communities","category":"REPORT","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/foundation/news/article/2013/investing-in-what-works-for-americas-communities","tags":["Report Migration"]},{"summary":"More than 2 billion people, a majority of which are women, are currently financially excluded. Women are more than twice as likely to be financially excluded as men, and efforts to support their financial inclusion are bolstered by compelling research that shows investments in women contribute to greater development achievements. See examples of the Citi Foundation's investments in women here.","image":"6372179e0de6635088314f81","month":"01","destinationLink":"https://www.citifoundation.com/citi/foundation/womens_empowerment/#/1/","year":"2013","publishDate":"January 01, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Advancing Financial Inclusion Through Women's Economic Empowerment","category":"REPORT","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/foundation/news/article/2013/advancing-financial-inclusion-through-womens-economic-empowerment","tags":["Report Migration"]},{"summary":"Women's World Banking, supported by the Citi Foundation, released a case study about Project Samruddhi (Gujarati for \"prosperity\"), a two-year collaboration between Women's World Banking and India's Self Employed Women's Association (SEWA) Bank to improve financial inclusion outcomes among low-income, low-literacy women clients. The project aimed to determine whether comprehensive financial education linked with clients' financial goals catalyzed a savings habit as well as increased the frequency and amount saved. The project's results supports a key finding from the Citi Foundation-funded \"Bridging the Gap\" report-financial education activities can shift from a cost center to a business driver.","image":"637217a10de6635088314f8a","month":"01","destinationLink":"https://www.citigroup.com/rcs/citigpa/akpublic/storage/public/finedu_engine.pdf","year":"2013","publishDate":"January 01, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Can Financial Education Be the Engine for Savings Growth? A Case Study","category":"REPORT","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/foundation/news/article/2013/can-financial-education-be-the-engine-for-savings-growth-a-case-study","tags":["Report Migration"]},{"summary":"The Five-Year Capstone Report of the Postsecondary Success Collaborative (PSC) shows how higher education can be made more accessible for millions of students in the United States. PSC has served more than 12,000 students since it was launched by FHI 360 and the Citi Foundation in 2008. The program has transformed the way participating schools and partners map resources and needs and collaborate to support college readiness and completion. The capstone report provides steps that schools and communities can take to ensure that more low-income youth are getting the education, tools and skills they need to succeed in higher education and an increasingly competitive job market.","image":"637217a70de6635088314f9d","month":"01","destinationLink":"https://www.citigroup.com/rcs/citigpa/akpublic/storage/public/fhi360.pdf","year":"2013","publishDate":"January 01, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Postsecondary Success for All Students: Leveraging Partners and Assets","category":"REPORT","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/foundation/news/article/2013/postsecondary-success-for-all-students-leveraging-partners-and-assets","tags":["Report Migration"]},{"summary":"Small Changes, Real Impact summarizes the findings from the Behavioral Economics Technical Assistance (BETA) Project, an initiative housed at CFED to build the capacity of community-based asset building programs that want to apply insights and lessons from behavioral economics to their own program designs. Drawing on the experience and direct results of three partner sites -- Accion Texas, Cleveland Housing Network and Neighborhood Trust Financial Partners - the report describes the process of applying ideas42's Behavioral Diagnosis and Design approach to help identify potential barriers that hinder desired client behaviors and outcomes and provides helpful tips on how to incorporate the behavioral perspective to increase the impact and effectiveness of asset building programs.","image":"637217ac0de6635088314fb3","month":"01","destinationLink":"https://www.citigroup.com/rcs/citigpa/akpublic/storage/public/cfed_report.pdf","year":"2013","publishDate":"January 01, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Small Changes, Real Impact: Applying Behavioral Economics in Asset-Building Programs","category":"REPORT","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/foundation/news/article/2013/small-changes-real-impact-applying-behavioral-economics-in-asset-building-programs","tags":["Report Migration"]},{"summary":"This study assesses the state of the \"Missing Middle\" to better understand their needs and the challenges they face. It addresses how governments and other stakeholders can help them reach their potential for growth and job creation to positively impact the MENA region. Commissioned by the Citi Foundation and Shell Foundation, the new research is based on in-depth interviews with over 200 public and private leaders and SMEs in Saudi Arabia, Jordan, UAE and Egypt.","image":"637217990de6635088314f70","month":"01","destinationLink":"https://www.citigroup.com/rcs/citigpa/storage/public/mena_enterprises.pdf","year":"2013","publishDate":"January 01, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Small and Medium Sized Enterprises in MENA: Leveraging Growth Finance for Sustainable Development","category":"REPORT","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/foundation/news/article/2013/small-and-medium-sized-enterprises-in-mena-leveraging-growth-finance-for-sustainable-development","tags":["Report Migration"]},{"summary":"This report highlights innovative trends and common features in the proposals from the second round of the Financial Capability Innovation Fund, developed by the Center for Financial Services Innovation, in partnership with the Citi Foundation, and shares insights into how nonprofits are promoting financial capability among their clients.","image":"637217990de6635088314f6d","month":"01","destinationLink":"https://www.citigroup.com/rcs/citigpa/storage/public/strechtime_reach.pdf","year":"2013","publishDate":"January 01, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Stretch Time: Continuing to Reach for Financial Capability, Trends from the Financial Capability Innovation Fund II","category":"REPORT","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/foundation/news/article/2013/stretch-time-continuing-to-reach-for-financial-capability-trends-from-the-financial-capability-innovation-fund-ii","tags":["Report Migration"]},{"summary":"ideas42 released a white paper, funded by the Citi Foundation, that describes how the design of postsecondary education programs could align with principles of behavior to achieve significantly better outcomes. This paper and a corresponding convening that was held on May 23, 2013, are the beginning of ideas42's engagement in this important subject area. Read a blog introducing the paper and download a copy here.","image":"637217a00de6635088314f87","month":"01","destinationLink":"https://www.citigroup.com/rcs/citigpa/storage/public/ideas42.pdf","year":"2013","publishDate":"January 01, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Using Behavioral Economics for Postsecondary Success","category":"REPORT","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/foundation/news/article/2013/using-behavioral-economics-for-postsecondary-success","tags":["Report Migration"]},{"summary":"Researchers commissioned by the Rainforest Alliance, with the generous support of the Citi Foundation, compared financial recordkeeping variables between Rainforest Alliance Certified farms and noncertified farms; they also surveyed social lenders and local, in-country financial institutions. The study established a common minimum set of metrics for producers to record/report in order to apply for credit. Results showed that certified producers are better at tracking financial metrics and demonstrated that certified producers have better access to credit.","image":"6372179e0de6635088314f84","month":"01","destinationLink":"https://www.citigroup.com/rcs/citigpa/storage/public/Citi_bankability_singles.pdf","year":"2013","publishDate":"January 01, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Farmer Bankability and Sustainable Finance: Farm-Level Metrics that Matter","category":"REPORT","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/foundation/news/article/2013/farmer-bankability-and-sustainable-finance-farm-level-metrics-that-matter","tags":["Report Migration"]},{"summary":"Asset Funders Network, with support from the Citi Foundation, released a new white paper, \"Strategic Philanthropy: Creating Opportunity, Building Wealth and Driving Community Change.\" Developed by the Institute on Assets and Social Policy (IASP) at Brandeis University, this paper illuminates the growing field of asset building and provides guidance for foundations looking for ways to leverage the asset building framework to advance the impact of their work.","image":"6372179d0de6635088314f7e","month":"01","destinationLink":"https://www.citigroup.com/rcs/citigpa/storage/public/afn_asset_building_funder_brief.pdf","year":"2013","publishDate":"January 01, 2013","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Strategic Philanthropy: Creating Opportunity, building Wealth, and Driving Community Change","category":"REPORT","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/foundation/news/article/2013/strategic-philanthropy-creating-opportunity-building-wealth-and-driving-community-change","tags":["Report Migration"]},{"summary":"Nobody knows for sure what will happen in the financial markets in 2013. But that doesn't mean you should sit on your hands. Here are four financial ideas for the year ahead:","image":"638e30f8a3c47c530c0a5efd","year":"2012","publishDate":"December 31, 2012","type":"insights","title":"Whither 2013? Here Are Four Financial Ideas for the Year Ahead","author.jobTitle":["Director of Financial Education, Citi Personal Wealth Management"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2012/four-financial-ideas-for-the-year-ahead","tags":["Perspective Migration"],"month":"12","author.displayName":["Jonathan Clements"],"siteId":"citigpa","category":"PERSPECTIVES"},{"summary":"Shanghai - Citi has been named by <i>The Asset</i> magazine as the \"Best Bank in China\" in 2012.","month":"12","year":"2012","publishDate":"December 27, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Named Best Bank in China","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2012/citi-named-best-bank-in-china-2","tags":["Press Release Migration","Institutional Clients Group","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"New York – Citigroup Inc. (<B>\"Citigroup\"</B>) announced today the expiration and final tender results of the previously announced cash tender offers (each, an <B>\"Offer\"</B> and, collectively, the <B>\"Offers\"</B>) by Citigroup with respect to each series of notes listed in the tables below (the <B>\"Notes\"</B>).","month":"12","year":"2012","publishDate":"December 24, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citigroup Announces Expiration and Final Tender Results of Offers to Purchase Twelve Series of Outstanding Notes","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2012/citigroup-announces-expiration-and-final-tender-results-of-offers-to-purchase-twelve-series-of-outstanding-notes","tags":["Press Release Migration","Citi-Wide"]},{"image":"638e30faa3c47c530c0a5f05","month":"12","year":"2012","publishDate":"December 21, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Turns 200: Ensuring access for all","category":"PERSPECTIVES","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2012/citi-turns-200-ensuring-access-for-all","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"<a href=\"https://www.nyc.gov/portal/site/nycgov/menuitem.c0935b9a57bb4ef3daf2f1c701c789a0/index.jsp?pageID=mayor_press_release&catID=1194&doc_name=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.nyc.gov%2Fhtml%2Fom%2Fhtml%2F2012b%2Fpr482-12.html&cc=unused1978&rc=1194&ndi=1\">Today, Citi has launched the Storm Recovery Loan Fund</a>, a pilot program to provide up to $40 million in low-cost loans to fund the repair of multi-family buildings damaged by Hurricane Sandy along with Mayor Michael R. Bloomberg, and <a href=\"https://www.communityp.com/\">The Community Preservation Corporation</a>. Building owners can put the funds toward resiliency measures, like installing state-of-the-art heating and electric plants that are repositioned to withstand the next storm by being located on higher floors and/or in waterproof compartments. This focus on mitigation will decrease the cost of recovery and reduce the destructive impact of future storms. The program will also promote green improvements that will conserve energy and save money over the long term. The new fund blends a subsidy from <a href=\"https://www.nyc.gov/html/hpd/html/home/home.shtml\">Housing Preservation and Development</a> with Community Preservation Corporation financing to provide loans that are below market rate, allowing owners to make needed repairs in the aftermath of Sandy. <br><br>Both for-profit and not-for-profit owners of multifamily buildings in NYC are eligible to apply for the Storm Recovery Loan Fund. Loan proceeds may be used for repair work ranging from systems replacement and storm mitigation retrofits to gut rehab, where necessary. Storm Recovery Loans may have up to a 30-year term. CPC's portion of the loan will have a rate of approximately 4.5%, and HPD's funds have an interest rate of 1%, for a blended rate below other conventional financing. <br><br>All projects must comply with HPD standard specifications and substantial rehab projects must achieve Enterprise Green Communities Certification. In keeping with NYC's Greener Greater Buildings Plan, all of the properties financed under this program will be benchmarked for energy usage and retrofit for energy savings will be included in their scopes of work. All buildings burning number 6 oil will be converted to comply with the City's Clean Heat initiative. In addition, gut rehabilitation projects must meet HPD's construction specifications and design guidelines. <br><br>Citi is proud to be part of this initiative to help rebuild the communities that were affected by this catastrophic event and we will continue to be an active participant in the ongoing recovery efforts. We are confident that the Storm Recovery Loan Fund will help provide a quick and efficient funding source throughout the rebuilding process. <br><br>Building owners who are interested in applying for the program should go to <a href=\"https://nyc.gov/\">NYC.gov</a> or call 311.","image":"638e9423aa239337929deb4f","year":"2012","publishDate":"December 21, 2012","type":"insights","title":"Citi Launches $40M Sandy Recovery Loan Fund with Mayor Bloomberg and CPC","author.jobTitle":["Co-Head of Citi Community Capital"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2012/citi-launches-40m-sandy-recovery-loan-fund-with-mayor-bloomberg-and-cpc","tags":["Perspective Migration"],"month":"12","author.displayName":["Andrew Ditton"],"siteId":"citigpa","category":"PERSPECTIVES"},{"summary":"New York - Mayor Michael R. Bloomberg, Director of Housing Recovery Operations Brad Gair, New York City Department of Housing Preservation and Development Commissioner Mathew M. Wambua, New York City Housing Development Corporation President Marc Jahr, The Community Preservation Corporation President and CEO Rafael E. Cestero, and Citi Community Capital Co-Head Andrew Ditton have launched the Storm Recovery Loan Fund, a pilot program to provide up to $40 million in low-cost loans to fund the repair of multi-family buildings damaged by Hurricane Sandy. Building owners can put the funds toward resiliency measures, like installing state-of-the-art heating and electric plants that are repositioned to withstand the next storm by being located on higher floors and/or in waterproof compartments. This focus on mitigation will decrease the cost of recovery and reduce the destructive impact of future storms. The program will also promote green improvements that will conserve energy and save money over the long term. The new fund blends a subsidy from Housing Preservation and Development with Community Preservation Corporation financing to provide loans that are below market rate, allowing owners to make needed repairs in the aftermath of Sandy.","month":"12","year":"2012","publishDate":"December 20, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"U.S.: Mayor Bloomberg, Community Preservation Corporation and Citi Launch $40 Million Storm Recovery Loan Fund for Multi-Family Residential Buildings","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2012/us-mayor-bloomberg-community-preservation-corporation-and-citi-launch-40-million-storm-recovery-loan-fund-for-multi-family-residential-buildings","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance","Institutional Clients Group"]},{"summary":"Dubai - True to its vision for innovation and client excellence, Citibank, a member of Citi, will be the first bank in Central Europe Middle East and Africa region to partner with Visa on the launch of Visa Signature on its award-winning PremierMiles credit platform. ","month":"12","year":"2012","publishDate":"December 19, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Becomes the First Bank in CEMEA to Launch Visa Signature Premium Credit Card","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2012/citi-becomes-the-first-bank-in-cemea-to-launch-visa-signature-premium-credit-card","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"Citi and the Wall Street Journal have teamed up to name the \"<a href=\"https://on.citi.us/COTY\">City of the Year</a>,\" an award given