au of Applied Research of the National Bank of Poland, for his publication, 'Polish Monetary Policy. Theoretical and Empirical Research.'","month":"11","year":"2012","publishDate":"November 21, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Poland: Citi Presents the 2012 Bank Handlowy Award","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2012/poland-citi-presents-the-2012-bank-handlowy-award","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"New York - Citigroup Inc. (\"<b>Citigroup</b>\") today announced the commencement of offers to purchase for cash certain of its notes of the series set forth in the table below (each offer with respect to any series set forth in the table below, an \"<b>Offer</b>\" and, collectively, the \"<b>Offers</b>\"). We refer to our offer to purchase each series of Notes as an \"Offer\" and collectively as the \"Offers.\" Each of the Offers with respect to each series of Notes listed under \"Fixed Spread Offers\" in the table below is being made on a fixed spread basis (each, a \"<b>Fixed Spread Offer</b>\" and, collectively, the \"<b>Fixed Spread Offers</b>\"), and each of the Offers with respect to each series of Notes listed under \"Fixed Price Offers\" in the table below is being made on a fixed price basis (each, a \"<b>Fixed Price Offer</b>\" and, collectively, the \"<b>Fixed Price Offers</b>\"). The Notes have an aggregate principal amount outstanding of approximately $18,436,573,000 as of November 21, 2012.","month":"11","year":"2012","publishDate":"November 21, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citigroup Inc. Announces Offers to Purchase Twelve Series of Outstanding Notes","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2012/citigroup-inc-announces-offers-to-purchase-twelve-series-of-outstanding-notes","tags":["Press Release Migration","Citi-Wide"]},{"summary":"Luxembourg - Citi Microfinance and C