e":"On the Women & Co. Blog: What Does It Mean to Live Within Your Means?","category":"PERSPECTIVES","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2012/on-the-women-co-blog-what-does-it-mean-to-live-within-your-means","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"Bucharest, Romania - In times of economic crises, when new business models emerge, particularly those leading to cost reductions, it becomes even clearer that entrepreneurship is important for economic growth, productivity, innovation and employment. Citi Romania and Junior Achievement have partnered to launch a new in-school educational program called 'Be Entrepreneurial,' supported by a US$50,000 grant from the Citi Foundation. The program is aimed at promoting entrepreneurial thinking among 4,500 students aged 15-17 from high schools across the country and to encourage them to consider starting up a business later on.","month":"11","year":"2012","publishDate":"November 19, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi and Junior Achievement Launch the 'Be Entrepreneurial' Education Program in Romania","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/foundation/news/press-release/2012/citi-and-junior-achievement-launch-the-be-entrepreneurial-education-program-in-romania","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"New York - A new Urban Manufacturing Alliance (UMA) has been launched to accelerate the growth of urban manufacturing across the U.S. and to capitalize on the sector's ability to create stable, high-quality jobs.","month":"11","year":"2012","publishDate":"November 19, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Urban Manufacturing Alliance Launched to Boost Urban Manufacturing and Job Creation Across U.S.","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2012/urban-manufacturing-alliance-launched-to-boost-urban-manufacturing-and-job-creation-across-us","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"There are more than five million Americans who have been actively seeking a job for six months or longer. The so-called long-term unemployed represent 40% of all unemployed workers, and face the additional challenges of job-search fatigue and a lengthy period during which they lack previous levels of regular income, or none at all.","month":"11","author.displayName":["Bob Annibale"],"year":"2012","publishDate":"November 19, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Putting the Long-Term Unemployed Back to Work","category":"PERSPECTIVES","author.jobTitle":["Citi Pride Affinity Co-lead"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2012/putting-the-long-term-unemployed-back-to-work","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"U.S. home sales have been picking up in recent months, which is a good sign for the economy--and for home sellers, too. Soon, however, it will be winter, which is traditionally a slow time in the real-estate market. In fact, many sellers elect to take their homes off the market and then re-list as spring approaches.","image":"638e311aa3c47c530c0a5fa2","year":"2012","publishDate":"November 19, 2012","type":"insights","title":"Thinking of Selling Your Home? These Tips May Help","author.jobTitle":["Director of Financial Education, Citi Personal Wealth Management"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2012/thinking-of-selling-your-home-these-tips-may-help","tags":["Perspective Migration"],"month":"11","author.displayName":["Jonathan Clements"],"siteId":"citigpa","category":"PERSPECTIVES"},{"summary":"In celebration of Citigroup's 200th Anniversary, we are sharing stories from our rich history here on this blog. The 33rd installment below covers how the bank became a strategic ally in financing overseas sales for aircraft maker, Embraer. <a href=\"https://blog.citigroup.com/2012/11/citi-turns-200-mergers-create-banking-giants-abroad.shtml\">Read the 32nd installment explaining how the bank merged with Banamex, here</a>.","image":"638e30faa3c47c530c0a5f05","month":"11","year":"2012","publishDate":"November 16, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Turns 200: Brazilian aerospace giant finds strategic ally","category":"PERSPECTIVES","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2012/citi-turns-200-brazilian-aerospace-giant-finds-strategic-ally","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"Diners Club has partnered with Qantas to launch a new rewards payment card giving members exceptional value on their purchases. Members also have access to a companion World MasterCard on the Diners Club account, which increases acceptance with merchants to over 34 million locations around the globe.","month":"11","year":"2012","publishDate":"November 15, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Australia: Diners Club Partners with Qantas to Give Members Exceptional Value","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2012/australia-diners-club-partners-with-qantas-to-give-members-exceptional-value","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"Bridgeport, Conn. - The WorkPlace, with the support of AARP Foundation, Citi Community Development and the Walmart Foundation, announces the national expansion of the highly successful Platform to Employment (P2E) program, which creates a pathway to employment for the long-term unemployed. Long-term unemployment impacts more than 5 million Americans who have been actively seeking a job for more than six months. This population represents 40 percent of unemployed workers.","month":"11","year":"2012","publishDate":"November 15, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"U.S.: Successful Connecticut Program Putting the Long-Term Unemployed Back to Work Will Go National","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2012/us-successful-co