ing Madness' took place September 29-30. All over Poland, Citi Handlowy credit cards holders and readers of <i>Elle</i> and <i>Instyle</i> took advantage of special discount coupons, enjoyed discounts and deals and were able to take part in special fashion events at more than 160 Citi Handlowy credit card partner stores.","month":"10","year":"2012","publishDate":"October 09, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Handlowy's 'Shopping Madness' Campaign","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2012/citi-handlowy-s-shopping-madness-campaign","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"Asia Pacific - Just four years after launching Citi's mobile banking application - Citi Mobile - in Asia Pacific, the bank has passed the 1 million client mark. This makes Citi Mobile the most active and widely used mobile banking platform in the region, adding further to the bank's reputation as the market leader in digital banking in Asia Pacific.","month":"10","year":"2012","publishDate":"October 09, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Mobile Clients Top 1 Million Mark in Asia Pacific","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2012/citi-mobile-clients-top-1-million-mark-in-asia-pacific","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"The federal-estate tax gets all the attention, with politicians often debating its size and merits. But for taxpayers in a third of all states, including some of the most populous, it's the \"death tax\" imposed by their state government that can prove more costly.","image":"638e3153a3c47c530c0a6095","year":"2012","publishDate":"October 09, 2012","type":"insights","title":"Estate Taxes: How Hard Does Your State Hit?","author.jobTitle":["Director of Financial Education, Citi Personal Wealth Management"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2012/estate-taxes-how-hard-does-your-state-hit","tags":["Perspective Migration"],"month":"10","author.displayName":["Jonathan Clements"],"siteId":"citigpa","category":"PERSPECTIVES"},{"summary":"Budapest, Hungary - Citibank Hungary is planting another 59,000 trees around Budapest this autumn in the continuation of its Plant-a-Tree Program. When launching this program in 2008, Citibank promised to plant a tree for every customer switching from printed to paperless e-statements. Citibank's overall aim in this global initiative is to drive environmentally friendly behavior among its customers and to contribute to the conservation of forests in partnership with customers, non-governmental organizations and forestry companies.","month":"10","year":"2012","publishDate":"October 08, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"In Its Fifth Year, Citibank's Plant-a-Tree Program Surpasses 111,000 Trees Planted","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2012/in-its-fifth-year-citibank-s-plant-a-tree-program-surpasses-111000-trees-planted","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"Mumbai and Hong Kong - Citi's Securities and Fund Services, a division of Citi Transaction Services, today announced that it is the first international custodian bank to offer securities lending services on the National Stock Exchange (NSE) in India. This launch reinforces Citi's dominance in the emerging markets globally, making its proprietary OpenLendSM platform now available in 72 markets globally.","month":"10","year":"2012","publishDate":"October 05, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Launches Securities Lending Service in India","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2012/citi-launches-securities-lending-service-in-india","tags":["Press Release Migration","Institutional Clients Group"]},{"summary":"<p>According to a U.S. Census Bureau <a href=\"https://www.census.gov/prod/2012pubs/p60-243.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-link-source=\"tiny\">report</a> published last week, U.S. real median household income declined between 2011 and 2010 by 1.5% to $50,054 - 8.9% below its peak in 1999. For non-citizen households, median household income is even lower at $37,894. In contrast, median income of naturalized citizen households is $51,926 - 37% higher than non-citizen households and 3.7% higher than the national median income. Numbers and trends don't tell the whole story, but the magnitude of the difference indicates that citizenship is a valuable economic asset and that naturalization leads to opportunities for higher income and achieving other household goals.</p>","image":"638e3155a3c47c530c0a609c","year":"2012","publishDate":"October 05, 2012","type":"insights","title":"U.S. Citizenship as an Economic Asset","author.jobTitle":["Citi Pride Affinity Co-lead"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2012/us-citizenship-as-an-economic-asset","tags":["Perspective Migration"],"month":"10","author.displayName":["Bob Annibale"],"siteId":"citigpa","category":"PERSPECTIVES"},{"summary":"In celebration of Citigroup's 200th Anniversary, we are sharing stories from our rich history here on this blog. The 28th installation below covers how technological advances in the1980s improved banking processes and customer service. <a href=\"https://blog.citigroup.com/2012/09/citi-turns-200-internationalizing-senior-management.shtml\">Read the 27th installment explaining how John Reed helped internationalize senior management, here</a>.","image":"638e30faa3c47c530c0a5f05","month":"10","year":"2012","publishDate":"October 05, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Turns 200: Technological advances point to future","category":"PERSPECTIVES","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2012/citi-turns-200-technological-advances-point-to-future","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"London - The African Development Bank (AfDB) Group, Citi and International Finance Corporation (IFC), a member of the World Bank Group, have agreed to provide a $175 million three-year revolving credit facility covering short-term trades for exporters and importers in Africa. This agreement builds on the success of a previous similar program launched in 2010 to help boost economic growth in the region.","month":"10","year":"2012","publishDate":"October 04, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"AfDB, Citi and IFC Enter New Agreement to Support Trade Finance in Africa","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2012/afdb-citi-and-ifc-enter-new-agreement-to-support-trade-finance-in-africa","tags":["Press Release Migration","Institutional Clients Group"]},{"summary":"Warsaw, Poland - Seventeen Citi employees took part in the 34th Warsaw Marathon in celebration of Citi's 200 year-anniversary as well as to raise money for the Multifunctional Education Institution in Brzezie.","month":"10","year":"2012","publishDate":"October 04, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Poland: Citi Volunteers Run Warsaw Marathon to Raise Money for Children in Brezie","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2012/poland-citi-volunteers-run-warsaw-marathon-to-raise-money-for-children-in-breie","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"Kuala Lumpur - Global brand names Citibank and AirAsia have further strengthened their partnership with the introduction of two new cards for the savvy Malaysian consumer. The AirAsia-Citibank Visa Platinum and AirAsia-Citibank Visa Gold Credit Cards offer exciting new benefits that include AirAsia X Premium Flatbed upgrades, free in-flight meals and free Pick a Seat.","month":"10","year":"2012","publishDate":"October 04, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Malaysia: Enjoy Exciting Benefits with the New AirAsia-Citibank Credit Cards","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2012/malaysia-enjoy-exciting-benefits-with-the-new-airasia-citibank-credit-cards","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"In a new blog post, Women &amp; Co. President and CEO, Linda Descano CFA®, recounts a recent discussion she had with Citi Personal Wealth Management's Jonathan Clements about getting past the pain of an investment loss. One of his suggestions is not to invest money in stocks you plan to spend in the next five years. <a href=\"https://blog.womenandco.com/2012/09/overcoming-financial-fears.html\">Read more about managing financial risk on their blog</a>.","image":"638e3117a3c47c530c0a5f95","month":"10","year":"2012","publishDate":"October 04, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"On the Women & Co. Blog: Overcoming Financial Fears","category":"PERSPECTIVES","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2012/on-the-women-co-blog-overcoming-financial-fears","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"New York and Mountain View, Calif. - Citi and LinkedIn today released results from their first <i>Today's Professional Woman Report</i>, a national survey exploring what women see as their biggest career challenges, their most pressing financial concerns and how they define success. Inspired by insights from members of the <a href=\"http://www.linkedin.com/groups/Connect-Professional-Womens-Network-Powered-4409416?goback=.gmp_4409416\" target=\"blank\"><i>Connect: Professional Women's Network</i></a>, the fast-growing LinkedIn community of more than 60,000 professional women powered by Citi, the survey content also explored the notion of \"having it all\" - and why, according to the survey results, 96 percent of today's professional women think it is something that is attainable.","month":"10","year":"2012","publishDate":"October 03, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Redefining \"Having it All\": New Study from Citi and LinkedIn Explores Professional Women's Top Career and Financial Concerns - and Their New Definition of Success","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2012/redefining-having-it-all-new-study-from-citi-and-linkedin-explores-professional-women-s-top-career-and-financial-concerns-and-their-new-definition-of-success","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"Prague - On October 3, 2012, Citibank Europe plc launched in co-operation with the Liberec Region, the Citi Opuscard cobranded credit card - the first multifunctional credit card of its kind in the Czech Republic. The card combines the advantages of the Citi Life credit card and the regional multifunctional Opuscard, which to date has mainly been used for payments in regional transport.","month":"10","year":"2012","publishDate":"October 03, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Czech Republic and Liberec Region Unveil New Cobranded Citi Opuscard","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2012/citi-cech-republic-and-liberec-region-unveil-new-cobranded-citi-opuscard","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"We are proud to announce that David Brownstein, Citi's Managing Director and Co-Head of Public Finance for Municipal Securities has been named recipient of the <a href=\"https://www.sifma.org/\">Securities Industry and Financial Market's Association</a>'s 2012 Honor Roll Award. The SIFMA award recognizes outstanding service to the municipal securities industry.","image":"638e3157a3c47c530c0a60ab","month":"10","year":"2012","publishDate":"October 03, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"SIFMA Honors David Brownstein with Municipal Division Honor Roll Award","category":"PERSPECTIVES","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2012/sifma-honors-david-brownstein-with-municipal-division-honor-roll-award","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"\"Give a man a fish, and you'll feed him for a day. Teach a man to fish, and you've fed him for a lifetime.\" It's a common quote that we've all heard before, but did Confucius really say it first?","image":"638e30fda3c47c530c0a5f13","year":"2012","publishDate":"October 03, 2012","type":"insights","title":"Meet YEC's Jason Nazar of Docstoc.com on #StartupLab","author.jobTitle":["The Young Entrepreneur Council"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2012/meet-yecs-jason-nazar-of-docstoccom-on-startuplab","tags":["Perspective Migration"],"month":"10","author.displayName":["The Young Entrepreneur Council"],"siteId":"citigpa","category":"PERSPECTIVES"},{"summary":"Philippines - Citi says the Federal Reserve's Quantitative Easing (QE) 3 move has had a powerful impact on the Asian markets so far and expects policymakers to welcome the boost given the region's current growth dynamics.","month":"10","year":"2012","publishDate":"October 02, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Sees More Upbeat Response to QE3 in Asia","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2012/citi-sees-more-upbeat-response-to-qe3-in-asia","tags":["Press Release Migration","Institutional Clients Group"]},{"summary":"Jakarta - Citi Indonesia, the Overseas Private Investment Corporation (OPIC) and Bank Andara announced the closing of a US$18.5 million term loan to fund the growth and strategy of Bank Andara's Microfinance business and to promote the financial inclusion of micro entrepreneurs and small businesses in Indonesia. This loan will be disbursed in two periods within six months. This is also the second one from Citi and OPIC for the microfinance sector in Indonesia and is a part of Citi's and OPIC's joint global initiative to support microfinance lending in emerging markets worldwide.","month":"10","year":"2012","publishDate":"October 02, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi, Opic and Bank Andara Support the Rapid Growth of the Microfinance Sector in Indonesia with $18.5 Million Term Loan Funding","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2012/citi-opic-and-bank-andara-support-the-rapid-growth-of-the-microfinance-sector-in-indonesia-with-185-million-term-loan-funding","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance","Institutional Clients Group"]},{"summary":"Budapest, Hungary - Citibank Hungary's new Premium Personal Loan offers consumers an outstanding opportunity to realize their financial plans requiring funds from HUF 3 million to HUF 6 million. The annual interest rate of the new Citibank Premium Loan is from 17.9 to 19.9 percent subject to status and applies to applications submitted via all channels, including branches, direct sales agents, telephone and online, under contractual terms and conditions.","month":"10","year":"2012","publishDate":"October 02, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citibank Hungary's New Premium Personal Loan is Now Available from a 17.9 Percent Interest Rate","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2012/citibank-hungary-s-new-premium-personal-loan-is-now-available-from-a-179-percent-interest-rate","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"Citibank Taiwan held a grand opening ceremony October 2 to launch its sixth Citigold Private Client (CPC) center in Taiwan and retrofitted Taoyuan Branch. During the ceremony, the bank also announced that it will offer a series of promotional events for its branch clients, OBU (offshore banking unit) customers, and credit card holders to celebrate Citi's 200th anniversary.","month":"10","year":"2012","publishDate":"October 02, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citibank Taiwan Upgrades Taoyuan Branch to Include Smart Banking and Citigold Priva