Most Powerful Women in Banking list highlights 25 of the most powerful women in banking, 25 women to watch and the 25 most powerful women in finance.","month":"10","year":"2012","publishDate":"October 01, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"American Banker Names Eight Citi Executives to Most Powerful Women in Banking List","category":"PERSPECTIVES","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2012/american-banker-names-eight-citi-executives-to-most-powerful-women-in-banking-list","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"month":"10","author.displayName":["Jonathan Clements"],"year":"2012","publishDate":"October 01, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Worried About Your Job? Know Your Fixed Costs","category":"PERSPECTIVES","author.jobTitle":["Director of Financial Education, Citi Personal Wealth Management"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2012/worried-about-your-job-know-your-fixed-costs","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"New York - Mayor Michael R. Bloomberg, Schools Chancellor Dennis M. Walcott, New York Public Library President Tony Marx, Brooklyn Public Library President and CEO Linda E. Johnson, Queens Library President and CEO Thomas W. Galante and Citi Chief Executive Officer Vikram Pandit today announced the expansion of <i>MyLibraryNYC</i>, an initiative that connects New York City public schools with the millions of books and other learning materials available through the public libraries. <i>MyLibraryNYC</i> supplements the materials available in public school libraries and will provide access to the more than 17 million books and other items that are a part of the New York, Brooklyn and Queens Public Library catalogs to up to 250,000 students in 400 public schools this year and 1.1 million students by 2015. The program is made possible with $5 million in funding from Citi. The Mayor, Chancellor, public library leaders, and Mr. Pandit made the announcement at the 50th Street School Campus in Manhattan, which houses five high schools, and were joined by School Librarian Adelena Kavanagh and students.","month":"09","year":"2012","publishDate":"September 28, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Mayor Bloomberg, Chancellor Walcott, Public Libraries and Citi Announce Expansion of MyLibraryNYC Initiative to Connect Schools Citywide to Millions of Books and Other Learning Materials","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2012/mayor-bloomberg-chancellor-walcott-public-libraries-and-citi-announce-expansion-of-mylibrarynyc-initiative-to-connect-schools-citywide-to-millions-of-books-and-other-learning-materials","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"month":"09","author.displayName":["Don Burback"],"year":"2012","publishDate":"September 28, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Empowering low-income individuals to become long-term savers","category":"PERSPECTIVES","author.jobTitle":["Global Director, Citi Community Development and Microfinance"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2012/empowering-low-income-individuals-to-become-long-term-savers","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"<a href=\"https://nypl.org/\">The New York Public Library</a>, together with the library systems of Brooklyn and Queens, is happy to announce the expansion of MyLibraryNYC, a groundbreaking program that brings together the public schools and public libraries throughout New York City, which is made possible by funding from Citi and the <a href=\"https://schools.nyc.gov/\">New York City Department of Education</a>.","image":"638e315fa3c47c530c0a60d0","year":"2012","publishDate":"September 28, 2012","type":"insights","title":"NYC Public Libraries and Citi Announce Expansion of MyLibraryNYC Initiative","author.jobTitle":["Global Director, Citi Community Development and Microfinance"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2012/nyc-public-libraries-and-citi-announce-expansion-of-mylibrarynyc-initiative","tags":["Perspective Migration"],"month":"09","author.displayName":["Tony Marx"],"siteId":"citigpa","category":"PERSPECTIVES"},{"summary":"<br>On Aug. 21, we announced the issuance of Citi's sole-branded credit card in China, becoming the first global bank in China to do so. Citi is the largest credit card issuer in the world and we expect China to be the world's largest credit card market by the end of the decade. We were the first foreign bank to enter the retail banking market in China in 2002, and Citi is deeply committed to China. With the Citi credit card, we are now in a better position to provide our customers in China a full suite of products and services to meet their spending needs and help with their financial planning. <br><br>","image":"638e3160a3c47c530c0a60d9","year":"2012","publishDate":"September 28, 2012","type":"insights","title":"Citi Unveils Sole-Branded Credit Cards in China","author.jobTitle":["Chairman and CEO, Citi China"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2012/citi-unveils-sole-branded-credit-cards-in-china","tags":["Perspective Migration"],"month":"09","author.displayName":["Andrew Au"],"siteId":"citigpa","category":"PERSPECTIVES"},{"summary":"Lima - Citibank Peru, the leader in the Peruvian financial system with an uninterrupted presence of 92 years in the country, is consolidating its corporate payment solutions through the introduction of corporate credit cards in partnership with Visa Inc.","month":"09","year":"2012","publishDate":"September 27, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Peru: Citibank Launches Corporate Payment Solution","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2012/peru-citibank-launches-corporate-payment-solution","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"New York - John Gerspach, Chief Financial Officer, and Eric Aboaf, Treasurer, will conduct the Citigroup third quarter 2012 Fixed Income Investor Review at 10 a.m. (EDT) on Wednesday, October 24, 2012. The review will be available live via webcast and teleconference.","month":"09","year":"2012","publishDate":"September 27, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Third Quarter 2012 Fixed Income Investor Review","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2012/citi-third-quarter-2012-fixed-income-investor-review","tags":["Press Release Migration","Citi-Wide"]},{"summary":"New York - Today the Financial Times and Citi announced the finalists for the inaugural FT/Citi Ingenuity Awards: Urban Ideas in Action program, sponsored by Citi. The awards aim to recognize leaders, teams, organizations and community groups that have developed innovative solutions to urban challenges that benefit cities, citizens and urban communities in the fields of education, energy, healthcare and infrastructure.","month":"09","year":"2012","publishDate":"September 27, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Financial Times and Citi Announce Finalists for 2012 FT/Citi Ingenuity Awards","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2012/financial-times-and-citi-announce-finalists-for-2012-ftciti-ingenuity-awards","tags":["Press Release Migration","Citi-Wide"]},{"summary":"NGO","image":"638e942caa239337929deb5c","year":"2012","publishDate":"September 27, 2012","type":"insights","title":"Citi Helps Launch Better Than Cash Alliance, Accelerating Transition to E-payments","author.jobTitle":["Citi Pride Affinity Co-lead"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2012/citi-helps-launch-better-than-cash-alliance-accelerating-transition-to-e-payments","tags":["Perspective Migration"],"month":"09","author.displayName":["Bob Annibale"],"siteId":"citigpa","category":"PERSPECTIVES"},{"summary":"More than half of the world's population now lives in urban areas, and 180,000 people move into cities every day. As urbanization accelerates, cities are under increasing pressure to provide their citizens with essential resources, services and a meaningful quality of life. <br><br>To recognize those fueling growth and economic progress in cities around the world, Citi partnered with the Financial Times to launch the FT/Citi Ingenuity Awards: Urban Ideas in Action program. <br><br><a href=\"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2012/financial-times-and-citi-announce-finalists-for-2012-ftciti-ingenuity-awards\">Today, we are pleased to join with the FT to announce the finalists.</a> Submissions were received from more than 40 countries in four categories - infrastructure, energy, healthcare, and education. Finalists were chosen in each category. A global winner and category winners will be announced at an awards dinner in New York City in December. <br><br><strong><u>Education: <br></u></strong><br><strong>Abhyas Trust - Power of Seeing, India:</strong> Engaging schoolchildren with their urban environment using an innovative curriculum that inspires them to improve their city <br><br><strong>Aprendo Contigo, Peru:</strong> Offering schooling in Peru's largest pediatric hospital to provide education and distraction to hospitalized children","image":"638e3164a3c47c530c0a60e9","month":"09","year":"2012","publishDate":"September 27, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Ingenuity Awards: The Finalists","category":"PERSPECTIVES","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2012/citi-ingenuity-awards-the-finalists","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"Seoul - Citibank Korea announced the introduction of wheelchair-friendly ATMs in accordance with national standards. Supplied by Chungho ComNet, the ATMs will first be installed and operated in three Citibank branches.","month":"09","year":"2012","publishDate":"September 26, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citibank Korea Introduces Wheelchair-Friendly ATMs","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2012/citibank-korea-introduces-wheelchair-friendly-atms","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"Education is the key to enabling the next generation of progress-makers. At Citi, we have <a href=\"https://blog.citigroup.com/tagsearch?tag=Education\">a long history of supporting education in the U.S.</a>, from financial literacy and college savings programs to financing the construction of schools themselves. <br><br>Yesterday marked the end of the <a href=\"https://www.educationnation.com/index.cfm?objectid=6EC639D0-01D6-11E2-897D000C296BA163\">2012 Citi Innovation Challenge</a>, an initiative sponsored by Citi, NBC News, and NewSchools Venture Fund which set out to shine a spotlight on the role that education innovation can play in creating solutions and improving education. I was proud to present the winning check to <a href=\"https://noredink.com/\">NoRedInk</a>, a web-based learning platform that helps students improve their grammar/writing skills by creating content from their favorite celebrities, friends, and personal interests. <br><br>Watch this clip from this morning's TODAY Show to see the announcement of the winners and the check presentation:","image":"638e3165a3c47c530c0a60f0","year":"2012","publishDate":"September 26, 2012","type":"insights","title":"NoRedInk Named Winners of 2012 Citi Innovation Challenge","author.jobTitle":["Executive Vice President | Enterprise Services and Public Affairs"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2012/noredink-named-winners-of-2012-citi-innovation-challenge","tags":["Perspective Migration"],"month":"09","author.displayName":["Ed Skyler"],"siteId":"citigpa","category":"PERSPECTIVES"},{"summary":"Some companies start with a problem.","image":"638e30fda3c47c530c0a5f13","year":"2012","publishDate":"September 26, 2012","type":"insights","title":"Meet YEC's Shane Snow of Contently on #StartupLab","author.jobTitle":["The Young Entrepreneur Council"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2012/meet-yecs-shane-snow-of-contently-on-startuplab","tags":["Perspective Migration"],"month":"09","author.displayName":["The Young Entrepreneur Council"],"siteId":"citigpa","category":"PERSPECTIVES"},{"summary":"Kuwait City - Citi Transactions Services (CTS), a division of Citi, recently held a trade roundtable in Kuwait, featuring key financial institutions as well as top corporates. The event was an opportunity to discuss the latest macroeconomic developments in the region as well as emerging trends in global trade and their direct and indirect effects on Kuwait's economy.","month":"09","year":"2012","publishDate":"September 25, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Kuwait Holds Trade Roundtable for Corporates and Financial Institutions","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2012/citi-kuwait-holds-trade-roundtable-for-corporates-and-financial-institutions","tags":["Press Release Migration","Institutional Clients Group"]},{"summary":"London - The South African Government Bond Index is now included in the Citi World Government Bond Index (WGBI). It becomes the first African government bond market to be incorporated within Citi's influential WGBI.","month":"09","year":"2012","publishDate":"September 25, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"South Africa Joins the Citi World Government Bond Index","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2012/south-africa-joins-the-citi-world-government-bond-index","tags":["Press Release Migration","Institutional Clients Group"]},{"summary":"I recently had the opportunity to join a coalition of committed public, private and nonprofit sector leaders at the <a href=\"https://nchv.org/index.php/news/headline_article/2012_veteran_access_to_housing_summit/\">2012 Veteran Access to Housing Summit</a>, where we shared ideas about how to end veteran homelessness. Hosted by the <a href=\"https://www.nchv.org/\">National Coalition for Homeless Veterans</a> (NCHV), this gathering was supported by Citi as a joint effort of our <a href=\"https://blog.citigroup.com/tagsearch?tag=Citi%20salutes\">Citi Salutes</a> initiative and <a href=\"https://www.citicommunitydevelopment.com/\">Citi Community Development</a>.","month":"09","author.displayName":["Natalie Abatemarco"],"year":"2012","publishDate":"September 25, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Toward sustainable housing solutions for America's homeless veterans","category":"PERSPECTIVES","author.jobTitle":["Managing Director, Citi Community Development"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2012/toward-sustainable-housing-solutions-for-americas-homeless-veterans","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"New York - The Migration Policy Institute today honored Citi with the 2012 <i>E Pluribus Unum Prizes'</i> Corporate Leadership Award for its work to help remove financial barriers to naturalization for eligible United States immigrants and economically empower underserved individuals and communities. The presentation was made at the National Immigrant Integration Conference in Baltimore, Maryland.","month":"09","year":"2012","publishDate":"September 24, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Earns National Award for its Work Removing Financial Barriers to Naturalization and Expanding Financial Inclusion for New Americans","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2012/citi-earns-national-award-for-its-work-removing-financial-barriers-to-naturaliation-and-expanding-financial-inclusion-for-new-americans","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"Our public education system is facing incredibly difficult times with severe budget cuts, labor disputes, and a persistent achievement gap. Yet, I'm encouraged by the spirit of American ingenuity always seeking out new solutions to our problems. Since our nation's founding the impulse to create, build, and solve our way through obstacles has remained constant. The education technology sector is a great example - it's booming with ideas to help us find ways to better support our students and this year's Innovation Challenge gives us a small snapshot. ","image":"638e316aa3c47c530c0a6103","year":"2012","publishDate":"September 24, 2012","type":"insights","title":"Innovation and Entrepreneurship in Education","author.jobTitle":["NewSchools Venture Fund"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2012/innovation-and-entrepreneurship-in-education","tags":["Perspective Migration"],"month":"09","author.displayName":["Jen Carolan"],"siteId":"citigpa","category":"PERSPECTIVES"},{"summary":"After a punishing decline, the real-estate market is showing signs of stabilizing. In 2012's second quarter, home prices were 1.2% higher than a year earlier, according to S&P/Case-Shiller's national composite home-price index.","month":"09","author.displayName":["Jonathan Clements"],"year":"2012","publishDate":"September 24, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Your Home: How Long Should You Stay?","category":"PERSPECTIVES","author.jobTitle":["Director of Financial Education, Citi Personal Wealth Management"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2012/your-home-how-long-should-you-stay","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"Warsaw, Poland - The results of this year's <i>Newsweek</i> \"Friendly Bank\" and <i>Forbes'</i> \"Best Banks for Small and Medium Enterprises\" were announced yesterday evening at the Bank Congress in Warsaw. Citi Handlowy took a higher position compared to last year and climbed the podium in the <i>Newsweek's</i> \"Friendly Bank for Traditional Customers\" category. The third place and three stars were also won by Citi Handlowy in <i>Forbes'</i> \"Best Banks for Small and Medium Enterprises.\"","month":"09","year":"2012","publishDate":"September 21, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Handlowy Named Newsweek's \"Friendly Bank\"","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2012/citi-handlowy-named-newsweek-s-friendly-bank","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"<a href=\"https://ventures.citi.com/\">Citi Ventures</a> collaborates with internal and external partners on new ventures that have the potential to help Citi clients succeed, to generate new value for Citi and to transform the banking industry. <a href=\"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2012/citi-ventures-makes-strategic-investment-in-square\">We are proud to announce a strategic investment in Square</a>, a payments innovator.","month":"09","author.displayName":["Chris Kay"],"year":"2012","publishDate":"September 21, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Ventures Invests in Mobile Payment Technology Square","category":"PRESS RELEASE","author.jobTitle":["Global Director, Citi Microfinance and Community Development"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2012/citi-ventures-invests-in-mobile-payment-technology-square"},{"image":"638e3170a3c47c530c0a611e","month":"09","author.displayName":["John Havens"],"year":"2012","publishDate":"September 21, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Accepts 2012 Secretary of Defense Employer Support Freedom Award","category":"PERSPECTIVES","author.jobTitle":["President & Chief Operating Officer, Citi"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2012/citi-accepts-2012-secretary-of-defense-employer-support-freedom-award","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"In celebration of Citigroup's 200th Anniversary, we are sharing stories from our rich history here on this blog. The 27th installation below covers how John Reed helped internationalize senior management. <a href=\"https://blog.citigroup.com/2012/09/citi-turns-200-cards-revolutionize-banking.shtml\">Read the 26th installment explaining how the credit card business revolutionized banking, here</a>.","image":"638e30faa3c47c530c0a5f05","month":"09","year":"2012","publishDate":"September 21, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Turns 200: Internationalizing Senior Management","category":"PERSPECTIVES","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2012/citi-turns-200-internationalizing-senior-management","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"New York - Maintaining and increasing sales is the most important short-term business issue for 74 percent of small business owners, 41 percent of whom cite lackluster consumer spending as the root cause, according to the Citibank® Small Business Pulse released today.","month":"09","year":"2012","publishDate":"September 20, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"U.S.: New Citibank Small Business Pulse Finds Sales Growth Isn't Enough to Keep Cash Flowing","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2012/us-new-citibank-small-business-pulse-finds-sales-growth-isn-t-enough-to-keep-cash-flowing","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"The <em><a href=\"https://ftcitiawards.com/\">FT/Citi Ingenuity Awards</a></em> recognizes ingenious individuals or organizations that have developed solutions to urban challenges. Yesterday, we hosted the FT/Citi Ingenuity Awards Education Forum in London. \"This Forum has highlighted critical trends, challenges and opportunities facing educators in cities across the world - the sharing of global best practices and ideas will help us all achieve better outcomes for young people,\" said Mark Cheng, UK Director for Ashoka and one of the Forum's panelists.","image":"638e3172a3c47c530c0a612b","month":"09","year":"2012","publishDate":"September 20, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"FT/Citi Ingenuity Awards Education Forum: Urban Ideas In Action","category":"PERSPECTIVES","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2012/ftciti-ingenuity-awards-education-forum-urban-ideas-in-action","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"Gorno-Altaisk, Moscow - Citi Foundation and the WWF summed up the results of their joint program \"Development of Eco-Tourism in the Altai Mountains and Western Tuva.\" The program aimed to provide the local population with training on the basics of entrepreneurship and provide microloans for the development of businesses with a strong nature preservation component (ecotourism in the habitat of the argali mountain sheep and snow leopard, production of souvenirs and products made of felt, improvement of livestock quality, etc.).","month":"09","year":"2012","publishDate":"September 19, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Russia: Citi and WWF Help Develop Eco-Tourism in the Altai Republic","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/foundation/news/press-release/2012/russia-citi-and-wwf-help-develop-eco-tourism-in-the-altai-republic","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"London - Rapid population growth in cities across the world is putting a strain on urban education infrastructure. While technological advancements and increased interconnectivity are breaking down geographic and economic barriers to education, these improvements are being outpaced by current urbanization rates. As a result, current education systems must innovate to meet the learning needs and provide the necessary skills for citizens to succeed in an increasingly competitive environment.","month":"09","year":"2012","publishDate":"September 19, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Education Experts Call for Renewed Focus on Leadership and Skills Training to Prepare Youth for Employment in an Increasingly Competitive Workforce","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2012/education-experts-call-for-renewed-focus-on-leadership-and-skills-training-to-prepare-youth-for-employment-in-an-increasingly-competitive-workforce","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"New York - As part of Citibank's efforts to simplify the banking experience for customers, the bank announced today a new paperless solution: electronic ATM receipts delivered to a designated personal email account.","month":"09","year":"2012","publishDate":"September 19, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"U.S.: Citibank Launches Electronic ATM Receipts","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2012/us-citibank-launches-electronic-atm-receipts","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"Shanghai, China - Citibank (China) Co., Ltd. (\"Citi China\") today unveiled the features of its sole-branded credit card in China. On Aug. 21, Citi announced the issuance of its sole-branded credit card in China, making it the first global bank in China to do so. Stephen Bird, Asia Pacific Chief Executive Officer, Jonathan Larsen, Global Head of Retail Banking and Asia Pacific Head of Consumer Banking, Andrew Au, Chairman and Chief Executive Officer of Citi China, and Simon Chow, Head of Consumer Bank of Citi China, attended the press conference to introduce the full set of the Citi sole-branded credit cards.","month":"09","year":"2012","publishDate":"September 19, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Unveils Its Sole-branded Credit Cards in China","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2012/citi-unveils-its-sole-branded-credit-cards-in-china","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"Since its introduction in 1975, the earned-income tax credit (EITC) has been one of our nation's most effective anti-poverty policies. A new article we co-authored in the Fall 2012 issue of Democracy: A Journal of Ideas entitled \"Tax Policy: Spreading the Benefits More Widely,\" explores how this powerful anti-poverty program can do even more. We argue that linking the Earned Income Tax Credit with long-term savings opportunities can expand financial security among low-income people.","image":"638e3176a3c47c530c0a613a","year":"2012","publishDate":"September 19, 2012","type":"insights","title":"Tax Time Savings Strategies: Exploring the Earned Income Tax Credit and More","author.jobTitle":["Citi Pride Affinity Co-lead","President and CEO of The Leadership Conference"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2012/tax-time-savings-strategies-exploring-the-earned-income-tax-credit-and-more","tags":["Perspective Migration"],"month":"09","author.displayName":["Bob Annibale","Wade Henderson"],"siteId":"citigpa","category":"PERSPECTIVES"},{"summary":"New York - NBC News, Citi and NewSchools Venture Fund announced today that they are launching the second-annual \"Citi Innovation Challenge\" at NBC News' \"Education Nation\" Summit in hopes of helping the country understand the game-changing impact of education innovation in expanding opportunities for students.","month":"09","year":"2012","publishDate":"September 18, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"U.S.: NBC News, Citi and NewSchools Venture Fund to Launch Second Annual \"Citi Innovation Challenge\" at \"Education Nation\"","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2012/us-nbc-news-citi-and-newschools-venture-fund-to-launch-second-annual-citi-innovation-challenge-at-education-nation","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"Prague, Czech Republic - Citibank Europe plc launched the Citi BILLA cobranded contactless credit card on the Czech market on S