-release/2012/morgan-stanley-and-citigroup-reach-agreement-for-full-purchase-of-mssb-and-related-deposits-by-june-2015-at-a-135-billion-valuation-subject-to-regulatory-approval","tags":["Press Release Migration","Citi-Wide"]},{"summary":"New York - Citigroup will issue its third quarter results via press release at approximately 8 a.m. (ET) on Monday, October 15, 2012. At 11 a.m. (ET), results will be reviewed via live webcast and teleconference.","month":"09","year":"2012","publishDate":"September 11, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Third Quarter 2012 Earnings Review","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2012/citi-third-quarter-2012-earnings-review","tags":["Press Release Migration","Citi-Wide"]},{"summary":"Each year, two blue beams of light shine into the sky in place of the Twin Towers. Citi is proud to sponsor the \"Tribute in Light\" in remembrance of all those who were lost on September 11th. The lights are located at West and Morris streets in lower Manhattan and will be on beginning at sunset on September 11, 2012 and fading away at dawn on September 12th.","image":"638e318da3c47c530c0a6199","year":"2012","publishDate":"September 11, 2012","type":"insights","title":"Citi Remembers September 11th with the \"Tribute in Light\"","author.jobTitle":["Executive Vice President | Enterprise Services and Public Affairs"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2012/citi-remembers-september-11th-with-the-tribute-in-light","tags":["Perspective Migration"],"month":"09","author.displayName":["Ed Skyler"],"siteId":"citigpa","category":"PERSPECTIVES"},{"summary":"During his recent trip to Asia Pacific, Citi CEO Vikram Pandit appeared on Australia's \"Inside Business\" to discuss issues that included responsible finance, getting back to banking basics, the Eurozone and serving clients. <a href=\"https://www.abc.net.au/insidebusiness/content/2011/s3576095.htm\">Watch the interview in full, here</a>.","image":"638e318fa3c47c530c0a61a0","month":"09","year":"2012","publishDate":"September 11, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi CEO Pandit Discusses Banking Basics, Eurozone and More","category":"PERSPECTIVES","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2012/citi-ceo-pandit-discusses-banking-basics-eurozone-and-more","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"If you have a spouse or children who depend on you financially, you likely need life insurance. But how much? One rule of thumb says your coverage should be equal to five to seven times your annual salary. That means that, if you're earning $75,000 a year, you might buy a $375,000 to $525,000 policy. There's also a slew of online calculators that can help you tackle the question, but the answers offered can differ widely. Indeed, either method - a multiple of your salary or an online calculator - may leave you buying much more or less coverage than you really need.","month":"09","author.displayName":["Jonathan Clements"],"year":"2012","publishDate":"September 10, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Life Insurance: How Much is Enough?","category":"PERSPECTIVES","author.jobTitle":["Director of Financial Education, Citi Personal Wealth Management"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2012/life-insurance-how-much-is-enough","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"New York - Have you wondered what it would be like to cook alongside a celebrity chef or hear your favorite music live from VIP seats? Citi® Private Pass®, an entertainment access program, offers access to thousands of events each year including presales, preferred seating and VIP experiences. Citi® credit or debit card customers can purchase tickets through <a href=\"http://www.citiprivatepass.com\" target=\"blank\">www.citiprivatepass.com</a>, and some events are complimentary. The experiences offered across sports, dining and music are illustrated in the new Citi advertising campaign, \"MORE\" and broadcast commercial, \"The Ex.\"","month":"09","year":"2012","publishDate":"September 07, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi® Campaign Brings to Life More Music, Sports and Dining for Credit and Debit Card Customers","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2012/citi-campaign-brings-to-life-more-music-sports-and-dining-for-credit-and-debit-card-customers","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"<a href=\"https://blog.citigroup.com/2011/03/citi-is-proud-sponsor-of-2012-us-olympic-and-paralympic-teams.shtml\">Citi is proud to sponsor the 2012 U.S. Olympic and Paralympic teams</a>. Last week, Citi Chairman Michael O'Neill attended the Opening Ceremony to cheer on Team Citi athletes Kari Miller and Amanda McGrory as well as the U.S. Olympic Committee's \"Celebrate Heroes\" reception in London to celebrate the history and heroes of the Paralympic movement.","image":"638e3191a3c47c530c0a61ab","month":"09","year":"2012","publishDate":"September 07, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Celebrates the U.S. Paralympic Movement","category":"PERSPECTIVES","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2012/citi-celebrates-the-us-paralympic-movement","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"How can robust ethical standards and integrity be boosted in the finance sector?","image":"638e3192a3c47c530c0a61b2","year":"2012","publishDate":"September 07, 2012","type":"insights","title":"Announcing the Ethics in Finance Robin Cosgrove Prize 2012-2013","author.jobTitle":["Director, Ethics in Finance Robin Cosgrove Prize"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2012/announcing-the-ethics-in-finance-robin-cosgrove-prize-2012-2013","tags":["Perspective Migration"],"month":"09","author.displayName":["Carol Cosgrove-Sacks"],"siteId":"citigpa","category":"PERSPECTIVES"},{"summary":"In celebration of Citigroup's 200th Anniversary, we are sharing stories from our rich history here on this blog. The 25th installation below covers how business focus shifted to retail banking and how the ATM impacted the consumer experience. Read the 24th installment on how National City Bank nurtured a client relationship to last over a century, here.","image":"638e30faa3c47c530c0a5f05","month":"09","year":"2012","publishDate":"September 07, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Turns 200: Focus shifts to retail banking","category":"PERSPECTIVES","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2012/citi-turns-200-focus-shifts-to-retail-banking","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"São Paulo - Citi's Microentrepreneurship Award celebrates its eighth edition this year. Funded by the Citi Foundation in 28 countries, the award honors entrepreneurs who employ microfinance resources to boost their businesses, either through startups or by improving products and services, and contribute to economic and social development within their communities. Microfinance institutions can nominate their clients online at <a href=\"http://www.pcmm.com.br\" target=\"blank\">www.pcmm.com.br</a> between September 10 and October 10, 2012. Loan officers will play a fundamental role in the process through their visits to businesses and close work with clients.","month":"09","year":"2012","publishDate":"September 06, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Brazil: Citi Microentrepreneurship Awards Highlight Top Entrepreneurs Funded by Microfinance","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/foundation/news/press-release/2012/brail-citi-microentrepreneurship-awards-highlight-top-entrepreneurs-funded-by-microfinance","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"Citi Asia Pacific hauled a record of 26 awards in this year's Global Finance magazine's annual World's Best Internet Banks across the corporate/institutional and consumer banks categories. In the best corporate/institutional internet category, Citi won in 15 out of 16 Asian markets. Citi was recognized for Best Trade Finance Services, Best in Mobile Banking and Best Web Site Design in Asia Pacific. Of the 14 consumer markets in the region, Citi won in seven for Best Consumer Internet Bank in Australia, Guam, Indonesia, India, Philippines, South Korea and Thailand. Citi was also lauded for Best Information Security in Asia Pacific. <br><br>It is our pleasant privilege that our efforts to provide our customers with seamless user experience and innovative services have been recognized by our peers and the market. The team has worked hard to introduce innovative features such as mobile and tablet-based location services, real-time click to chat, electronic delivery of statements/advices and global view of accounts. We will continuously strive to raise the bar with more innovations in the Internet and Mobile space to serve our customers better.","image":"638e3195a3c47c530c0a61bd","year":"2012","publishDate":"September 06, 2012","type":"insights","title":"Citi wins 26 Global Finance Awards for \"Best Internet Banks in Asia\"","author.jobTitle":["APAC Regional Head of eBusiness & Global Mobile Head"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2012/citi-wins-26-global-finance-awards-for-best-internet-banks-in-asia","tags":["Perspective Migration"],"month":"09","author.displayName":["Rajesh Yohannan"],"siteId":"citigpa","category":"PERSPECTIVES"},{"summary":"Dubai - Citi Transaction Services (CTS), a Division of Citi, today signed a comprehensive Memorandum of Understanding (MoU) with the Department of Economic Development (DED) - Government of Dubai - designed to boost Dubai's attractiveness as an investment destination and a trade hub for multinational corporations, as well as promote a more conducive environment for the establishment of small and medium-sized enterprises (SMEs) in the country.","month":"09","year":"2012","publishDate":"September 05, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi and DED Sign Comprehensive Memorandum of Understanding for Joint Promotion of Dubai as Trade and Investment Destination","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2012/citi-and-ded-sign-comprehensive-memorandum-of-understanding-for-joint-promotion-of-dubai-as-trade-and-investment-destination","tags":["Press Release Migration","Institutional Clients Group"]},{"summary":"Recently, several colleagues and I were honored to sit onstage at Naval Station Mayport near Jacksonville, Florida, with First Lady Michelle Obama as she announced that, through the <a href=\"https://www.whitehouse.gov/joiningforces/\">Joining Forces</a> initiative, 125,000 veterans and military spouses have been hired or trained by participating private sector employers since the initiative's launch in April 2011. The milestone received widespread national media attention, and is highlighted in a <a href=\"https://www.whitehouse.gov/blog/2012/08/24/announcing-125000-hires-through-joining-forces\">White House blog post</a> that includes a video featuring interviews with Citi military veteran employees Barrett Scruggs and Nicole Alcalde. These new colleagues are among the first participants in Citi's Junior Military Officer Leadership Program, a pilot program that is one of the many ways we are fulfilling our ongoing hiring commitment as a founding partner in Joining Forces.","month":"09","author.displayName":["John Tien"],"year":"2012","publishDate":"September 05, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Joining Forces: Citi Celebrates Veterans Hiring Milestone with First Lady Michelle Obama","category":"PERSPECTIVES","author.jobTitle":["Co-lead of Citi Salutes"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2012/joining-forces-citi-celebrates-veterans-hiring-milestone-with-first-lady-michelle-obama","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"Prague, Czech Republic - Citibank Europe plc has introduced Citi Global Banking, a new service utilizing Citibank's wide international network of branches to facilitate more convenient banking between the Czech Republic and foreign countries for Citi clients.","month":"09","year":"2012","publishDate":"September 04, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Czech Republic Launches New Service Citi Global Banking","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2012/citi-cech-republic-launches-new-service-citi-global-banking","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"Let's face it, it's a nice problem to have: Your income is so high that you don't qualify to make regular annual contributions to a Roth Individual Retirement Account. In 2012, you can't fully fund a Roth if you're single and your modified adjusted gross income is more than $110,000, while the threshold for married couples filing jointly is $173,000. Your ability to contribute phases out above these income limits.","month":"09","author.displayName":["Jonathan Clements"],"year":"2012","publishDate":"September 04, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Roth IRAs -- Via the Backdoor","category":"PERSPECTIVES","author.jobTitle":["Director of Financial Education, Citi Personal Wealth Management"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2012/roth-iras----via-the-backdoor","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"Kingston, Jamaica - The <a href=\"http://www.citifoundation.com/\">Citi Foundation</a>, the <a href=\"http://www.caribbeanmicrofinancealliance.com/\" target=\"blank\">Caribbean Microfinance Alliance</a> and the <a href=\"http://www.iadb.org/mif\" target=\"blank\">Multilateral Investment Fund (MIF)</a> are pleased to announce the winners for the inaugural <a href=\"http://events.iadb.org/calendar/eventDetail.aspx?lang=en&id=3377&OID=452\" target=\"blank\">Citi Micro-entrepreneurship Awards for the Caribbean</a>. The Awards recognize a microfinance institution and a micro-entrepreneur that have each demonstrated remarkable success in the English-speaking Caribbean. Five finalists were chosen for each award, and a jury of six experts on microfinance and micro-entrepreneurship in the region has selected the winners.","month":"09","year":"2012","publishDate":"September 03, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Winners Announced for the Citi Micro-Entrepreneurship Awards for the Caribbean","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/foundation/news/press-release/2012/winners-announced-for-the-citi-micro-entrepreneurship-awards-for-the-caribbean","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"Shanghai, China - Citi has been named by <i>FinanceAsia</i> magazine as the \"Best Foreign Commercial Bank in China\" in 2012.","month":"09","year":"2012","publishDate":"September 03, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Named Best Foreign Commercial Bank in China","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2012/citi-named-best-foreign-commercial-bank-in-china","tags":["Press Release Migration","Institutional Clients Group"]},{"summary":"Budapest, Hungary - On August 29, NESsT and Citibank announced the winners of the 2011/2012 NESsT-Citibank For-Profit Social Enterprise Development Program, which supports the development of for-profit social enterprises in Hungary. Anna Horvath, NESsT Enterprise Development Manager in Hungary, and Batara Sianturi, Citi Country Officer for Hungary, presented the awards to the winners at the ceremony.","month":"09","year":"2012","publishDate":"September 03, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Hungary and NESsT Announce Winners of 2012 Social Enterprise Competition","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/foundation/news/press-release/2012/citi-hungary-and-nesst-announce-winners-of-2012-social-enterprise-competition","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"New York - Citigroup Inc. (\"<b>Citigroup</b>\") announced today the early tender results of the previously announced cash tender offers (each, an \"<b>Offer</b>\" and, collectively, the \"<b>Offers</b>\") by Citigroup and its wholly-owned subsidiary Associates First Capital Corporation (\"<b>Associates</b>\") with respect to each series of notes listed in the tables below (the \"<b>Notes</b>\").","month":"08","year":"2012","publishDate":"August 31, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citigroup Announces Early Tender Results of Offers to Purchase Seven Series of Outstanding Notes","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2012/citigroup-announces-early-tender-results-of-offers-to-purchase-seven-series-of-outstanding-notes","tags":["Press Release Migration","Citi-Wide"]},{"summary":"New York - Vikram Pandit, Chief Executive Officer of Citi, will present at the Barclays Capital Global Financial Services Conference on Monday, September 10, 2012. The presentation is expected to begin at approximately 2:00 PM (Eastern). A live webcast and presentation materials will be available at <a href=\"https://www.citigroup.com/global/investors\">www.citigroup.com/global/investors</a>. A replay and transcript of the webcast will be available shortly after the event.","month":"08","year":"2012","publishDate":"August 31, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citigroup CEO Vikram Pandit to Present at the Barclays Capital Global Financial Services Conference","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2012/citigroup-ceo-vikram-pandit-to-present-at-the-barclays-capital-global-financial-services-conference","tags":["Press Release Migration","Citi-Wide"]},{"summary":"In celebration of Citigroup's 200th Anniversary, we are sharing stories from our rich history here on this blog. The 24th installation below covers how National City Bank nurtured a client relationship to last over a century. <a href=\"https://blog.citigroup.com/2012/08/citi-turns-200-negotiable-certificates-of-deposit.shtml\">Read the 23rd installment on how National City Bank became the leading bank in the New York metropolitan area and overseas here</a>.","image":"638e30faa3c47c530c0a5f05","month":"08","year":"2012","publishDate":"August 31, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Turns 200: Client relationship lasts over a century","category":"PERSPECTIVES","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2012/citi-turns-200-client-relationship-lasts-over-a-century","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"New York - Citigroup Inc. (\"<b>Citigroup</b>\") and its wholly-owned subsidiary Associates First Capital Corporation (\"<b>Associates</b>\") announced today the applicable Reference Yield and Total Consideration in the previously announced cash tender offers with respect to each series of Notes subject to the Fixed Spread Offers listed in the table below.","month":"08","year":"2012","publishDate":"August 29, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citigroup Inc. Announces the Reference Yields and Total Consideration for Fixed Spread Offers","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2012/citigroup-inc-announces-the-reference-yields-and-total-consideration-for-fixed-spread-offers-2","tags":["Press Release Migration","Citi-Wide"]},{"summary":"New York - Citigroup Inc. today announced it has agreed, subject to court approval, to settle a class action lawsuit brought on behalf of investors who purchased Citigroup common stock during the period February 26, 2007 through April 18, 2008. Under the terms of the proposed settlement, Citi would pay a total of $590 million. Plaintiffs in the class action had contended, among other things, that they were fraudulently misled by misstatements and omissions in the company's disclosures during this period. Citigroup denies the allegations and is entering into this settlement solely to eliminate the uncertainties, burden and expense of further protracted litigation. The amount to be paid under the proposed settlement is covered by Citi's existing litigation reserves.","month":"08","year":"2012","publishDate":"August 29, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Media Statement on Citigroup Common Stock Class Action Suit","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2012/citi-media-statement-on-citigroup-common-stock-class-action-suit","tags":["Press Release Migration","Citi-Wide"]},{"summary":"Budapest, Hungary - Five talented university graduate professionals received the 2012 Andras Felkai Academic Award in an award ceremony in Budapest on August 28, 2012. The awards were presented by Batara Sianturi, Citi Country Officer for Hungary, and Tamas Felkai, representing the Andras Felkai Foundation.","month":"08","year":"2012","publishDate":"August 29, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Presents the 2012 Andras Felkai Academic Awards in Hungary","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2012/citi-presents-the-2012-andras-felkai-academic-awards-in-hungary","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"New York - Citigroup Inc. (\"<b>Citigroup</b>\") announced today its intention to upsize the aggregate principal amount of outstanding Notes to be accepted for purchase pursuant to the previously announced cash tender offers (each, an \"<b>Offer</b>\" and, collectively, the \"<b>Offers</b>\") by Citigroup and its wholly-owned subsidiary Associates First Capital Corporation (\"<b>Associates</b>\") from $675 million to $1.65 billion.","month":"08","year":"2012","publishDate":"August 29, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citigroup Announces Intention to Upsize the Previously Announced Offers to Purchase Seven Series of Outstanding Notes from $675 Million to up to $1.65 Billion","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2012/citigroup-announces-intention-to-upsie-the-previously-announced-offers-to-purchase-seven-series-of-outstanding-notes-from-675-million-to-up-to-165-billion","tags":["Press Release Migration","Citi-Wide"]},{"summary":"Thank you for sharing your comments and questions in response to <a href=\"https://blog.citigroup.com/2012/08/you-spoke-we-listened.shtml\">my recent blog post</a>. I am encouraged by your feedback on our improvements, yet also know that some of your experiences have been less than perfect. And there is more that we can do. I can assure you that we are committed to delivering the products and service that you desire and deserve.","month":"08","author.displayName":["Jud Linville"],"year":"2012","publishDate":"August 29, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Cards Answers Your Questions","category":"PERSPECTIVES","author.jobTitle":["Citi Cards CEO"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2012/citi-cards-answers-your-questions-2","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"New York - Morgan Stanley and Citigroup have agreed to extend the date on which the determination of fair market value of the Morgan Stanley Smith Barney joint venture and the related deposit amount is to be made to September 10, 2012.","month":"08","year":"2012","publishDate":"August 28, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi and Morgan Stanley Agree to Extend JV Appraisal Period","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2012/citi-and-morgan-stanley-agree-to-extend-jv-appraisal-period","tags":["Press Release Migration","Citi-Wide"]},{"summary":"Mumbai - Citi and Parinaam Foundation have come together to make financial literacy training available to more than 31,000 women in 14 states in India. Supported by a Citi Foundation grant of INR 1 crore, Parinaam's Diksha Financial Literacy Program will reach out to microfinance customers in Karnataka, Tamil Nadu, Kerala, Maharashtra, Gujarat, Bengal, Orissa, Jharkhand, Bihar, Assam, Delhi, Rajasthan, Uttar Pradesh and Punjab.","month":"08","year":"2012","publishDate":"August 28, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"India: Citi Facilitates Financial Literacy Training for 31,000 Women","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/foundation/news/press-release/2012/india-citi-facilitates-financial-literacy-training-for-31000-women","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"If you hope to buy a house next spring, it's time to get moving. With prices 33% below their mid-2006 peak, as measured by the S&P/Case-Shiller Home Price Indices, you might be tempted to buy that first house, trade up to a larger place or purchase a vacation property. But buying a home is a major undertaking--and it can take months to get your finances ready. Here are some steps to consider.","month":"08","author.displayName":["Jonathan Clements"],"year":"2012","publishDate":"August 27, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Moves to Make Before You Move","category":"PERSPECTIVES","author.jobTitle":["Director of Financial Education, Citi Personal Wealth Management"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2012/moves-to-make-before-you-move","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"Warsaw, Poland - Slawomir S. Sikora, CEO of Citi Handlowy, earned a spot in a prestigious list of the top 20 most effective managers in this <i>Bloomberg Businessweek Polska's</i> \"TOP 20 Best Managers in Times of Crisis\" awards 2012.","month":"08","year":"2012","publishDate":"August 24, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Poland: Citi Handlowy CEO in Bloomberg Businessweek Polska's Top-20 Best Managers List","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2012/poland-citi-handlowy-ceo-in-bloomberg-businessweek-polska-s-top-20-best-managers-list","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"Houston - CITGO Petroleum Corporation and Citi Retail Services are launching a new private-label consumer credit card that allows CITGO customers to earn five cents-per-gallon credits for fuel purchases at all CITGO locations. Launching Sept. 1, the new CITGO Rewards Card program is one of the most robust rewards offerings in the industry.","month":"08","year":"2012","publishDate":"August 24, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citgo and Citi Retail Services Partner to Launch New Citgo Rewards™ Credit Card","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2012/citgo-and-citi-retail-services-partner-to-launch-new-citgo-rewards-credit-card","tags":["Press Release Migration","Citi-Wide","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"In celebration of Citigroup's 200th Anniversary, we are sharing stories from our rich history here on this blog. The 23rd installation below covers how National City Bank became the leading bank in the New York metropolitan area and overseas. <a href=\"https://blog.citigroup.com/2012/08/citi-turns-200-industrial-promise-on-us-west-coast.shtml\">Read the 22nd installment on how emerging technologies in the electronics and aircraft sectors lead to the establishment of a specialized aerospace division on the west coast, here. </a>","image":"638e30faa3c47c530c0a5f05","month":"08","year":"2012","publishDate":"August 24, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Turns 200: Negotiable Certificates of Deposit","category":"PERSPECTIVES","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2012/citi-turns-200-negotiable-certificates-of-deposit","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"New York - Citigroup Inc. (\"<b>Citigroup</b>\") today announced the extension of the Early Tender Date, the Price Determination Date and the Expiration Date of the previously announced cash tender offers (each, an \"<b>Offer</b>\" and, collectively, the \"<b>Offers</b>\") by Citigroup and its wholly-owned subsidiary Associates First Capital Corporation (\"<b>Associates</b>\").","month":"08","year":"2012","publishDate":"August 23, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citigroup Inc. Announces the Extension of the Early Tender Date, the Price Determination Date and the Expiration Date","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2012/citigroup-inc-announces-the-extension-of-the-early-tender-date-the-price-determination-date-and-the-expiration-date-2","tags":["Press Release Migration","Citi-Wide"]},{"summary":"New York, N.Y - Citi held its final Citi Field Kids event for the 2012 season when the New York Mets hosted the Colorado Rockies at Citi Field. The event featured Gabrielle Douglas, who won the all-around individual women's gold medal in gymnastics at the London 2012 Olympic Games. The 16-year-old Douglas, who was also part of the gold medal-winning U.S. squad that won the team competition, made history by becoming the first American gymnast to win gold in both the individual all-around and team competitions at the same Olympics. Prior to the day's game, she shared her inspiring story of success with kids from the YMCA.","month":"08","year":"2012","publishDate":"August 23, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"London 2012 Olympic Games Gold Medalist Gabrielle Douglas Inspires Kids from the YMCA in Final Citi Field Kids Event of the Season","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2012/london-2012-olympic-games-gold-medalist-gabrielle-douglas-inspires-kids-from-the-ymca-in-final-citi-field-kids-event-of-the-season","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"New York - A nationwide survey issued today by Citi and conducted by Hart Research Associates revealed that Americans are more optimistic about economic conditions than in any quarter since the survey began in September 2009. The Citi Economic Pulse, a quarterly measure of Americans' attitudes toward the economy, remains in negative territory but rose to a new high of -4 in Q3 2012 after hitting its lowest point of -17 in Q3 2011. Unlike 2010 and 2011, when the Pulse advanced in the first quarter only to turn downward again later in the year, attitudes have continued to improve in 2012.","month":"08","year":"2012","publishDate":"August 23, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"New Quarterly Citi Survey Reveals Americans' Economic Outlook Reaches Highest Point Since Study Began in Fall 2009","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2012/new-quarterly-citi-survey-reveals-americans-economic-outlook-reaches-highest-point-since-study-began-in-fall-2009","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"A nationwide survey issued today by Citi and conducted by Hart Research Associates revealed that Americans are more optimistic about economic conditions than in any quarter since the survey began in September 2009. The Citi Economic Pulse, a quarterly measure of Americans' attitudes toward the economy, remains in negative territory but rose to a new high of -4 in Q3 2012 after hitting its lowest point of -17 in Q3 2011. Unlike 2010 and 2011, when the Citi Economic Pulse advanced in the first quarter only to turn downward again later in the year, attitudes have continued to improve in 2012.","image":"638e319ca3c47c530c0a61e1","year":"2012","publishDate":"August 23, 2012","type":"insights","title":"Americans' Economic Outlook on the Rise","author.jobTitle":["Chief Marketing Officer, Citibank"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2012/americans-economic-outlook-on-the-rise","tags":["Perspective Migration"],"month":"08","author.displayName":["Michelle Peluso"],"siteId":"citigpa","category":"PERSPECTIVES"},{"summary":"New York, N.Y. - Citi and the New York Mets Alumni Association Presented by Citi teamed up at Citi Field to honor and thank U.S. veterans, military families and survivors at a luncheon and panel discussion focusing on veterans' issues. Mets personnel and alumni, including Mets General Manager Sandy Alderson and Hall-of-Famer Tom Seaver, participated. The project is part of the Mets and Citi's \"Teammates in the Community\" initiative, reflecting their ongoing commitment to be active participants in the community.","month":"08","year":"2012","publishDate":"August 22, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi and the Mets Alumni Association Presented by Citi Honor and Thank U.S. Veterans, Military Families and Survivors at Citi Field","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2012/citi-and-the-mets-alumni-association-presented-by-citi-honor-and-thank-us-veterans-military-families-and-survivors-at-citi-field","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"Flushing, N.Y. - The New York Mets and Citi held a special YMCA Jr. Mets event at Marconi Park in Jamaica, Queens, featuring Mets stars Ruben Tejada and Justin Turner addressing and instructing kids from the local Jamaica YMCA. The project is part of the Mets and Citi's \"Teammates in the Community\" initiative, reflecting their ongoing commitment to being active participants in the community.","month":"08","year":"2012","publishDate":"August 21, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Mets Stars Ruben Tejada and Justin Turner Headline 'YMCA Jr. Mets Supported By Citi' Program at Marconi Park In Jamaica, Queens","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2012/mets-stars-ruben-tejada-and-justin-turner-headline-ymca-jr-mets-supported-by-citi-program-at-marconi-park-in-jamaica-queens","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"New York - Today the <i>Financial Times</i> announced the panel of judges participating in the FT/Citi Ingenuity Awards: Urban Ideas in Action program, sponsored by Citi. The judges, all leaders in their respective fields, will select the most innovative solutions to urban challenges in the fields of education, healthcare, energy and infrastructure.","month":"08","year":"2012","publishDate":"August 20, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Financial Times Announces Judging Panel for the FT/Citi Ingenuity Awards","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2012/financial-times-announces-judging-panel-for-the-ftciti-ingenuity-awards","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"The government gives--and the government takes away.","month":"08","author.displayName":["Jonathan Clements"],"year":"2012","publishDate":"August 20, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Social Security Benefits: The Taxman Cometh","category":"PERSPECTIVES","author.jobTitle":["Director of Financial Education, Citi Personal Wealth Management"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2012/social-security-benefits-the-taxman-cometh","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"Seoul - Citibank Korea opened its first Citigold Private Client Center on the 12th floor of Gangnam Finance Center August 17, 2012. Senior management from regional and local offices, including Jonathan Larsen, Global Retail Banking Head; YK Ha, Citibank Korea Chief Executive; and Paul Hodes, Asia Pacific Consumer Bank Wealth Management Head, joined Citi employees and clients to celebrate the center's opening.","month":"08","year":"2012","publishDate":"August 17, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citibank Korea Launches Citigold Private Client, a Wealth Management Service for High Net-Worth Individuals (HNWIs)","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2012/citibank-korea-launches-citigold-private-client-a-wealth-management-service-for-high-net-worth-individuals-hnwis","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"<strong>An Update for our Customers</strong>","month":"08","author.displayName":["Jud Linville"],"year":"2012","publishDate":"August 17, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"You Spoke. We Listened.","category":"PERSPECTIVES","author.jobTitle":["Citi Cards CEO"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2012/you-spoke-we-listened-2","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"In celebration of Citigroup's 200th Anniversary, we are sharing stories from our rich history here on this blog. The 22nd installation below covers how emerging technologies in the electronics and aircraft sectors lead to the establishment of a specialized aerospace division. <a href=\"https://blog.citigroup.com/2012/08/citi-turns-200-focus-on-middle-east-and-africa.shtml\">Read the 21st installment on how National City Bank extended its operations beyond Europe and Asia to the Middle East and Africa, here</a>.","image":"638e30faa3c47c530c0a5f05","month":"08","year":"2012","publishDate":"August 17, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Turns 200: Industrial Promise on U.S. West Coast","category":"PERSPECTIVES","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2012/citi-turns-200-industrial-promise-on-us-west-coast","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"Hong Kong - Come visit the \"200 Years Citi Celebration Store\" at ifc mall from now until October 7, 2012, to celebrate Citi's bicentennial anniversary and enjoy a wide range of exclusive offers and activities.","month":"08","year":"2012","publishDate":"August 16, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Hong Kong: Celebrate Citi's 200th Anniversary at ifc mall Citibank's Celebration Store This Summer","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2012/hong-kong-celebrate-citi-s-200th-anniversary-at-ifc-mall-citibank-s-celebration-store-this-summer","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"Hong Kong - Citi Asia Pacific was a big winner in this year's <i>Global Finance</i> magazine's annual World's Best Internet Banks, hauling a total of 26 awards across the corporate/ institutional and consumer banks categories.","month":"08","year":"2012","publishDate":"August 15, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Wins 26 Global Finance Awards as Best Internet Banks in Asia","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2012/citi-wins-26-global-finance-awards-as-best-internet-banks-in-asia","tags":["Press Release Migration","Institutional Clients Group","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"New York - On July 18, 2012, Citigroup Inc. announced the declaration by its Board of Directors of a dividend of $0.01 per share of common stock payable on August 24, 2012, to holders of record on August 6, 2012. Effective on the payment of this dividend, an adjustment will be made to the settlement rates and certain other terms of Citi's T-DECS, as set forth below. No adjustment will be made to the terms of Citi's warrants or convertible preferred stock because the amount of the dividend to be paid is less than the threshold amount required for an adjustment. You should refer to the T-DECS Prospectus dated December 16, 2009, and the related Current Report on Form 8-K filed on December 24, 2009 for the definitions of the terms below and for other relevant provisions of the T-DECS.","month":"08","year":"2012","publishDate":"August 14, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citigroup Inc. Announces T-DECS Adjustments to Result From Common Dividend","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2012/citigroup-inc-announces-t-decs-adjustments-to-result-from-common-dividend-3","tags":["Press Release Migration","Citi-Wide"]},{"summary":"<a href=\"https://www.citigroup.com/rcs/citigpa/storage/public/august%20COTM.png\"></a>It is often worthwhile to gauge market expectations by assessing the long-term average equity risk premium and compare the expected return from stocks versus bonds. This approach allows one to consider very long-term expectations, recognizing that at any point in time investors may demonstrate extreme risk aversion or tolerance. In this context, the investment community has retreated back to its Great Recession anxiety because long-term earnings expectations appear to be matching late 2008/early 2009 lows.","image":"638e31a1a3c47c530c0a61f7","year":"2012","publishDate":"August 14, 2012","type":"insights","title":"Equity Strategy: August 2012 Chart of the Month","author.jobTitle":["Chief US Equity Strategist, Citi"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2012/equity-strategy-august-chart-of-the-month","tags":["Perspective Migration"],"month":"08","author.displayName":["Tobias Levkovich"],"siteId":"citigpa","category":"PERSPECTIVES"},{"summary":"Which is better, a traditional tax-deductible Individual Retirement Account or a Roth IRA? The traditional IRA gives you an immediate tax deduction, but all withdrawals are taxed as ordinary income. With a Roth, there's no upfront tax deduction, but all withdrawals in retirement can be tax-free.","month":"08","author.displayName":["Jonathan Clements"],"year":"2012","publishDate":"August 13, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Tax-Deductible vs. Roth IRAs","category":"PERSPECTIVES","author.jobTitle":["Director of Financial Education, Citi Personal Wealth Management"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2012/tax-deductible-vs-roth-iras","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"In July 2012, customers of Citi Handlowy's mobile banking logged in to the system more than 100,000 times. The latest features such as FotoKasa or Bump to Transfer as well a change in the application interface were key reasons for the success.","month":"08","year":"2012","publishDate":"August 10, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Poland: Citi Mobile Customers Logged in 100,000 Times in July","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2012/poland-citi-mobile-customers-logged-in-100000-times-in-july","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"In celebration of Citigroup's 200th Anniversary, we are sharing stories from our rich history here on this blog. The 21st installation below covers how National City Bank extended its operations beyond Europe and Asia to the Middle East and Africa. <a href=\"https://blog.citigroup.com/2012/08/citi-turns-200-landmarks-in-transportation-finance.shtml\">Read the 20th installment on how innovative thinking within the bank contributed to a revolution in the shipping industry, here</a>.","image":"638e30faa3c47c530c0a5f05","month":"08","year":"2012","publishDate":"August 10, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Turns 200: Focus on Middle East and Africa","category":"PERSPECTIVES","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2012/citi-turns-200-focus-on-middle-east-and-africa","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"New York - Citigroup Inc. (\"<b>Citigroup</b>\") today announced the commencement of offers to purchase for cash certain notes issued by Citigroup Inc. and its wholly-owned subsidiary Associates First Credit Corporation (\"<b>Associates</b>\"), respectively. Citigroup, and with respect to the notes issued by Associates, Citigroup and Associates are offering to purchase notes of the series set forth in the table below (each offer with respect to any series set forth in the table below, an \"<b>Offer</b>\" and, collectively, the \"Offers\"). Each of the Offers is being made on a fixed spread basis (each, a \"<b>Fixed Spread Offer</b>\" and, collectively, the \"<b>Fixed Spread Offers</b>\"), except for the Offer with respect to the Floating Rate Senior Notes due 2014, which is being made on a fixed price basis (the \"<b>Fixed Price Offer</b>\"). The Notes have an aggregate principal amount outstanding of approximately $12,370,120,000 as of August 8, 2012. The Offers are part of a liability management strategy that utilizes excess cash to retire generally older vintage debt.","month":"08","year":"2012","publishDate":"August 09, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citigroup Inc. Announces Offers to Purchase Seven Series of Outstanding Notes","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2012/citigroup-inc-announces-offers-to-purchase-seven-series-of-outstanding-notes-1","tags":["Press Release Migration","Citi-Wide"]},{"summary":"Moscow - According to Citi Russia's annual survey, the volume of Russian spending abroad will increase by 19 percent in 2012 compared to 2011 and will reach 1.5 trillion rubles. Analysts forecast that the share of payments made abroad with Citi client's credit cards will account for 23 percent of the aggregate credit card spend in 2012.* Online spending will reach 46 percent of all credit card transactions abroad. The United States, Britain, Italy and France are again at the top of the list of countries by credit card spending.","month":"08","year":"2012","publishDate":"August 09, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Russia: Russians Will Spend 1.5 Trillion Rubles Abroad in 2012","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2012/citi-russia-russians-will-spend-15-trillion-rubles-abroad-in-2012","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"New York - CitiMortgage today announced the launch of the Home Rental Program, which will be managed by Carrington Capital Management, LLC and Carrington Mortgage Services LLC, a specialist in servicing distressed residential real estate assets. Developed by CitiMortgage and Carrington as a pilot program, the Home Rental Program is designed to provide an alternative to foreclosure and allow eligible borrowers to stay in their homes by entering into a deed-for-lease home agreement and establishing a lease.","month":"08","year":"2012","publishDate":"August 08, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"U.S.: CitiMortgage Announces Launch of Home Rental Program to Keep Distressed Borrowers in Their Homes","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2012/us-citimortgage-announces-launch-of-home-rental-program-to-keep-distressed-borrowers-in-their-homes","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"We are proud to announce that the Citi Foundation is continuing its work on groundbreaking initiatives with public and private sector partners with the start of the MyMoneyAppUp Challenge. Launched by the U.S. Treasury Department in partnership with the Doorways to Dreams Fund (D2D) and the Center for Financial Services Innovation (CFSI), MyMoneyAppUp invites American entrepreneurs, software developers, the public, and students to propose the best ideas and designs for next-generation mobile applications to help Americans control and shape their financial futures. The goal is to solicit more than 150 ideas and designs, from which a group of winners to receive prizes totaling more than $25,000 will be chosen.","image":"638e31a4a3c47c530c0a6209","year":"2012","publishDate":"August 08, 2012","type":"insights","title":"Citi Foundation Promotes Creation of Next-Gen Mobile Apps With MyMoneyAppUp Challenge","author.jobTitle":["CEO and President, the Citi Foundation and Director, Corporate Citizenship","Citi Pride Affinity Co-lead"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2012/citi-foundation-promotes-creation-of-next-gen-mobile-apps-with-mymoneyappup-challenge","tags":["Perspective Migration"],"month":"08","author.displayName":["Pam Flaherty","Bob Annibale"],"siteId":"citigpa","category":"PERSPECTIVES"},{"summary":"New York - Citi will hold its third <i>Citi Field Kids</i> program for the 2012 season, and the first outside the confines of Citi Field, August 8 at 11 a.m. at the Jacob A. Riis Neighborhood Settlement House in Long Island City, N.Y. The event will feature New York Mets All-Star pitcher R.A. Dickey, renowned knuckleballer and author, addressing kids from United Neighborhood Houses. SNY anchor and reporter Michelle Yu will once again serve as master of ceremonies.","month":"08","year":"2012","publishDate":"August 07, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Mets All-Star Pitcher R.A. Dickey to Inspire Kids From United Neighborhood Houses","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2012/mets-all-star-pitcher-ra-dickey-to-inspire-kids-from-united-neighborhood-houses","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"Shanghai, China - Citibank (China) Co., Ltd. (\"Citi China\") today opened its China flagship outlet in Shanghai. Located on West Nanjing Road, Shanghai's iconic business street, the new flagship outlet features Citi China's first Citigold Private Client Center. Stephen Bird, Asia Pacific Chief Executive Officer, Jonathan Larsen, Global Head of Retail Banking and Asia Pacific Head of Consumer Banking, Andrew Au, Chairman and Chief Executive Officer of Citi China, and Simon Chow, Head of Consumer Bank of Citi China, attended the opening ceremony. The new branch brings the total number of Citi's consumer outlets to 12 in Shanghai and 50 across China.","month":"08","year":"2012","publishDate":"August 07, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Opens China Flagship Outlet and First Citigold Private Client Center","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2012/citi-opens-china-flagship-outlet-and-first-citigold-private-client-center","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"Citi Pakistan is humbled to be awarded by the United Nations Global Compact Pakistan Network for our 'Best Practices in Corporate Social Responsibility (CSR).' The United Nations Global Compact is a strategic policy initiative for businesses that are committed to aligning their operations and strategies with 10 universally accepted principles in the areas of human rights, labor, environment and anti-corruption. This recognition comes on the heels of three other recent global CSR awards that Citi Pakistan has won during 2011 and 2012 for our pioneering work in the microfinance and education spheres in Pakistan.","image":"638e31a7a3c47c530c0a6214","year":"2012","publishDate":"August 07, 2012","type":"insights","title":"Citi Pakistan Awarded for 'Best Practices in Corporate Social Responsibility' by United Nations","author.jobTitle":["Assistant Vice President, Citi Pakistan"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2012/citi-pakistan-awarded-for-best-practices-in-corporate-social-responsibility-by-united-nations","tags":["Perspective Migration"],"month":"08","author.displayName":["Haroon Saeed"],"siteId":"citigpa","category":"PERSPECTIVES"},{"summary":"London - Citi today announced an agreement to sell its Diners Club card issuing businesses in UK and Republic of Ireland to private investor group Affiniture Cards Ltd. (Affiniture). Under the terms of the transaction, the group will acquire payment card accounts in these countries ensuring continuity and seamless service to cardholders during migration. The Affiniture management team has extensive experience in the cards and payments industry.","month":"08","year":"2012","publishDate":"August 06, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi to Sell Diners Club UK and Republic of Ireland Issuing Businesses to Affiniture Cards Ltd.","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2012/citi-to-sell-diners-club-uk-and-republic-of-ireland-issuing-businesses-to-affiniture-cards-ltd","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"I recently had the privilege of attending the National Urban League's annual conference in New Orleans. The National Urban League and Citi have a long-standing, multi-pronged relationship, and collaborate on numerous community programs through both Citi Community Development and Citi Foundation. This year's conference was particularly special as it opened with a speech from President Obama. In his address to the conference attendees, the President reiterated that \"Good jobs, quality schools... affordable housing -- these are all the pillars upon which communities are built.\" They are also important stepping stones for families to build long-term assets, such as earning college degrees, saving for retirement, or buying a home. However, with <a href=\"https://www.pewsocialtrends.org/2011/07/26/wealth-gaps-rise-to-record-highs-between-whites-blacks-hispanics/\">the Pew Institute's report revealing the country's record wealth gap in communities of color</a>, the President challenged attendees to be creative and urgent in making these asset building opportunities accessible to everyone. But how?","month":"08","author.displayName":["Natalie Abatemarco"],"year":"2012","publishDate":"August 06, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Asset Building: What Does the Future Look Like?","category":"PERSPECTIVES","author.jobTitle":["Managing Director, Citi Community Development"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2012/asset-building-what-does-the-future-look-like","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"As you head into retirement, you might be looking to move to an apartment or smaller house that will need less upkeep and that's closer to shopping and public transportation.","month":"08","author.displayName":["Jonathan Clements"],"year":"2012","publishDate":"August 06, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"About to Retire? Aim to Simplify Your Finances","category":"PERSPECTIVES","author.jobTitle":["Director of Financial Education, Citi Personal Wealth Management"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2012/about-to-retire-aim-to-simplify-your-finances","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"In a new blog post, Women & Co.'s Catherine Mcmanus shares highlights from a recent survey on Back-to-school spending conducted by Women & Co. and <a href=\"https://www.parenting.com/\">Parenting.com</a>.","image":"638e31aba3c47c530c0a6227","month":"08","year":"2012","publishDate":"August 03, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"On the Women & Co. Blog: Back-To-School Spending Survey","category":"PERSPECTIVES","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2012/on-the-women-co-blog-back-to-school-spending-survey","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"In celebration of Citigroup's 200th Anniversary, we are sharing stories from our rich history here on this blog. The 20th installation below covers how innovative thinking within the bank contributed to a revolution in the shipping industry. <a href=\"https://blog.citigroup.com/2012/07/citi-turns-200-new-hiring-and-training-practices-bring-greater-diversity.shtml\">Read the 19th installment on how the profile of National City Bank's employees evolved in the 1950's and 60's, becoming more diverse, here</a>.","image":"638e31aca3c47c530c0a622e","month":"08","year":"2012","publishDate":"August 03, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Turns 200: Landmarks in Transportation Finance","category":"PERSPECTIVES","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2012/citi-turns-200-landmarks-in-transportation-finance","tags"