unced that the <a href=\"https://itunes.apple.com/us/app/citi-news/id431387145\">Citi News App is now available for download on iPhone devices</a>, showing again that Citi is the industry leader in providing innovative communication tools. As with the iPad app, the iPhone version delivers a rich and interactive way to view the latest press releases and investor information from Citi. Within the app you'll find:","image":"638e31cea3c47c530c0a62db","month":"07","year":"2012","publishDate":"July 02, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi News App Now Available for iPhone","category":"PERSPECTIVES","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2012/citi-news-app-now-available-for-iphone","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"Like many folks, you may have one or more retirement accounts, where your investments can grow tax-deferred, and also regular taxable accounts, where each year you're taxed on your dividends, interest and realized capital gains.","month":"07","author.displayName":["Jonathan Clements"],"year":"2012","publishDate":"July 02, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Could You Make Your Financial Life Less Taxing?","category":"PERSPECTIVES","author.jobTitle":["Director of Financial Education, Citi Personal Wealth Management"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2012/could-you-make-your-financial-life-less-taxing","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"New York - Citi (NYSE:C) today announced the successful completion of the sale of EMI Music Publishing to an investor group comprised of Sony Corporation of America, the Estate of Michael Jackson, Mubadala Development Company PJSC, Jynwel Capital Limited, the Blackstone Group's GSO Capital Partners LP, and David Geffen. Citi received total consideration of $2.2 billion for EMI Music Publishing, a world-leading popular music publisher with a vast collection of musical compositions and a roster of highly talented songwriters. The business represents and administers one of the world's most comprehensive and diverse catalogs of more than 1.3 million music copyrights covering all genres, periods and territories of the world.","month":"06","year":"2012","publishDate":"June 29, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Successfully Completes Sale of EMI Music Publishing","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2012/citi-successfully-completes-sale-of-emi-music-publishing","tags":["Press Release Migration","Citi-Wide","Institutional Clients Group"]},{"summary":"The second installment of a special financial inclusion series underwritten by the Citi Foundation will debut this evening on the PBS weekly public affairs news program \"<a href=\"https://www.pbs.org/wnet/need-to-know/\">Need to Know</a>\". The five-part series, \"Your Money and Your Life,\" illustrates the Citi Foundation's commitment to educate, empower and transform low-income communities by supporting efforts to build financial capability among consumers. <a href=\"https://blog.citigroup.com/2012/05/with-citi-foundation-support-pbs-spotlights-financial-inclusion.shtml\">Click here to read a previous post about the series' debut</a>.","image":"638e3100a3c47c530c0a5f23","year":"2012","publishDate":"June 29, 2012","type":"insights","title":"Citi Foundation-supported PBS series continues, focusing on peer-to-peer assistance","author.jobTitle":["Citi Foundation Program Officer"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2012/citi-foundation-supported-pbs-series-continues-focusing-on-peer-to-peer-assistance","tags":["Perspective Migration"],"month":"06","author.displayName":["Daria Sheehan"],"siteId":"citigpa","category":"PERSPECTIVES"},{"summary":"In celebration of Citigroup's 200th Anniversary, we are sharing stories from our rich history here on this blog. The 15th installation below covers how National City Bank sought out to find a new look post World War II. <a href=\"https://blog.citigroup.com/2012/06/citi-turns-200-the-bank-embraces-air-travel.shtml\">Read the 14th installment on how National City Bank embraced air travel by recognizing the advantages of air mail and commercial air transport for staff, here</a>.","image":"638e31d2a3c47c530c0a62ef","month":"06","year":"2012","publishDate":"June 29, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Turns 200: Banks Faces Postwar Challenge","category":"PERSPECTIVES","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2012/citi-turns-200-banks-faces-postwar-challenge","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"New York - CitiMortgage today announced the launch of its proprietary 2012 Citi Military Road to Recovery Tour featuring five homeowner-support events near military bases around the country for current and former members of the Armed Forces. At these events, Citi's Homeowner Support Travel Team of mortgage experts and HUD (Department of Housing and Urban Development)-approved housing counselors will have one-on-one discussions with current and former members of the military in need of assistance with their mortgages. Borrowers do not have to be CitiMortgage customers to attend. The first event will take place June 29 in San Diego, Calif.","month":"06","year":"2012","publishDate":"June 28, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"U.S.: CitiMortgage Launches Military Road to Recovery Tour","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2012/us-citimortgage-launches-military-road-to-recovery-tour","tags":["Press Release Migration"]},{"summary":"New York - Citigroup today announced that Christy Wyatt will join the company's Global Consumer Technology team on August 1 as Global Head of Consumer eBusiness and Mobile Technology.","month":"06","year":"2012","publishDate":"June 28, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Hires Christy Wyatt to Lead Global Consumer eBusiness and Mobile Technology Unit","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2012/citi-hires-christy-wyatt-to-lead-global-consumer-ebusiness-and-mobile-technology-unit","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"Hong Kong - With nearly half of the world's population calling Asia home, rapid urbanization will further fuel the region's consumption of energy, which is already at a level surpassing the rest of the world. The modern energy needs required to sustain and improve the well-being of its population and its urban centers is transforming the energy landscape in the region.","month":"06","year":"2012","publishDate":"June 27, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Asia Energy Leaders Call for New Collaborations and Partnerships to Support Asia's Rapid Growth","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2012/asia-energy-leaders-call-for-new-collaborations-and-partnerships-to-support-asia-s-rapid-growth","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"\"There is no better way to celebrate our 200th anniversary than by honoring our history, embracing the future and working together to strengthen the communities where we live and work,\" noted Vikram Pandit about this year's Global Community Day. <a href=\"https://blog.citigroup.com/2012/06/citi-commemorates-200th-anniversary-with-hundreds-of-volunteer-projects-around-the-world-on-annual-g.shtml\">And in this year's Global Community Day effort, more than 100,000 volunteers spent 500,000 hours across 92 countries supporting 1,300 projects to help local communities</a>. These volunteers lent their time and skills to local efforts including neighborhood revitalization, housing, disaster relief, environmental protection, donation drives, and financial education and literacy.","image":"638e31d3a3c47c530c0a62f6","year":"2012","publishDate":"June 26, 2012","type":"insights","title":"Citi's Alumni Network Celebrates Citi's 200th Anniversary in Guam","author.jobTitle":["Citi Alumni Network"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2012/citis-alumni-network-celebrates-citis-200th-anniversary-in-guam","tags":["Perspective Migration"],"month":"06","author.displayName":["Citi Alumni Network"],"siteId":"citigpa","category":"PERSPECTIVES"},{"summary":"Moscow - Citibank has inaugurated the first branch in Russia that will provide exclusive banking service to Citigold Private Clients (CPC).","month":"06","year":"2012","publishDate":"June 25, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Russia: Citibank Opens First Branch for High-Net-Worth Individuals","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2012/russia-citibank-opens-first-branch-for-high-net-worth-individuals","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"Washington, D.C. - Tournament officials today announced the entry list for the 2012 Citi Open (formerly the Legg Mason Tennis Classic), an Association of Tennis Professionals (ATP) World Tour 500 event and a Women's Tennis Association (WTA) International Level event. The Citi Open will take place July 28 - August 5 at the William H.G. FitzGerald Tennis Center in Washington, D.C. Proceeds from the Citi Open benefit the Washington Tennis and Education Foundation (WTEF), which seeks to improve the lives of D.C.-area youth.","month":"06","year":"2012","publishDate":"June 25, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"2012 Citi Open Player Field Announced","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2012/2012-citi-open-player-field-announced","tags":["Press Release Migration"]},{"summary":"Whether we're pursuing investment performance or seeking safety, we often fail to consider the risks we are taking. Yet every investment, whether it's a highflying stock or a low-yielding certificate of deposit, is risky. The question is, which risks do we want to take?","month":"06","author.displayName":["Jonathan Clements"],"year":"2012","publishDate":"June 25, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Know Your Asset Classes","category":"PERSPECTIVES","author.jobTitle":["Director of Financial Education, Citi Personal Wealth Management"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2012/know-your-asset-classes","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"Miami, Florida - Citi received the prestigious annual award for <a href=\"http://www.gfmag.com/\" target=\"blank\">Best Sub-Custodian Bank in Latin America</a> from <i>Global Finance</i> for the ninth consecutive year. The bank became the undisputable leader in the provision of sub-custodian services across Latin America, obtaining the award in some of the region's most prominent markets, including Argentina, Chile (Banco de Chile), Colombia, Peru, Venezuela and Mexico (Banamex). Globally, Citi also received the award in the US, consolidating its leadership on the market for sub-custodian services across the Americas.","month":"06","year":"2012","publishDate":"June 22, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Named Best Sub-Custodian Bank in Latin America for Ninth Consecutive Year by Global Finance","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2012/citi-named-best-sub-custodian-bank-in-latin-america-for-ninth-consecutive-year-by-global-finance","tags":["Press Release Migration"]},{"summary":"<a href=\"https://www.citigroup.com/rcs/citigpa/akpublic/storage/public/200-blog-post-14.JPG\"></a>In celebration of Citigroup's 200th Anniversary, we are sharing stories from our rich history here on this blog. The 14th installation below covers how National City Bank embraced air travel by recognizing the advantages of air mail and commercial air transport for staff. <a href=\"https://blog.citigroup.com/2012/06/citi-turns-200-retail-branch-is-beacon-of-thrift.shtml\">Read the 13th instal