erday, Citi celebrated the LEED® (Leadership in Energy and Environmental Design) Platinum certification of its New York City flagship branch in Union Square, becoming the world's first bank with 200 LEED-certified projects. LEED is the U.S Green Building Council's leading rating system for designing and constructing the world's greenest, most energy efficient, and high performing buildings.","image":"638e31d7a3c47c530c0a6313","month":"06","year":"2012","publishDate":"June 21, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Becomes World's First Bank with 200 LEED® Certified Projects","category":"PERSPECTIVES","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2012/citi-becomes-worlds-first-bank-with-200-leed-certified-projects","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"New York - Citi today celebrates the LEED® (Leadership in Energy and Environmental Design) Platinum certification of its New York City flagship branch in Union Square, becoming the world's first bank with 200 LEED-certified projects. LEED is the U.S Green Building Council's leading rating system for designing and constructing the world's greenest, most energy efficient, and high performing buildings.","month":"06","year":"2012","publishDate":"June 20, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Becomes World's First Bank with 200 LEED® Certified Projects","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2012/citi-becomes-world-s-first-bank-with-200-leed-certified-projects","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"New York - John Gerspach, Chief Financial Officer, and Eric Aboaf, Treasurer, will conduct the Citigroup second quarter 2012 Fixed Income Investor Review at 10 a.m. (EDT) on Friday, July 20, 2012. The review will be available live via webcast and teleconference.","month":"06","year":"2012","publishDate":"June 19, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Second Quarter 2012 Fixed Income Investor Review","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2012/citi-second-quarter-2012-fixed-income-investor-review","tags":["Press Release Migration","Citi-Wide"]},{"summary":"Citi CEO Vikram Pandit was interviewed this afternoon on <a href=\"https://www.cnbc.com/id/35186609\">CNBC's Closing Bell</a>, where he discussed capital and liquidity, emerging markets, the Eurozone, Citi's 200th Anniversary and more.","month":"06","year":"2012","publishDate":"June 18, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi CEO Vikram Pandit Talks Eurozone and Emerging Markets with CNBC Closing Bell","category":"PERSPECTIVES","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2012/citi-ceo-vikram-pandit-talks-eurozone-and-emerging-markets-with-cnbc-closing-bell","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"This past Saturday, June 16th 2012, Citi illustrated its ongoing commitment to helping communities by marking its 200th anniversary with its seventh annual Global Community Day. In 92 countries around the world, more than 100,000 Citi volunteers - the largest number of participants ever - gathered in the days leading up to and including Global Community Day to participate in 1,300 service projects that benefited local communities.","image":"638e31d9a3c47c530c0a631e","year":"2012","publishDate":"June 18, 2012","type":"insights","title":"Citi Commemorates 200th Anniversary with Hundreds of Volunteer Projects Around the World on Annual Global Community Day","author.jobTitle":["CEO and President, the Citi Foundation and Director, Corporate Citizenship"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2012/citi-commemorates-200th-anniversary-with-hundreds-of-volunteer-projects-around-the-world-on-annual-g","tags":["Perspective Migration"],"month":"06","author.displayName":["Pam Flaherty"],"siteId":"citigpa","category":"PERSPECTIVES"},{"summary":"Citi CEO Vikram Pandit was interviewed this morning on <a href=\"https://www.cnbc.com/id/15838381\">CNBC's Squawk on the Street</a>, where he discussed Citi's 200th anniversary-- celebrated this past Saturday, June 16th --the situation in Greece/Europe, and the state of the U.S. economic recovery. The interview followed CEO Pandit ringing the opening bell at the New York Stock Exchange in celebration of Citi's 200th anniversary.","month":"06","year":"2012","publishDate":"June 18, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi CEO Vikram Pandit Rings NYSE Opening Bell In Honor of 200th Anniversary","category":"PERSPECTIVES","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2012/citi-ceo-vikram-pandit-rings-nyse-opening-bell-in-honor-of-200th-anniversary","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"It's a quandary for retirees: Record low interest rates may be great for borrowers, but it means tough choices if you need investment income.","month":"06","author.displayName":["Jonathan Clements"],"year":"2012","publishDate":"June 18, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"A Retirement-Income Strategy When Rates are Low","category":"PERSPECTIVES","author.jobTitle":["Director of Financial Education, Citi Personal Wealth Management"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2012/a-retirement-income-strategy-when-rates-are-low","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"New York - Citi will highlight its ongoing commitment to helping communities by marking its 200th anniversary on Saturday, June 16, with its seventh annual Global Community Day. In 92 countries around the world, more than 100,000 Citi volunteers - the largest number of participants ever - will gather in the days leading up to and including Global Community Day to participate in 1,300 service projects that will benefit local communities.","month":"06","year":"2012","publishDate":"June 16, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Commemorates 200th Anniversary with Hundreds of Volunteer Projects Around the World on Annual Global Community Day","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2012/citi-commemorates-200th-anniversary-with-hundreds-of-volunteer-projects-around-the-world-on-annual-global-community-day","tags":["Press Release Migration","Citi-Wide","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"<a href=\"https://www.citigroup.com/rcs/citigpa/akpublic/storage/public/200-blog-post-13.JPG\"></a>In celebration of Citigroup's 200th Anniversary, we are sharing stories from our rich history here on this blog. The 13th installation below covers how National City Bank's new branches and compound interest department helped create new opportunities in retail banking. <a href=\"https://blog.citigroup.com/2012/06/citi-turns-200-new-technologies-bring-communications-revolution.shtml\">Read the 12th installment on how National City Bank embraced new communication technologies, here</a>.","image":"638e31dca3c47c530c0a632f","month":"06","year":"2012","publishDate":"June 15, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Turns 200: Retail branch is \"beacon of thrift\"","category":"PERSPECTIVES","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2012/citi-turns-200-retail-branch-is-beacon-of-thrift","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"Euromoney Magazine* is monthly periodical dedicated to international banking finance and capital markets news, analysis. FX, asset management, investment banking, M&A, private banking, debt and equity markets. The Awards for Excellence honor institutions and individuals that demonstrate leadership, innovation, and provide the highest levels of service and expertise to their customers.","image":"638e31dda3c47c530c0a6336","year":"2012","publishDate":"June 14, 2012","type":"insights","title":"Euromoney Names Citi 'Best Investment Bank in the Middle East'","author.jobTitle":["Director of Corporate Affairs, Citi UAE"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2012/euromoney-names-citi-best-investment-bank-in-the-middle-east","tags":["Perspective Migration"],"month":"06","author.displayName":["Karim Seifeddine"],"siteId":"citigpa","category":"PERSPECTIVES"},{"summary":"Budapest, Hungary - Four students attending the master's course at the Enterprise Finances Department of the Corvinus University of Budapest received an award from Batara Sianturi, Citi Country Officer for Hungary, Dr. Miklos Virag, Head of Department of Enterprise Finances, and Dr. Attila Fiath, professor of the Corvinus University, at the 2012 Citi Case Study Competition award ceremony on June 12, 2012.The first prize went to Gabor Papp for his work titled, 'Venture capital in Hungary - The role of the JEREMIE funds in the venture capital markets and financing in Hungary.'","month":"06","year":"2012","publishDate":"June 13, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Hungary: Citi - Corvinus Case Study Competition 2012","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/foundation/news/press-release/2012/hungary-citi-corvinus-case-study-competition-2012","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"São Paulo - Businesses around the world are seeking opportunities to leverage their businesses during the 2014 Soccer World Cup and 2016 Olympic Games. In Brazil, the opportunities are even greater; these are catalyzing events that give our country a chance to show itself as fertile ground for doing business. For this to be true, however, investment in infrastructure is required. Brazil's states and municipalities are searching for partnership opportunities in this area, including public/private financing.","month":"06","year":"2012","publishDate":"June 12, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi-Sponsored Event Promotes Investment in Brazilian Infrastructure","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2012/citi-sponsored-event-promotes-investment-in-brailian-infrastructure","tags":["Press Release Migration"]},{"summary":"Bahrain - For the third consecutive year, INJAZ Bahrain and Citibank Bahrain held the Banks in Action (BIA) Competition for the 2011-2012 academic year. Six schools' teams took part in the final round of the INJAZ Bahrain (BIA) Competition, which was held at Citibank's headquarters in the Seef District on June 11, 2012.","month":"06","year":"2012","publishDate":"June 12, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Bahrain: Banks in Action Competition 2012","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2012/bahrain-banks-in-action-competition-2012","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"New York - Today, the U.S. Agency for International Development (USAID) and Citi announced a global partnership to broaden financial inclusion by fostering the rapid adoption of \"mobile money\" technology in developing countries. The announcement was made at USAID's Frontiers in Development Forum at Georgetown University. Of the five billion mobile phone users worldwide, nearly two billion lack access to banking services, instead relying on cash transactions that expose them to potential theft, fraud or loss, and high-cost lending and remittance providers that leave them vulnerable to endless debt and high fees. USAID and Citi will work with governments, donors, industry and other participants in the payments system. USAID expects to continue to support local mobile money platforms with over $23 million, and Citi will integrate its core banking services with mobile money platforms to provide seamless integration between banking and last-mile, mobile-based payments services.","month":"06","year":"2012","publishDate":"June 12, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"U.S. Agency for International Development & Citi to Accelerate Mobile Money Adoption","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2012/us-agency-for-international-development-citi-to-accelerate-mobile-money-adoption","tags":["Press Release Migration","Citi-Wide"]},{"summary":"Seattle, Wash. - Demonstrating its continued commitment to help end the jobs crisis in America, Starbucks Coffee Company (NASDAQ: SBUX) today announced the launch of the Indivisible collection. The collection includes Indivisible Blend™ Coffee and two new products to support Create Jobs for USA, an innovative program enabling Americans to unite in helping Americans get back to work. With each purchase from the Indivisible collection, Starbucks will make a donation to Opportunity Finance Network® (OFN) for the Create Jobs for USA Fund to help create and retain jobs across the country.","month":"06","year":"2012","publishDate":"June 12, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Starbucks Introduces New Indivisible Collection and Citi Donates $1 Million to Support Create Jobs for USA","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/foundation/news/press-release/2012/starbucks-introduces-new-indivisible-collection-and-citi-donates-1-million-to-support-create-jobs-for-usa","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"Women & Co.'s President and CEO, Linda Descano CFA®, recently spoke with Don Callahan, Chief Administrative Officer and Chief Operations & Technology Officer for Citi, on the topic of leadership. In her latest <a href=\"https://blog.womenandco.com/2012/05/lessons-in-leadership.html\">blog post</a>, she shares four key takeaways.","image":"638e3117a3c47c530c0a5f95","month":"06","year":"2012","publishDate":"June 12, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"On the Women & Co. Blog: Lessons in Leadership","category":"PERSPECTIVES","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2012/on-the-women-co-blog-lessons-in-leadership","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"New York - Citigroup will issue its second quarter results via press release at approximately 8 a.m. (EDT) on Monday, July 16, 2012. At 10 a.m. (EDT), results will be reviewed via live webcast and teleconference.","month":"06","year":"2012","publishDate":"June 11, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Second Quarter 2012 Earnings Review","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2012/citi-second-quarter-2012-earnings-review","tags":["Press Release Migration","Citi-Wide"]},{"summary":"According to a 2009 study by the National Institute of Justice, 5% of Americans age 60 and older have been victims of financial abuse by a family member and 6.5% were the target of a non-family member. Meanwhile, a 2011 report by insurer MetLife estimates that financial fraud, including telemarketing fraud, cost the elderly nearly $3 billion a year.","month":"06","author.displayName":["Jonathan Clements"],"year":"2012","publishDate":"June 11, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"How to Help Protect a Senior's Finances","category":"PERSPECTIVES","author.jobTitle":["Director of Financial Education, Citi Personal Wealth Management"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2012/how-to-help-protect-a-seniors-finances","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"New York - Citigroup Inc. today released the following statement on the re-submission of its 2012 Comprehensive Capital Analysis and Review (CCAR) capital plan and the redemption of trust preferred securities issued by Citigroup Capital XII and Citigroup Capital XXI:","month":"06","year":"2012","publishDate":"June 08, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citigroup Statement on Re-Submission of 2012 Comprehensive Capital Analysis and Review (CCAR) and Redemption of Trust Preferred Securities","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2012/citigroup-statement-on-re-submission-of-2012-comprehensive-capital-analysis-and-review-ccar-and-redemption-of-trust-preferred-securities","tags":["Press Release Migration","Citi-Wide"]},{"summary":"Moscow - Citibank announced the launch of a new, more functional, technologically advanced and secure version of the Citibank Online Internet banking portal. Effective immediately, Citi clients will have access to the following self-care features: activate, block or reissue the card; link an account to a debit card; nickname payees and accounts; change the spend limit on a supplementary card; set up deposits online and much more.","month":"06","year":"2012","publishDate":"June 08, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Russia: Citibank Online Changes Its Interface","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2012/russia-citibank-online-changes-its-interface","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"<a href=\"https://www.citigroup.com/rcs/citigpa/akpublic/storage/public/200-blog-post-12.JPG\"></a><a href=\"https://www.citigroup.com/rcs/citigpa/akpublic/storage/public/200-blog-post-12.JPG\"></a>In celebration of Citigroup's 200th Anniversary, we are sharing stories from our rich history here on this blog. The 12th installation below covers how National City Bank embraced new communication technologies. <a href=\"https://blog.citigroup.com/2012/06/citi-turns-200-the-impact-of-world-war-i.shtml\">Read the 11th installment on how World War I created career opportunities for women, here</a>.","image":"638e31e0a3c47c530c0a6347","month":"06","year":"2012","publishDate":"June 08, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Turns 200: New technologies bring communications revolution","category":"PERSPECTIVES","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2012/citi-turns-200-new-technologies-bring-communications-revolution","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"Budapest - Citibank Hungary has launched the Citi Hungary Alumni Network in Budapest. Hungary's Citi Country Officer Batara Sianturi hosted the event, which was attended by 120 Citi Alumni, members of the Citibank Senior Management team and Gabor Kovacs, the founding owner of KOGART House of Arts, who, as the first Citibank Hungary employee, will act as the Citi Hungary Alumni Ambassador. The Citi Alumni Network is a global electronic platform, at <a href=\"http://www.facebook.com/CitibankMagyarorszag\">www.citialumninetwork.com</a>, with dedicated country pages that will facilitate former Citi employees around the world to reconnect with Citi and with each other.","month":"06","year":"2012","publishDate":"June 07, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citibank Launches Citi Alumni Network in Hungary","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2012/citibank-launches-citi-alumni-network-in-hungary","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"New York - Military service members, veterans and their families and survivors need unique guidance and support to maintain their long-term financial health. Today, <a href=\"https://www.citigroup.com/global\">Citi</a> joined with <a href=\"http://iava.org/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Iraq and Afghanistan Veterans of America</a> (IAVA), the <a href=\"http://www.taps.org/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Tragedy Assistance Program for Survivors</a> (TAPS), and the <a href=\"http://www.msccn.org/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Military Spouse Corporate Career Network</a> (MSCCN) to announce the launch of <a href=\"http://www.credability.org/en/partner-programs/partner-sites/reconnect.aspx\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><em>CredAbility ReConnect</em></a>, a free online financial education and counseling program specifically designed to help these communities resolve financial difficulties and build economic security. The program, supported by a grant from Citi Community Development, was developed by <a href=\"http://www.credability.org/en/partner-programs/partner-sites/reconnect.aspx\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">CredAbility</a>, a national nonprofit credit counseling organization, in collaboration with each of these established veterans' service organizations.","month":"06","year":"2012","publishDate":"June 07, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"U.S.: Citi and CredAbility Join With IAVA, TAPS and MSCCN to Launch Online Financial Education and Counseling Program for Armed Forces Members, Veterans and Their Families","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2012/us-citi-and-credability-join-with-iava-taps-and-msccn-to-launch-online-financial-education-and-counseling-program-for-armed-forces-members-veterans-and-their-families","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"Caracas, Venezuela - For more than a decade, Citibank Venezuela and its partner NGO, Jóvenes Emprendedores, have offered <i>Bancos en Acción</i>, the first and only contest in the country that teaches high school students about banking with an exclusive simulator component.","month":"06","year":"2012","publishDate":"June 07, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Venezuela: Citibank Trains Students in Virtual Banking Program","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2012/veneuela-citibank-trains-students-in-virtual-banking-program","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"New York - Citi Realty Services announced today that it has achieved LEED-Silver for Existing Buildings certification from the U.S. Green Building Council for the One Court Square building Citi occupies in Long Island City, New York. Leadership in Energy and Environmental Design (LEED) is the U.S. Green Building Council's leading rating system for designing and constructing the world's greenest, most energy efficient and high-performing buildings. The LEED for Existing Buildings (LEED EB) Rating System helps building owners and operators maximize the efficiency of existing buildings while minimizing environmental impacts.","month":"06","year":"2012","publishDate":"June 07, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Building in New York's Long Island City Earns LEED® for Existing Buildings Certification","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2012/citi-building-in-new-york-s-long-island-city-earns-leed-for-existing-buildings-certification","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"<a href=\"https://www.citigroup.com/rcs/citigpa/akpublic/storage/public/june-chart-of-the-month.JPG\"></a><a href=\"https://www.citigroup.com/rcs/citigpa/storage/public/june%20chart%20of%20the%20month%201.jpg\"></a><a href=\"https://www.citigroup.com/rcs/citigpa/storage/public/june%20chart%20of%20the%20month%201.jpg\"></a>With the focus on Europe, China and the latest nonfarm payrolls number, investors may be missing a major change in US housing. A recent report of disappointing US job growth has further deepened the investment community gloom even as credit conditions remain very positive for future domestic business activity. Moreover, there are positive dynamics brewing as well.","image":"638e31e1a3c47c530c0a634e","year":"2012","publishDate":"June 07, 2012","type":"insights","title":"Equity Strategy: June 2012 Chart of the Month","author.jobTitle":["Chief US Equity Strategist, Citi"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2012/equity-strategy-june-2012-chart-of-the-month","tags":["Perspective Migration"],"month":"06","author.displayName":["Tobias Levkovich"],"siteId":"citigpa","category":"PERSPECTIVES"},{"summary":"New York - Forty-three percent of small-business owners consider business conditions to be positive, according to the latest Citibank small business survey released today. This is a significant increase since August 2010, when 24 percent of small-business owners surveyed reported overall positive business conditions.","month":"06","year":"2012","publishDate":"June 06, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Percentage of U.S. Small Business Owners Reporting Positive Business Conditions Nearly Doubles Since 2010","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2012/percentage-of-us-small-business-owners-reporting-positive-business-conditions-nearly-doubles-since-2010","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"month":"06","author.displayName":["Michelle Peluso"],"year":"2012","publishDate":"June 06, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi's Tracey Weber Named 2012 Mobile Banker of the Year","category":"PERSPECTIVES","author.jobTitle":["Chief Marketing Officer, Citibank"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2012/citis-tracey-weber-named-2012-mobile-banker-of-the-year","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"Citi celebrates the 25th anniversary of our credit card relationship with American Airlines this year, and during that time we have been proud to earn the loyalty of customers like you.","month":"06","author.displayName":["Ralph Andretta"],"year":"2012","publishDate":"June 05, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"The American Airlines AAdvantage® program recognized by travelers as the industry's best airline loyalty program","category":"PERSPECTIVES","author.jobTitle":["Head of U.S. Branded Cards, Citi"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2012/the-american-airlines-aadvantage-program-recognized-by-travelers-as-the-industrys-best-airline-loyal","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"By Irene Blake, Coordinator of Citi's US \"Wireless Drop-Off\"","image":"638e31e5a3c47c530c0a6362","year":"2012","publishDate":"June 05, 2012","type":"insights","title":"Citi Employees' Recycled Phones Help Domestic Violence Victims","author.jobTitle":["Coordinator of Citi's Wireless Drop-off Campaign"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2012/citi-employees-recycled-phones-help-domestic-violence-victims","tags":["Perspective Migration"],"month":"06","author.displayName":["Irene Blake"],"siteId":"citigpa","category":"PERSPECTIVES"},{"summary":"Miami, Florida - Citi has launched Renminbi Letters of Credits for importers and exporters (RMB LCs) in Latin America. Citi is one of the leading banks in Latin America to offer a trade services solution suite available in RMB. This new capability will allow clients in Latin America to issue, receive and settle RMB-denominated Letters of Credit (LCs) with their Chinese trading partners while also providing clients with new alternatives for trade financing, trade processing and risk mitigation.","month":"06","year":"2012","publishDate":"June 04, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Launches Renminbi (RMB) Exporters and Importers Letters of Credit in Latin America","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2012/citi-launches-renminbi-rmb-exporters-and-importers-letters-of-credit-in-latin-america","tags":["Press Release Migration","Institutional Clients Group"]},{"summary":"Suppose the U.S. economy falls back into recession. Or loose monetary policy leads to renewed inflation. Or Europe can't solve its economic problems. Investors often fret that a particular economic or political scenario will come to pass--and they position their portfolio to sidestep the imagined calamity and perhaps even turn a handsome profit.","month":"06","author.displayName":["Jonathan Clements"],"year":"2012","publishDate":"June 04, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Imagining Disaster? What If Your Imagination Is Wrong?","category":"PERSPECTIVES","author.jobTitle":["Director of Financial Education, Citi Personal Wealth Management"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2012/imagining-disaster-what-if-your-imagination-is-wrong","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"In celebration of Citigroup's 200th Anniversary, we are sharing stories from our rich history here on this blog. The 11th installation below covers how World War I created career opportunities for women. <a href=\"https://blog.citigroup.com/2012/05/citi-turns-200-training-graduates-for-careers-overseas.shtml\">Read the tenth installment on how National City Bank expanded their staff education to accommodate employees abroad, here</a>.","image":"638e31eda3c47c530c0a6387","month":"06","year":"2012","publishDate":"June 01, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Turns 200: The impact of World War I","category":"PERSPECTIVES","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2012/citi-turns-200-the-impact-of-world-war-i","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"Elk Grove, Ill. - The Citi Team USA Flag Tour made its seventh stop today at Citi's site in Elk Grove. U.S. Olympic triathlete Gwen Jorgensen, a member of Team Citi through Citi's sponsorship of the United States Olympic Committee, joined Citi Site President Joe Sharp and Citi colleagues in celebration and support of Team USA.","month":"05","year":"2012","publishDate":"May 31, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Team USA Flag Tour Stops in Elk Grove to Celebrate Citi's Team USA Sponsorship and the Every Step of the Way Program","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2012/citi-team-usa-flag-tour-stops-in-elk-grove-to-celebrate-citi-s-team-usa-sponsorship-and-the-every-step-of-the-way-program","tags":["Press Release Migration"]},{"summary":"Toronto - Starting a business can be challenging for any entrepreneur but for those with a history of mental health or addiction issues, the task can be even more daunting. But a program from Rise Asset Development, a financial initiative of the