nniversary, we are sharing stories from our rich history here on this blog. The ninth installation below covers how National City Bank built a presence in Europe during World War I. <a href=\"https://blog.citigroup.com/2012/05/citi-turns-200-business-blooms-in-latin-america.shtml\">Read the eighth installment on how the opening of National City Bank's first foreign branch in Buenos Aires lead to an expansion throughout Latin America here</a>.","image":"638e31faa3c47c530c0a63d5","month":"05","year":"2012","publishDate":"May 18, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Turns 200: National City Bank puts down new European roots","category":"PERSPECTIVES","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2012/citi-turns-200-national-city-bank-puts-down-new-european-roots","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"A special financial inclusion series underwritten by the Citi Foundation will debut this evening on the PBS weekly public affairs news program <strong><a href=\"https://www.pbs.org/wnet/need-to-know/\">\"Need to Know\"</a></strong>. The five-part series, \"Your Money and Your Life\", illustrates the Citi Foundation's commitment to educate, empower and transform low-income communities by supporting efforts to build financial capability among consumers. \"Your Money and Your Life\" will cover the financial lives and needs of low-income Americans to provide a unique view into their communities, profile model programs, and detail public policy recommendations.","image":"638e3100a3c47c530c0a5f23","year":"2012","publishDate":"May 18, 2012","type":"insights","title":"With Citi Foundation support, PBS spotlights financial inclusion","author.jobTitle":["Citi Foundation Program Officer"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2012/with-citi-foundation-support-pbs-spotlights-financial-inclusion","tags":["Perspective Migration"],"month":"05","author.displayName":["Daria Sheehan"],"siteId":"citigpa","category":"PERSPECTIVES"},{"s