":"Citi employees at the Out on the Street™ LGBT Leadership Conference","image":"638e31fca3c47c530c0a63e0","month":"05","year":"2012","publishDate":"May 17, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi sponsors second annual Out on the Street™ LGBT Conference","category":"PERSPECTIVES","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2012/citi-sponsors-second-annual-out-on-the-street-lgbt-conference","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"Managua, Nicaragua - As part of Citi's 200th anniversary celebration around the world, the bank launched a corporate social responsibility program in Nicaragua based on volunteer work by its employees and an alliance with Agora Partnerships.","month":"05","year":"2012","publishDate":"May 16, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Celebrating 200 Years of Citi: Agora Partnerships and Citibank Nicaragua S.A. Launch \"Citi Líderes\" Business Mentoring Program","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/foundation/news/press-release/2012/celebrating-200-years-of-citi-agora-partnerships-and-citibank-nicaragua-sa-launch-citi-líderes-business-mentoring-program","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"In a recent <a href=\"https://blog.womenandco.com/2012/05/rewire-not-retire.html\">blog post</a>, Women & Co.'s President and CEO, Linda Descano CFA®, talks about creating your mission statement for retirement and building the capital needed to finance your vision.","image":"638e31f6a3c47c530c0a63bb","month":"05","year":"2012","publishDate":"May 16, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"On the Women & Co. blog: Rewire Not Retire","category":"PERSPECTIVES","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2012/on-the-women-co-blog-rewire-not-retire","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"Doha - Citi launched its International Personal Bank Europe, Middle East and Africa (Citi IPB EMEA) Service Centre in Qatar with an event held at the Four Seasons, Doha, on May 14, 2012. The move affirms the bank's aspiration, as it celebrates its 200th anniversary, to address the growing needs of affluent clients in the Middle East region.","month":"05","year":"2012","publishDate":"May 15, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Launches New Wealth Management Service Center in Qatar","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2012/citi-launches-new-wealth-management-service-center-in-qatar","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"To \"Sell in May\" is a fabled investment thesis. But does it actually work? Over the past 20 years, EM equities have tended to do better in the three months up to May (+2.8%, on average) than the three months after (-0.4%). We also show that May-October has been the worst rolling six months of the year for EM since 1990 (average monthly fall of 0.2%). However, while, since 1991, EM equities have risen in the three months to mid-May in 15 out of 22 years (68% of the time) they have still risen in the three months after mid-May in only 11 of 21 years (52%). So, \"Sell in May\" does work, but barely. Asia and EMEA have clear \"Sell in May\" effects; for Latin America, they are less clear.","month":"05","author.displayName":["Geoffrey Dennis"],"year":"2012","publishDate":"May 15, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Does \"Sell in May and Go Away\" Work?","category":"PERSPECTIVES","author.jobTitle":["Global Emerging Markets Strategist"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2012/does-sell-in-may-and-go-away-work","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"New York - Today, Citi, the official bank sponsor of the 2012 U.S. Olympic and Paralympic Teams, unveiled a national advertising and marketing campaign that is the largest and most integrated U.S. sponsorship campaign in the company's history. The campaign, which features 13 Olympic and Paralympic qualifiers, hopefuls and alumni who are members of Team Citi, includes broadcast, print, out-of-home, digital, events, promotions and retail activation. This is the first time Citi has sponsored the U.S. Olympic and Paralympic Teams.","month":"05","year":"2012","publishDate":"May 14, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Launches Advertising Campaign for First-Ever Sponsorship of U.S. Olympic and Paralympic Teams","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2012/citi-launches-advertising-campaign-for-first-ever-sponsorship-of-us-olympic-and-paralympic-teams","tags":["Press Release Migration"]},{"summary":"Hong Kong, Singapore - Citi today announced the launch of its Payment Analytics tool, a module within CitiDirect® BE, its next-generation online banking platform. The new service from Citi Transaction Services positions Citi among the first in the industry to provide an analytics solution that allows organizations to strategically manage their overall payables activities across multiple payment types, currencies and geographies.","month":"05","year":"2012","publishDate":"May 14, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Launches Payment Analytics Tool on CitiDirect® BE to Empower Clients with Increased Visibility of Payment Activities","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2012/citi-launches-payment-analytics-tool-on-citidirect-be-to-empower-clients-with-increased-visibility-of-payment-activities","tags":["Press Release Migration","Institutional Clients Group"]},{"summary":"Students take all kinds of things to college with them, including laptop computers, smart phones, mini-refrigerators and microwaves. But perhaps the most useful item - and potentially the most financially dangerous - could be a credit card.","month":"05","author.displayName":["Jonathan Clements"],"year":"2012","publishDate":"May 14, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"