LEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2012/citibank-launches-citimall-in-bahrain-city-centre","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"New York, N.Y. - Citi will hold its first Citi Field Kids program for the 2012 season when the Mets host the Miami Marlins tomorrow at 1:10 p.m. at Citi Field. The program, recognizing the Month of the Military Child, will include children from TAPS, the Wheelchair Sports Federation and United Neighborhood Houses.","month":"04","year":"2012","publishDate":"April 25, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Field Kids Salutes Children of America's Veterans During First Program of 2012 Season","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2012/citi-field-kids-salutes-children-of-america-s-veterans-during-first-program-of-2012-season","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"New York - In a deal that combines microloans in Mongolia with the sale of carbon credits on the European Union Emissions Trading Scheme (EU ETS), Citi's London-based Environmental Products Trading and Origination team, working with Citi Microfinance, has agreed to purchase 1.17 million metric tons of carbon credits over the next seven years from Seattle-based social enterprise MicroEnergy Credits. The carbon credits will be generated by capturing reductions of greenhouse gas emissions following the installation of more efficient household insulation and heating fixtures in Ulaanbaatar, the capital and largest city in Mongolia. The purchase and installation of the fixtures will be funded through microloans from Mongolia's XacBank.","month":"04","year":"2012","publishDate":"April 25, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi to Purchase 1.17 Million Tons of Carbon Credits in Innovative Microfinance Deal with MicroEnergy Credits and Mongolia's XacBank","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2012/citi-to-purchase-117-million-tons-of-carbon-credits-in-innovative-microfinance-deal-with-microenergy-credits-and-mongolia-s-xacbank","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance","Institutional Clients Group"]},{"summary":"Citi and the March of Dimes have worked together for <a href=\"https://blog.citigroup.com/2012/04/citi-and-the-march-of-dimes.shtml\">the past dozen years</a> by donating funds to improve the health of babies. Our employees and their families have been eager to participate in our fundraising efforts - especially when the cause hits close to home. Read a story from Citi employees, Sierra and Bob Clemments, below:","month":"04","year":"2012","publishDate":"April 25, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi and the March of Dimes: Employee Testimonial","category":"PERSPECTIVES","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2012/citi-and-the-march-of-dimes-employee-testimonial","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"<i>Paraguay's Secretary of Tourism lauds the guide's contribution to the national tourism sector </i>","month":"04","year":"2012","publishDate":"April 24, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citibank Publishes City of Asuncion Tourism Guide as Part of Celebrations Marking the Bank's 200th Anniversary Around the World","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2012/citibank-publishes-city-of-asuncion-tourism-guide-as-part-of-celebrations-marking-the-bank-s-200th-anniversary-around-the-world","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"Washington, D.C. - Citi, the Washington Tennis & Education Foundation (WTEF) and Lagarde`re Unlimited today announced that Citi has been named the new title sponsor of the ATP World Tour 500 Tournament called the Citi Open, previously known as the Legg Mason Tennis Classic. As part of a multi-year commitment, Citi becomes just the seventh title sponsor in the 44-year history of the tournament, replacing Legg Mason, which had been the longest-running ATP title sponsor in North America to date (since 1994).","month":"04","year":"2012","publishDate":"April 24, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Named New Title Sponsor of former Legg Mason Tennis Classic, Now \"Citi Open\"","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2012/citi-named-new-title-sponsor-of-former-legg-mason-tennis-classic-now-citi-open","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"Today, Citi announced the launch of Citi Tuesdays, a new program designed to provide added value to Citi customers who are Mets fans. The promotion, which will take place during all Tuesday home games beginning on April 24, offers unique experiences and exclusive access to benefits and rewards to fans simply for using their Citi credit or debit card at Citi Field.","image":"638e320da3c47c530c0a6450","year":"2012","publishDate":"April 24, 2012","type":"insights","title":"Citi Cardholders who are Mets Fans get special perks on \"Citi Tuesdays\"","author.jobTitle":["Chief Brand Officer"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2012/citi-cardholders-who-are-mets-fans-get-special-perks-on-citi-tuesdays","tags":["Perspective Migration"],"month":"04","author.displayName":["Dermot Boden"],"siteId":"citigpa","category":"PERSPECTIVES"},{"summary":"Thank you for taking the time to <a href=\"https://blog.citigroup.com/2012/04/you-spoke-we-listened.shtml\">post your comments and questions</a>. We read through all of them. We are always happy to hear your positive experiences and suggestions. We also understand for some of you, your experiences haven't been perfect. We know we have a lot more to do and we are working on it.","month":"04","author.displayName":["Matt Jenkins"],"year":"2012","publishDate":"April 24, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Cards Answers Your Questions","category":"PERSPECTIVES","author.jobTitle":["Head of Service Delivery"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2012/citi-cards-answers-your-questions","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"Last week, more than 50 highly talented Citi employees spent the day using their expertise to help ten nonprofit organizations address critical capacity building projects. It is the first of hopefully many Citi Skills Marathons. We have been working with the Citi Foundation and Citi Women for the last few months to orchestrate the event and are excited to see it come to life.","month":"04","author.displayName":["Aaron Hurst"],"year":"2012","publishDate":"April 24, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi and the Taproot Foundation launch Citi Skills Marathon","category":"PERSPECTIVES","author.jobTitle":["Global Consumer Chief Marketing and Internet Officer, Citi"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2012/citi-and-the-taproot-foundation-launch-citi-skills-marathon","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"New York - A new nationwide survey issued today by Citi revealed that while 74 percent of Americans consider themselves financially stable, more than 48 percent do not have the savings they say they need to achieve actual stability. More than half (51 percent) say that number is less than $100,000 and more than one in five (22 percent) believe it to be less than $10,000. Americans understand the importance of savings - 76 percent say it is very or extremely important - but nearly two-thirds have no savings goals and 25 percent say they expect to save $0 in 2012.","month":"04","year":"2012","publishDate":"April 23, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"New Citi Survey Reveals Most Americans Consider Themselves Financially Stable But Only Half Have the Savings They Say They Need","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2012/new-citi-survey-reveals-most-americans-consider-themselves-financially-stable-but-only-half-have-the-savings-they-say-they-need","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"Asunción, Paraguay - Citi has announced the winners of the \"2011 in Images - The Best in Paraguayan Photojournalism\" contest. The awards ceremony, held at the Citi Cultural Center, featured a collective exhibit of the entries.","month":"04","year":"2012","publishDate":"April 23, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Announces Winners of the \"2011 in Images - Best in Paraguayan Photojournalism\" Contest","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2012/citi-announces-winners-of-the-2011-in-images--best-in-paraguayan-photojournalism-contest","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"You might tell your children to finish their homework before they can go out and play. You insist they eat their main course before they get dessert. And maybe you make them save their pocket money for a few weeks before they can buy that new toy. It's all about delaying gratification--and it is one of the most important financial skills any of us can learn.","month":"04","author.displayName":["Jonathan Clements"],"year":"2012","publishDate":"April 23, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Teaching Kids About Money","category":"PERSPECTIVES","author.jobTitle":["Director of Financial Education, Citi Personal Wealth Management"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2012/teaching-kids-about-money-1","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"Citi Pakistan and the Social Enterprise Development Centre at Lahore University of Management Sciences (LUMS) are collaborating on a capacity-building project that aims to create stronger linkages between higher education institutions and the industry. This project is supported by a $50,000 grant from the Citi Foundation.","month":"04","year":"2012","publishDate":"April 22, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Pakistan: Citi Launches Phase 1 of 'Project Change'","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/foundation/news/press-release/2012/pakistan-citi-launches-phase-1-of-project-change-","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"In celebration of Citigroup's 200th Anniversary, we are sharing stories from our rich history here on this blog. The sixth installation below covers how we expanded abroad by opening a foreign exchange department. Read the fifth installment on how Jacob Schiff helped us break into investment banking, <a href=\"https://blog.citigroup.com/2012/04/citi-turns-200-national-city-bank-forges-investment-bank-alliance.shtml\">here</a>.","image":"638e3212a3c47c530c0a646a","month":"04","year":"2012","publishDate":"April 20, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Turns 200: New forex department for clients with operations abroad","category":"PERSPECTIVES","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2012/citi-turns-200-new-forex-department-for-clients-with-operations-abroad","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"São Paulo - Pró-Viveiros will present the results of its pilot project at the Rio de Janeiro State Industries Federation (FIRJAN) auditorium on April 20. The program, a partnership between Conservation International, Natural Partners and Refloresta with the support of Citi Brazil and the Citi Foundation, is an initiative to develop and qualify tree nurseries to contribute to reforestation in critical areas of the Atlantic Forest in Rio de Janeiro state. In addition to awarding the first round of certificates in the program, the presentation is designed to encourage contacts between potential producers and the groups with the most demand for seedlings in the state.","month":"04","year":"2012","publishDate":"April 19, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Conservation International Presents Results of Tree Nursery Qualification Project","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2012/conservation-international-presents-results-of-tree-nursery-qualification-project","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"New York - Citi today announced that it will launch Citi Tuesdays, a new program designed to provide added value to Citi customers and Mets fans. The promotion, which will take place during all Tuesday home games beginning on April 24, will offer unique experiences and exclusive access to benefits and rewards to fans simply for using their Citi credit or debit card at Citi Field. From savings on tickets and merchandise, to special access to Citi Field's Acela and Caesars Clubs, there are a variety of offers for fans who are Citi cardholders to enjoy while cheering on the Mets.","month":"04","year":"2012","publishDate":"April 19, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi to Introduce \"Citi Tuesdays\" Added-Value Specials for Mets Fans Who Are Citi Cardholders","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2012/citi-to-introduce-citi-tuesdays-added-value-specials-for-mets-fans-who-are-citi-cardholders","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"Since 2000, Citi and the March of Dimes have worked together to improve the health of babies by donating funds for research that helps prevent birth defects, premature birth, and infant mortality. Over the years, we have seen an incredible response from our employees and their families--and this year, we plan on keeping the momentum going.","month":"04","author.displayName":["Michelle Peluso"],"year":"2012","publishDate":"April 19, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi and the March of Dimes","category":"PERSPECTIVES","author.jobTitle":["Chief Marketing Officer, Citibank"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2012/citi-and-the-march-of-dimes","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"New York - CitiMortgage today announced the launch of its proprietary 2012 Road to Recovery Tour featuring homeowner support events in thirty-five cities across the country beginning April 24. At Road to Recovery events, Citi's Homeowner Support Travel Team, featuring Citi's mortgage assistance experts, consults one-on-one with local CitiMortgage customers in need of assistance with their mortgages.","month":"04","year":"2012","publishDate":"April 18, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"CitiMortgage Launches 2012 Road to Recovery Tour","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2012/citimortgage-launches-2012-road-to-recovery-tour","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"Miami, Fla. - Citi Latin America announced today the appointment of the new Executive Management Team, effective immediately, under the leadership of Francisco Aristeguieta, appointed CEO for Latin America, excluding Mexico, on January 1, 2012.","month":"04","year":"2012","publishDate":"April 18, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Latin America Announces Executive Management Team in Support of Its Growth Strategy for the Region","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2012/citi-latin-america-announces-executive-management-team-in-support-of-its-growth-strategy-for-the-region","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"New York - The Board of Directors of Citigroup Inc. today declared a quarterly dividend on the company's common stock of $0.01 per share, payable on May 25, 2012 to stockholders of record on May 7, 2012.","month":"04","year":"2012","publishDate":"April 18, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citigroup Declares Dividends","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2012/citigroup-declares-dividends-13","tags":["Press Release Migration","Citi-Wide"]},{"summary":"Guiyang - Citibank (China) Co. Ltd (Citi) announced today its Guiyang branch has provided funding in support of establishing libraries or electronic libraries in seven primary and secondary schools in three counties of Guizhou province in Western China. Citi worked with the China Friendship Foundation for Peace and Development and the Guizhou Provincial People's Association for Friendship with Foreign Countries to implement the program. Paul Ouyang, Branch Manager of Citi Guiyang, Hu Jianhuai, Secretary General of China Friendship Foundation for Peace and Development, and Chen Guode, Acting Vice Chairman of Guizhou Provincial People's Association for Friendship with Foreign Countries, attended a donation ceremony in Guiyang.","month":"04","year":"2012","publishDate":"April 18, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"China: Citi Supports Schools in Guizhou Province","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2012/china-citi-supports-schools-in-guihou-province","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"In light of yesterday's vote by shareholders, we wanted to share some information about our CEO's compensation in recent years.","month":"04","author.displayName":["Ed Skyler"],"year":"2012","publishDate":"April 18, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Executive Compensation at Citi","category":"PERSPECTIVES","author.jobTitle":["Executive Vice President | Enterprise Services and Public Affairs"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2012/executive-compensation-at-citi","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"Yesterday, Citi released its 12th annual <a href=\"https://cts.businesswire.com/ct/CT?id=smartlink&url=http%3A%2F%2Fcitizenship.citigroup.com%2Fciti%2Fabout%2Fglobal_citizenship.html&esheet=50241350&lan=en-US&anchor=Global+Citizenship+Report&index=1&md5=df52b29fa23c00be980770156238f27b\">Global Citizenship Report</a>, detailing the bank's progress and performance on key environmental and social indicators. Highlights of the report include Citi surpassing its 2011 goal to reduce greenhouse gas (GHG) emissions by 10% and the Citi Foundation reaching 1.6 million people to date through grants that expand financial inclusion and economic empowerment.","month":"04","author.displayName":["Pam Flaherty"],"year":"2012","publishDate":"April 18, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Releases 2011 Global Citizenship Report","category":"PERSPECTIVES","author.jobTitle":["CEO and President, the Citi Foundation and Director, Corporate Citizenship"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2012/citi-releases-2011-global-citizenship-report","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"Bengaluru - In keeping with the focus to provide a differentiated customer experience, Citi today announced the opening of its fourth Citi Wealth Advisors (CWA) smart broking branch in India and the first in Bengaluru. CWA is the retail business unit of Citigroup Global Markets India Private Limited and aims to serve the growing wealth needs of its customers across the wealth continuum. Located at Umiya Emporium, No-97, Hosur Main Road, Koramangala, the branch was inaugurated by Anand Selvakesari, Country Business Manager, Global Consumer Group, Citi India, in the presence of senior colleagues and clients. CWA now has a total of eight branches nationally, with three of them located in the southern cities of Bengaluru, Chennai and Hyderabad.","month":"04","year":"2012","publishDate":"April 17, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"India: Citi Launches Its First Smart Broking Branch in Bengaluru","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2012/india-citi-launches-its-first-smart-broking-branch-in-bengaluru","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"New York - Citi today released its 12th annual Global Citizenship Report, detailing the bank's progress and performance against key environmental and social indicators. Highlights of the report include Citi surpassing its 2011 goal to reduce greenhouse gas (GHG) emissions by 10 percent and the Citi Foundation reaching 1.6 million people to date through grants that expand financial inclusion and economic empowerment.","month":"04","year":"2012","publishDate":"April 17, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Releases 2011 Global Citizenship Report","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2012/citi-releases-2011-global-citienship-report","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"New York - Citi today announced that Michael E. O'Neill was appointed Chairman of the Board of Directors of Citi following its annual meeting of stockholders in Dallas. In addition, Franz B. Humer and Joan E. Spero were elected by stockholders to Citi's Board of Directors.","month":"04","year":"2012","publishDate":"April 17, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Michael E. O'Neill Named Chairman of Citi","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2012/michael-e-o-neill-named-chairman-of-citi","tags":["Press Release Migration","Citi-Wide"]},{"summary":"In time for its 200th anniversary, Citi has launched an online site that connects thousands of the bank's former employees across the globe. The <a href=\"http://www.citialumninetwork.com\">Citi Alumni Network</a> is a global electronic platform for alumni to reconnect with their former colleagues and keep up to date with news in and around Citi.","month":"04","year":"2012","publishDate":"April 17, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Alumni Network Launched in the Ph