't have any earned income.","month":"03","author.displayName":["Jonathan Clements"],"year":"2012","publishDate":"March 19, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Spousal IRAs: This Tax Season, Don't Forget Hubby","category":"PERSPECTIVES","author.jobTitle":["Director of Financial Education, Citi Personal Wealth Management"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2012/spousal-iras-this-tax-season-dont-forget-hubby","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"While economic data generally has been good, the mean reversion characteristic of the Citi Economic Surprise Index (CESI) from extreme highs or lows inherent in its construction can affect market perceptions about economic activity. The index is aptly named since it compares the reality of data relative to a set of expectations and, not surprisingly, equity markets react to any deviation from forecasts.","image":"638e322aa3c47c530c0a64e1","year":"2012","publishDate":"March 16, 2012","type":"insights","title":"Equity Strategy: March 2012 Chart of the Month","author.jobTitle":["Chief US Equity Strategist, Citi"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2012/equity-strategy-march-2012-chart-of-the-month","tags":["Perspective Migration"],"month":"03","author.displayName":["Tobias Levkovich"],"siteId":"citigpa","category":"PERSPECTIVES"},{"summary":"Caracas - Ernesto Tovar, head of the microeconomics desk at El Universal, won the Citi Journalism Award for Excellence 2012 for his piece, \"MKG usó al menos $109 millones para comprar bonos Pdvsa 2014\" (\"Michael Kenwood Group Used at Least $109 million to buy 2014 PDVSA Bonds\"), published March 13, 2011. Ernesto will join more than 20 reporters from around the world as Venezuela's delegate at a seminar on economic and financial journalism at New York's Columbia University.","month":"03","year":"2012","publishDate":"March 15, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Venezuela: Ernesto J. Tovar Wins Citi Journalism Award for Excellence 2012","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2012/veneuela-ernesto-j-tovar-wins-citi-journalism-award-for-excellence-2012","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"Atlanta - Citi Retail Services and CITGO Petroleum Corporation today announced a multi-year renewal of their long-standing U.S. private label credit card relationship. This extension is the latest in a series of new and renewed partnerships between the recently rebranded Citi Retail Services and leading retailers, such as CITGO, across the country.","month":"03","year":"2012","publishDate":"March 15, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Retail Services Renews Private Label Card Program with CITGO","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2012/citi-retail-services-renews-private-label-card-program-with-citgo","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"Phoenix - Citi announced that on Wednesday, March 14, nearly 1,000 volunteers will give back to the Phoenix community by supporting the work of several local nonprofit organizations. At two events, Citi employees, along with friends and family, will clearly show Citi's commitment to strengthening communities, participating in a number of activities that will make a lasting impact on the area.","month":"03","year":"2012","publishDate":"March 14, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Announces Major Volunteer Effort in Phoenix","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2012/citi-announces-major-volunteer-effort-in-phoenix","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"There has been a great deal of media coverage about the results of the Federal Reserve stress tests that were released yesterday. It is important to make clear that Citi did not 'fail' the stress test. As the report from the Federal Reserve makes clear, Citi has the capital to withstand the 'severe stress scenario' simulated by the Fed.","month":"03","author.displayName":["Edward Skyler"],"year":"2012","publishDate":"March 14, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Statement on Comprehensive Capital Analysis and Review Decision","category":"PERSPECTIVES","author.jobTitle":["Head of Enterprise Services & Public Affairs"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2012/citi-statement-on-comprehensive-capital-analysis-and-review-decision-1","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"Guatemala City - Citi Guatemala and the China-Guatemala Chamber of Cooperation and Trade joined forces recently to present \"Interacting with the Asian Giant,\" a seminar about services and tools the bank offers for doing business directly with China.","month":"03","year":"2012","publishDate":"March 13, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Guatemala Presents Financial Solutions to Promote Business with China","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2012/citi-guatemala-presents-financial-solutions-to-promote-business-with-china","tags":["Press Release Migration","Institutional Clients Group"]},{"summary":"Chongqing - Citibank (China) Co. Ltd. (\"Citi\") and Humana People to People (\"HPP\") today announced the launch of a new initiative known as \"Citi-HPP Wanzhou Rural Small Enterprise Development Program,\" implemented by HPP in cooperation with the Wanzhou District Poverty Alleviation and Development Office. The program will take place in Wanzhou, a district of the city of Chongqing. Made possible by a Citi Foundation grant, the program aims to provide small and growing household enterprises in the district with technical and practical training on sustainable agricultural production and animal husbandry, with the objective of increasing farmers' income levels while generating \"triple bottom-line\"