ion","Citi-Wide"]},{"summary":"With more than half of the world's population now living in urban areas, cities are more important than ever to the world's societal and economic development. For most countries, economic success today hinges on the performance of their cities, as they together generate 80% of the world's GDP; for most global businesses and therefore our clients, expansion strategies are increasingly shifting from a country perspective to a city perspective. And as mass urbanization continues across the world, particularly in growth economies, cities will wield greater and greater influence in the coming years.","month":"03","author.displayName":["Francesco Vanni d'Archirafi"],"year":"2012","publishDate":"March 12, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"New Economist Intelligence Unit report, commissioned by Citi, reveals world's \"Hot Spots\"","category":"PERSPECTIVES","author.jobTitle":["CEO of Citi Holdings and Chairman of the Board of Governors of Junior Achievement Worldwide"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2012/new-economist-intelligence-unit-report-commissioned-by-citi-reveals-worlds-hot-spots","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"As winter turns to spring, many homeowners' thoughts turn to remodeling.","month":"03","author.displayName":["Jonathan Clements"],"year":"2012","publishDate":"March 12, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"When Remodeling Pays--and When It Doesn't","category":"PERSPECTIVES","author.jobTitle":["Director of Financial Education, Citi Personal Wealth Management"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2012/when-remodeling-pays--and-when-it-doesnt","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"Seoul - Citibank Korea today announced its donation of $400,000 to the 'Think Money - Financial Education through Learning and Experience' program for teenagers.","month":"03","year":"2012","publishDate":"March 08, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insight