an, Puerto Rico - The Puerto Rico Housing Finance Authority (PRHFA), in partnership with Citi Community Capital, a department of Citigroup's Municipal Securities Division, has created a revolving loan fund that will provide capital for the construction of for-sale single- and multifamily-homes for low- and moderate-income residents of Puerto Rico. The Puerto Rico Community Development Fund, a subsidiary of the PRHFA, will utilize its 2009 New Markets Tax Credit (NMTC) allocation for the transaction. CBO Financial acted as financial advisor to the PRHFA in securing the NMTC allocation, placing the equity and structuring the fund.","month":"03","year":"2012","publishDate":"March 01, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Puerto Rico Housing Finance Authority and Citi Community Capital Partner to Create Revolving Loan Fund to Finance Affordable Housing Development","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2012/puerto-rico-housing-finance-authority-and-citi-community-capital-partner-to-create-revolving-loan-fund-to-finance-affordable-housing-development","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"The Citi Foundation has played a major role in Haiti's recovery from the massive earthquake that rocked our nation just a few short years ago. Through a $500,000 grant, the Foundation has helped rebuild our country and save lives. Citi Haiti recently had the pleasure of hosting Pam Flaherty, President and CEO of the Citi Foundation, during a visit in which she toured the island and witnessed the recovery effort first-hand.","month":"03","author.displayName":["Gladys Coupet"],"year":"2012","publishDate":"March 01, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Foundation Visits Haiti","category":"PERSPECTIVES","author.jobTitle":["Citi Chief Country Officer, Haiti"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2012/citi-foundation-visits-hai