ikram-pandit-to-present-at-the-citi-2012-financial-services-conference","tags":["Press Release Migration","Citi-Wide"]},{"summary":"Citi's commitment to <a href=\"https://www.citigroup.com/citi/citizen/people/diversity/\">diversity</a> spans the entire company -- and is particularly visible through the activities of Citi's Employee Networks and through the events and activities <a href=\"https://www.archives.gov/eeo/special-observances/\">designated</a> to celebrate the culture, history and contributions of various communities. February, for example, is <strong><a href=\"https://www.africanamericanhistorymonth.gov/\">African American History Month</a></strong>, declared by <a href=\"https://www.whitehouse.gov/the-press-office/2012/01/31/presidential-proclamation-national-african-american-history-month-2012\">Presidential Proclamation</a> as a time to \"celebrate the rich legacy of African Americans and honor the remarkable contributions they have made.\"","month":"02","author.displayName":["Nandika Madgavkar"],"year":"2012","publishDate":"February 28, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Celebrating African American History Month at Citi","category":"PERSPECTIVES","author.jobTitle":["Senior Vice President, Communications, Citi Community Development"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2012/celebrating-african-american-history-month-at-citi","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"Karachi - Citi Pakistan has partnered with the Lahore University of Management Sciences (LUMS) for 'Project Change,' a capacity-building program that aims to create stronger links between universities and industry.","month":"02","year":"2012","publishDate":"February 27, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Pakistan: Citi Joins Hands with Top Management School, LUMS, For Project 'Change'","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2012/pakistan-citi-joins-hands-with-top-management-school-lums-for-project-change-","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"Americans say they expect to retire at age 65. But it turns out that the typical retirement age is actually 62, according to the Employee Benefit Research Institute's 2011 Retirement Confidence Survey.","month":"02","author.displayName":["Jonathan Clements"],"year":"2012","publishDate":"February 27, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Should You Stay Late at the Office?","category":"PERSPECTIVES","author.jobTitle":["Director of Financial Education, Citi Personal Wealth Management"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2012/should-you-stay-late-at-the-office","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"New York - Citi today announced that it will offer Citi credit and debit cardholders an exclusive opportunity to purchase New York Mets single-game tickets to the 2012 season at Citi Field before they go on sale to the general public through an online presale at <a href=\"http://www.Mets.com/CitiPresale\">www.Mets.com/CitiPresale</a>. The two-day promotion begins on Monday, February 27 at 10 a.m. and ends on Tuesday, February 28 at 11:59 p.m.","month":"02","year":"2012","publishDate":"February 24, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi to Offer Cardholders Exclusive Opportunity to Purchase Mets Single Game Tickets Via Online Presale Monday and Tuesday February 27 and 28","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2012/citi-to-offer-cardholders-exclusive-opportunity-to-purchase-mets-single-game-tickets-via-online-presale-monday-and-tuesday-february-27-and-28","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"New York - Citigroup will issue its first quarter results via press release at approximately 8 a.m. (Eastern) on Monday, April 16, 2012. At 11 a.m. (Eastern), results will be reviewed via live webcast and teleconference.","month":"02","year":"2012","publishDate":"February 24, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi First Quarter 2012 Earnings Review","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2012/citi-first-quarter-2012-earnings-review","tags":["Press Release Migration","Citi-Wide"]},{"summary":"Citi recently announced that we are offering credit and debit cardholders an exclusive opportunity to purchase New York Mets single game tickets for the 2012 season at Citi Field before they go on sale to the general public. Cardholders can access the presale online at <a href=\"https://www.mets.com/CitiPresale\">www.Mets.com/CitiPresale</a>. <strong>The two-day promotion begins on Monday, February 27 at 10:00 AM and ends on Tuesday, February 28 at 11:59 PM.</strong>","month":"02","year":"2012","publishDate":"February 24, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi offers cardholders exclusive presale opportunity for Mets single game tickets","category":"PERSPECTIVES","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2012/citi-offers-cardholders-exclusive-presale-opportunity-for-mets-single-game-tickets","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"<em>Citi Community Development and the Latino Economic Development Corporation (LEDC) recently announced a substantial contribution to help small businesses in the District of Columbia access microloans to support business expansion, income growth, and job creation. LEDC's successful micro-lending program provides alternative financing to small businesses, the most important engines of economic growth in the District. Citi's $500,000 commitment will enable LEDC to expand its micro-lending program and increase lending to small businesses by nearly 50 percent over the next year.</em>","month":"02","year":"2012","publishDate":"February 24, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Community Development to Assist LEDC in Boosting Lending to Washington, DC Small Businesses","category":"PERSPECTIVES","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2012/citi-community-development-to-assist-ledc-in-boosting-lending-to-washington-dc-small-businesses","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"New York/Mumbai - Citigroup Inc. today announced it has sold 145.3 million shares in Housing Development Finance Corporation Ltd. (HDFC) through the National Stock Exchange, representing the entirety of its 9.85 percent interest, for INR 657.56 per share. Total proceeds from the transaction are expected to be $1.9 billion at the current exchange rate, resulting in a pre-tax gain to Citigroup of $1.1 billion (INR 54.9 billion) and an after-tax gain of approximately $722 million (INR 35.5 billion).","month":"02","year":"2012","publishDate":"February 23, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citigroup Successfully Executes Sale of 9.85% Interest in HDFC Ltd.","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2012/citigroup-successfully-executes-sale-of-985-interest-in-hdfc-ltd","tags":["Press Release Migration","Citi-Wide"]},{"summary":"Citi Community Capital and Rose Investments, a division of Jonathan Rose Companies, recently announced the launch of a $75 million fund which will preserve affordable housing for low- and moderate-income families across East Coast urban areas. The Rose Green Cities Fund LLC will acquire and renovate existing multifamily properties with cost-effective, high-impact green technologies, preserving their affordability for the long-term. The Fund will target projects in high-demand, mass-transit accessible locations, focusing on locations in Connecticut, New Jersey and the Washington, D.C. metro area.","month":"02","year":"2012","publishDate":"February 23, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Community Capital and Jonathan Rose Companies announce new affordable housing fund","category":"PERSPECTIVES","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2012/citi-community-capital-and-jonathan-rose-companies-announce-new-affordable-housing-fund","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"Hong Kong - Citi in Asia Pacific was awarded best bank from leading industry trade magazines <i>IFR Asia</i>, <i>FinanceAsia</i> and <i>The Asset</i> for 2011 in their recently announced annual best bank awards. Earlier in 2011, Citi picked up best bank from <i>Euromoney</i> in Asia making it a clean sweep for 2011 for Citi in Asia Pacific, the first time the bank has picked up all four in a single year since 2004.","month":"02","year":"2012","publishDate":"February 22, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Sweeps Best Bank in Asia Awards","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2012/citi-sweeps-best-bank-in-asia-awards","tags":["Press Release Migration","Institutional Clients Group","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"The extended April 17 tax-filing deadline is fast approaching--and with it the chance to fund an Individual Retirement Account for the 2011 tax year. In both 2011 and 2012, the maximum annual contribution to all IRAs combined is $5,000, or $6,000 if you're age 50 or older.","month":"02","author.displayName":["Jonathan Clements"],"year":"2012","publishDate":"February 22, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"IRA Contributions: Know Your (Income) Limits","category":"PERSPECTIVES","author.jobTitle":["Director of Financial Education, Citi Personal Wealth Management"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2012/ira-contributions-know-your-income-limits","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"St. Petersburg, Russia - Citi, the world's leading financial corporation, announced partnership with the Graduate School of Management at St. Petersburg University (GSOM SPbU) implementing its Corporate Finance Master's Program.","month":"02","year":"2012","publishDate":"February 21, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Russia: Citi Becomes Key Partner in St. Petersburg University's Master in Corporate Finance Program","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2012/russia-citi-becomes-key-partner-in-st-petersburg-university-s-master-in-corporate-finance-program","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"Washington, D.C. - Today, Citi Community Development and the Latino Economic Development Corporation (LEDC) announced a substantial contribution to help small businesses in the district access microloans to support business expansion, income growth and job creation. LEDC's successful micro-lending program provides alternative financing to small businesses, the most important engines of economic growth in the District of Columbia. Citi's $500,000 commitment will enable LEDC to expand its micro-lending program and increase lending to small businesses by nearly 50 percent over the next year.","month":"02","year":"2012","publishDate":"February 21, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"U.S.: Citi Community Development to Assist LEDC in Boosting Lending to Washington, D.C. Small Businesses","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2012/us-citi-community-development-to-assist-ledc-in-boosting-lending-to-washington-dc-small-businesses","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"It's tax season, and for millions of low-income taxpayers, tax refunds through the Earned Income Tax Credit (EITC) program provide a vital financial boost. Last year, hardworking individuals and families who filed their taxes received $59 billion in EITC refunds. Yet 20 percent of eligible taxpayers are still not claiming the EITC, leaving billions of dollars on the table that could be used to increase family savings, invest in small businesses, or meet college expenses. To ensure that as many families as possible benefit from 