"Imagine a couple, both age 65, who have just retired. They have $400,000 in long-term corporate bonds that are yielding 5%, giving them $20,000 in annual interest.","month":"01","author.displayName":["Jonathan Clements"],"year":"2012","publishDate":"January 09, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"How Inflation Could Derail Your Retirement","category":"PERSPECTIVES","author.jobTitle":["Director of Financial Education, Citi Personal Wealth Management"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2012/how-inflation-could-derail-your-retirement","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"New York - Citi Chief Executive Officer Michael Corbat today announced the roles and responsibilities of the members of his management team and appointed Jamie Forese and Manuel Medina-Mora as Co-Presidents of Citi. Mr. Forese will be responsible for all of Citi's Institutional businesses, and Mr. Medina-Mora will continue to oversee Global Consumer Banking and Citi's franchise in Mexico. The Operations & Technology functions supporting the Institutional and Consumer businesses will now directly report to Mr. Forese and Mr. Medina-Mora, respectively, to better align the functions with the priorities of each business and improve efficiency.","month":"01","year":"2012","publishDate":"January 07, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi CEO Michael Corbat Announces Management Team","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2012/citi-ceo-michael-corbat-announces-management-team-1","tags":["Press Release Migration","Citi-Wide"]},{"summary":"Today, Citi Chief Economist Willem Buiter will be awarded an honorary doctorate by the University of Amsterdam for his research in the field of macro-economics. A native of the Netherlands, Buiter joined Citi in January of 2010. Prior to his work at Citi, Buiter was Professor of Political Economy at the London School of Economics. He has served in many public service capacities, including Chief Economist for the European Bank for Reconstruction & Development and as an external member of the Monetary Policy Committee of the Bank of England. He has been a consultant to the IMF, the World Bank, the Inter-American Development Bank and the Asian Development Bank, the European Commission and an advisor to many central banks and finance ministries.","month":"01","year":"2012","publishDate":"January 06, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi's Buiter to receive honorary degree","category":"PERSPECTIVES","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2012/citis-buiter-to-receive-honorary-degree","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"Sofia, Bulgaria - Supported by Citi Foundation, the Financial Education Project aims to strengthen the financial capability of low-income households, so they can protect their scarce resources and build assets through smart debt decisions.","month":"01","year":"2012","publishDate":"January 05, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Mikrofond AD, Microfinance Centre and Citi Foundation Support Financial Inclusion of Low-Income Individuals in Bulgaria","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2012/mikrofond-ad-microfinance-centre-and-citi-foundation-support-financial-inclusion-of-low-income-individuals-in-bulgaria","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"month":"01","year":"2012","publishDate":"January 04, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"On the Women & Co. Blog: Re-Gifting and the Truth About Tipping","category":"PERSPECTIVES","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2012/on-the-women-co-blog-re-gifting-and-the-truth-about-tipping","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"New York - Citi today announced the first Facebook application from a loyalty program that is both a rewarding <i>and</i> social experience: the Citi ThankYou® Point Sharing App. This new Facebook app makes it quick and easy for ThankYou® Rewards members who are Facebook friends to pool their points together and use their points' collective value towards a shared goal or reward. ThankYou members on Facebook can combine their points to make a charitable donation, or choose from millions of rewards on <a href=\"http://www.thankyou.com\">www.thankyou.com</a>, from travel to electronics.","month":"01","year":"2012","publishDate":"January 03, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Introduces First Facebook App to Make Rewards Social","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2012/citi-introduces-first-facebook-app-to-make-rewards-social","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"Here's a resolution for the New Year: As we make financial choices in 2012, let's try to stay focused on the bigger picture. To that end, we might want to keep these five financial principles in mind:","month":"01","author.displayName":["Jonathan Clements"],"year":"2012","publishDate":"January 03, 2012","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Five Financial Principles","category":"PERSPECTIVES","author.jobTitle":["Director of Financial Education, Citi Personal Wealth Management"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2012/five-financial-principles","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"This policy brief outlines the various financial barriers that low-income and first-generation students face when trying to fund their higher education. It also highlights successful programs, including Financial Aid U, that have been able to increase access to the much-needed financial aid, grants, scholarships and other tuition support.","image":"637217b80de6635088314fe8","month":"01","destinationLink":"https://www.citigroup.com/rcs/citigpa/storage/public/Strengthening_Higher_Education_Access_Affordability.pdf","year":"2012","publishDate":"January 01, 2012","site