,"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2011/qa-with-rainforest-alliances-tensie-whelan","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"This week, we announced that Citi Retail Services will be the new name for Citi's U.S. private label credit card business, formerly known as Citi Retail Partner Cards.","month":"12","author.displayName":["Bill Johnson"],"year":"2011","publishDate":"December 16, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"A New Beginning","category":"PERSPECTIVES","author.jobTitle":["EVP, Managing Director, Global Consumer Bank"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2011/a-new-beginning","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"Singapore - A new institute for training treasury executives will open its doors in Singapore this year. The Association for Financial Professionals (AFP) and Citi announced the joint launch of the AFP-Citi Asia Pacific Treasury Management Institute to advance the treasury profession in the region through a world-class training and skills enhancement certificate program.","month":"12","year":"2011","publishDate":"December 15, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi and the Association for Financial Professionals Launch Asia Pacific Treasury Management Institute","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/citi-and-the-association-for-financial-professionals-launch-asia-pacific-treasury-management-institute","tags":["Press Release Migration","Institutional Clients Group"]},{"summary":"Budapest, Hungary - The new Citi Life credit card program with extended benefits to resonate with the needs of today's customer provides a 3 percent return on food retail purchases, a 2 percent return on petrol spends and a 1 percent return on all other retail purchases across Hungary in addition to existing program benefits. The new Citi Life cards are designed to allow for a safe contactless payment at PayPass terminals for purchases