ngary's credit card holders are the first in the country to have access to the free Internet Secure Code Service (3-D Secure technology) that greatly enhances the security of online purchases through participating merchant networks. Citi Life, Malév-Citibank and Shell-Citibank co-brand cardholders who subscribe to Citibank's SMS Alert Service for monitoring card transactions have automated access to this free service. The service can be conveniently activated by calling the 24-hour CitiPhone Banking hotline.","month":"12","year":"2011","publishDate":"December 13, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citibank Hungary Launches Another First in the Market: Unique Free Internet Secure Code Service to Enhance Online Purchase Security","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/citibank-hungary-launches-another-first-in-the-market-unique-free-internet-secure-code-service-to-enhance-online-purchase-security","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"month":"12","year":"2011","publishDate":"December 13, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"On the Women & Co. blog: 5 Tips for Traveling Abroad & Recession-Proof Gifting","category":"PERSPECTIVES","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2011/on-the-women-co-blog-5-tips-for-traveling-abroad-recession-proof-gifting","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"Bahrain - Eight school teams have participated in inJAz Bahrain Banks in Action (BIA) Competition, which was held at Citibank's headquarters at the Seef District on December 12, 2011. Citibank, a long-time partner of inJAz Bahrain, hosted the \"Banks in Action\" competition for the third consecutive year.","month":"12","year":"2011","publishDate":"December 12, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"inJAz Bahrain, Citibank Hold Banks in Action Competition","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/inja-bahrain-citibank-hold-banks-in-action-competition-2","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"Citi today announced the launch of a new program, in collaboration with Raza Development Fund (RDF), to support its community development lending programs that serve Latino and low-income families across the Southwestern United States. Under this program, named the Southwest Community Development Initiative, RDF will deploy $100 million in capital over five years for community development projects in border counties and cities in South Texas, Arizona and California. The program, made possible in part by a $1 million capacity-building grant from the Citi Foundation, will help RDF advance its work in increasing affordable housing, education and health services opportunities for low- to-moderate-income Latino communities.","month":"12","year":"2011","publishDate":"December 12, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi and Raza Development Fund Announce Initiative to Strengthen Latino Communities in the Southwest","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/foundation/news/press-release/2011/citi-and-raa-development-fund-announce-initiative-to-strengthen-latino-communities-in-the-southwest","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance","Institutional Clients Group"]},{"summary":"With nine Appropriations bills not yet passed, a Continuing Resolution (CR) that expires December 16, extended unemployment benefits and a payroll tax holiday on the brink of expiration, as well as the so-called \"doc fix\" - Medicare reimbursement rates for doctors - looming, many will be surprised to learn that Congress will likely check off its list long before DC observers get through their own holiday shopping.","month":"12","author.displayName":["Candi Wolff"],"year":"2011","publishDate":"December 12, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Congress' End Game","category":"PERSPECTIV