ion Day at Citi Pond","category":"PERSPECTIVES","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2011/citi-honors-veterans-and-active-service-members-with-military-appreciation-day-at-citi-pond","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"Last week, Citi CEO Vikram Pandit signed the Statement of Employer Support for the Guard & Reserve as part of Citi's overall effort to provide America's men and women in uniform with opportunities in the financial services sector, and to ensure that military families around the country have the support they need. The Statement reinforces our commitment to those who choose to serve their country through the Guard and Reserve.","image":"638e2faea3c47c530c0a58fc","month":"11","year":"2011","publishDate":"November 11, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi CEO Vikram Pandit signs Statement of Employer Support for the Guard & Reserve","category":"PERSPECTIVES","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2011/citi-ceo-vikram-pandit-signs-statement-of-employer-support-for-the-guard-reserve","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"Singapore - Citi today cleared its first interest rate swaps on LCH.Swapclear for clients in the Asia Pacific (APAC) region. The firm has now cleared more than US$28 billion in notional interest rate swaps for its clients across the Americas, Europe and now APAC. In addition to successfully clearing interest rate swaps on LCH.Swapclear, Citi has successfully cleared interest rate and credit default swaps on the Chicago Mercantile Exchange (CME) and has successfully cleared credit default swaps on ICE Clear Credit.","month":"11","year":"2011","publishDate":"November 10, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Clears First Asian Trades on LCH.Swapclear","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/citi-clears-first-asian-trades-on-lchswapclear","tags":["Press Release Migration","Institutional Clients Group"]},{"summary":"New York - Manuel Medina-Mora, Chief Executive Officer of Citi's Global Consumer Banking unit, will present at the Bank of America Merrill Lynch Banking and Financial Services Conference on Wednesday, November 16, 2011. The presentation is expected to begin at approximately 8 a.m. (EST). A live webcast of the presentation will be available at <a href=\"https://www.citigroup.com/citi/fin/\">http://www.citigroup.com/citi/fin/</a>. Presentation materials will be available for download 30 minutes prior to the event. A replay of the webcast will be available at <a href=\"https://www.citigroup.com/citi/fin/pres.htm\">http://www.citigroup.com/citi/fin/pres.htm</a>.","month":"11","year":"2011","publishDate":"November 10, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Manuel Medina-Mora, CEO of Citi Global Consumer Banking, to Present at the Bank of America Merrill Lynch 2011 Banking and Financial Services Conference","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/manuel-medina-mora-ceo-of-citi-global-consumer-banking-to-present-at-the-bank-of-america-merrill-lynch-2011-banking-and-financial-services-conference","tags":["Press Release Migration","Citi-Wide"]},{"summary":"New York, N.Y. - Citi will honor veterans and active duty members of the U.S. Armed Forces, along with their families, in a Veterans Day remembrance and celebration at Citi Pond at Bryant Park on November 11 at 8 a.m. All branches of the military will be represented at a ceremony with former United States Marine and Major League Baseball Hall of Fame pitcher Tom Seaver, 2011 Rock and Roll Hall of Fame inductee Darlene Love, and other honored guests. The event is to thank all the military men and women for their service and sacrifice on behalf of the U.S.","month":"11","year":"2011","publishDate":"November 10, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"U.S.: Citi to Honor Veterans and Active Service Members with Military Appreciation Day at Citi Pond at Bryant Park","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/us-citi-to-honor-veterans-and-active-service-members-with-military-appreciation-day-at-citi-pond-at-bryant-park","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"We are pleased to share this year's Green Jobs Award winners, who will be celebrated at an awards reception at Citi's offices in New York City tonight. These private businesses are providing significant contributions to both the economy and the environment within their communities and beyond. The Green Jobs Award program and the winners of this nationally recognized award are helping to define the emerging clean economy with solid examples of successful businesses with both sustainable business models and highly engaged employees. The Citi Foundation has been the primary supporter of the program since its inception last year.","month":"11","author.displayName":["Erin Payne"],"year":"2011","publishDate":"November 10, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"2011 Green Jobs Award Winners Announced","category":"PERSPECTIVES","author.jobTitle":["Program Associate, SJF Institute"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2011/2011-green-jobs-award-winners-announced","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"San Francisco - Though many Californians do not expect significant economic improvement in 2012, the majority are prepared for continued challenges and adjusting their spending and saving habits, according to the latest Citi California Pulse®. Additionally, Citibank's latest quarterly survey found that the majority of Californians (63 percent) continue to rate the state as an excellent or good place to live.","month":"11","year":"2011","publishDate":"November 09, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi California Pulse® Survey Finds Majority of Californians Prepared for Prolonged Economic Challenges","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/citi-california-pulse-survey-finds-majority-of-californians-prepared-for-prolonged-economic-challenges","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"Guatemala City - Citi Guatemala has opened a new branch in Guatemala City, which will serve more than 5,500 customers. Located at Portales Mall in Carretera Al Atlántico zona, 17 Plaza Financiera, the branch is open Monday to Friday from 9 a.m. to 6 p.m. and on Saturdays from 9 a.m. to 1 p.m.","month":"11","year":"2011","publishDate":"November 08, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Opens New Branch in Guatemala City","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/citi-opens-new-branch-in-guatemala-city","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"New York - On November 10 from 6-8 p.m., SJF Institute will recognize the 2011 Green Jobs Award honorees at a reception at the Citi Executive Conference Center keynoted by Jonathan Greenblatt, the Director of the White House Office of Social Innovation and Civic Participation. The Green Jobs Award honors private businesses that contribute to both the economy and the environment. Applicants are judged on their contribution to environmental quality, the quality of their jobs and benefits, the diversity of employment opportunities and their level of community engagement.","month":"11","year":"2011","publishDate":"November 08, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"2011 Green Jobs Award Honorees Announced","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/foundation/news/press-release/2011/2011-green-jobs-award-honorees-announced","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"New York - The Equator Principles Association, World Wildlife Fund (WWF) and the Business and Biodiversity Offsets Program (BBOP) today announced the