pens New Branch in Wuxi","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/citi-opens-new-branch-in-wuxi","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"Irving, Texas - The Citi Team USA Flag Tour made its second stop today in Irving, one of Citi's largest sites in the United States, where two-time Olympian Jeremy Wariner (track and field) and Paralympian Gina McWilliams (Paralympic sitting volleyball) joined Citi Site President Rodney Phelps, Citi employees, and members of the Carrollton Farmers Branch Independent School District's Ranchview High School Drumline and Track team in celebration and support of Team USA and the athletes' journeys to the London 2012 Olympic Games.","month":"11","year":"2011","publishDate":"November 03, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Team USA Flag Tour Stops in Irving to Celebrate Sponsorship of 2012 U.S. Olympic & Paralympic Teams","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/citi-team-usa-flag-tour-stops-in-irving-to-celebrate-sponsorship-of-2012-us-olympic-paralympic-teams","tags":["Press Release Migration","Citi-Wide"]},{"summary":"In a new <a href=\"https://blog.womenandco.com/2011/11/rosy-or-gloomy.html\">blog post</a>, Women & Co.'s Cassandra Pare discusses how recent Citibank survey results reveal U.S. women are remaining optimistic about their personal financial situations, in spite of the country's daunting economic outlook.","month":"11","year":"2011","publishDate":"November 03, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"On the Women & Co. Blog: Rosy or Gloomy?","category":"PERSPECTIVES","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2011/on-the-women-co-blog-rosy-or-gloomy","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"Today, the Citi Team USA Flag Tour made its second stop in Irving, one of Citi's largest sites in the United States, where two-time Olympian Jeremy Wariner (track and field) and Paralympian Gina McWilliams (Paralympic sitting volleyball) joined Citi Site President Rodney Phelps, Citi employees, and members of the Carrollton Farmers Branch Independent School District's Ranchview High School Drumline and Track team in celebration and support of Team USA and the athletes' journeys to the London 2012 Olympic Games.","month":"11","year":"2011","publishDate":"November 03, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Team USA Flag-Raising Tour stops in Irving to celebrate sponsorship of 2012 U.S. Olympic & Paralympic Teams","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/citi-team-usa-flag-raising-tour-stops-in-irving-to-celebrate-sponsorship-of-2012-us-olympic-paralymp"},{"summary":"On October 22nd, Citi's Institutional Clients Group (ICG) hosted a day of family activities as part of our bank's sixth annual Global Community Day. Among other events in the New York City area, Citi partnered with the New York Police and Fire Widows' and Children's Benefit Fund and gathered on Manhattan's Pier 46 to learn life-safety skills from the Fire Department of New York. There were over 500 people in attendance partaking in the family fun day.","month":"11","author.displayName":["Ed Skyler"],"year":"2011","publishDate":"November 02, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi's Institutional Clients Group hosts Family Fun Day for Global Community Day","category":"PERSPECTIVES","author.jobTitle":["Executive Vice President | Enterprise Services and Public Affairs"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2011/citis-institutional-clients-group-hosts-family-fun-day-for-global-community","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"Sandip Sen, Citi's Managing Director & Global Head of Alternative Energy, has published a piece on the American Council on Renewable Energy's blog. In the post, The Global Race for Sustainable Energy, he writes, in part:","month":"11","year":"2011","publishDate":"November 02, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Sandip Sen writes on sustainable energy","category":"PERSPECTIVES","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2011/sandip-sen-writes-on-sustainable-energy","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"Langley Park, Md. - Today, Citi Community Development and CASA de Maryland (CASA) launched an innovative microloan program for legal permanent residents (LPRs) seeking to become naturalized citizens. CASA will collaborate with two community development financial institutions (CDFI's) - the <a href=\"http://www.ledcmetro.org/\">Latino Economic Development Corporation</a> (LEDC) and the <a href=\"http://www.ecdcinternational.org/\">Ethiopian Community Development Council Enterprise Development Group</a> (EDG) - to launch and test the innovative citizenship microloan program that will lower the financial barriers to naturalization while simultaneously building an individual's credit and financial literacy. The loan program is the latest addition to a set of naturalization services available through Citizenship Maryland, a wrap-around comprehensive effort led by CASA and participated in by partner AmeriCorps volunteer host organizations that seek to support the hundreds of thousands of eligible legal permanent residents in Maryland become citizens.","month":"11","year":"2011","publishDate":"November 01, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"U.S.: Innovative Microloan Product to Ease Pathway to Citizenship for Legal Immigrants","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/us-innovative-microloan-product-to-ease-pathway-to-citienship-for-legal-immigrants","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"Hanoi, Vietnam - Citibank Vietnam announced today its partnership with Prudential Vietnam Assurance to offer an integrated insurance-banking package for greater customer convenience.","month":"11","year":"2011","publishDate":"November 01, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citibank-Prudential Vietnam Assurance Partnership to Offer Greater Convenience to Customers","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/citibank-prudential-vietnam-assurance-partnership-to-offer-greater-convenience-to-customers","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"Frankfurt am Main, Germany - Today, the Technical Relief Agency of the German government (Bundesanstalt Technisches Hilfswerk, THW) started a pilot project in the area of procurement with Citigroup Global Transaction Services (GTS). The objective: increasing the efficiency of the federal agency's payment mechanisms by working with GTS.","month":"11","year":"2011","publishDate":"November 01, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"German Technical Relief Agency (THW) Uses Citigroup's Cashless Payment System","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/german-technical-relief-agency-thw-uses-citigroup-s-cashless-payment-system","tags":["Press Release Migration","Institutional Clients Group"]},{"summary":"Citi Pakistan has been awarded the Best Community Program Award for its initiative, 'Beyond Sustainability: Driving poverty alleviation through microfinance in Pakistan' in the Poverty Alleviation category of the Asian Corporate Social Responsibility Awards 2011, which were held in conjunction with Intel. Citi Pakistan was competing against 175 entries from 129 companies in 14 countries for this award.","month":"10","year":"2011","publishDate":"October 31, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Pakistan Wins 'Best Community Program' at the Asian CSR Awards 2011","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/citi-pakistan-wins-best-community-program-at-the-asian-csr-awards-2011","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"It's important that children grow up to be prudent managers of their own money, including learning how to save diligently.","month":"10","author.displayName":["Jonathan Clements"],"year":"2011","publishDate":"October 31, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Teaching kids about money","category":"PERSPECTIVES","author.jobTitle":["Director of Financial Education, Citi Personal Wealth Management"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2011/teaching-kids-about-money","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"In a new <a href=\"https://blog.womenandco.com/2011/10/late-fee-free.html\">blog post</a>, Women & Co.'s Linda Descano discusses how strategically adjusting credit card due dates can save time and reduce the chance of missing a payment. Also, Gabby Phillips wants to know if your company made the 2011 Working Mother 100 Best Companies list in \"<a href=\"https://blog.womenandco.com/2011/10/did-you-make-the-cut.html\">Did You Make The Cut?</a>.\"","month":"10","year":"2011","publishDate":"October 28, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"On the Women & Co. blog: avoiding late fees and Working Mother's 100 Best Companies","category":"PERSPECTIVES","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2011/on-the-women-co-blog-avoiding-late-fees-and-working-mothers-100-best-companies","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"Albuquerque, New Mexico - Today, Citi Community Development and the Albuquerque-based <a href=\"http://rgcdc.org/\">Rio Grande Community Development Corporation</a> (RGCDC) announced that they will work together to launch \"Los Mercados: Collaboration for Small Business,\" an innovative program that will enable start-up food-service entrepreneurs in the Albuquerque area to increase market penetration through peer collaboration.","month":"10","year":"2011","publishDate":"October 27, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"U.S.: Albuquerque Business Incubator Launches Platform Allowing Emerging Entrepreneurs to Collaborate on Marketing and Co-Distribution Efforts","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/us-albuquerque-business-incubator-launches-platform-allowing-emerging-entrepreneurs-to-collaborate-on-marketing-and-co-distribution-efforts","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"Kuwait City - For the third year in a row, the Citi Foundation, Citi's social investment arm, and the College of Business Administration (CBA) at Kuwait University are cooperating to offer the Citi-Financial Market Trading Program (Citi-FMTP), which trains CBA's top students on real-life dealing-room simulations. The course culminates with a degree in financial market trading. Thirty CBS students will be taking part in the first round of this market-leading training program this year.","month":"10","year":"2011","publishDate":"October 26, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Kuwait University and Citi Foundation Launch 2011 Financial Market Trading Program","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/foundation/news/press-release/2011/kuwait-university-and-citi-foundation-launch-2011-financial-market-trading-program","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"Hungary, Budapest - NESsT and Citibank Hungary today announced the launch of their third joint social-enterprise-developing program in the for-profit sector. Ten businesses will be selected in a tender closing on November 14 to participate in this comprehensive management training and financing program. Applications of those businesses will be considered, which in addition to generating profit also aim to solve critical social problems by improving local communities through increased employment opportunities, access to health and education services, reduced energy and resource consumption, or other environmental programs.","month":"10","year":"2011","publishDate":"October 26, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"NESsT and Citibank Hungary Launch 2011 For-Profit Social Enterprise Development Program","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/foundation/news/press-release/2011/nesst-and-citibank-hungary-launch-2011-for-profit-social-enterprise-development-program","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"This Friday, October 28th, Citi Pond® at Bryant Park will open for its seventh season inviting guests to \"Take a Snow Day\" in New York City's premier winter wonderland, featuring ice skating, holiday shopping, dining and entertainment. For the 2011 - 2012 season, visitors will take part in newly unveiled programming and events, in addition to Citi Passport rewards program offering Citi cardmembers savings and exclusive access at The Holiday Shops, Celsius and select neighborhood retail destinations. This season also marks the completion of the permanent power facility project in Bryant Park, inaugurating a major green energy initiative for Citi Pond, Bryant Park and the surrounding neighborhood.","month":"10","year":"2011","publishDate":"October 26, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Pond® at Bryant Park kicks-off its seventh season inviting guests to \"Take A Snow Day\"","category":"PERSPECTIVES","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2011/citi-pond-at-bryant-park-kicks-off-its-seventh-season-inviting-guests-to-take-a-snow-day","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"I am proud to work for Citi, an organization that has such a strong and active commitment to diversity, both internally and in our communities. Earlier this year, I had the opportunity to spend time with the nearly 300 affiliate members of the <a href=\"https://www.nclr.org/\">National Council of La Raza \n </a>(NCLR), the nation's largest Latino civil rights and advocacy organization and a longstanding partner of Citi's. For many years, we have worked with NCLR to enable its member organizations to advance economic empowerment and asset building for underserved members of society.","month":"10","author.displayName":["Salvador Villar"],"year":"2011","publishDate":"October 26, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Enabling the American Dream, across the spectrum","category":"PERSPECTIVES","author.jobTitle":["Chairman and CEO, Banamex USA"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2011/enabling-the-american-dream-across-the-spectrum","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"Hong Kong - In an independent report commissioned by Citi's Securities and Fund Services and Mirae Asset Global Investments, Asia's assets under management are expected to nearly double, reaching US$4 trillion by 2015, underpinned by a growing emerging-affluent segment, new pools of insurance and retirement assets, and increased interest from foreign investors.","month":"10","year":"2011","publishDate":"October 25, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Asia's Emerging Affluent to Drive Asset Management's Growth","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/asia-s-emerging-affluent-to-drive-asset-management-s-growth","tags":["Press Release Migration","Institutional Clients Group"]},{"summary":"New York - Manhattan's celebrated holiday epicenter, Citi Pond<sup>SM</sup> at Bryant Park opens for its seventh season on Friday, October 28, inviting guests to \"Take a Snow Day\" in New York City's premier winter wonderland, featuring ice skating, holiday shopping, dining and entertainment. For the 2011 - 2012 season, visitors will take part in newly unveiled programming and events, in addition to Citi Passport rewards program offering Citi cardmembers savings and exclusive access at The Holiday Shops, Celsius and select neighborhood retail destinations. This season also marks the completion of the permanent power facility project in Bryant Park, inaugurating a major green energy initiative for Citi Pond, Bryant Park and the surrounding neighborhood.","month":"10","year":"2011","publishDate":"October 24, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"U.S.: Citi Pond at Bryant Park Kicks-Off Its Seventh Season Inviting Guests to \"Take a Snow Day\"","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/us-citi-pond-at-bryant-park-kicks-off-its-seventh-season-inviting-guests-to-take-a-snow-day","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"Atlanta, Ga. - Today, Citi announced a multi-year renewal of its long-standing U.S. private-label credit card agreement with Sears Holdings Corporation, the nation's fourth-largest retailer. Sears Holdings' retail brands include Sears, the leading home appliance retailer in North America, Kmart and Lands' End, the nation's largest online apparel retailer.","month":"10","year":"2011","publishDate":"October 24, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Renews U.S. Private-Label Card Agreement with Sears Holdings Corporation","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/citi-renews-us-private-label-card-agreement-with-sears-holdings-corporation","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"New York - Citi today announced it has launched a new, firm-wide series entitled Citi Global Perspectives & Solutions (GPS). This thought-leadership product suite is designed to deliver insights and viewpoints on compelling issues and structural thematic trends in the global economy. The series was developed as a means to deliver the depth of strategic thought that exists across Citi to a wide audience, including institutional investors, corporate, public sector and individuals. Citi GPS will provide clients with the basis of informed dialogue on key topics of global relevance.","month":"10","year":"2011","publishDate":"October 24, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Launches Thought Leadership Product Suite, Citi Global Perspectives & Solutions","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/citi-launches-thought-leadership-product-suite-citi-global-perspectives-solutions","tags":["Press Release Migration","Citi-Wide"]},{"summary":"Washington, D.C. - Today, Capital Area Asset Builders (CAAB) and Citi Community Development formally announced the new Jobs &amp; Entrepreneurship Stimulus Account (JESA) program, an accelerated Individual Development Account (IDA) savings program for individuals who agree to save $500 towards their small business or job-training costs.","month":"10","year":"2011","publishDate":"October 24, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"U.S.: CAAB and Citi Using Innovative Savings Model and Training to Boost Entrepreneurship, Job Readiness and Financial Capability","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/us-caab-and-citi-using-innovative-savings-model-and-training-to-boost-entrepreneurship-job-readiness-and-financial-capability","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"Bahrain - Under the patronage of HE Rasheed M. Al Maraj, Governor of the Central Bank of Bahrain, Citibank today inaugurated its Amwaj Islands Branch in the presence of several dignitaries and officials.","month":"10","year":"2011","publishDate":"October 24, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Under the Patronage of HE Rasheed Al Maraj, Central Bank of Bahrain Governor, Citibank Inaugurates Amwaj Islands Branch","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/under-the-patronage-of-he-rasheed-al-maraj-central-bank-of-bahrain-governor-citibank-inaugurates-amwaj-islands-branch","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"Voluntary service is at the core of who we are as Americans. It is our nature to help our neighbors in times of struggle and to work together to establish \"our more perfect union.\"","month":"10","author.displayName":["Michelle Nunn"],"year":"2011","publishDate":"October 24, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Partners with Points of Light to Celebrate the Power of Service","category":"PERSPECTIVES","author.jobTitle":["CEO of Points of Light"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2011/citi-partners-with-points-of-light-to-celebrate-the-power-of-service","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"The U.S. savings rate was 4.5% of disposable personal income in August, the latest month for which data is available, according to the Commerce Department's Bureau of Economic Analysis. That's far better than it was in 2005, when the monthly savings rate bounced around between 1% and 2%, but below May 2008's 8.3%, when we recorded the highest monthly savings rate since the early 1990s. Even as Americans endeavor to save regularly, they are trying to get their debts under control. The New York Federal Reserve reported that total consumer borrowing amounted to $11.4 trillion at the end of 2011's second quarter, well below the $12.5 trillion peak that was hit in 2008's third quarter.","month":"10","author.displayName":["Jonathan Clements"],"year":"2011","publishDate":"October 24, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Why saving can be a bargain","category":"PERSPECTIVES","author.jobTitle":["Director of Financial Education, Citi Personal Wealth Management"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2011/why-saving-can-be-a-bargain","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"New York - Citi volunteers around the world will demonstrate their commitment to service during the company's sixth annual \"Global Community Day,\" on Saturday, October 22. In 78 countries around the world, an expected 40,000 Citi employee volunteers will participate in nearly 1,100 local service projects.","month":"10","year":"2011","publishDate":"October 22, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"40,000 Citi Employee Volunteers in 78 Countries to Answer Call to Service as Part of Company's Sixth Annual \"Global Community Day\"","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/40000-citi-employee-volunteers-in-78-countries-to-answer-call-to-service-as-part-of-company-s-sixth-annual-global-community-day","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"Yesterday evening, Citi CEO Vikram Pandit was honored by ACCION, a nonprofit pioneer and leader in global microfinance, at its 50th anniversary dinner. Committed to bringing the benefits of financial services to the underserved and unbanked, ACCION has lifted countless individuals, families and communities out of poverty. And Citi, ACCION's longest-tenured corporate partner, has been their partner every step of the way for more than 45 years.","month":"10","year":"2011","publishDate":"October 21, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Microfinance pioneer ACCION celebrates its 50th anniversary, honors Citi CEO Vikram Pandit","category":"PERSPECTIVES","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2011/microfinance-pioneer-accion-celebrates-its-50th-anniversary-honors-citi-ceo-vikram-pandit","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"If you're a frequent visitor to new.citi.com, you've seen the work of some of the brightest minds in the company. Citi's Investment Research & Analysis (CIRA) division covers global markets and industry sectors, providing top-notch insight and critical analysis. Earlier this month, 26 of our equity analysts were recognized by Institutional Investor's All-America Research Team annual poll. CIRA also moved up two spots in market share to top five, an improvement reflective of the hard work of our analysts and macro strategists.","month":"10","year":"2011","publishDate":"October 21, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi researchers honored","category":"PERSPECTIVES","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2011/citi-researchers-honored","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"New York, N.Y. - Tonight ACCION International, the microfinance pioneer, celebrated its 50th anniversary and the 20th anniversary of ACCION in the United States at Cipriani 42nd Street in New York City. The event raised more than $1.6 million for this important work.","month":"10","year":"2011","publishDate":"October 20, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Microfinance Pioneer ACCION Marks 50th Birthday with New York Gala; Citigroup CEO Vikram Pandit Honored","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/microfinance-pioneer-accion-marks-50th-birthday-with-new-york-gala-citigroup-ceo-vikram-pandit-honored","tags":["Press Release Migration","Citi-Wide"]},{"summary":"Budapest - Citibank Hungary is planting another 15,000 trees this autumn in and around Budapest, continuing the company's Plant-a-Tree Program launched in 2008. At the launch of this initiative, Citibank promised to plant a tree for every one of its Consumer and SME customers who switches to paperless e-statements, driving environmentally friendly behavior among its customers and playing a part in efforts to conserve the forests in partnership with customers, NGOs and forestry companies.","month":"10","year":"2011","publishDate":"October 20, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Hungary: 15,000 Trees Planted This Fall in Citibank's 2011 Plant-a-Tree Program","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/hungary-15000-trees-planted-this-fall-in-citibank-s-2011-plant-a-tree-program","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"While some may be concerned by the latest survey results from the National Federation of Independent Business (NFIB), the numbers do not indicate dire trends. Yes, the data has been softer than expected across a wide spectrum--including leading indices and weak ISM orders. But in the recently released small business poll, there are a few positive surprises buried in the details that should alleviate some of the anxiety evident within the investment community.","month":"10","author.displayName":["Tobias Levkovich"],"year":"2011","publishDate":"October 20, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Large insights from small sources","category":"PERSPECTIVES","author.jobTitle":["Chief US Equity Strategist, Citi"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2011/large-insights-from-small-sources","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"Mumbai - Citi India today announced that it has partnered with 12 non-governmental organizations (NGOs) in 2011 towards social development projects to promote economic empowerment in India. Citi India has sharpened its focus around the concept of economic inclusion, which integrates financial inclusion, market access and financial education. This concept addresses each stage of the economic cycle of a household, thereby creating truly economically empowered communities.","month":"10","year":"2011","publishDate":"October 19, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi India Partners with 12 NGOs for Economic Inclusion Projects in 2011","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/foundation/news/press-release/2011/citi-india-partners-with-12-ngos-for-economic-inclusion-projects-in-2011","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"New York - Citigroup Inc. (NYSE: C) announced today that one of its U.S. broker-dealer affiliates, Citigroup Global Markets Inc. (CGMI), has agreed to a settlement with the U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission resolving the SEC's industry-wide investigation of certain collateralized debt obligations (CDOs). The agreement is subject to court approval. Citigroup is fully reserved for this matter as of September 30, 2011.","month":"10","year":"2011","publishDate":"October 19, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citigroup Announces Class V Settlement","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/citigroup-announces-class-v-settlement","tags":["Press Release Migration","Citi-Wide"]},{"summary":"New York - The Board of Directors of Citigroup Inc. today declared a quarterly dividend on the company's common stock of $0.01 per share, payable on November 23, 2011 to stockholders of record on November 7, 2011.","month":"10","year":"2011","publishDate":"October 19, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citigroup Declares Dividends","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/citigroup-declares-dividends-9","tags":["Press Release Migration","Citi-Wide"]},{"summary":"Budapest - Citibank is pleased to be among the first financial institutions to join the Combined Credit with Guarantee (CCG) Program announced by Hungary's National Development Office. Citibank's small to medium-enterprise (SME) clients who wish to participate in the CCG Program can manage their Economic Operational Program and Central Hungary Operational Program-related tender documentation, submission and loan application through Citibank in a convenient one-stop shop.","month":"10","year":"2011","publishDate":"October 19, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citibank Hungary's SME Clients Now Have Access to the Combined Credit with Guarantee Program Announced by the National Development Office","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/citibank-hungary-s-sme-clients-now-have-access-to-the-combined-credit-with-guarantee-program-announced-by-the-national-development-office","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"Budapest, Hungary - NESsT and Citibank announced the winners of the 2010-2011 NESsT-Citibank For-Profit Social Enterprise Development Program on September 29, supporting the development of for-profit social enterprises in Hungary. Roxana Damaschin-Tecu, NESsT Enterprise Development Director in Europe, and Batara Sianturi, Citi Country Officer for Hungary, presented the awards to the winners at an award ceremony on September 29.","month":"10","year":"2011","publishDate":"October 18, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"NESsT and Citibank Hungary Announce Winners of the 2010/2011 For-Profit Social Enterprise Competition","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/foundation/news/press-release/2011/nesst-and-citibank-hungary-announce-winners-of-the-20102011-for-profit-social-enterprise-competition","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"Beijing - Citibank (China) Co. Ltd. (\"Citi\") and the China Banking Association today announced the winners of the seventh annual Microentrepreneurship Awards in China. The awards ceremony, which has become the largest and most influential annual event for Chinese microfinance practitioners to interact with and learn from each other, was held in Beijing and was attended by 150 microfinance practitioners.","month":"10","year":"2011","publishDate":"October 18, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"2011 China Banking Association - Citi Microentrepreneurship Awards Held in Beijing","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/foundation/news/press-release/2011/2011-china-banking-association--citi-microentrepreneurship-awards-held-in-beijing","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"Citi today announced that it was again rated Number One in the \"Market Capability: Emerging Markets\" category in the Global Investor/ISF 2011 Equity Lending Survey. This marks the second year in a row that Citi has achieved this industry-leading position in the increasingly important emerging markets space.","month":"10","year":"2011","publishDate":"October 18, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"For Second Consecutive Year, Citi Rated Number One in Emerging Markets Securities Lending in a Survey of Top Borrowers","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/for-second-consecutive-year-citi-rated-number-one-in-emerging-markets-securities-lending-in-a-survey-of-top-borrowers","tags":["Press Release Migration","Institutional Clients Group"]},{"summary":"Moscow – ZAO Citibank announced the launch of One Bill, a service enabling Moscow residents to pay their bills for utilities, city landline telephone (MGTS) and OAO Mosenergosbyt by automatic charges to Citibank credit or debit cards. All payments will be commission-free. ","month":"10","year":"2011","publishDate":"October 17, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Russia: Citibank Helps Its Customers Tackle Utility Bills","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/russia-citibank-helps-its-customers-tackle-utility-bills","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"Budapest - Citibank Hungary's retail customers now have the ability to initiate instant, real-time online bank transfer transactions between their accounts, to family and business partners' individual bank accounts hold with Citi in 26 countries around the world. This new innovative digital service leverages the unmatched global network of Citi to bring unique benefits to customers around the globe.","month":"10","year":"2011","publishDate":"October 17, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Global Transfers Launch in Hungary Enables Real Time Account Transactions to 26 Countries Around the World","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/citi-global-transfers-launch-in-hungary-enables-real-time-account-transactions-to-26-countries-around-the-world","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"Dubai – \"With over 3500 Chinese companies present today in the UAE, including energy, construction, telecommunication and trading firms, and establishing regional offices that cover the whole of the Middle East and Africa market, Dubai has evolved into a major trade and business hub for top Chinese multinationals. This is evidenced as well by the number of Chinese residents in the country, a number that has doubled within a year to more than 200,000.\" ","month":"10","year":"2011","publishDate":"October 17, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Holds China Day Event in Dubai","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/citi-holds-china-day-event-in-dubai","tags":["Press Release Migration","Institutional Clients Group","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"New York - Citigroup Inc. today reported net income of $3.8 billion, or $1.23 per diluted share, for the third quarter of 2011, which was 74% higher than the prior year period and 13% above the second quarter 2011. Third quarter revenues of $20.8 billion increased slightly from the prior year period and the second quarter 2011.","month":"10","year":"2011","publishDate":"October 17, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citigroup Reports Third Quarter 2011 Net Income of $3.8 Billion, Compared to $2.2 Billion in Third Quarter 2010","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/citigroup-reports-third-quarter-2011-net-income-of-38-billion-compared-to-22-billion-in-third-quarter-2010","tags":["Press Release Migration","Citi-Wide"]},{"summary":"Leaving your current job? You may want to roll over money in your employer's 401(k) plan into an Individual Retirement Account, where you might enjoy greater investment choice and lower investment costs.","month":"10","author.displayName":["Jonathan Clements"],"year":"2011","publishDate":"October 17, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Job Changes and 401(k) Rollovers","category":"PERSPECTIVES","author.jobTitle":["Director of Financial Education, Citi Personal Wealth Management"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2011/job-changes-and-401k-rollovers","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"Earlier this morning, Citi released its earnings report for the third quarter of 2011. Chief Financial Officer John Gerspach discusses the report in this video.","image":"638e2fc0a3c47c530c0a5959","month":"10","year":"2011","publishDate":"October 17, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi releases third quarter 2011 earnings.","category":"PERSPECTIVES","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2011/citi-releases-third-quarter-2011-earnings","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"A large amount of protesters entered our branch at 555 La Guardia Place, New York City, around 2 p.m. today. They were very disruptive and refused to leave after being repeatedly asked, causing our staff to call 911. The police asked the branch staff to close the branch until the protesters could be removed. Only one person asked to close an account and was accommodated.","month":"10","year":"2011","publishDate":"October 15, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citibank Statement Regarding Protester Arrests","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/citibank-statement-regarding-protester-arrests","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"<font style=\"FONT-SIZE: 1em\">Citibank Public Affairs issued the following statement regarding today's incident: \"A large number of protesters entered our branch at 555 La Guardia Place around 2:00 PM today. They were very disruptive and refused to leave after being repeatedly asked, causing our staff to call 911. The Police asked the branch staff to close the branch until the protesters could be removed. Only one person asked to close an account and was accommodated.\"</font>","month":"10","author.displayName":["Citibank Public Affairs"],"year":"2011","publishDate":"October 15, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citibank Statement Regarding Protester Arrests","category":"PERSPECTIVES","author.jobTitle":["Citibank Public Affairs"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2011/citibank-statement-regarding-protester-arrests-1","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"New York – Highlighting the top companies that are paving the way for new moms and families everywhere, <i><a href=\"http://www.workingmother.com/\">Working Mother</a></i> magazine has announced Citi as one of the <a href=\"http://www.workingmother.com/best-companies\">2011 Working Mother 100 Best Companies</a>. Citi, which has appeared on the \"100 Best Companies\" list for 21 consecutive years, was recognized for its comprehensive diversity and employee benefit programs that foster professional advancement and offer flextime hours, telecommuting, paid maternity leave and employee assistance programs. ","month":"10","year":"2011","publishDate":"October 14, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Working Mother also names Citi to \"100 Best Companies for Kids\" and \"Best Companies for Multi-Cultural Women\" Lists","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/working-mother-also-names-citi-to-100-best-companies-for-kids-and-best-companies-for-multi-cultural-women-lists","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"Thank you for taking the time to post your <a href=\"https://blog.citigroup.com/2011/09/citi-cards-you-spoke-we-listened.shtml\">comments and questions</a>. We have read every comment closely. As we work hard to transform our products and services to better serve and delight our cardmembers, your feedback is enormously valuable. What follows are responses to some of the most common questions and concerns raised. For those of you who had specific questions about your account, our Customer Service team has reached out to you directly by phone or email to address.","month":"10","author.displayName":["Matthew Jenkins"],"year":"2011","publishDate":"October 14, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Cards answers your questions","category":"PERSPECTIVES","author.jobTitle":["Head of Service Delivery"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2011/post","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"Working Mother magazine annually recognizes the top companies paving the way for new moms and families. And this year, Citi has once again been named a Working Mother 100 Best Company. Citi, which has appeared on the \"100 Best Companies\" list for twenty-one consecutive years, was also named to Working Mother's \"Best Companies for Multi-Cultural Women 2011\" and Working Mother's \"Best Companies for Kids\" lists due to our comprehensive diversity and employee benefit programs that foster professional advancement and offer flextime hours, telecommuting, paid maternity leave and employee assistance.","month":"10","year":"2011","publishDate":"October 14, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi named to Working Mother's 2011 \"100 Best Companies\" list for 21st consecutive year","category":"PERSPECTIVES","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2011/citi-named-to-working-mothers-2011-100-best-companies-list-for-21st-consecutive-year","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"Philippines - Citibank, in partnership with the country's top hospitals. has introduced new benefits that come with the Mercury Drug Citiba