icrofinance, entrepreneurship, institutional strengthening and financial capabilities. These activities are scheduled to take place October 10 - 14 in San Jose, Costa Rica. ","month":"10","year":"2011","publishDate":"October 11, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Costa Rica: Financial Inclusion Experts Discuss Industry Trends During Citi's \"Financial Inclusion Week\"","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/foundation/news/press-release/2011/costa-rica-financial-inclusion-experts-discuss-industry-trends-during-citi-s-financial-inclusion-week","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"Hong Kong - Coca-Cola Beverage (CCB), the Coca-Cola Company's Korean bottling partner in Korea's soft-drink manufacturing industry, has implemented a mobile collections solution from Citi's Global Transaction Services business. Citi's solution has eliminated the need for cash collections and, as a result, has significantly enhanced CCB's receivables processes.","month":"10","year":"2011","publishDate":"October 11, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Coca-Cola Beverage Company Korea Streamlines Receivables with Citi's Mobile Collections Solution","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/coca-cola-beverage-company-korea-streamlines-receivables-with-citi-s-mobile-collections-solution","tags":["Press Release Migration","Institutional Clients Group"]},{"summary":"If you have children or grandchildren who are planning to attend college, there are all kinds of strategies to help save for those costs, including buying savings bonds, setting up accounts under the Uniform Transfers to Minors Act and simply keeping money in your own name.","month":"10","author.displayName":["Jonathan Clements"],"year":"2011","publishDate":"October 10, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"College Savings and Saving Taxes.","category":"PERSPECTIVES","author.jobTitle":["Director of Financial Education, Citi Personal Wealth Management"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2011/college-savings-and-saving-taxes","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"Manama, Bahrain – The Citi Foundation continues its sponsorship of inJAz Bahrain's \"Banks in Action\" program, which provides financial education for school students in Bahrain. Citi will invest US$85,000 in the Banks in Action program this year. ","month":"10","year":"2011","publishDate":"October 09, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Increases Its Contribution to InJAz Bahrain to US$85,000","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/foundation/news/press-release/2011/citi-increases-its-contribution-to-inja-bahrain-to-us85000","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"image":"638e2fc5a3c47c530c0a5971","month":"10","author.displayName":["Steve Troutner"],"year":"2011","publishDate":"October 09, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Understanding Citibank Checking Package Changes","category":"PERSPECTIVES","author.jobTitle":["Head of Banking Products, US Consumer Banking"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2011/understanding-citibank-checking-package-changes","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"Montevideo, Uruguay – Citi Uruguay announced the launching of their new Citi Green campaign during a paper-recycling workshop for employee's children. ","month":"10","year":"2011","publishDate":"October 07, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Uruguay Launches Green Campaign \"Less Paper - More Notebooks\"","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/citi-uruguay-launches-green-campaign-less-paper--more-notebooks","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"New York - Citi today announced that its Treasury and Trade Solutions business was voted the #1 Cash Management Bank globally for the fifth consecutive year in Euromoney's annual cash management survey. In addition to capturing the top spot in the global poll, Citi also took top honors with five regional awards and 13 country awards as voted by clients.","month":"10","year":"2011","publishDate":"October 07, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Clients Vote for Citi as the Best Cash Management Bank in Euromoney's 2011 Annual Cash Management Survey","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/clients-vote-for-citi-as-the-best-cash-management-bank-in-euromoney-s-2011-annual-cash-management-survey","tags":["Press Release Migration","Institutional Clients Group"]},{"summary":"With less than a year to go until the London 2012 Olympic Games, Citi is kicking off its Citi Team USA Flag Tour. As the official bank of the 2012 U.S. Olympic and Paralympic Teams and the <a href=\"https://www.teamusa.org/\">U.S. Olympic Committee</a>, Citi is bringing the Olympic spirit to Citi sites and locations across the country--and we started yesterday in Sioux Falls, South Dakota.","image":"638e2fc8a3c47c530c0a597a","year":"2011","publishDate":"October 07, 2011","type":"insights","title":"U.S. Olympians help kick off Citi Team USA Flag Tour","author.jobTitle":["Citi"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2011/us-olympians-help-kick-off-citi-team-usa-flag-tour","tags":["Perspective Migration"],"month":"10","author.displayName":["Citi"],"siteId":"citigpa","category":"PERSPECTIVES"},{"summary":"Sioux Falls, S.D. – Today, Citi announced the launch of the Citi Team USA Flag Tour at its first stop in Sioux Falls, one of Citi's largest sites in the United States. Two-time Olympian Derek Miles (track & field, pole vault) and 2008 Olympic silver medalist Chellsie Memmel (gymnastics) joined Citibank Site President Ken Stork, Citi employees and students from the Laura B. Anderson Elementary School in celebration and support of Team USA and the athletes' journeys to the London 2012 Olympic Games.","month":"10","year":"2011","publishDate":"October 06, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Kicks Off 'Citi Team USA Flag Tour' in Sioux Falls to Celebrate Sponsorship of 2012 U.S. Olympic & Paralympic Teams","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/citi-kicks-off-citi-team-usa-flag-tour-in-sioux-falls-to-celebrate-sponsorship-of-2012-us-olympic-paralympic-teams","tags":["Press Release Migration","Citi-Wide"]},{"summary":"Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia – Giant and Citibank are introducing the new Giant-Citibank Credit Card to help customers enjoy comprehensive benefits and will set new industry benchmarks in the form of highest rebates for daily grocery purchases in the market today. ","month":"10","year":"2011","publishDate":"October 06, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Malaysia: Giant and Citibank Increase Rebates to Address Rising Prices","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/malaysia-giant-and-citibank-increase-rebates-to-address-rising-prices","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"Kyiv, Ukraine – Citibank held a roundtable discussion, \"Is Ukraine prepared for a new economic downturn?\" and shared its macroeconomic forecast for Ukraine with representatives of the country's leading economic and financial publications. Elina Ribakova, Citi Russia, and CIS Chief Economist, Natalia Novikova, Economist for Citi Russia and CIS, presented the forecast. They discussed with journalists the country's current macroeconomic situation and analyzed the main trends for the short- and medium-term developments on the local and global financial markets. ","month":"10","year":"2011","publishDate":"October 06, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi: \"Is Ukraine Prepared for New Economic Downturn?\"","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/citi-is-ukraine-prepared-for-new-economic-downturn-","tags":["Press Release Migration","Institutional Clients Group"]},{"month":"10","author.displayName":["Citi"],"year":"2011","publishDate":"October 06, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"On the Women & Co. blog: Staying on top of Social Security Benefits.","category":"PERSPECTIVES","author.jobTitle":["Citi"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2011/on-the-women-co-blog-staying-on-top-of-social-security-benefits","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"Buenos Aires, Argentina – Citi opened four new branches in Argentina: two in the provinces of Mendoza and Tucuman; and two in Buenos Aires, in Escobar and Canning. By the end of 2011, the company will have 74 locations within its distribution network, comprising 69 branches and five points of service centers. ","month":"10","year":"2011","publishDate":"October 05, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Argentina Keeps Growing with New Branches","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/citi-argentina-keeps-growing-with-new-branches","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"Prague, Czech Republic – Citibank Europe plc has launched the new contactless Citi Life Metropole credit card, which offers clients many benefits when shopping at Metropole as well as other shopping centers. Cardholders can be rewarded with 2-percent cash back on purchases up to 2,000 CZK monthly. Customers receive the reward in the form of Citi Life Premiums, which are credited to a card holder's Citi Life Premium account. These premiums can be drawn in the form of 500 CZK and 1,000 CZK shopping vouchers to be subsequently used for purchases in all stores and restaurants at the Metropole Zlicin shopping center. Clients may also choose to use collected premium points to cover the credit card's annual maintenance fee. ","month":"10","year":"2011","publishDate":"October 05, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Czech Republic: Citibank and Metropole Zlicin Shopping Center Partner to Launch a New Contactless Credit Card","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/cech-republic-citibank-and-metropole-zlicin-shopping-center-partner-to-launch-a-new-contactless-credit-card","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"Each year, the American Banker releases its prestigious rankings of the top women in financial services. This year, six Citi executives were named to the list.","month":"10","author.displayName":["Citi"],"year":"2011","publishDate":"October 05, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Six Citi leaders named to Top Women in Banking list.","category":"PERSPECTIVES","author.jobTitle":["Citi"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2011/six-citi-leaders-named-to-top-women-in-banking-list","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"Citi Prime Finance--a multi-broker, multi-strategy integrated business unit comprised of prime brokerage, financing solutions, business advisory and capital introductions--has teamed up with First Derivatives, a global provider of software and consulting services to the financial services industry, on a new study of hedge fund information technology spending. The study suggests that hedge funds will spend approximately $2.09 billion on IT in 2011.","month":"10","author.displayName":["Citi"],"year":"2011","publishDate":"October 04, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi survey reveals hedge funds will spend more than $2 billion on IT in 2011.","category":"PERSPECTIVES","author.jobTitle":["Citi"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2011/citi-survey-reveals-hedge-funds-will-spend-more-than-2-billion-on-it-in-2011","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"Praha, Czech Republic – Citibank is bringing yet another innovation and convenience to the Czech market – comprehensive banking on customers' smart phones with the launch of Citi Mobile, which is in line with the growing penetration of smart phones in the market. Citi Mobile is accessible from any internet-enabled smart phone and offers the most comprehensive mobile banking solution with no fee for its customers and is yet another way to manage their accounts 24/7. ","month":"10","year":"2011","publishDate":"October 03, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Czech Republic: Citibank Launches Mobile Banking for All Smart Phones","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/cech-republic-citibank-launches-mobile-banking-for-all-smart-phones","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"New York – Through the support of GROW South Dakota and the Shannon County School District, a new educational facility for Batesland is under construction. Located in Batesland, South Dakota, the current school is in serious disrepair with part of the facility unusable. The new facility will increase the capacity of the school to accommodate a growing population as well as provide modernized facilities and enhanced technology to improve the quality of education for some of the U.S.'s neediest students. ","month":"10","year":"2011","publishDate":"October 03, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"U.S.: Shannon County to Build New School with Citi Financing","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/us-shannon-county-to-build-new-school-with-citi-financing","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"Manama, Bahrain - As part of its growth and expansion strategy, Citibank N.A. announced the installation of three automated teller machines (ATMs) at three new locations across Bahrain.","month":"10","year":"2011","publishDate":"October 03, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citibank Launches Three New ATMs at Three Locations Across Bahrain","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/citibank-launches-three-new-atms-at-three-locations-across-bahrain","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"New York – Citibank today unveiled its new online experience for U.S. Consumer Banking clients. The new Citibank Online offers a dramatically streamlined design and an intuitive user experience, and brings simplicity, flexibility and control to everyday household financial management – a dramatic shift from the online banking experience currently offered by most major banks. ","month":"10","year":"2011","publishDate":"October 03, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citibank Unveils New Consumer Banking Website - Raises The Bar","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/citibank-unveils-new-consumer-banking-website--raises-the-bar","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"Today, Citibank unveiled a new online experience for its U.S. Consumer Banking clients. The new <a href=\"https://www.citibank.com/\">Citibank Online</a> offers a dramatically streamlined design, an intuitive user experience, and brings simplicity, flexibility, and control to everyday household financial management.","image":"638e2fcba3c47c530c0a598e","year":"2011","publishDate":"October 03, 2011","type":"insights","title":"Check out the new Citibank.com.","author.jobTitle":["Head of Internet and Mobile Banking, North America Consumer Banking"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2011/check-out-the-new-citibankcom","tags":["Perspective Migration"],"month":"10","author.displayName":["Tracey Weber"],"siteId":"citigpa","category":"PERSPECTIVES"},{"summary":"After the wild market fluctuations of the past four years, including the recent stock-market slump, you might have heard folks argue that \"buy-and-hold doesn't work anymore.\"","month":"10","author.displayName":["Jonathan Clements"],"year":"2011","publishDate":"October 03, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Buy-and-Hold Investing","category":"PERSPECTIVES","author.jobTitle":["Director of Financial Education, Citi Personal Wealth Management"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2011/buy-and-hold-investing","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"<strong>An update for our cardholders</strong><br>Every day we work to deliver the experience you deserve and we won't be satisfied until you are. And we're listening hard to make sure we deliver solutions that meet your needs. While we recognize that we can always do better, I'd like to share some of the changes we've made over the past year based on the feedback we've heard from customers like you.","month":"09","author.displayName":["Jud Linville"],"year":"2011","publishDate":"September 30, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Cards: You Spoke. We listened.","category":"PERSPECTIVES","author.jobTitle":["Citi Cards CEO"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2011/citi-cards-you-spoke-we-listened","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"<p class=\"blog-listing-body\">Nathan Sheets has joined Citigroup as Global Head of International Economics within our Investment Research & Analysis division. </p>,<p class=\"blog-listing-body\">Mr. Sheets will work with Willem Buiter to lead the Firm's team of international economists, with a special focus on the position of the US in the global economy. Mr. Sheets joins from the Federal Reserve Board in Washington D.C. where he served as Director of the Division of International Finance and as an Economist to the FOMC. </p>,<p class=\"blog-listing-body\">Among his most notable accomplishments, Mr. Sheets acted as the Fed Chairman's international adviser at the onset of the European fiscal crisis in the spring of 2010. He was also a driving force behind the Federal Reserve Board's global emergency lending program. Mr. Sheets acted as senior advisor to the U.S. Executive Director at the International Monetary Fund (IMF) while on leave from the Federal Reserve. In this capacity, he served as a liaison between the IMF and various U.S. government agencies. <br></p>,<p class=\"blog-listing-body\">Mr. Sheets received his Bachelors of Economics from Brigham Young University and his PhD from the Massachusetts Institute of Technology. </p>","month":"09","author.displayName":["Citi"],"year":"2011","publishDate":"September 30, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Nathan Sheets joins Citi as Senior Global Economist","category":"PERSPECTIVES","author.jobTitle":["Citi"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2011/nathan-sheets-joins-citi-as-senior-global-economist","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"San Jose, Costa Rica – Citi Foundation and Junior Achievement (JA) Costa Rica launched a program that encourages entrepreneurship among Costa Rican youth. The <i>Youth Entrepreneurship Workshops</i>, a JA program, is one of the most successful economic education programs of JA worldwide. Citi Costa Rica executives volunteered their time to train 15 microenterprises founded by students from eight schools nationwide. This program demonstrates Citi's commitment to financial education, the development of the country and JA Costa Rica. ","month":"09","year":"2011","publishDate":"September 29, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Foundation Supports Young Entrepreneurs Program in Costa Rica","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/foundation/news/press-release/2011/citi-foundation-supports-young-entrepreneurs-program-in-costa-rica","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"Citibank Thailand has opened its second branch in Thailand. The Silom Smart Banking branch, located at the United Center Building along Silom Road, Bangkok, offers a range of financial services with a unique customer experience, reaffirming Citibank's status as the leading foreign bank in Thailand.","month":"09","year":"2011","publishDate":"September 29, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citibank Thailand Opens Second Branch; Introduces New Country Business Manager","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/citibank-thailand-opens-second-branch-introduces-new-country-business-manager","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"New York – Hedge funds will spend approximately $2.09 billion on information technology (IT) in 2011, representing an average of approximately nine basis points of assets under management, according to the Prime Finance 2011 IT Survey released today by Citi (NYSE:C) Prime Finance, a multi-broker, multi-strategy integrated business unit comprised of prime brokerage, financing solutions, business advisory and capital introductions, and First Derivatives, a global provider of software and consulting services to the financial services industry. The report, <b>\"Managing Your Hedge Fund IT Spend to Achieve Differentiation,\"</b> which surveyed more than 75 hedge funds in the U.S. and Europe and 15 vendors, documents for the first time both the industry's aggregate expenditure on information technology and the average expenditure per hedge fund. ","month":"09","year":"2011","publishDate":"September 29, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Hedge Funds to Spend $2.09 Billion on Information Technology in 2011","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/hedge-funds-to-spend-209-billion-on-information-technology-in-2011","tags":["Press Release Migration","Institutional Clients Group"]},{"summary":"Philadelphia – <a href=\"https://www.citigroup.com/citi/citizen/community/index.html\">Citi Community Development</a> and the Philadelphia-based nonprofits <a href=\"http://www.finanta.org/\">Finanta</a> and <a href=\"http://www.myentrepreneurworks.org/\">Entrepreneur Works</a> today announced that they will collaborate on the pioneering \"Circles of Success\" program to provide a combination of lending, credit building and financial literacy for underserved and low-income entrepreneurs. The program was launched and highlighted during an event at Finanta headquarters at which Philadelphia Mayor Michael A. Nutter announced a $2.3 million commitment to a group of community organizations providing small business assistance. ","month":"09","year":"2011","publishDate":"September 29, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"U.S.: Finanta and Entrepreneur Works Partner with Citi to Build Credit and Grow Small Businesses in Philadelphia","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/us-finanta-and-entrepreneur-works-partner-with-citi-to-build-credit-and-grow-small-businesses-in-philadelphia","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"The Citi Foundation today announced a $2.75 million commitment to the Housing Partnership Network (HPN) to support the Innovations in Neighborhood Stabilization and Foreclosure Prevention Initiative, an effort to develop new and innovative solutions to neighborhood stabilization challenges in 10 metropolitan areas across the country. The initiative will provide leading community-based housing organizations with grants and other resources to support high-impact neighborhood revitalization projects that can yield important lessons and be replicated in communities across the country. ","month":"09","year":"2011","publishDate":"September 29, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"U.S.: Housing Partnership Network and Citi Foundation Launch Fund to Advance Innovations in Neighborhood Stabilization","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/foundation/news/press-release/2011/us-housing-partnership-network-and-citi-foundation-launch-fund-to-advance-innovations-in-neighborhood-stabiliation","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"Las Vegas, Nev. – Citi volunteers joined forces in late September to give back to the Las Vegas community, contributing 540 service-hours at Three Square Food Bank to sort and pack food for needy individuals and families. In one afternoon, Citi employees sorted more than 80,000 pounds of perishable and non-perishable food items and packed 2,415 backpack meals for children who may otherwise go without food on the weekends.","month":"09","year":"2011","publishDate":"September 28, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"U.S.: Citi Delivers for Three Square Food Bank","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/us-citi-delivers-for-three-square-food-bank","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"Washington, D.C. – The Aspen Institute announced today the launch of the Asset Building Through Credit pilot program, a research effort that will study a multi-dimensional approach to building credit and financial opportunities for aspiring low-income entrepreneurs. The pilot program will study whether financial education and coaching combined with an innovative secured credit-card platform can increase credit scores and expand the small businesses of more than 600 low-income entrepreneurs in five markets nationwide. The study is funded by a $750,000 grant from the Citi Foundation.","month":"09","year":"2011","publishDate":"September 28, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"U.S.: The Aspen Institute and Citi to Study Innovative Credit-Building Model for Entrepreneurs","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/foundation/new