al Clients Group"]},{"summary":"Guatemala City, Guatemala - Citi, the leading global financial services company, together with Gallo Beer and Tigo bring pop rock band, Mana, to Guatemala for their \"Drama and Light\" world tour. The legendary group comes to Guatemala, after performing sold-out concerts in all major cities around the world.","month":"09","year":"2011","publishDate":"September 14, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Brings Iconic Pop Rock Band Mana to Guatemala","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/citi-brings-iconic-pop-rock-band-mana-to-guatemala","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"New York - Citigroup today announced a new tool to help students at select universities participate in its campus recruiting process. The Citi® On Campus App for iPhone digitally connects students with Citi's campus recruiting activities.","month":"09","year":"2011","publishDate":"September 14, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"U.S.: Citi Creates Citi On Campus App for iPhone, to Stand Out in Competitive World of On-Campus Recruiting","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/us-citi-creates-citi-on-campus-app-for-iphone-to-stand-out-in-competitive-world-of-on-campus-recruiting","tags":["Press Release Migration","Institutional Clients Group","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"Three developments that Citi Community Capital helped build, renovate or preserve as low-income housing won top honors in <em>Affordable Housing Finance</em> magazine's latest <a href=\"https://www.housingfinance.com/news/ahf/090711-ahf-AHF-Announces-7th-Annual-Readers-Choice-Winners.htm?cid=AHFBU090711\">Readers' Choice Awards</a>. Voters rated two Citi projects as the top \"Green\" efforts of the year in a tie and a third project as best in the \"Preservation\" category.","month":"09","author.displayName":["Citi"],"year":"2011","publishDate":"September 14, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi efforts win Affordable Housing Finance awards.","category":"PERSPECTIVES","author.jobTitle":["Citi"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2011/citi-efforts-win-affordable-housing-finance-awards","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"Santo Domingo, Dominican Republic - The Citi Foundation continued its support of the Mir Foundation by providing scholarships, facility upgrades and supplies to assist students in the Foundation's programs.","month":"09","year":"2011","publishDate":"September 13, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Dominican Republic: Citi Foundation Supports Launch of Culinary Development Program","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/foundation/news/press-release/2011/dominican-republic-citi-foundation-supports-launch-of-culinary-development-program","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"Bogotá, Colombia – Citibank Colombia and International Action \"<i>Acción Internacional</i>\" recently announced a competition for the <i>2011 Citi-Accion Colombian Micro entrepreneurship Awards</i>, which recognize the recurring efforts of Colombian small business owners who promote entrepreneurship in the country. The awards cover four categories: commerce, services, production, and community banks - rural solidarity groups. Since its inception, the awards have contributed to the growth of 66 Colombian microentrepreneurs, their families and communities.","month":"09","year":"2011","publishDate":"September 13, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Searches for Top Colombian Micro Entrepreneurs","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/foundation/news/press-release/2011/citi-searches-for-top-colombian-micro-entrepreneurs","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"On Wednesday, CitiMortgage launches an autumn phase of our Road to Recovery Tour with an event in Portland, Oregon aiming to raise awareness of distressed homeowners to the assistance available to them. It continues through November, hitting 15 cities nationwide, seeking to connect struggling borrowers with mortgage assistance and foreclosure prevention experts to provide information and discuss options. This phase of the tour also recently added dates in the Eastern U.S. to include areas hard hit by Hurricane Irene and its aftermath in recognition of the very immediate need to help homeowners cope with weather-related issues.","month":"09","author.displayName":["Sanjiv Das"],"year":"2011","publishDate":"September 13, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"CitiMortgage Road to Recovery Tour continues.","category":"PERSPECTIVES","author.jobTitle":["CEO, CitiMortgage"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2011/citimortgage-road-to-recovery-tour-continues","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"month":"09","author.displayName":["Citi"],"year":"2011","publishDate":"September 13, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"FT blog cites Citi research on implications of a Greek exit from Euro area.","category":"PERSPECTIVES","author.jobTitle":["Citi"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2011/ft-blog-cites-citi-research-on-implications-of-a-greek-exit-from-euro-area","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"Tegucigalpa, Honduras – Citi Honduras presents Juan Luis Guerra in concert, October 22, 2011, at the Chochi Sosa Stadium in Tegucigalpa. Guerra is recognized as the top Latin Grammy winner in the history of Latin music.","month":"09","year":"2011","publishDate":"September 12, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"For the First Time in Honduras: Citi Presents Juan Luis Guerra in Concert","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/for-the-first-time-in-honduras-citi-presents-juan-luis-guerra-in-concert","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"Managua, Nicaragua - Once again, Citi Nicaragua held its popular One Million Multipremios Miles drawing for miles accumulated in the One Million Savings Account. The goal of this program is to continue fostering a culture of savings among Nicaraguan families. Citi encourages its existing customers to increase their account balance to improve their chances of participating in the quarterly drawing. The third drawing of the year took place September 6, and the lucky winner was Jose Alejandro Alvarado Talavera, who has been Citi's client in the Ciudad Jardin branch since April 2009.","month":"09","year":"2011","publishDate":"September 12, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Presents the Winner of the One Million Multipremios Miles Promotion in Nicaragua","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/citi-presents-the-winner-of-the-one-million-multipremios-miles-promotion-in-nicaragua","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"New York – CitiMortgage's Road to Recovery homeowner assistance program kicks off its autumn tour on Wednesday, September 14, in Portland, Oregon. Due to the damage from Hurricane Irene in the Eastern United States, Citi has developed a schedule to rush help to areas affected by the hurricane. Following initial events in Portland and Riverside, California, Citi's team of mortgage assistance experts will travel to Norfolk, Va., for an event on September 30, followed by Philadelphia on October 3 and Long Island, N.Y., on October 12. By that time, the areas affected by the hurricane are expected to be in recovery, allowing CitiMortgage experts to engage with local homeowners in need of assistance.","month":"09","year":"2011","publishDate":"September 12, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"CitiMortgage Launches Next Road to Recovery Tour - Helping Distressed Homeowners in Their Markets","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/us-citimortgage-launches-next-road-to-recovery-tour-helping-distressed-homeowners-in-their-markets","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"Ted Teo, a managing director covering North China for Citi's Global Banking group, <a href=\"https://www.citibank.com/transactionservices/home/corporations/industries/videos/ted_ma_video.jsp\">discusses</a> the reasons Chinese energy and chemical companies are driven to pursue cross-border M&A as well as their strategies for finding potential merger partners.","image":"638e2fe3a3c47c530c0a59f7","year":"2011","publishDate":"September 12, 2011","type":"insights","title":"Chinese energy companies ready for M&A.","author.jobTitle":["Citi"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2011/chinese-energy-companies-ready-for-ma","tags":["Perspective Migration"],"month":"09","author.displayName":["Citi"],"siteId":"citigpa","category":"PERSPECTIVES"},{"summary":"If you need to borrow money to, say, buy a car or pay an unexpected tax bill, your first thought might be to take out an auto loan, use a credit card or apply for an unsecured personal bank loan. But don't overlook these other sources of borrowed money.","month":"09","author.displayName":["Jonathan Clements"],"year":"2011","publishDate":"September 12, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Lending a hand.","category":"PERSPECTIVES","author.jobTitle":["Director of Financial Education, Citi Personal Wealth Management"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2011/lending-a-hand","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"Central Harlem, New York – NYC's Department of Housing Preservation and Development (HPD) Commissioner Mathew Wambua and Manhattan Borough President Scott Stringer joined Grammy Award-winning recording artist Cyndi Lauper and West End Intergenerational Residence HDFC, Inc at the ribbon cutting for True Colors Residence. Located in Central Harlem at 269 W 154th Street, it is the first permanent housing development in New York City with a preference for 18-24 year-old lesbian, gay, bisexual and transgender (LGBT) young adults with a history of homelessness. Also in attendance were New York State Assemblyman Herman 'Denny' Farrell, New York City Council Member Inez Dickens, President of Richman Housing Resources William Traylor and Bill Yates, Director of Citi Community Development.","month":"09","year":"2011","publishDate":"September 09, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"HPD Commissioner Wambua, Manhattan Borough President Stringer, Cyndi Lauper and West End Intergenerational Residence Celebrate the Opening of True Colors Supportive Housing","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/us-hpd-commissioner-wambua-manhattan-borough-president-stringer-cyndi-lauper-and-west-end-intergenerational-residence-celebrate-the-opening-of-true-colors-supportive-housing","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"<em>\"The purpose of the SCRA is no less lofty than to provide servicemembers' peace of mind, knowing that while they put their lives at risk to protect this great nation, their personal affairs and economic interests will be protected\". <a href=\"https://veterans.house.gov/sites/republicans.veterans.house.gov/files/documents/112-1transcriptFC2-9-11.htm\">[1]</a></em>","month":"09","author.displayName":["John P. Carey"],"year":"2011","publishDate":"September 09, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Protecting our protectors: SCRA and the CFPB's Office of Servicemember Affairs.","category":"PERSPECTIVES","author.jobTitle":["Chief Administrative Officer, North America Consumer Banking"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2011/protecting-our-protectors-scra-and-the-cfpbs-office-of-servicemember-affairs","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"San Franciscans recently marked the completion of extensive renovations of the <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/citi#p/u/6/uAtEn_TSY90\">Martin Luther King-Marcus Garvey Square Cooperative Apartments</a>, a landmark affordable housing project in the city's Fillmore District. A rededication ceremony brought together the wide range of partners and interests involved in this important community reinvestment project, including its developer Related California, the San Francisco Redevelopment Agency (SFRA), the U.S. Department of Housing and Urban Development (HUD), Freddie Mac, the development's co-op board and Citi Community Capital.","image":"638e2fe6a3c47c530c0a5a06","year":"2011","publishDate":"September 09, 2011","type":"insights","title":"Helping preserve landmark San Francisco affordable housing.","author.jobTitle":["Citi"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2011/helping-preserve-landmark-san-francisco-affordable-housing","tags":["Perspective Migration"],"month":"09","author.displayName":["Citi"],"siteId":"citigpa","category":"PERSPECTIVES"},{"summary":"<a href=\"https://www.bestofnky.com/NKY/Articles/33.aspx\"></a><em>Northern Kentucky Magazine</em> <a href=\"https://www.bestofnky.com/NKY/Articles/33.aspx\">covered</a> Citi's local philanthropy, support for Greater Cincinatti causes and employee volunteer efforts in its Fall 2011 issue. Among the efforts it mentioned were Citi's regular internal campaigns to raise money for United Way and March of Dimes and the company's and employees' involvement in supporting a wide range of \"hands-on\" learning and job-skills programs in area schools and colleges.","month":"09","author.displayName":["Citi"],"year":"2011","publishDate":"September 09, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Regional magazine puts spotlight on Citi's community role.","category":"PERSPECTIVES","author.jobTitle":["Citi"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2011/regional-magazine-puts-spotlight-on-citis-community-role","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"New York – Citi and the New York Mets Alumni Association presented by Citi announced today that they will team up with the nonprofit MyGoodDeed to help commemorate the 10th anniversary of the attacks of September 11 by encouraging people to perform good deeds, support charitable causes, volunteer and engage in other acts of service. The project is part of the Mets and Citi's \"Teammates in the Community\" initiative, reflecting their ongoing commitment to be active participants in the community.","month":"09","year":"2011","publishDate":"September 08, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi and the Mets Alumni Association Presented by Citi to Partner with MyGoodDeed to Commemorate 9/11 as a National Day of Service and Remembrance","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/us-citi-and-the-mets-alumni-association-presented-by-citi-to-partner-with-mygooddeed-to-commemorate-911-as-a-national-day-of-service-and-remembrance","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"Tokyo - Citi announced today new funding for the Banking with the Poor Network (BWTP), the only pan-Asia microfinance network, as part of Citi's continued commitment to promoting financial inclusion globally. ","month":"09","year":"2011","publishDate":"September 08, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Extends Partnership with Banking with the Poor Network to Promote Financial Inclusion in Asia","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/foundation/news/press-release/2011/citi-extends-partnership-with-banking-with-the-poor-network-to-promote-financial-inclusion-in-asia","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"Budapest - Consumers with questions related to Citibank Hungary's products and services can now get instant answers through the new, revolutionary CitiChat live service from wherever they are traveling in the world. CitiChat is the first live chat service offered in the Hungarian banking market and is available free to all existing customers and any consumers who are looking for a fast and convenient way for getting information or assistance related to Citibank's products. Chats can be initiated through Citibank Hungary's website without any registration from a computer with an internet connection. Trained CitiChat bankers are answering enquiries and are helping customers with their online applications.","month":"09","year":"2011","publishDate":"September 08, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Consumers Can Get Instant Responses to Enquiries through the Banking-Market-First CitiChat Live Service from Citibank Hungary","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/consumers-can-get-instant-responses-to-enquiries-through-the-banking-market-first-citichat-live-service-from-citibank-hungary","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"<a href=\"https://www.iengage-staging.infosys-platforms.com/citi-mortgage/blogs/newciticom/AN00033653_001.jpg\"></a><a href=\"https://www.citigroup.com/rcs/citigpa/storage/public/AN00033653_001.jpg\"></a><a onclick=\"window.open('resources/photos/blog/AN00033653_001-424.shtml','popup','width=2500,height=1775,scrollbars=no,resizable=no,toolbar=no,directories=no,location=no,menubar=no,status=no,left=0,top=0'); return false\" href=\"https://blog.citigroup.com/resources/photos/blog/AN00033653_001-424.shtml\"></a>One of the big challenges I mentioned in the <a href=\"https://blog.citigroup.com/2011/08/making-a-new-money-gallery-at-the-british-museum.shtml\">last post</a> is that this new display in the Money Gallery at the British Museum supported by Citi will cover a long timeframe, and talk about the story of money from its beginnings to the present day. Making a selection from the million or so objects in the collections of the <a href=\"https://www.britishmuseum.org/the_museum/departments/coins_and_medals.aspx\">Department of Coins and Medals</a> requires some careful thinking - what should we include, and, of course, what are going to have to leave out.","image":"638e2fe8a3c47c530c0a5a11","year":"2011","publishDate":"September 08, 2011","type":"insights","title":"From the British Museum and Citi: 4,000 years of the history of money in one room.","author.jobTitle":["British Museum"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2011/from-the-british-museum-and-citi-4000-years-of-the-history-of-money-in-one-room","tags":["Perspective Migration"],"month":"09","author.displayName":["Catherine Eagleton"],"siteId":"citigpa","category":"PERSPECTIVES"},{"summary":"Bangkok – Citi announced today a US$1 million commitment from the Citi Foundation to partner with Habitat for Humanity in launching an innovative three-year multi-country microsavings and financial education initiative. ","month":"09","year":"2011","publishDate":"September 07, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Commits US$1 Million to Habitat for Humanity for Microsavings and Financial Education","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/foundation/news/press-release/2011/citi-commits-us1-million-to-habitat-for-humanity-for-microsavings-and-financial-education","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"New York - According to the latest Citibank small-business survey released today, the majority of small-business owners believe they are poised to grow or are already in growth mode. Forty-nine percent say they are \"holding their own, but poised to grow when the climate is right\" and 28 percent indicated they are already growing. Despite feeling as though they are primed to grow should the opportunity present itself, the vast majority (90 percent) of small-business owners remain concerned about the economy, including the possibility of a double-dip recession. The results also show an increasing trend in small businesses feeling more prepared to withstand longer-term challenges.","month":"09","year":"2011","publishDate":"September 06, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citibank Survey Finds U.S. Small-Business Owners Prepared for Longer-Term Economic Challenges and Poised for Growth in 2012","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/citibank-survey-finds-us-small-business-owners-prepared-for-longer-term-economic-challenges-and-poised-for-growth-in-2012","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"In an appearance on Bloomberg TV's \"The Pulse,\" Jeremy Hale, global macro strategist at Citi, <a href=\"https://www.bloomberg.com/video/74852882/\">discusses</a> macroeconomic factors weighing on U.S. and European markets as well as policy options that could improve the outlook for growth.","image":"638e2feba3c47c530c0a5a1d","year":"2011","publishDate":"September 06, 2011","type":"insights","title":"Hale outlines macroeconomic pressures.","author.jobTitle":["Citi"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2011/hale-outlines-macroeconomic-pressures","tags":["Perspective Migration"],"month":"09","author.displayName":["Citi"],"siteId":"citigpa","category":"PERSPECTIVES"},{"summary":"If you're thinking of selling your home, you probably won't recoup the full cost of a major renovation. But there are plenty of relatively inexpensive things you can do that might make the place more attractive to buyers.","month":"09","author.displayName":["Jonathan Clements"],"year":"2011","publishDate":"September 06, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Fixing to sell.","category":"PERSPECTIVES","author.jobTitle":["Director of Financial Education, Citi Personal Wealth Management"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2011/fixing-to-sell","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"Budapest, Hungary - Six talented university graduate professionals received the 2011 Andras Felkai Academic Award on the 10th anniversary of the program. Mr. Batara Sianturi, Citibank Hungary's Citi Country Officer, Mr. Tamas Felkai, representing the Judging Committee, and Prof. Dr. Laszlo Palkovics, representing the organization joining the program as a new donor, presented the awards.","month":"09","year":"2011","publishDate":"September 05, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Hungary: Six Talented Young Hungarian Professionals Receive the 2011 Andras Felkai Academic Awards","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/hungary-six-talented-young-hungarian-professionals-receive-the-2011-andras-felkai-academic-awards","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"Citi Community Capital (CCC), the community development lending and investing division of Citi, recently closed a <a href=\"https://www.citigroup.com/citi/press/2011/110805b.htm\">tax-exempt bond issue</a> that will preserve and provide rehabilitation of 555 units of affordable housing, including 33 units for the physically impaired and 12 units for the hearing and sight impaired, in Hawaii.","month":"09","author.displayName":["Citi"],"year":"2011","publishDate":"September 05, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi helps finance the largest public affordable housing development in Hawaii.","category":"PERSPECTIVES","author.jobTitle":["Citi"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2011/citi-helps-finance-the-largest-public-affordable-housing-development-in-hawaii","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"Sao Paulo, Brazil - Credicard, a subsidiary of Citi in Brazil, launched the first ad featuring renowned celebrity Roberto Carlos for a new campaign for the Credicard <i>Emoções</i> (\"Emotions\") card. The commercial is part of a brand strategy that includes the sponsorship of the mega-show, \"<i>Emoções</i> in Jerusalem.\" Roberto Carlos is partnering with Credicard, who named the card after one of his greatest hits - the song \"<i>Emoções</i>.\" The singer's deep involvement in the project led him to act as co-author of the commercial, created by Publicis.","month":"09","year":"2011","publishDate":"September 02, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Roberto Carlos is the Celebrity Behind New Credicard Campaign","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/roberto-carlos-is-the-celebrity-behind-new-credicard-campaign","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"Managua, Nicaragua – Citi Nicaragua unveiled its exclusive global service, Citigold, at the first edition of the \"Nicaragua is\" awards, held September 1 in Managua.","month":"09","year":"2011","publishDate":"September 02, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Nicaragua Introduces Citigold During the First \"Nicaragua Is\" Awards","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/citi-nicaragua-introduces-citigold-during-the-first-nicaragua-is-awards","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"Ade Ayeyemi, Africa Head for Global Transaction Services, Citi, <a href=\"https://www.citibank.com/transactionservices/home/corporations/industries/videos/ade_africa_video.jsp\">discusses</a> the benefits to both China and Africa from the expansion of trade between the two regions as well as the role China is playing in developing Africa's infrastructure such as roads, rail, waterways and airports.","image":"638e2feda3c47c530c0a5a2c","year":"2011","publishDate":"September 02, 2011","type":"insights","title":"Connecting Africa with China.","author.jobTitle":["Citi"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2011/connecting-africa-with-china","tags":["Perspective Migration"],"month":"09","author.displayName":["Citi"],"siteId":"citigpa","category":"PERSPECTIVES"},{"summary":"Bucharest - After launching Citi Mobile, the first downloadable application in Romania that allows customers to perform transactions on smartphone devices, such as Apple, Android, Nokia and Blackberry, Citibank Romania has now made the service available for all mobile phones through the launch of the browser-based mobile banking solution.","month":"09","year":"2011","publishDate":"September 01, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Romania: Citi Mobile is Now Available for All Mobile Phone Browsers","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/romania-citi-mobile-is-now-available-for-all-mobile-phone-browsers","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"After a summer of unnerving debt ceiling negotiations, a U.S. credit downgrade, and a volatile stock market, consumers show a level of financial insecurity that is still high three years after the height of the financial crisis, according to a new nationwide survey issued by Citibank.","month":"09","author.displayName":["Citi"],"year":"2011","publishDate":"September 01, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Consumer confidence: \"Shaken by a tumultuous summer.\"","category":"PERSPECTIVES","author.jobTitle":["Citi"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2011/consumer-confidence-shaken-by-a-tumultuous-summer","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"Jason Johnson, Global Banking head of Citi's Energy, Power and Chemicals group in the Asia Pacific region, <a href=\"https://www.citibank.com/transactionservices/home/corporations/industries/videos/jason_growth_video.jsp\">says</a> he expects to see continued strong interest from Chinese energy companies in pursuing global M&A in 2011-2012, with potential moves in four key areas: deep water, larger countries, liquified natural gas, and refining.","image":"638e2fefa3c47c530c0a5a37","year":"2011","publishDate":"September 01, 2011","type":"insights","title":"Global M&A focus for China's energy companies.","author.jobTitle":["Citi"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2011/global-ma-focus-for-chinas-energy-companies","tags":["Perspective Migration"],"month":"09","author.displayName":["Citi"],"siteId":"citigpa","category":"PERSPECTIVES"},{"summary":"New York - A new nationwide survey issued today by Citibank finds a decline in consumers' expectations for the economy, even though their assessment of current economic conditions are virtually unchanged since the start of 2011. Three years after the height of the financial crisis, 72 percent of consumers believe the economy still has a way to go to reach bottom and 44 percent feel less financially secure now than they did in 2008. A silver lining to the results is the American public's self assessment, which remains largely unchanged. Sixty percent remain somewhat or very optimistic about their own personal economic situation over the next 12 months while 36 percent are somewhat or very pessimistic. ","month":"08","year":"2011","publishDate":"August 31, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"New Citibank Survey Shows Significant Shift in Consumer Psychology","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/new-citibank-survey-shows-significant-shift-in-consumer-psychology","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"In a <a href=\"https://www.citibank.com/transactionservices/home/corporations/industries/videos/au_china_video.jsp\">new video</a>, Citi China CEO Andrew Au speaks about the developing trade and investment corridors with other emerging markets. While Au says there are challenges for these multinationals in determining how much capital to deploy to support local operations and how to source it, there are opportunities as well \"to create a competitive edge relative to their peers in the industry if they do it well.\"","image":"638e2ff1a3c47c530c0a5a3e","year":"2011","publishDate":"August 30, 2011","type":"insights","title":"China increasing links with emerging markets.","author.jobTitle":["Citi"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2011/china-increasing-links-with-emerging-markets","tags":["Perspective Migration"],"month":"08","author.displayName":["Citi"],"siteId":"citigpa","category":"PERSPECTIVES"},{"summary":"The cover story of the August/September 2011 issue of <em>Working Mother</em> magazine names Citi to its list of top ten \"<a href=\"https://www.workingmother.com/node/115438/list\">Best Companies for Kids</a>.\" The survey evaluates companies on the health, financial and programmatic benefits they offer to employees who are parents, such as childcare, flexible work, company culture, women's career development and work/life programs.","month":"08","author.displayName":["Citi"],"year":"2011","publishDate":"August 30, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi among 2011 Working Mother Best Companies for Kids.","category":"PERSPECTIVES","author.jobTitle":["Citi"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2011/citi-among-2011-working-mother-best-companies-for-kids","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"Dubai, United Arab Emirates - flydubai and Citibank today announced a joint partnership that names Citibank as flydubai's first international banking partner and allows Citibank's PremierMiles and Citi Life Credit Cardmembers direct access to flydubai flights and services through the Citi Miles and CitiDollars loyalty programs.","month":"08","year":"2011","publishDate":"August 29, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"UAE: Citibank Partnership to Strengthen flydubai's Global Reach","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/ua