ed-best-foreign-bank-by-alpha-southeast-asia-magaine-2","tags":["Press Release Migration","Institutional Clients Group","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"Citi has partnered with the Pakistan Microfinance Network (PMN) to launch a comprehensive social impact study of microfinance in Pakistan. This initiative is based on a US$60,000 grant by the Citi Foundation, as Citi Pakistan celebrates its 50th year in the country.","month":"08","year":"2011","publishDate":"August 25, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Pakistan & PMN: Breaking New Ground in Microfinance Research","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/foundation/news/press-release/2011/citi-pakistan-pmn-breaking-new-ground-in-microfinance-research","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"Moscow - Citibank and Elecsnet agreed to offer free cash-in for the bank clients to make outstanding loan and credit-card balance payments.","month":"08","year":"2011","publishDate":"August 25, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Russia: Free Loan Payments via Elecsnet Terminals for Citibank Clients","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/russia-free-loan-payments-via-elecsnet-terminals-for-citibank-clients","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"Santo Domingo, Dominican Republic - Citi Foundation and the Council of American Foundations for Development (SOLIDARIOS), launched the seventh edition of the Citi Microenterprise Awards. One of the main objectives of the awards is to recognize entrepreneurs who have gradually achieved a social and economic impact with their efforts, reaching more than 25 percent of gross domestic product in the country. The introductory event was held at the Citi Tower in the Plaza Acropolis.","month":"08","year":"2011","publishDate":"August 24, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Foundation Launches the \"2011 Microenterprise Awards\"","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/foundation/news/press-release/2011/citi-foundation-launches-the-2011-microenterprise-awards","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"New York, N.Y. - As part of its partnership with Women's Professional Soccer (WPS), Citi today announced that it will kick off WPS Championship Weekend with a <i>Get Active with Citi Soccer Kids </i> clinic tomorrow in New York City.","month":"08","year":"2011","publishDate":"August 24, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi and Women's Professional Soccer Bring \"Get Active with Citi Soccer Kids\" Community Program to New York City's Iconic Bryant Park","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/citi-and-women-s-professional-soccer-bring-get-active-with-citi-soccer-kids-community-program-to-new-york-city-s-iconic-bryant-park","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"Citi and the New York Mets Alumni Association Presented by Citi hosted a luncheon and panel discussion to honor veterans at Citi Field on August 5. Moderator Howie Rose, of Sports Radio 66 WFAN, introduced the program, and then Adam Bryant, Membership Director of Iraq and Afghanistan Veterans of America (IAVA), and Chris Page, Citi's Vice President for Military Programs, briefly spoke about each organization's programs and goals for supporting veterans and their families.","image":"638e2ff4a3c47c530c0a5a4d","year":"2011","publishDate":"August 24, 2011","type":"insights","title":"Citi and the Mets Alumni honor veterans at Citi Field.","author.jobTitle":["Citi"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2011/citi-and-the-mets-alumni-honor-veterans-at-citi-field","tags":["Perspective Migration"],"month":"08","author.displayName":["Anu Ahluwalia"],"siteId":"citigpa","category":"PERSPECTIVES"},{"summary":"In an <a href=\"https://www.bloomberg.com/video/74263164/\">appearance</a> today on Bloomberg TV, Geoffrey Dennis, Citi's global emerging markets strategist, shared his short-term and long-term outlook for emerging markets equities amid softer U.S. economic data.","image":"638e2ff5a3c47c530c0a5a56","year":"2011","publishDate":"August 22, 2011","type":"insights","title":"Dennis discusses emerging markets fundamentals.","author.jobTitle":["Citi"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2011/dennis-discusses-emerging-markets-fundamentals","tags":["Perspective Migration"],"month":"08","author.displayName":["Citi"],"siteId":"citigpa","category":"PERSPECTIVES"},{"summary":"iMentor, currently pairing 1,800 New York professionals with local public high school students, recently <a href=\"https://www.imentor.org/blog/citi-volunteers-are-making-a-difference\">blogged</a> about the commitment of Citi volunteers to its College Success program. More than 40 Citi employees have provided 1,350 hours of volunteer service to iMentor this year, working on various activities with their mentees such as college and scholarship applications, making a successful transition in their freshman year of college, writing resumes and practicing interview skills.","month":"08","author.displayName":["Citi"],"year":"2011","publishDate":"August 22, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"iMentor blogs about Citi volunteers' support.","category":"PERSPECTIVES","author.jobTitle":["Citi"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2011/imentor-blogs-about-citi-volunteers-support","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"Whenever we get periods of market turmoil like we've had in recent weeks, you will hear financial advisors talk about \"rebalancing.\" What's that? Imagine you had settled on a mix of 60% in U.S. and foreign stocks and 40% in high-quality bonds, certificates of deposit and other conservative investments.","month":"08","author.displayName":["Jonathan Clements"],"year":"2011","publishDate":"August 22, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Keeping your balance.","category":"PERSPECTIVES","author.jobTitle":["Director of Financial Education, Citi Personal Wealth Management"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2011/keeping-your-balance","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"For their pioneering work in microfinance and vocational training, Citi Philippines and Citi Pakistan have been recognized and awarded the 'Best Community Program' in the Gold Category at the Global CSR Summit 2011.","month":"08","year":"2011","publishDate":"August 19, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Philippines and Citi Pakistan Win the Gold Award for 'Best Community Program' at the Global CSR Summit 2011","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/foundation/news/press-release/2011/citi-philippines-and-citi-pakistan-win-the-gold-award-for-best-community-program-at-the-global-csr-summit-2011","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"Casablanca - The Citi Foundation announced a grant of US$40,000 this year in support of several educational programs set forth by Injaz Al Maghrib, including \"Entrepreneurship Masterclass,\" \"Success Skills\" and \"Banks in Action.\"","month":"08","year":"2011","publishDate":"August 19, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Morocco: Citi Foundation Supports Injaz Al Maghrib in the Launch of New Educational Programs","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/foundation/news/press-release/2011/morocco-citi-foundation-supports-inja-al-maghrib-in-the-launch-of-new-educational-programs","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"Atlanta, Ga. - Today, Citi announced a multi-year renewal of its long-standing U.S. credit card relationship with Shell.","month":"08","year":"2011","publishDate":"August 18, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Renews Credit Card-Issuing Relationship with Shell","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/citi-renews-credit-card-issuing-relationship-with-shell","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"New York - Citi, in collaboration with Best Buy®, is introducing the first mobile rewards app to provide a new and convenient way to redeem points from Citi ThankYou(SM) Rewards on your iPhone, iPod touch or Android device. Citi ThankYou members can opt to shop and redeem ThankYou® Points and pick up products within minutes at any Best Buy store, or have products shipped anywhere in the continental U.S. Citi ThankYou members can download the app for free from the App Store(SM) or Android Market.","month":"08","year":"2011","publishDate":"August 18, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Introduces the New ThankYou® Rewards App","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/citi-introduces-the-new-thankyou-rewards-app","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"Singapore - More than 140 of Citi's senior managers and partners teed off for a good cause today. They raised a record-breaking sum of S$570,000 for ChildAid, a charity concert in aid of The Straits Times School Pocket Money Fund and The Business Times Budding Artists Fund. It is the largest amount of funds raised in a single event organized by Citi Singapore. All proceeds of the Citi Information Technology and Partners Charity Golf 2011 event will go towards helping the underprivileged children who are receiving assistance from the two Funds.","month":"08","year":"2011","publishDate":"August 17, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Singapore: Citi Raises More Than $570,000 for ChildAid through Charity Golf Event","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/singapore-citi-raises-more-than-570000-for-childaid-through-charity-golf-event","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"Guangzhou - Citibank (China) Co., Ltd. (\"Citibank China\") today opened a new sub-branch in Guangzhou and will also open a new sub-branch in Shenzhen this week. The openings continue Citibank's strong growth momentum in China and follow last week's opening of a new Smart Banking sub-branch in Shanghai.","month":"08","year":"2011","publishDate":"August 17, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citibank Opens New Sub Branches in Southern China","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/citibank-opens-new-sub-branches-in-southern-china","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"Warsaw - Citi Handlowy, in partnership with Wizz Air, is introducing a new product - the Citibank Wizz Air World MasterCard® credit card. Formed in partnership with the largest low-fare airline in Central and Eastern Europe, it is the first airline card of its type in Poland that offers Wizz Air services and air tickets with several features. The card provides all incentives that are usually offered for the holders of Citi Handlowy credit cards, plus guaranteed discounts at nearly 5,000 points of sale across Poland.","month":"08","year":"2011","publishDate":"August 17, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citibank Wizz Air World Mastercard® Credit Card","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/citibank-wi-air-world-mastercard-credit-card","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"Traditionally, mortgage lenders in the United States (banks, savings & loans, mortgage bankers and credit unions) generally made a loan to a borrower under guidelines provided by investors, including government sponsored entities (GSEs) such as Fannie Mae or Freddie Mac, or made a loan according to their own institution's guidelines. In either case, the lender certified that the loan met the applicable guidelines. Many of these loans were sold and the lender used the money to make more loans. This system was called the \"originate-to-distribute\" lending model.","month":"08","author.displayName":["John P. Carey"],"year":"2011","publishDate":"August 17, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"The Dodd-Frank Act and Qualified Residential Mortgages.","category":"PERSPECTIVES","author.jobTitle":["Chief Administrative Officer, North America Consumer Banking"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2011/the-dodd-frank-act-and-qualified-residential-mortgages","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"The Money gallery at the British Museum opened 14 years ago, and was at the time a new way of displaying coins and medals. It represented a new way of thinking about the history of money, and changed the way museums around the world told this global story.","image":"638e2ff9a3c47c530c0a5a69","year":"2011","publishDate":"August 16, 2011","type":"insights","title":"Making a new Money gallery at the British Museum.","author.jobTitle":["British Museum"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2011/making-a-new-money-gallery-at-the-british-museum","tags":["Perspective Migration"],"month":"08","author.displayName":["Catherine Eagleton"],"siteId":"citigpa","category":"PERSPECTIVES"},{"summary":"Sao Paulo - Citibank Brazil launched a major campaign called \"Discover your Citi\" to reinforce the bank's position. \"We are emphasizing what we do best: premium quality and personalized service for our customers,\" says the Citi Country Officer of Citibank Brazil, Paula Cardoso.","month":"08","year":"2011","publishDate":"August 15, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Brazil: Citibank in the Media with a New Campaign Designed by Publicis","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/brail-citibank-in-the-media-with-a-new-campaign-designed-by-publicis","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"Today, <a href=\"http://www.citicommunitydevelopment.com/\">Citi Community Development</a> and the <a href=\"http://www.self-help.org/california/self-help-federal-credit-union-in-california/micro-branch\">Center for Community Self-Help</a> (\"Self-Help\") announced a joint effort to advance the Micro Branch model, a cutting-edge approach to providing responsible check cashing and other financial services typically offered by alternative, sometimes predatory financial services providers. Self-Help's Micro Branch is a unique check-casher/credit union hybrid model that has the look and feel of a check cashing business but provides responsible financial products and services tailored for unbanked individuals. Self-Help's first Micro Branch, which serves primarily Latino immigrants, opened in San Jose in January 2010.","month":"08","year":"2011","publishDate":"August 15, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi and Self-Help Expand Micro Branch Model to Move People Away From Alternative and Often Costly Financial Services","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/citi-and-self-help-expand-micro-branch-model-to-move-people-away-from-alternative-and-often-costly-financial-services","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"Budapest - Mobile user penetration is estimated at 95 percent in Hungary, and with the rapidly growing number of busy and tech savvy customers, there is an increasing customer demand for mobile banking services. In response to this customer need, Citibank introduces its state-of-art mobile banking service, Citi Mobile, which allows customers to enjoy a superior, secure and smart banking experience anytime and anywhere in the world, including transactions on their Citibank accounts.","month":"08","year":"2011","publishDate":"August 15, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citibank Hungary Launches Mobile Banking","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/citibank-hungary-launches-mobile-banking","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"To help reduce the risk of investing in stocks, we're told to diversify. But diversification has its limits. To understand those limits, consider the crucial distinction between \"specific\" and \"systematic\" risk.","month":"08","author.displayName":["Jonathan Clements"],"year":"2011","publishDate":"August 15, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Diversification's limits.","category":"PERSPECTIVES","author.jobTitle":["Director of Financial Education, Citi Personal Wealth Management"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2011/diversifications-limits","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"Santo Domingo, Dominican Republic - Citi Dominican Republic supports the MIR Foundation and low-income youth in La Romana. Maximo R. Vidal, Citi Country Officer for the Dominican Republic, along with other Citi executives, traveled to eastern Dominican Republic to gather with Citi Foundation-sponsored students, which will take part in the Professional Training School Program.","month":"08","year":"2011","publishDate":"August 11, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Dominican Republic Visits the MIR Foundation","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/foundation/news/press-release/2011/citi-dominican-republic-visits-the-mir-foundation","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"New York - Citi® today announced the launch of the Citi® Corporate Chip and PIN card, a compliant smart card designed for U.S. corporate cardholders traveling abroad, a first by any U.S. commercial card issuer. The cards, which 