, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Supporting America's veterans.","category":"PERSPECTIVES","author.jobTitle":["CEO"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2011/supporting-americas-veterans-1","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"Do you get statements from your mutual-fund company or brokerage firm telling you how your account has performed? It's important to understand how those returns are calculated.","month":"08","author.displayName":["Jonathan Clements"],"year":"2011","publishDate":"August 08, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Time-weighted vs. dollar-weighted returns.","category":"PERSPECTIVES","author.jobTitle":["Director of Financial Education, Citi Personal Wealth Management"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2011/time-weighted-vs-dollar-weighted-returns","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"month":"08","author.displayName":["Citi"],"year":"2011","publishDate":"August 05, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"\"Money Spent, Money Mourned.\"","category":"PERSPECTIVES","author.jobTitle":["Citi"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2011/money-spent-money-mourned","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"Citi Community Development has committed $200,000 for IFF, a leading Community Development Financial Institution (CDFI) based in Chicago, to develop a scalable framework for designing, developing and financing community health centers. That groundwork is the first step in IFF's \"Health Centers for Healthy Communities\" <a href=\"https://www.citigroup.com/citi/press/2011/110728d.htm\">initiative</a>, which aims to develop or expand a minimum of 10 community-based health care clinics in the Midwest.","month":"08","author.displayName":["Citi"],"year":"2011","publishDate":"August 05, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Tackling critical community development with IFF.","category":"PERSPECTIVES","author.jobTitle":["Citi"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2011/tackling-critical-community-development-with-iff","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"London-based Environmental Finance magazine named the Citi-led deal to finance the Shepherd's Flat Wind Farm in Oregon as Renewable Energy Deal of the Year in its 2011 awards series. On the blog in January, we <a href=\"https://blog.citigroup.com/2011/01/citi-helps-bring-more-wind-energy-to-the-us.shtml\">noted</a> that the Shepherd's Flat project was expected to produce enough renewable energy to power more than 200,000 average California households, would create hundreds of jobs directly and indirectly for the local economy and would set a precedent as the first deal of its kind supported with a U.S. Department of Energy loan guarantee.","month":"08","author.displayName":["Citi"],"year":"2011","publishDate":"August 05, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Shepherd's Flat is Environmental Finance Renewable Energy Deal of the Year.","category":"PERSPECTIVES","author.jobTitle":["Citi"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2011/shepherds-flat-is-environmental-finance-renewable-energy-deal-of-the-year","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"New York - Citi and the New York Mets Alumni Association Presented by Citi announced that they will team up Friday, August 5, at Citi Field to honor and thank U.S. veterans at a luncheon and panel discussion with Mets alumni, including Hall of Famers Tom Seaver and Ralph Kiner. Additionally, the Mets and Citi will honor the Iraq and Afghanistan Veterans of America (IAVA), the country's first and largest non-profit, non-partisan organization dedicated to improving the lives of the more than 2.2 million veterans of Iraq and Afghanistan and their families. The project is part of the Mets and Citi's \"Teammates in the Community\" initiative, reflecting their ongoing commitment to be active participants in the community.","month":"08","year":"2011","publishDate":"August 04, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi and the Mets Alumni Association Presented by Citi to Honor and Thank U.S. Veterans at Citi Field Luncheon","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/citi-and-the-mets-alumni-association-presented-by-citi-to-honor-and-thank-us-veterans-at-citi-field-luncheon","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"Hawaii - Citi Community Capital (CCC), the community development lending and investing division of Citigroup, recently closed a tax-exempt bond issue that provided a permanent loan for Kuhio Park Terrace with credit enhancement from Freddie Mac. The transaction will preserve and provide financing for the rehabilitation of 555 units of affordable housing, including 33 units for the physically impaired and 12 units for the hearing and sight impaired.","month":"08","year":"2011","publishDate":"August 04, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Closes Financing on Kuhio Park Terrace, the Largest Public Affordable Housing Development in Hawaii","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/citi-closes-financing-on-kuhio-park-terrace-the-largest-public-affordable-housing-development-in-hawaii","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"Hong Kong - Citi has set up a new business to service the fast-developing Exchange Traded Fund (ETF) market in Asia. The new business, Citi ETF Services, will cover the Asia Pacific region - the fastest growing region for ETFs - and will provide a single channel for clients looking to launch ETFs within the region.","month":"08","year":"2011","publishDate":"August 04, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Launches ETF Services in Asia Pacific","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/citi-launches-etf-services-in-asia-pacific","tags":["Press Release Migration","Institutional Clients Group"]},{"summary":"Steven Wieting, managing director of economic and marketing analysis at Citi, <a href=\"https://www.bloomberg.com/video/73477530/\">spoke</a> to Bloomberg TV about weak U.S. economic data, the impact of the debt-ceiling debate on the equity markets and prospects for a third round of quantitative easing by the Federal Reserve. He said probability is low for a double-dip recession, noting that \"we think the expansion is intact\" and \"there is a big difference between slow growth and recession.\"","image":"638e3001a3c47c530c0a5a94","year":"2011","publishDate":"August 04, 2011","type":"insights","title":"On Bloomberg TV: Wieting shares his view of U.S. economic outlook.","author.jobTitle":["Citi"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2011/on-bloomberg-tv-wieting-shares-his-view-of-us-economic-outlook","tags":["Perspective Migration"],"month":"08","author.displayName":["Citi"],"siteId":"citigpa","category":"PERSPECTIVES"},{"summary":"Athough Americans have heard a lot about the debt ceiling negotiations in Washington over the past few weeks, many do not fully understand the problem of the U.S. debt load itself, which is likely to generate severe challenges in the years ahead. Indeed, the U.S. debt to gross domestic product (GDP) ratio is back up to levels last seen after World War II. Given current budget deficits, the ratio likely will climb further. Economists will contend that faster economic growth would be very helpful in addressing this uncomfortable situation but there will be major hurdles to climb.","month":"08","author.displayName":["Tobias Levkovich"],"year":"2011","publishDate":"August 04, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Debt difficulties.","category":"PERSPECTIVES","author.jobTitle":["Chief US Equity Strategist, Citi"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2011/debt-difficulties","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"Miami, Fla. - Citi announced today that it has won 26 awards in the first round of <i>Global Finance</i> magazine's <a href=\"http://www.gfmag.com/tools/best-banks/11329-worlds-best-internet-banks-in-latin-america-2011.html\" target=\"blank\">World's Best Internet Banks in Latin America</a> 2011 competition, including eight of eight in the regional sub-category awards and 18 country awards in the <a href=\"http://www.gfmag.com/tools/best-banks/11329-worlds-best-internet-banks-in-latin-america-2011.html\" target=\"blank\">Best Corporate/Institutional Internet Banks</a> category.","month":"08","year":"2011","publishDate":"August 03, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Latin America: Citi Recognized by Global Finance with 26 Awards for \"World's Best Internet Banks in Latin America 2011\"","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/latin-america-citi-recognied-by-global-finance-with-26-awards-for-world-s-best-internet-banks-in-latin-america-2011","tags":["Press Release Migration","Institutional Clients Group","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"Jakarta - Citi Indonesia, the Overseas Private Investment Corporation (OPIC) and Bank Danamon announced the closing of a $20 million term loan to fund the growth of Bank Danamon's Microfinance program, Danamon Simpan Pinjam (DSP), and to promote the financial inclusion of microentrepreneurs and small businesses in Indonesia. This loan will be the first from Citi and OPIC for the microfinance sector in Indonesia and is a part of Citi's and OPIC's $250 million joint global initiative to support microfinance lending in emerging markets worldwide.","month":"08","year":"2011","publishDate":"August 03, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi, Opic and Bank Danamon Support the Rapid Growth of the Microfinance Sector in Indonesia with $20 Million Term Funding","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/citi-opic-and-bank-danamon-support-the-rapid-growth-of-the-microfinance-sector-in-indonesia-with-20-million-term-funding","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"San Francisco and New York - Citi, the leading global financial services company, and BabyCenter®, the #1 pregnancy and parenting destination worldwide, have teamed up to release the \"U.S. 2011 BabyCenter Cost of Raising a Child\" report. BabyCenter tapped into its national member network to identify the financial challenges moms face, particularly in today's economy. More than 1,000 moms completed the survey, answering questions about how money impacts their decisions, from having children to prioritizing saving for retirement versus their child's college education and more. Citi sponsored the report as part of its ongoing efforts to provide insights that help women manage their finances as well as strategies and tools to help simplify their financial lives.","month":"08","year":"2011","publishDate":"August 03, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Teams Up with BabyCenter to Reach Moms During the Moments That Matter","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/citi-teams-up-with-babycenter-to-reach-moms-during-the-moments-that-matter","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"Citi and the Lahore University of Management Sciences have partnered once again on a Financial Capability and Asset Building Program for students who are part of LUMS' National Outreach Program, based on a $35,000 Citi Foundation grant. As part of this program, students from all across Pakistan participated in an intensive workshop, which included modules on the basics of banking, savings, managing money, concepts of credit and smart investments among other elements of financial capability and asset building. The program was based on the case-study method to provide students with maximum exposure to real-world situations.","month":"08","year":"2011","publishDate":"August 02, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Living Literacy, Changing Lives: Citi Partners with Premier Business School LUMS for a Financial Capability-Building Program","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/foundation/news/press-release/2011/living-literacy-changing-lives-citi-partners-with-premier-business-school-lums-for-a-financial-capability-building-program","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"Guiyang - Citibank (China) Co. Ltd. (\"Citi\") and The Mountain Institute (\"TMI\") today announced the launch of a new initiative known as \"Citi-TMI Guizhou Indigenous Batik Development Program.\" Made possible by a Citi Foundation grant, the program aims to increase income levels of 1,000 rural artisan household enterprises in Danzhai County, Guizhou Province by enhancing their production and marketing skills of batik, a traditional Miao handicraft. In addition to enhancing production and preservation of this traditional handicraft, the program will also generate economic, environmental and social benefits.","month":"08","year":"2011","publishDate":"August 02, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"China: Citi Supports Indigenous Batik Development Program in Guizhou Province","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/foundation/news/press-release/2011/china-citi-supports-indigenous-batik-development-program-in-guihou-province","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"Moscow - The Entrepreneurship Competition will be held from Aug. 1 until Dec. 30, 2011.The goal is to encourage the best microentrepreneurs and micro-financing organizations across Russia and to raise public and government awareness about entrepreneurship in the microfinance industry. This competition is actually a part of Citi Foundation's global program operating in 28 countries.","month":"08","year":"2011","publishDate":"August 02, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Russia: Seventh Annual Citi Russia Micro-Enterprise Awards","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/foundation/news/press-release/2011/russia-seventh-annual-citi-russia-micro-enterprise-awards","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"Citi recently hosted \"Pride in Citi\", a panel discussion and networking event for LGBT undergraduate and graduate students at the company's markets and banking division, headquartered in downtown New York City. Suni Harford, ICG Regional Head of Markets for North America, kicked off the panel by emphasizing Citi's commitment to all forms of diversity. \"Diversity in our employee talent pool at Citi is a business imperative given the diversity of our clients, the diversity of our products, the diversity of the geographic regions in which we work, and the diversity inherent in the communities in which we serve,\" she said to the over 50 students in attendance, comprising mainly interns at Citi and other firms on Wall Street.","month":"08","author.displayName":["Sophia Stewart"],"year":"2011","publishDate":"August 02, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"\"Pride in Citi.\"","category":"PERSPECTIVES","author.jobTitle":["Institutional Clients Group, Citi"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2011/pride-in-citi","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"Hong Kong - Citigroup Asia Pacific was named the World's Best Internet Bank in 13 markets across Asia Pacific by <i>Global Finance</i> magazine. The award assesses banks' capabilities in consumer and corporate/institutional internet banking across countries and service/process categories.","month":"08","year":"2011","publishDate":"August 01, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Earns World's Best Internet Banks Awards","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/citi-earns-world-s-best-internet-banks-awards","tags":["Press Release Migration","Institutional Clients Group","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"Citi, the leading global financial services company, and JCB International (JCBI), the international operations subsidiary of JCB, announced today that they will extend their partnership by adding JCB credit card merchants in nine countries and territories throughout Asia.","month":"08","year":"2011","publishDate":"August 01, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi and JCB International Extend Partnership in Asia","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/citi-and-jcb-international-extend-partnership-in-asia","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"As co-host on CNBC's Squawk Box today, Citi's Chief U.S. Equity Strategist Tobias Levokovich was among those looking at the <a href=\"https://video.cnbc.com/gallery/?video=3000036209\">impact</a> of a debt ceiling deal, slow growth and unemployment on markets.","image":"638e3005a3c47c530c0a5aa7","year":"2011","publishDate":"August 01, 2011","type":"insights","title":"Levkovich on U.S. growth and debt concerns.","author.jobTitle":["Citi"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2011/levkovich-on-us-growth-and-debt-concerns","tags":["Perspective Migration"],"month":"08","author.displayName":["Citi"],"siteId":"citigpa","category":"PERSPECTIVES"},{"summary":"Did you owe the IRS a lot in taxes last year? You still have several months to make adjustments for 2011 and perhaps avoid a significant tax penalty.","month":"08","author.displayName":["Jonathan Clements"],"year":"2011","publishDate":"August 01, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"To have and to withhold.","category":"PERSPECTIVES","author.jobTitle":["Director of Financial Education, Citi Personal Wealth Management"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2011/to-have-and-to-withhold","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"Dubai - Citi today announced that it has won several awards in the first round of <i>Global Finance</i> magazine's awards for the 2011 Best Internet Banks in the Middle East and Africa.","month":"07","year":"2011","publishDate":"July 31, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Named Winner in Global Finance Magazine's Awards for \"World's Best Internet Bank 2011\"","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/citi-named-winner-in-global-finance-magaine-s-awards-for-world-s-best-internet-bank-2011","tags":["Press Release Migration","Institutional Clients Group","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"Dalian – Citibank (China) Co., Ltd. (\"Citibank\") today opened its first sub-branch in Dalian. The new sub-branch is Citibank's first Smart Banking outlet in the city and is designed to provide customers with a unique and superior banking experience. Jonathan Larsen, Head of Consumer Bank and Cards, Citi Asia Pacific, Andrew Au, Chief Executive Officer, Citi China, and Simon Chow, Country Business Manager of Consumer Bank, Citi China, attended the opening ceremony.","month":"07","year":"2011","publishDate":"July 29, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citibank China Expands Presence in Dalian","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/citibank-china-expands-presence-in-dalian","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"month":"07","author.displayName":["Citi"],"year":"2011","publishDate":"July 29, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"In the FT: Buiter and Rahbari on the debt ceiling impasse.","category":"PERSPECTIVES","author.jobTitle":["Citi"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2011/in-the-ft-buiter-and-rahbari-on-the-debt-ceiling-impasse","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"Empowering individuals to establish or re-establish good credit is a key part of asset building and achieving financial inclusion. In today's economy, establishing a positive credit history often opens the door to lower cost and wider choice as well as to appropriate financial services that can contribute to building assets such as a home or small business. Good credit also enables people to manage emergencies; avoid alternative financial services; and build financial capability.","month":"07","author.displayName":["Bob Annibale"],"year":"2011","publishDate":"July 29, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"A new coalition of organizations to support credit-building through financial coaching and access.","category":"PERSPECTIVES","author.jobTitle":["Citi Pride Affinity Co-lead"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2011/a-new-coalition-of-organizations-to-support-credit-building-through-financial-coaching-and-access","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"Chicago, Ill. – Citi and <a href=\"http://www.iff.org/\" target=\"blank\">IFF</a>, a leading Community Development Financial Institution (CDFI) based in Chicago, today announced a new partnership for developing community infrastructure at scale by innovatively combining IFF's financing and real estate development services. The goal of the \"Health Centers for Healthy Communities\" initiative is to use at least $75 million in private sector capital and to develop or expand a minimum of 10 community-based health care clinics across five Midwest states. <a href=\"http://www.citicommunitydevelopment.com/\">Citi Community Development</a> is providing a $200,000 contribution to IFF to support the creation of this new model, including the necessary market research, policy analysis and community outreach. IFF, which has extensive experience in financing health care clinics, will be ready by the end of this year to implement the platform for the development of nonprofit clinics in Chicago and across IFF's five-state service area of Illinois, Indiana, Iowa, Missouri and Wisconsin.","month":"07","year":"2011","publishDate":"July 28, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Community Development and IFF Will Lay Groundwork for Expansion of Community-Based Health Care Facilities in Five States","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/citi-community-development-and-iff-will-lay-groundwork-for-expansion-of-community-based-health-care-facilities-in-five-states","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"San Jose, Calif. and New York – SunPower Corp. (NASDAQ: SPWRA, SPWRB) and Citi (NYSE: C) today announced a new fund for approximately $105 million in residential solar lease projects. SunPower will use the fund to extend its SunPower® Lease to customers in eight states, expanding the financing options available to homeowners interested in high-efficiency SunPower solar power systems, the most efficient solar technology available today. Citi is contributing $80 million to the fund.","month":"07","year":"2011","publishDate":"July 28, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"SunPower and Citi Team to Finance $105 Million in Residential Solar Lease Projects","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/sunpower-and-citi-team-to-finance-105-million-in-residential-solar-lease-projects","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"I'm excited to report that Citi has launched its first-ever consumer banking app designed specifically for iPad®, an engaging, visually rich tool allowing U.S. clients to track, analyze and plan their finances. It is a real departure from traditional ledger-style banking, taking advantage of the unique tablet experience to offer interesting visual representations of consumer accounts and transactions. For example, users can:","image":"638e300aa3c47c530c0a5abc","year":"2011","publishDate":"July 28, 2011","type":"insights","title":"Citibank debuts App for iPad®.","author.jobTitle":["Head of Internet and Mobile Banking, North America Consumer Banking"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2011/citibank-debuts-app-for-ipad","tags":["Perspective Migration"],"month":"07","author.displayName":["Tracey Weber"],"siteId":"citigpa","category":"PERSPECTIVES"},{"summary":"Starting this month, changes to federal law require that lenders disclose to consumers certain information, including the credit score used to (1) turn down a loan application (known as an \"adverse action\") or (2) approve a loan, but not at the best available interest rate (known as a \"risk-based pricing\" decision). This change to federal law adds to the existing requirement that lenders disclose or provide upon request a general reason for an adverse action credit decision.","month":"07","author.displayName":["John P. Carey"],"year":"2011","publishDate":"July 28, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Dodd-Frank Act mandates free credit scores for prospective borrowers.","category":"PERSPECTIVES","author.jobTitle":["Chief Administrative Officer, North America Consumer Banking"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2011/dodd-frank-act-mandates-free-credit-scores-for-prospective-borrowers","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"San Salvador, El Salvador – Citi El Salvador will be hosting the Citi Solutions Fair, aiming to provide clients with the best solutions to their financial needs.","month":"07","year":"2011","publishDate":"July 27, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"El Salvador: Citi Solutions Fair Offers Clients Financial Alternatives","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/el-salvador-citi-solutions-fair-offers-clients-financial-alternatives","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"New York – To mark the year-out milestone to the London 2012 Olympic Games, Citi, an official sponsor of the 2012 U.S. Olympic and Paralympic Teams and the U.S. Olympic Committee, held a ceremonial Citi Team USA flag-raising event outside the Citibank Financial Center at its headquarters in New York City. Olympic silver medalist Alicia Sacramone (gymnastics), Olympic gold medalist Susan Francia (rowing), and two-time Paralympic gold medalist Jeremy Campbell (discus, pentathlon) joined Citi CEO Vikram Pandit and employees to kick off the one-year countdown.","month":"07","year":"2011","publishDate":"July 27, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Celebrates Sponsorship of 2012 U.S. Olympic & Paralympic Teams With Flag-Raising Event to Mark \"Year-Out\" Milestone","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/citi-celebrates-sponsorship-of-2012-us-olympic-paralympic-teams-with-flag-raising-event-to-mark-year-out-milestone","tags":["Press Release Migration","Citi-Wide"]},{"summary":"Boston, Mass. – As part of its partnership with Women's Professional Soccer (WPS), Citi today announced that <i>Get Active with Citi Soccer Kids</i>, a program that connects current stars from the league with future stars from its communities and promotes a healthy lifestyle for kids, is coming to Boston tomorrow, July 28. This initiative is taking place in league markets and includes access to WPS players and coaches, tickets to games, gift bags and memorable in-game experiences for kids associated with America SCORES, an after-school program that empowers students in urban communities.","month":"07","year":"2011","publishDate":"July 27, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi and Women's Professional Soccer Bring \"Get Active with Citi Soccer Kids\" Community Program to Boston to Benefit Area Youth","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/citi-and-women-s-professional-soccer-bring-get-active-with-citi-soccer-kids-community-program-to-boston-to-benefit-area-youth","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"New York – Furthering CEO Vikram Pandit's vision to become the world's digital bank, Citibank today unveiled its first consumer banking app designed specifically for iPad. Citibank for iPad® provides U.S. consumer banking clients with an engaging, visually rich tool to track, analyze and plan their finances.","month":"07","year":"2011","publishDate":"July 27, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citibank Sets New Standard for Digital Banking with Debut of Citibank for iPad® App","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/citibank-sets-new-standard-for-digital-banking-with-debut-of-citibank-for-ipad-app","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"New York – Citi announced today that its Global Transaction Services business began providing Direct Custody and Clearing (DCC) services to clients investing in Panama. This new service expands Citi's proprietary DCC network to eight markets across Latin America.","month":"07","year":"2011","publishDate":"July 26, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Establishes Direct Custody and Clearing Services in Panama","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/citi-establishes-direct-custody-and-clearing-services-in-panama","tags":["Press Release Migration","Institutional Clients Group"]},{"summary":"Port of Spain, Trinidad &amp; Tobago – Citi and Citi Foundation will provide funding to KIND in support of its Integrated Literacy Development Program for 2011-2012. This program is expected to benefit approximately 100 children from low-income families.","month":"07","year":"2011","publishDate":"July 26, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi's Par