 Migration","Institutional Clients Group"]},{"summary":"San Salvador, El Salvador – Citi El Salvador launches a new promotion for its clients, offering prizes when redeeming Citi debit card vouchers.","month":"07","year":"2011","publishDate":"July 25, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Offers Giveaways with Debit Card Vouchers","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/citi-offers-giveaways-with-debit-card-vouchers","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"New York – More than half of consumers have paid a bill late in their lifetime, according to the Citi Simplicity Survey. Forgetting a due date was the top cause of delay, and late fees were the primary concern stated by survey respondents who have paid a bill late. Responding to consumers' desire for a simplified credit experience, Citi Cards is introducing the Citi Simplicity Card to U.S. consumers. The Citi Simplicity Card uniquely offers the combination of: a single rate across all purchases, balance transfers and cash advances, no late fees and no penalty rate.","month":"07","year":"2011","publishDate":"July 25, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Simplifies Credit with a Single APR and No Late Fees or Penalty Rate","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/citi-simplifies-credit-with-a-single-apr-and-no-late-fees-or-penalty-rate","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"London – Citi today announced that its subsidiary Egg Banking plc has entered into an agreement to sell its Egg and Pi-branded Mortgage and Savings Business, along with the Egg and Pi Brands, to Yorkshire Building Society. The £2.5billion* savings book and £430 million* mortgage book represent approximately 550,000 customers.","month":"07","year":"2011","publishDate":"July 25, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi to Sell Egg Mortgage and Savings Business to Yorkshire Building Society","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/citi-to-sell-egg-mortgage-and-savings-business-to-yorkshire-building-society","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"month":"07","author.displayName":["Citi"],"year":"2011","publishDate":"July 25, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Raising capital for Delaware energy efficiency initiative.","category":"PERSPECTIVES","author.jobTitle":["Citi"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2011/raising-capital-for-delaware-energy-efficiency-initiative","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"Investing aficionados love to debate the relative merits of index funds, which simply seek to replicate the performance of a market index, and actively managed mutual funds, which aim to generate market-beating performance. But there's no arguing with the numbers. We're talking here about a regular report from Standard & Poor's, a unit of McGraw-Hill, that's known as SPIVA, short for Standard & Poor's Indices Versus Active. This scorecard compares the performance of actively managed funds to an appropriate benchmark index. The fund performance figures are not adjusted for initial or back-end sales commissions.","month":"07","author.displayName":["Jonathan Clements"],"year":"2011","publishDate":"July 25, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Index vs. active funds.","category":"PERSPECTIVES","author.jobTitle":["Director of Financial Education, Citi Personal Wealth Management"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2011/index-vs-active-funds","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"San Salvador, El Salvador – With the launch of Citi at Work, the bank is always within your reach. This new program offers a wide range of opportunities, benefits, privileges and products tailored to companies and their personnel.","month":"07","year":"2011","publishDate":"July 22, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Meet Citi at Work El Salvador - An Exclusive Program for Companies and Their Employees","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/meet-citi-at-work-el-salvador--an-exclusive-program-for-companies-and-their-employees","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"Chicago – Representatives of 11 Chicago-area community development organizations and Citi will gather today to applaud Chicago City Treasurer Stephanie D. Neely's launch of the <i>Bank On Chicago</i> financial inclusion initiative and to announce that they have joined together to form the Chicago Credit Building Coalition (CCBC).","month":"07","year":"2011","publishDate":"July 22, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Chicago Credit Building Coalition to Provide Innovative, Credit-Building Financial Products along with Financial Education and Coaching","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/chicago-credit-building-coalition-to-provide-innovative-credit-building-financial-products-along-with-financial-education-and-coaching","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"It is always interesting to look at investor survey work since it tends to provide some quantitative backdrop to the qualitative sense one gets discussing portfolios and markets with fund managers. Our latest data gathered earlier in the month from about 125 mutual, pension and hedge fund professionals argue that risk aversion has not truly come out in full force despite general economic and political concerns. For instance, while cash holdings have ticked up from about 6% of assets under management in April to over 7.5% currently, that is far less than the 11% level experienced last July when economic double-dip fears raged.","image":"638e300ea3c47c530c0a5ad1","year":"2011","publishDate":"July 22, 2011","type":"insights","title":"Parsing our investor poll.","author.jobTitle":["Chief US Equity Strategist, Citi"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2011/parsing-our-investor-poll","tags":["Perspective Migration"],"month":"07","author.displayName":["Tobias Levkovich"],"siteId":"citigpa","category":"PERSPECTIVES"},{"summary":"The Consumer Financial Protection Bureau (CFPB), which launched this week, has received a great deal of Congressional, consumer and media attention during the past several weeks and months. Its mission is \"to make markets for consumer financial products and services work for Americans--whether they are applying for a mortgage, choosing among credit cards, or using any number of other consumer financial products.\"","month":"07","author.displayName":["John P. Carey"],"year":"2011","publishDate":"July 22, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"The CFPB proposes simplified mortgage forms.","category":"PERSPECTIVES","author.jobTitle":["Chief Administrative Officer, North America Consumer Banking"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2011/the-cfpb-proposes-simplified-mortgage-forms","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"Kuala Lumpur – Citibank is leveraging the most popular social media in modern times with its newly launched Citibank Facebook Fan Page to increase brand awareness among specific customer segments and build stronger customer relationships via direct interaction and feedback.","month":"07","year":"2011","publishDate":"July 21, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citibank Malaysia's Facebook Page to Attract More Than 100,000 Fans in 12 Months","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/citibank-malaysia-s-facebook-page-to-attract-more-than-100000-fans-in-12-months","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"New York, N.Y. – Citi will hold its fourth Citi Field Kids program for the 2011 season when the New York Mets host the St. Louis Cardinals today at 12:10 p.m. at Citi Field.","month":"07","year":"2011","publishDate":"July 21, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Handlowy Listed on the Elite Respect Index for the Third Time","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/citi-handlowy-listed-on-the-elite-respect-index-for-the-third-time","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"Warsaw – Citi Handlowy, for the third consecutive year, has been listed on the RESPECT Index that recognizes socially responsible investing in the Polish capital market.","month":"07","year":"2011","publishDate":"July 21, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Field Kids Program Provides Children in New York City Communities with Motivational and Education Experience","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/citi-field-kids-program-provides-children-in-new-york-city-communities-with-motivational-and-education-experience","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"Shanghai – MetLife and Citibank China jointly launched a Daily Step-up Variable Annuity product in Shanghai today. The new offering has been designed specifically by MetLife to meet customers' needs on long-term savings and retirement with stable investment returns. It is the first time that the Variable Annuity offering has been made available for sale through a bank in mainland China.","month":"07","year":"2011","publishDate":"July 21, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citibank China Launches Daily Step-up Variable Annuity Product","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/citibank-china-launches-daily-step-up-variable-annuity-product","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"month":"07","author.displayName":["Citi"],"year":"2011","publishDate":"July 21, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"In the FT: Citi's view on the market for water.","category":"PERSPECTIVES","author.jobTitle":["Citi"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2011/in-the-ft-citis-view-on-the-market-for-water","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"At NextBillion, we are focused broadly on development through enterprise, and specifically on ways to help the \"next billion\" people rise into the middle class from the base of the economic pyramid. <a href=\"https://www.nextbillion.net/\">NextBillion.net</a> launched in 2005 as an initiative of the <a href=\"https://www.wri.org/\">World Resources Institute</a> (WRI) and it has evolved into a blog, newsroom, research tool and career center for business leaders, social entrepreneurs, NGOs, policy makers and academics working to open opportunities for the world's approximately 4 billion low-income producers and consumers.","month":"07","author.displayName":["Scott Anderson"],"year":"2011","publishDate":"July 21, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"How Citi helps leverage expertise to benefit the \"next billion.\"","category":"PERSPECTIVES","author.jobTitle":["Managing editor, NextBillion.net"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2011/how-citi-helps-leverage-expertise-to-benefit-the-next-billion","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"The financial services industry has entered an era of significant change, driven in part by the Dodd-Frank Wall Street Reform and Consumer Protection Act. While many of these changes are intended to provide greater clarity, choice, and control for clients over their financial lives, we also realize that the pace and complexity of change may seem difficult to navigate. That's why we're using this and future blog posts on new.citi.com to create a conversation--to help you learn more about some of the basics of the Dodd-Frank Act, to better understand the changes it will bring, and to hear your questions and concerns.","month":"07","author.displayName":["John P. Carey"],"year":"2011","publishDate":"July 21, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"The Dodd-Frank Act and you: What you need to know to navigate the world of financial reform.","category":"PERSPECTIVES","author.jobTitle":["Chief Administrative Officer, North America Consumer Banking"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2011/the-dodd-frank-act-and-you-what-you-need-to-know-to-navigate-the-world-of-financial-reform","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"Santiago, Dominican Republic – On July 18, Citi Dominican Republic hosted a breakfast, led by Country Treasurer Javier Guerrero, for its clients in the northern region.","month":"07","year":"2011","publishDate":"July 20, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Dominican Republic Introduces Risk Management Products","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/citi-dominican-republic-introduces-risk-management-products","tags":["Press Release Migration","Institutional Clients Group"]},{"summary":"Chicago – Citi will conclude its 2011 Citi Cubs Kids season when the Cubs host the Houston Astros on Friday, July 22. The program will be held at The Inter-American Magnet School (851 W. Waveland Ave, Chicago) and will feature former Cubs legend and National Baseball Hall of Famer Ernie Banks as well as Chicago native Rick Santelli of CNBC.","month":"07","year":"2011","publishDate":"July 20, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Cubs Kids Program to Conclude Second Season of Providing Chicago Children with Motivational and Educational Experience","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/citi-cubs-kids-program-to-conclude-second-season-of-providing-chicago-children-with-motivational-and-educational-experience","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"New York – John Gerspach, Chief Financial Officer, and Eric Aboaf, Treasurer, will conduct the second quarter 2011 Fixed Income Investor Review at 11:00 a.m. (EDT) on Thursday, July 21, 2011. The review was originally scheduled for 10 a.m. The review will be available live via webcast and teleconference.","month":"07","year":"2011","publishDate":"July 19, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Second Quarter 2011 Fixed Income Investor Review Scheduled for 11 a.m. on Thursday, July 21","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/citi-second-quarter-2011-fixed-income-investor-review-scheduled-for-11-am-on-thursday-july-21","tags":["Press Release Migration","Citi-Wide"]},{"summary":"New York and London – CitiFX Pro has been named \"Best Retail Platform\" by <i>FX Week</i> at its 2011 e-FX awards. The award recognizes industry excellence in a bank or vendor platform designed for electronic foreign exchange trading by individuals and small institutions.","month":"07","year":"2011","publishDate":"July 19, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"CitiFX Pro Named Best Retail Platform by FX Week","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/citifx-pro-named-best-retail-platform-by-fx-week","tags":["Press Release Migration","Citi-Wide","Institutional Clients Group"]},{"summary":"Kuala Lumpur – Citigroup First Investment Management Ltd. (\"CFIM\") in cooperation with HwangDBS Investment Management Bhd. (\"HwangDBS IM\") today launched the HwangDBS China Select Fund (\"the Fund\") the first-of-its-kind feeder fund that allows Malaysian investors to benefit from the expertise of China's leading asset management company and the growth opportunities of China companies listed locally and globally.","month":"07","year":"2011","publishDate":"July 19, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citibank Malaysia Launches HwangDBS China Select Fund","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/citibank-malaysia-launches-hwangdbs-china-select-fund","tags":["Press Release Migration","Citi-Wide"]},{"summary":"One background concern of emerging market (EM) investors in the first half of 2011 has been that the combination of sluggish economic growth in the developed world and higher inflation in EM countries would lead to significant earnings downgrades and so invalidate the \"attractive valuation\" story for EM equities. While earnings momentum in EMs is indeed slowing, we continue to see few signs of broad earnings downgrades that would put longer-term earnings projections under pressure. Indeed, the story remains one of strong earnings recovery from the recent trough associated with the recession of 2008-9.","month":"07","author.displayName":["Geoffrey Dennis"],"year":"2011","publishDate":"July 19, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Emerging market earnings: Holding up well.","category":"PERSPECTIVES","author.jobTitle":["Global Emerging Markets Strategist"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2011/emerging-market-earnings-holding-up-well","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"Now halfway through its third season, Citi Field Kids is an educational and motivational community-based initiative for New York City middle- and high- school students developed by Citi in collaboration with the Jackie Robinson Foundation, United Neighborhood Houses of New York and the Mets. Launched in 2009 in conjunction with Major League Baseball's annual Jackie Robinson Day, Citi Field Kids has hosted more than 2,500 students.","image":"638e3013a3c47c530c0a5aee","year":"2011","publishDate":"July 19, 2011","type":"insights","title":"Season three for Citi Field Kids.","author.jobTitle":["Citi"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2011/season-three-for-citi-field-kids","tags":["Perspective Migration"],"