ation with the Pakistan Microfinance Network (PMN), launched a three-day seminar and workshop on Risk Management (RM) as part of Citi Foundation's support to disaster relief in the aftermath of Pakistan's floods. This series, led by Christian Ruehmer, a leading expert for Risk Management for the International Financial Corporation (IFC) in the area of Risk Management, will conclude with a joint research publication in collaboration with IFC and Consultative Group to Assist the Poor (CGAP) to be disseminated as a best practice for lessons learned by the microfinance sector during disasters.","month":"07","year":"2011","publishDate":"July 18, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Collaborates with PMN and IFC to Launch a Disaster and Risk Management Series for the Microfinance Sector","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/foundation/news/press-release/2011/citi-collaborates-with-pmn-and-ifc-to-launch-a-disaster-and-risk-management-series-for-the-microfinance-sector","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"New York – Just in time for the busy air travel season, Citi Cards and American Airlines announce today a new addition to the 24-year Citi® / AAdvantage® credit card portfolio that has served millions of cardmembers with its products and service. The Citi Executive<sup>SM</sup> / AAdvantage® World Elite MasterCard® will deliver exclusive elite-level travel services and experiences to American's flyers.","month":"07","year":"2011","publishDate":"July 18, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Cards and American Airlines Introduce New Elite Traveler Credit Card with Expanded Suite of Co-Branded Product Offerings","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/citi-cards-and-american-airlines-introduce-new-elite-traveler-credit-card-with-expanded-suite-of-co-branded-product-offerings","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"Bogota – On July 5, Citibank Colombia and Cititrust, the management company, in association with BlackRock, began operations of the first exchange traded fund in the Colombian public exchange market. BlackRock, considered the world's largest exchange traded funds manager, will act as the professional manager for the ETF. iShares COLCAP began trading today in the Colombian Stock Exchange (BVC).","month":"07","year":"2011","publishDate":"July 18, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"The Major Leagues Arrive in Colombia","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/the-major-leagues-arrive-in-colombia","tags":["Press Release Migration","Institutional Clients Group"]},{"summary":"If you own a small business, you might have started it as a sole proprietorship. That certainly keeps things simple: You have less paperwork, it's easier to start and stop the business without legal expenses, and you don't have to pay taxes as a corporation. You just fill out Schedule C with your federal tax return and you're done.","month":"07","author.displayName":["Jonathan Clements"],"year":"2011","publishDate":"July 18, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Small businesses, big choices.","category":"PERSPECTIVES","author.jobTitle":["Director of Financial Education, Citi Personal Wealth Management"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2011/small-businesses-big-choices","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"New York - Citigroup Inc. today reported second quarter 2011 net income of $3.3 billion, or $1.09 per diluted share, on revenues of $20.6 billion. Second quarter net income grew 24% from the prior year period and 11% from the first quarter 2011, while net revenues were 7% lower versus the prior year period and 5% higher than the first quarter 2011.","month":"07","year":"2011","publishDate":"July 15, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citigroup Reports Second Quarter 2011 Net Income of $3.3 Billion, Compared to $2.7 Billion in Second Quarter 2010","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/citigroup-reports-second-quarter-2011-net-income-of-33-billion-compared-to-27-billion-in-second-quarter-2010","tags":["Press Release Migration","Citi-Wide"]},{"summary":"We began measuring the environmental impact of Citi facilities and publicly released our first carbon footprint reduction goal in 2006. In 2010, after meeting important milestones, the Citi Realty Services team expanded on the company's existing goals by creating additional targets for 2015 which include: reducing greenhouse gas (GHG) emissions from buildings by 25%, reducing waste to landfill by 40%, reducing water use by 20% and having 15% of the real estate portfolio LEED-certified by the US Green Building Council. (These reduction metrics are based on a 2005 baseline).","month":"07","author.displayName":["John Killey"],"year":"2011","publishDate":"July 15, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Driving sustainability gains.","category":"PERSPECTIVES","author.jobTitle":["Global Head of Building Operations, Citi"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2011/driving-sustainability-gains","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"Earlier this morning, Citi released its earnings report for the second quarter of 2011. Chief Financial Officer John Gerspach discusses the report in this <a href=\"https://citi.us/op1YUy\">video</a>. For more information and the full earnings report, visit the <a href=\"https://www.citigroup.com/citi/fin/\">Investor Relations</a> section of Citigroup's website.","image":"638e3017a3c47c530c0a5b03","year":"2011","publishDate":"July 15, 2011","type":"insights","title":"Citi releases second quarter 2011 earnings.","author.jobTitle":["Citi"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2011/citi-releases-second-quarter-2011-earnings","tags":["Perspective Migration"],"month":"07","author.displayName":["Citi"],"siteId":"citigpa","category":"PERSPECTIVES"},{"summary":"New York, N.Y. – Citi and the New York Mets Alumni Association Presented by Citi announced that they will team up once again with Habitat for Humanity - New York City (Habitat-NYC) tomorrow to build affordable housing for New York City families. The project is part of the Mets and Citi's \"Teammates in the Community\" initiative, reflecting their ongoing commitment to be active participants in the community.","month":"07","year":"2011","publishDate":"July 14, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Mets Alumni Association Presented by Citi to Team Up with Habitat-NYC to Build Affordable Homes in Brooklyn","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/mets-alumni-association-presented-by-citi-to-team-up-with-habitat-nyc-to-build-affordable-homes-in-brooklyn","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"Savings has a significantly positive effect on children and families -- research has shown that a child with a college savings account held in his or her name is seven times more likely to attend college than one without, regardless of income, race or academic achievement.","month":"07","author.displayName":["Leigh Phillips"],"year":"2011","publishDate":"July 14, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Kindergarten to College: Save steady, dream huge.","category":"PERSPECTIVES","author.jobTitle":["Chief Executive, EARN"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2011/kindergarten-to-college-save-steady-dream-huge","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"Chengdu – Citibank (China) Co., Ltd. (\"Citibank\") today opened its first sub-branch in Chengdu. The new location is a smart-banking branch, designed to provide a unique and superior banking experience to Citibank customers. Andrew Au, Chief Executive Officer, Citi China, and Simon Chow, Country Business Manager, Citibank China, attended the opening ceremony.","month":"07","year":"2011","publishDate":"July 13, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"China: Citibank Deepens Presence in Chengdu","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/china-citibank-deepens-presence-in-chengdu","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"Moscow – The aggregate spend made by Russians abroad in 2011 has reached pre-crisis 2007 levels, according to Citibank's annual research published today. Share of international payments has grown to 28 percent in 2011 as compared to 20.1 percent in 2010. Citibank's experts estimate that the total amount of purchases made abroad through the end of 2011, including credit card spending, will amount to 3 percent of the GDP, or US$40 billion.","month":"07","year":"2011","publishDate":"July 13, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Russian Spend Abroad Beats Pre-Crisis Records","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/russian-spend-abroad-beats-pre-crisis-records","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"New York – Citi today announced the launch of Citi Issuer Access, an innovative tablet-based suite of capital-markets content designed specifically for issuers involved in the capital formation process. As part of this initiative, issuers will receive dedicated tablet computers pre-loaded with a comprehensive suite of applications, including a real-time issuer view into the order book, access to investor profiles, dynamic roadshow travel and meeting schedule, post-pricing investor relations services and support. Citi Issuer Access will provide a transparent medium for both Citi and the issuer to remain connected on all offering-related matters, foster a closer working relationship and ensure greater transparency to corporate executives throughout the offering process.","month":"07","year":"2011","publishDate":"July 13, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Launches Tablet-Based IPO Solution for Issuers","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/citi-launches-tablet-based-ipo-solution-for-issuers","tags":["Press Release Migration","Institutional Clients Group"]},{"summary":"Steven Wieting, Citi's managing director of economic and market analysis, <a href=\"https://www.dailymotion.com/video/xjv6ts_wieting-sees-largest-earnings-gains-in-energy-materials_news\">spoke</a> to Bloomberg TV about the outlook for second quarter corporate earnings and expectations for longer-term growth.","image":"638e301aa3c47c530c0a5b10","year":"2011","publishDate":"July 13, 2011","type":"insights","title":"Wieting previews second-quarter earnings season.","author.jobTitle":["Citi"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2011/wieting-previews-second-quarter-earnings-season","tags":["Perspective Migration"],"month":"07","author.displayName":["Citi"],"siteId":"citigpa","category":"PERSPECTIVES"},{"summary":"Lima, Peru – Citibank, committed to continuously contributing to Peru's growth through innovation, has 91 years of uninterrupted presence in the country. Aiming to consolidate its position within the premium-market segment, Citibank introduces its new Citibank/AAdvantage® MasterCard Black, a product with exclusive features targeted to fulfilling the most-demanding needs of the affluent segment.","month":"07","year":"2011","publishDate":"July 12, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citibank Introduces New Citibank/AADVANTAGE® MasterCard Black to the Peruvian Market","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/citibank-introduces-new-citibankaadvantage-mastercard-black-to-the-peruvian-market","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"Warsaw – In June, Citi Handlowy began to issue Citibank Credit Cards that use special MasterCard® PayPass™ and Visa payWave technology. PayPass payments, an embedded chip, Poland's largest payment-card discount program and the opportunity to obtain the card \"on the spot\" at a branch make the Citibank Credit Card one of the most interesting market offers.","month":"07","year":"2011","publishDate":"July 12, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Handlowy Launches PayPass Credit Cards","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/citi-handlowy-launches-paypass-credit-cards","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"Athens – According to official data of Hellenic Exchanges SA, Citibank Greece's Securities &amp; Fund Services (SFS) Global Transaction Services ranked first in clearing and settlement of transactions in the Athens Stock Exchange during the first half of 2011.","month":"07","year":"2011","publishDate":"July 11, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citibank Greece's Securities & Fund Services, Global Transaction Services Ranked First in Clearing and Settlement of Transactions for the Athens Stock Exchange in the First Half of 2011","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/citibank-greece-s-securities-fund-services-global-transaction-services-ranked-first-in-clearing-and-settlement-of-transactions-for-the-athens-stock-exchange-in-the-first-half-of-2011","tags":["Press Release Migration","Institutional Clients Group"]},{"summary":"Citi Pakistan and Hong Kong successfully executed the first-ever Sinosure (Chinese ECA) backed term trade financing transaction for Citi in the Middle East and Pakistan region. The transaction covers the supply of telecommunication equipment from Huawei Hong Kong to Pakistan Mobile Communications Limited (Vimpelcom subsidiary), the largest cellular operating company in Pakistan. The deal size for the transaction is $25 million.","month":"07","year":"2011","publishDate":"July 11, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Introduces Sinosure Debut Transaction in Middle East North Africa Region","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/citi-introduces-sinosure-debut-transaction-in-middle-east-north-africa-region","tags":["Press Release Migration","Institutional Clients Group"]},{"summary":"Perhaps the most important part of an auto or homeowner's insurance policy is the liability coverage, which protects you against legal claims triggered by damage to people and property.","month":"07","author.displayName":["Jonathan Clements"],"year":"2011","publishDate":"July 11, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Grabbing an umbrella.","category":"PERSPECTIVES","author.jobTitle":["Director of Financial Education, Citi Personal Wealth Management"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2011/grabbing-an-umbrella","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"New Delhi – Citi Wealth Advisors (CWA), a retail business unit of Citigroup Global Markets India Private Limited, today announced the launch of its first smart broking branch in New Delhi. Located in South Delhi's New Friends Colony, the smart broking branch was inaugurated by Pramit Jhaveri, CEO, Citi India.","month":"07","year":"2011","publishDate":"July 08, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Wealth Advisors Opens Smart Broking Branch in New Delhi","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/citi-wealth-advisors-opens-smart-broking-branch-in-new-delhi","tags":["Press Release Migration","Institutional Clients Group"]},{"summary":"London – Citigroup is a founding corporate partner in Team London, the new volunteering campaign launched by Mayor Boris Johnson to mobilize 10,000 Londoners.","month":"07","year":"2011","publishDate":"July 08, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Joins Mayor of London's Team","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/citi-joins-mayor-of-london-s-team","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance","Institutional Clients Group","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"The lesbian, gay, bisexual, and transgender (LGBT)-owned small business community--comprising an estimated 1.4 million enterprises in the United States--has an enormous depth and promise. My job, as president of the 29,000-member <a href=\"https://www.nglcc.org/\">National Gay & Lesbian Chamber of Commerce</a> (NGLCC), is to help them reach their full potential.","month":"07","author.displayName":["Justin Nelson"],"year":"2011","publishDate":"July 08, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"\"Out\" for business.","category":"PERSPECTIVES","author.jobTitle":["President and Co-founder, National Gay & Lesbian Chamber of Commerce"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2011/out-for-business-1","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"Atlanta, Ga. – Today, Citi announced a multi-year renewal of its long-standing U.S. private-label credit card partnership with Office Depot, celebrating 25 years as a leading global provider of office supplies and services.","month":"07","year":"2011","publishDate":"July 07, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Renews Private-Label Card Partnership with Office Depot","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/citi-renews-private-label-card-partnership-with-office-depot","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"I'm extremely proud of Citi's performance in the latest round of <a href=\"https://www.euromoney.com/Article/2860648/Euromoney-Awards-for-Excellence-2011.html\">Awards for Excellence</a> bestowed by <em>Euromoney</em> magazine. All told, we won fifteen awards, including awards for our businesses in every single region where we operate and in six individual countries.","month":"07","author.displayName":["Vikram Pandit"],"year":"2011","publishDate":"July 07, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Our Euromoney Awards.","category":"PERSPECTIVES","author.jobTitle":["CEO"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2011/our-euromoney-awards","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"In an <a href=\"https://www.bloomberg.com/video/71922416/\">appearance</a> on Bloomberg TV, Ed Morse, Citi's Global Head of Commodities Research, discussed a range of issues affecting energy, metals and agricultural markets, including the possibility of the International Energy Agency making another release of oil from emergency stockpiles, the impact of ongoing disruption of Libya's oil supply, fixed-asset investment in emerging markets and weather events.","image":"638e301ea3c47c530c0a5b25","month":"07","year":"2011","publishDate":"July 07, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Morse interview covers commodities landscape.","category":"PERSPECTIVES","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2011/morse-interview-covers-commodities-landscape","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"In an opinion essay for Bloomberg View, Citi Vice Chairman Peter Orszag looks at the global consequences of mispriced water in China. He argues that higher prices would help reduce waste, improve the allocation of water \"across all its possible uses (including the energy sector)\" and \"teach...a lesson\" in using market economics to address environmental issues.","month":"07","author.displayName":["Citi"],"year":"2011","publishDate":"July 07, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Orszag: \"Why we care about price of water in China.\"","category":"PERSPECTIVES","author.jobTitle":["Citi"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2011/orszag-why-we-care-about-price-of-water-in-china","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"Citi has again joined forces with mobile app developer <a href=\"https://www.shopkick.com/\">shopkick</a>, this time to sponsor the wider rollout of the shopkick app and additional location-based technology to help deliver foot traffic to small and medium businesses and rewards to their shoppers. The same shopkick technology is already being used by major national retailers to reward customers who visit their stores.","month":"07","author.displayName":["Citi"],"year":"2011","publishDate":"July 06, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi sponsors shopkick mobile technology to drive foot traffic to local stores.","category":"PERSPECTIVES","author.jobTitle":["Citi"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2011/citi-sponsors-shopkick-mobile-technology-to-drive-foot-traffic-to-local-stores","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"Warsaw – The prestigious Citibank MasterCard® World Signia Ultime Credit Card already has many cardholders in Poland. Now, in addition to the exclusive plastic card, some lucky cardholders will also receive diamonds from the bank. This jewelry award is to be given to the first 10 holders of the Ultime card. In this way the bank emphasizes the uniqueness of both its customers and the product offered to them.","month":"07","year":"2011","publishDate":"July 05, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Diamonds for the First Holders of the Citibank MasterCard® World Signia Ultime Credit Card","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/diamonds-for-the-first-holders-of-the-citibank-mastercard-world-signia-ultime-credit-card","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"Citi Pakistan has joined hands with the Akhuwat Foundation (an interest-free microfinance institution in Pakistan), for an initiative specifically aimed at impacting female entrepreneurs in Pakistan, to provide them with a source of livelihood by enabling them to set up their own small-scale businesses. The program features a two-pronged approach of providing assets and grants for these women to set up their own businesses, coupled with structured microfinance training programs, to provide them with the required microentrepreneurship skill set to sustain their enterprises. The program is intended to help alleviate gender discrimination and provide a model for other women in the community to follow.","month":"07","year":"2011","publishDate":"July 05, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Pakistan: Promoting Pakistani Women through a First-of-Its-Kind Female Microentrepreneurship Program with Akhuwat","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/foundation/news/press-release/2011/citi-pakistan-promoting-pakistani-women-through-a-first-of-its-kind-female-microentrepreneurship-program-with-akhuwat","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"If you're age 70½ or older, you are expected to take a required minimum distribution, or RMD, from your traditional Individual Retirement Account each year. (No distributions are required from Roth IRAs.) The taxable sum involved is included on your tax return.","month":"07","author.displayName":["Jonathan Clements"],"year":"2011","publishDate":"July 05, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Donating IRA distributions.","category":"PERSPECTIVES","author.jobTitle":["Director of Financial Education, Citi Personal Wealth Management"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2011/donating-ira-distributions","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"Baltimore, Md. – OneMain Financial, the consumer finance lending arm of Citigroup, today completed the re-branding of its U.S. full-service network from CitiFinancial. Last December, the company announced the new name as part of a plan to distinguish its business with an identity that better represents who it is and what it does.","month":"07","year":"2011","publishDate":"July 01, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi's U.S. Consumer Finance Unit Completes Rebranding to OneMain Financial","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/citi-s-us-consumer-finance-unit-completes-rebranding-to-onemain-financial","tags":["Press Release Migration","Citi-Wide"]},{"summary":"For the 13th consecutive year, Citi Philippines is <i>FinanceAsia</i> magazine's top pick for Best Foreign Commercial Bank in the country. Citi has been winning this award from <i>FinanceAsia</i> since it was introduced in 1998, and this year, it also won in the Best Foreign Investment Bank category.","month":"07","year":"2011","publishDate":"July 01, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Philippines Named Best Foreign Bank for 13th Straight Year","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/citi-philippines-named-best-foreign-bank-for-13th-straight-year","tags":["Press Release Migration","Institutional Clients Group","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"Hong Kong/Vietnam – Citigroup today announced that it had acquired a 9.9 percent stake in Vietnam's Horizon Securities Corporation, subject to regulatory approval. With this investment, Citi will be among the first foreign financial institutions to partner with a local Vietnamese securities firm, allowing it to reinforce its leadership position in one of the fastest-growing markets in Asia Pacific.","month":"07","year":"2011","publishDate":"July 01, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Partners with Local Vietnamese Securities Firm","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/citi-partners-with-local-vietnamese-securities-firm","tags":["Press Release Migration","Institutional Clients Group"]},{"summary":"Citi in Japan, in cooperation with the National Institute on Consumer Education (\"NICE,\" President: Kazuko Takabu), will launch a new financial education program, \"Financial Life Skills and Money Management for Women,\" beginning October 2011.","month":"07","year":"2011","publishDate":"July 01, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi in Japan Launches Financial Life Skills and Money Management for Women","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/foundation/news/press-release/2011/citi-in-japan-launches-financial-life-skills-and-money-management-for-women","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"The investment community always seems to struggle with understanding the American consumer and often appears deeply influenced by a misperception that US household spending is driven by real estate values. Yet over the past two decades, stock market wealth has been far more instrumental than home prices in determining the direction of US core retail sales activity. This relationship reflects the reality that roughly 20% of American income earners on the higher end account for nearly 50% of discretionary spending and own 90% of the stock market.","month":"07","author.displayName":["Tobias Levkovich"],"year":"2011","publishDate":"July 01, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Soft patch solace.","category":"PERSPECTIVES","author.jobTitle":["Chief US Equity Strategist, Citi"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2011/soft-patch-solace","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"Launched in the Pakistani market for the first time by Citi, Citi at Work (CAW) has become a hallmark of Citi's pioneering contributions to the retail-banking space in the country. Serving more than 23,000 customers and over 200 CAW companies for its payroll product launched not long ago, the program is a unique synergy of relationship management, client engagement, targeted marketing and an unparalleled client excellence experienc