i"],"year":"2011","publishDate":"June 09, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"CitiMortgage Road to Recovery Tour.","category":"PERSPECTIVES","author.jobTitle":["Citi"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2011/citimortgage-road-to-recovery-tour","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"New York – Citi announced today the successful remarketing of $1.875 billion aggregate principal amount of debt securities, representing the last of four series of debt securities required to be remarketed under the terms of Citi's Upper DECS Equity Units issued to the Abu Dhabi Investment Authority in December 2007. Pursuant to the agreements governing the Upper DECS Equity Units, the interest rate on this fourth series of remarketed debt was reset to 3.953 percent. The remarketing will settle on June 15, 2011.","month":"06","year":"2011","publishDate":"June 08, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Prices Remarketing of 3.953% Senior Notes Due June 15, 2016","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/citi-prices-remarketing-of-3953-senior-notes-due-june-15-2016","tags":["Press Release Migration","Citi-Wide"]},{"summary":"Budapest, Hungary – NESsT and Citi awarded the winners of the 2010 NESsT-Citi Social Enterprise Competition on June 2. The goal of this competition is to promote excellence in social-enterprise development among local nonprofits belonging to the NESsT portfolio in Central Europe. Based in Budapest, NESsT provides capital and business development support to enable nonprofit organizations to plan for and better manage social enterprises. The awards recognize excellence in social enterprise performance, particularly among social enterprises that create employment opportunities for marginalized communities across Hungary, the Czech Republic and Slovakia. The Citi Foundation funds the program.","month":"06","year":"2011","publishDate":"June 08, 2011","siteId":"citi