, including hostile takeovers and cross-border deals focused on emerging markets.","image":"638e3048a3c47c530c0a5be9","year":"2011","publishDate":"June 08, 2011","type":"insights","title":" Kalvaria on deal climate.","author.jobTitle":["Citi"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2011/kalvaria-on-deal-climate","tags":["Perspective Migration"],"month":"06","author.displayName":["Citi"],"siteId":"citigpa","category":"PERSPECTIVES"},{"month":"06","author.displayName":["Citi"],"year":"2011","publishDate":"June 08, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"\"Confessions of a Wannabe Entrepreneur.\"","category":"PERSPECTIVES","author.jobTitle":["Citi"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2011/confessions-of-a-wannabe-entrepreneur","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"Hong Kong – Citi's Global Transaction Services (GTS) has launched its first career development program designed for women in Asia: the Aspirations program. Part of a career and talent development program called \"Power of 3: Empower,\" Citi continues to strive to help female employees meet their career goals.","month":"06","year":"2011","publishDate":"June 07, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi's Global Transaction Services Launches Aspirations Program for Women in Asia","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/citi-s-global-transaction-services-launches-aspirations-program-for-women-in-asia","tags":["Press Release Migration","Institutional Clients Group"]},{"summary":"Luxembourg – Citigroup today announced the opening of a new Global Markets legal entity, Citigroup Global Markets Luxembourg S.à.r.l. Citigroup Global Markets provides world-class products and financing solutions for corporations, governments and institutional investors through its sales and trading, and distribution capabilities. It will now have a physical presence in Luxembourg through the permanent establishment of a locally incorporated entity, allowing Citi to provide a more complete range of services to clients within Luxembourg and Europe.","month":"06","year":"2011","publishDate":"June 07, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi to Open Securities Lending Desk in Luxembourg","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/citi-to-open-securities-lending-desk-in-luxembourg","tags":["Press Release Migration","Institutional Clients Group"]},{"summary":"New York and San Francisco – Manilla today announced that its free personal account management service is now available for anyone who wants to try the simple new way to organize his or her life. According to a recent survey of American consumers conducted by research firm Catalyst Group, the typical American head of household feels overwhelmed by the clutter, time and worry around account management. Forty-five percent of survey respondents wished there were a better way to manage their household accounts, and 48 percent revealed they had forgotten to pay a bill last year. At Manilla.com, consumers can sign up today to immediately start managing all of their household accounts including bills, finances, travel-rewards programs and subscriptions in one secure place online. Manilla offers lifetime storage of all documents and an organized overview of all accounts and approaching due dates. For consumers, it takes just minutes to add accounts and start relying on Manilla for organizing accounts, scheduling recurring bill reminders, storing documents, comparing frequent flier miles and much more.","month":"06","year":"2011","publishDate":"June 07, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Available Now: Manilla.com to Clean Up Household Filing Cabinets, Mailboxes and Paper Clutter","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/available-now-manillacom-to-clean-up-household-filing-cabinets-mailboxes-and-paper-clutter","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"Kuala Lumpur – Citibank today launched its first state-of-the-art smart banking branch, underlining its commitment to customers and its continued investments in Malaysia. The Citibank Smart Banking branch in Malaysia is also Citi's largest smart-banking branch in the region, covering a floor area of more than 27,000 sq ft, and is the first of its kind in Malaysia.","month":"06","year":"2011","publishDate":"June 06, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citibank Launches First Smart-Banking Branch in Malaysia","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/citibank-launches-first-smart-banking-branch-in-malaysia","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"Rostov-on-Don, Russia – On June 6, 2011, Citibank celebrates five-year anniversary of operations in Rostov-on-Don. During its five years, the Donskoy branch of Citibank has successfully met business targets and demonstrated dynamic growth of financial indicators across all business segments, becoming one of the key participants in the local financial services market. Today every 20th working citizen of the region is the Citibank's client. By year-end 2010, the loan portfolio of Donskoy branch reached 470 million rubles and the number of issued credit cards exceeded 12,000. The largest companies in the region selected Citibank for payroll services.","month":"06","year":"2011","publishDate":"June 06, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citibank Anniversary in South Federal District","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/citibank-anniversary-in-south-federal-district","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"The launch of the Canyon-Agassi Charter School Facilities Fund, an investment group designed to help charter schools find permanent school buildings, noted the role of 