eers from Citi's Green Team-NYC joined forces with Lower East Side Ecology Center to take part in Partnerships for Parks' <a href=\"https://www.itsmypark.org/get_involved/volunteer/its_my_park_day.html\">It's My Park Day</a>. The event consists of thousands of volunteers coming together to beautify over 150 parks around New York City. Citi's volunteers specifically worked on \"dethistling\" a large area of blue flowers and cleaning up the East River Park Amphitheater in preparation for Lower East Side Ecology Center's Eco-Feast celebration, a vital benefit for the non-profit organization.","month":"05","author.displayName":["Greg Carbonella"],"year":"2011","publishDate":"May 25, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"\"It's My Park Day.\"","category":"PERSPECTIVES","author.jobTitle":["Analyst, Citi"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2011/its-my-park-day","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"New York – Citi today announced that its Global Transaction Services business has joined the United Nations World Food Program (WFP), the world's largest humanitarian organization, to support WFP's \"Fill the Cup\" campaign to fight child hunger. The business has marked its commitment with a donation of US$50,000 to the campaign, and is inviting its clients to support the campaign as well.","month":"05","year":"2011","publishDate":"May 24, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi® Commercial Cards Joins World Food Program to \"Fill the Cup\" for Hungry Children","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/citi-commercial-cards-joins-world-food-program-to-fill-the-cup-for-hungry-children","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"New York – CitiMortgage's Road to Recovery 10-city tour has completed events in its first four cities and is proceeding to the next six cities to help distressed homeowners. Preliminary events in Baltimore, Orlando, Cleveland and Atlanta showed nearly 65 percent of attendees qualified for loan modification programs. All homeowners who are having difficulty making their mortgage payments, including non-CitiMortgage customers, are strongly encouraged to attend the free, open-to-the-public functions.","month":"05","year":"2011","publishDate":"May 24, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"CitiMortgage Road to Recovery Tour - Helping Distressed Homeowners in Their Markets","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/citimortgage-road-to-recovery-tour--helping-distressed-homeowners-in-their-markets","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"Miami, Fla. – As part of its partnership with Women's Professional Soccer (WPS), Citi today announced that its Get Active with Citi Soccer Kids, a program that connects current stars from the league with future stars from its communities and promotes a healthy lifestyle for kids, will be coming to Miami tomorrow. This initiative is taking place in league markets and includes access to WPS players and coaches, tickets to games, gift bags and memorable in-game experiences.","month":"05","year":"2011","publishDate":"May 24, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi and Women's Professional Soccer to Bring New Season of \"Get Active with Citi Soccer Kids\" Community Program to Miami to Benefit Area Youth","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/citi-and-women-s-professional-soccer-to-bring-new-season-of-get-active-with-citi-soccer-kids-community-program-to-miami-to-benefit-area-youth","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"Mojave, Calif. - Advancing the development of a major wind energy resource, Google and Citi will finance part of the Alta Wind Energy Center (AWEC) being developed by Terra-Gen Power, an affiliate of ArcLight 