 averaging around 5%, while one-year adjustable-rate loans are nearer to 3½%, according to HSH.com. That 1½ percentage-points difference prompts the question: Should you go for an adjustable-rate loan instead? Like many things in life, it depends.","month":"05","author.displayName":["Jonathan Clements"],"year":"2011","publishDate":"May 09, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Fixed rate vs. adjustable mortgages.","category":"PERSPECTIVES","author.jobTitle":["Director of Financial Education, Citi Personal Wealth Management"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2011/fixed-rate-vs-adjustable-mortgages","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"New York – Citi, the New York Mets and the Mets Alumni Association Presented by Citi today announced that they will partner with Dress for Success (DFS), an organization that promotes the economic independence of disadvantaged women. They will support DFS's objectives during Mothers' Day weekend, along with Mets legends John Franco, George Foster, Edgardo Alfonzo, Kevin Elster, Ed Hearn and George Theodore, who will participate in special events throughout the weekend, including appearances at local Citi branches and other activities.","month":"05","year":"2011","publishDate":"May 06, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi, the New York Mets and the Mets Alumni Association Presented by Citi to Partner with Dress for Success to Celebrate Mothers' Day Weekend","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/citi-the-new-york-mets-and-the-mets-alumni-association-presented-by-citi-to-partner-with-dress-for-success-to-celebrate-mothers-day-weekend","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"Raj Seshadri, Head of Small Business Banking at Citibank, <a href=\"https://classic.cnbc.com/id/15840232?video=3000019470&amp;play=1\">spoke</a> with CNBC about the results of a new Citibank <a href=\"https://www.citigroup.com/citi/press/2011/110504a.htm\">survey</a> showing clear signs of an improving outlook among U.S. small businesses. \"What we see in the survey is there's a pivotal point where they're moving from survival mode into growth mode,\" she said.","image":"638e3075a3c47c530c0a5cbb","year":"2011","publishDate":"May 06, 2011","type":"insights","title":"New Citibank survey points to small business optimism.","author.jobTitle":["Citi"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2011/new-citibank-survey-points-to-small-business-optimism","tags":["Perspective Migration"],"month":"05","author.displayName":["Citi"],"siteId":"citigpa","category":"PERSPECTIVES"},{"summary":"New York – Citi will hold its first <em>Citi Field Kids</em> program for the 2011 season when the Mets host the defending World-Champion San Francisco Giants on Thursday, May 5, at 1:10 p.m. at Citi Field.","month":"05","year":"2011","publishDate":"May 05, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Field Kids Program Returns for Third Season to Provide Children in New York City Communities with Motivational and Educational Experience","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/citi-field-kids-program-returns-for-third-season-to-provide-children-in-new-york-city-communities-with-motivational-and-educational-experience","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance"]},{"summary":"New York – Citi today announced that it has added socially responsible investment solutions to its securities lending cash collateral investment program. Securities lending clients will now be able to elect to invest cash collateral under socially responsible investment (SRI) principles that consider environment, social and governance (ESG) factors. According to Eurosif, as of December 31, 2010, more than $11 trillion of assets are managed globally in a strategy of socially responsible investing. Without an SRI capability for the investment of cash collateral, firms that manage SRI strategies have found it difficult to participate in securities lending programs.","month":"05","year":"2011","publishDate":"May 05, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Enhances Securities Lending Cash Collateral Investment Program to Include Solutions for Socially Responsible Investors","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/citi-enhances-securities-lending-cash-collateral-investment-program-to-include-solutions-for-socially-responsible-investors","tags":["Press Release Migration","Environmental, Social & Governance","Institutional Clients Group"]},{"summary":"New York – More than 300 leaders from the financial services and business community gathered to honor Vikram Pandit, CEO of Citigroup, at UJA-Federation of New York's Wall Street and Financial Services Division's Banking and Finance Reception on May 4, 2011, at Gotham Hall in New York City. The event, honoring Pandit for his professional and philanthropic leadership, raised $900,000.","month":"05","year":"2011","publishDate":"May 05, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Vikram Pandit, CEO of Citigroup, Honored with UJA-Federation of New York's Banking and Finance Award","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/vikram-pandit-ceo-of-citigroup-honored-with-uja-federation-of-new-york-s-banking-and-finance-award","tags":["Press Release Migration","Citi-Wide"]},{"month":"05","author.displayName":["Citi"],"year":"2011","publishDate":"May 05, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"\"What are you doing this Mother's Day?\"","category":"PERSPECTIVES","author.jobTitle":["Citi"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2011/what-are-you-doing-this-mothers-day","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"The UJA-Federation of New York <a href=\"https://www.ujafedny.org/press-releases-2/view/vikram-pandit-ceo-of-citigroup-honored-with-uja-federation-of-new-yorks-banking-and-finance-award/\">honored</a> Citi CEO Vikram Pandit with its Banking and Finance Award yesterday for his professional and philanthropic leadership. In accepting the award, Pandit commended UJA and its partner agencies for their efforts to help individuals and families through financial difficulties even as non-profits faced their own challenges.","month":"05","author.displayName":["Citi"],"year":"2011","publishDate":"May 05, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Pandit receives UJA Banking and Finance honor.","category":"PERSPECTIVES","author.jobTitle":["Citi"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2011/pandit-receives-uja-banking-and-finance-honor","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"Credit conditions, which are critical for business investment and economic activity, continue to move in a positive direction. The latest senior loan officers survey released by the Federal Reserve Board shows further easing in loan standards, including those for small business and consumers, during 2Q11. <em>(See figure below.)</em> The standards survey has been a powerful nine-month lead indicator for investments in human, physical and working capital. As credit conditions improve, it is highly likely that business trends and GDP should remain constructive for the balance of 2011, reducing the probability of economic weakness developing. Still, actual commercial and industrial loan activity lags the survey by 18 months, and investors need to understand the differences in timing.","image":"638e3078a3c47c530c0a5cca","year":"2011","publishDate":"May 05, 2011","type":"insights","title":"Chart of the month: Credit climate keeps improving.","author.jobTitle":["Chief US Equity Strategist, Citi"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2011/chart-of-the-month-credit-climate-keeps-improving","tags":["Perspective Migration"],"month":"05","author.displayName":["Tobias Levkovich"],"siteId":"citigpa","category":"PERSPECTIVES"},{"summary":"Abidjan – Citi has reopened its office in Côte d'Ivoire and is working closely with the authorities in the government and central bank to restore the country's banking system.","month":"05","year":"2011","publishDate":"May 04, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi Reopens Côte d'Ivoire Office","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/citi-reopens-côte-d-ivoire-office","tags":["Press Release Migration","Institutional Clients Group"]},{"summary":"New York – In a sign that small businesses are finally emerging from the recession and looking to grow, an increasing number of business owners are adopting social media as a way to better market their business and reach more customers, according to the latest Citibank small business survey. The increased use of social media represents one of several findings in Citibank's survey that shows small businesses are taking concrete action to grow in 2011.","month":"05","year":"2011","publishDate":"May 04, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citibank Survey Finds Small Business Owners Taking Action to Grow in 2011","category":"PRESS RELEASE","url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/press-release/2011/citibank-survey-finds-small-business-owners-taking-action-to-grow-in-2011","tags":["Press Release Migration","Consumer Banking"]},{"summary":"In an appearance on Bloomberg TV, Citi's Chief US Equity Strategist Tobias Levkovich <a href=\"https://www.bloomberg.com/video/69283114/\">discusses</a> the potential impact on markets from a range of issues including geopolitical risk, gas prices, government deficits and the pullback on quantitative easing.","image":"638e307aa3c47c530c0a5cd1","year":"2011","publishDate":"May 04, 2011","type":"insights","title":"Levkovich offers broad market outlook.","author.jobTitle":["Citi"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2011/levkovich-offers-broad-market-outlook","tags":["Perspective Migration"],"month":"05","author.displayName":["Citi"],"siteId":"citigpa","category":"PERSPECTIVES"},{"month":"05","author.displayName":["Citi"],"year":"2011","publishDate":"May 04, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"\"Saving Up for a Rainy Day...or Pizza.\"","category":"PERSPECTIVES","author.jobTitle":["Citi"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2011/saving-up-for-a-rainy-dayor-pizza","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"month":"05","author.displayName":["Citi"],"year":"2011","publishDate":"May 04, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Galant discusses future of digital payments.","category":"PERSPECTIVES","author.jobTitle":["Citi"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2011/galant-discusses-future-of-digital-payments","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"month":"05","author.displayName":["Citi"],"year":"2011","publishDate":"May 04, 2011","siteId":"citigpa","type":"insights","title":"Citi wealth management talent honored.","category":"PERSPECTIVES","author.jobTitle":["Citi"],"url":"https://www.citigroup.com/global/news/perspective/2011/citi-wealth-management-talent-honored","tags":["Perspective Migration"]},{"summary":"I'm in Washington, D.C., this week, along with hundreds of others who are in the business of helping businesses, for the <a href=\"https://www.microenterpriseworks.org/\">Association for Enterprise Opportunity </a>'s (AEO) annual microfinance <a href=\"https://www.microenterpriseconference.org/\">conference</a>. We're here to share best practices and develop new approaches for supporting small business, which everyone agrees are the engines of any local economy and key sources of job creation. In fact, a Citi-funded AEO <a href=\"https://www.businesswire.com/news/home/20110502005672/en/Association-Enterprise-Opportunity-AEO-Releases-Report-Impact\">study</a> that was just released found that if one in three microe